label: Allard
comment: For over 80 years, Allard has been a must for gourmets in Paris. This authentic bistro in the heart of Saint-Germain-des-Prés is one of the city's few traditional restaurants. With its 1930s zinc counter, period tiling and intimate rooms, Allard offers a warm, authentic experience. The bourgeois cuisine offers sincere, tasty dishes in a deliciously retro atmosphere. A haven of conviviality in which to indulge.

Zapa symbolizes French elegance, sublimating femininity and offering modern, timeless collections.

label: Square Marcel Bleustein Blanchet
comment: Square Marcel Bleustein Blanchet, a spiral garden overlooking the Sacré-C?ur and Montmartre, lies at the intersection of Rue de la Bonne and Rue du Chevalier de la Barre. Its name derives from a 1770 mill demolished in 1827 due to quarrying. From 1853 to 1860, it was home to the Tour de Solférino guinguette. This 4,700 m² park offers visitors a green and relaxing space.

In Club Matignon, the ambiance imagined by Jacques Garcia is sumptuous, with gilded walls and comfortable sofas. With its eclectic musical program, the venue attracts fans of electro pop-rock on Fridays and house music on Saturdays.

label: Cimetière de Belleville
comment: Belleville Cemetery, opened in 1808, is a historic site in the commune of Belleville, which became part of Paris in 1860. With 3,200 graves, a memorial to the Paris Commune and the tomb of cinema pioneer Léon Gaumont, the cemetery offers a glimpse into history. There's also the Chappe Telegraph from the French Revolution and Plein Air, Paris's first urban flower farm, selling flowers on Saturdays. A place shaded by a hundred trees, combining history and nature in the heart of the capital.

label: Les Zygomates
comment: This bistro, formerly a butcher's shop from the 1920s, has preserved its period decor. Its menu features quality ingredients from the market, adapting to the seasons to offer an authentic and tasty culinary experience. A place steeped in history, where you can savour sincere, tasty dishes.

label: Musée de La Poste
comment: The Musée de La Poste is located in the heart of the Montparnasse district. Its collections on three levels present the historical, artistic, philatelic and scientific heritage of La Poste, from its origins to the present day. Collectors and the simply curious can discover the first post office route maps, the first postmen's uniforms, the first postage stamps... So many exceptional items that tell the story of the great adventure of postal history. The museum is suitable for all audiences and offers temporary exhibitions.

An unmissable address for lovers of Asian cuisine!

Whether it's for a shopping session, a trip or simply your daily commute, your shopkeepers will be delighted to give you a warm welcome.

It's also a cultural venue with exhibitions, concerts, card tournaments and plays. And don't miss the ball on the first Saturday of the month, a real institution. Come and enjoy an evening full of flavors and entertainment at La Gouttière, the neighborhood's not-to-be-missed address.

This "bistrot gastro" with its typically Parisian ambience offers a refined culinary experience at affordable prices. A warm and attentive welcome completes the picture of a place not to be missed.

comment: Le Louchebem, a must-visit Paris restaurant in the heart of the capital, is an institution renowned for its rotisserie and its exceptional menu. Tartare, aiguillette, leg of lamb, grilled entrecôte... a veritable symphony of delights to savor. The rotisseur's plate, with a trio of succulent meats, will satisfy even the most voracious appetites. At Louchebem, it's a feast for carnivores, where gourmandise is king. Bon appétit! (324 characters)

label: Roller parc Bercy
comment: The Bercy roller park, located in the eponymous park, is the second-largest skate park in Paris, with a surface area of 800 m². Suitable for skates, rollerblades and BMX, it offers a range of ramps and modules for all enthusiasts, beginners and advanced alike. Families and riders alike appreciate the friendly street atmosphere and graffiti. Thanks to a permanent roof, enthusiasts can enjoy the facilities in all weathers for year-round sliding sessions.

label: Église Saint-Éloi
comment: Saint-Éloi church, designed by architect Marc Leboucher, is located between Place de la Nation and Gare de Lyon. Its distinctive feature is a metal frame structure clad inside and out in aluminum. An imposing metal tower houses the bells, adding a modern touch to this religious edifice.

label: Paris Montparnasse - Top of the City
comment: From the Observatoire Paris Montparnasse, visitors can enjoy a breathtaking view of the capital and the Eiffel Tower, day and night. On the 56th floor, a virtual reality tour immerses visitors in the history of Paris, offering an immersive experience. At the top, a terrace 210m above sea level offers a 360° panoramic view of the City of Light. A vertiginous experience not to be missed by locals and visitors alike.

label: Rosa Bonheur - Buttes Chaumont
comment: Located in the 19th arrondissement of Paris, Rosa Bonheur is a lively guinguette in the Parc des Buttes-Chaumont. In homage to the artist Rosa Bonheur, this place is a festive oasis of the Camargue in Paris. Lovers of tapas and southern drinks enjoy a lively atmosphere, with upbeat music and dancing. A must for conviviality and festivities in the capital.

label: Immeuble Fulton
comment: The Fulton building, designed by Bernard Bühler architecte, stands elegantly in the Paris Rive Gauche district. Erected in 2017 on the Quai d'Austerlitz, it offers a breathtaking view of the Seine. The building houses 87 social housing units with colorful staggered balconies, as well as two shops on the first floor. The brightly colored balconies offer a unique visual experience, changing according to the angle of view. A charming address appreciated by residents and passers-by alike.

label: Hermès (rue de Sèvres)
comment: In 2010, Hermès opened its third Paris boutique in the former swimming pool of the historic Hôtel Lutetia. This 1,500 m² luxury concept store offers all the brand's collections, including ready-to-wear, leather goods, perfumes, watches and jewelry. In addition to traditional items, customers can also enjoy a florist, tea room and bookshop for a unique and elegant shopping experience.

label: Les Déchargeurs
comment: Since 1982, Les Déchargeurs, located in the heart of Paris in a 17th-century mansion, has offered an eclectic program ranging from musical theater to poetry and song. Renowned artists such as Fabrice Luchini regularly perform here. Directed by Lee Fou Messica, the establishment offers a participatory library, exhibitions and literary encounters. A must for lovers of culture and live entertainment in Paris.

label: Librairie de la Halle Saint-Pierre
comment: This publishing house stands out for its specialization in works dedicated to art, artists? books and all forms of contemporary creation beyond the norm. At the same time, it acts as a resource and documentation center for art enthusiasts and professionals. A true reference for all art lovers in search of knowledge and inspiration.

label: Square Suzanne Buisson
comment: In the heart of Montmartre, the Suzanne Buisson square is located on the historic site of the Château des Brouillards park. An Art Deco rotunda at the entrance pays homage to the Resistance fighter. This sunny garden with its terraces is ideal for relaxing and strolling, especially for families with its play areas. Petanque enthusiasts can also enjoy a game of boules on the pitch. A friendly place combining history, nature and leisure.

label: Italie Deux
comment: Italie 2, a vast Parisian shopping center nestling between the Gobelins and Chinatown, offers an ideal setting for shopping, with 130 boutiques, a wide variety of restaurants - some fifteen in all - and a sports club for the more sporty. And let's not forget its many services and the "Le 13e Art" auditorium, a real entertainment venue for visitors in search of relaxation and leisure.

label: Autour du saumon - Miron
comment: Located in the heart of the Marais district, Autour du Saumon is a must in Paris. With two establishments and several stores, this brand offers a selection of 7 different salmon origins (Norway, Scotland...). Lovers of wild fish will be delighted. In fine weather, the terrace is perfect for relaxing. And don't forget the gourmet delights waiting in the store. Autour du Saumon delights taste buds and pupils alike!

label: Vintage Désir
comment: You can't visit Paris without stopping by this famous thrift store. Known for its affordable prices and cutting-edge fashion, it's a must for shopping enthusiasts. The diversity of items on offer and the quality of the pieces make it a popular address for bargain-seeking fashionistas. Don't miss this opportunity to unearth the treasures you need to complete your wardrobe at the lowest possible cost, while staying on trend.

label: Passage du Grand-Cerf
comment: The Passage du Grand-Cerf, in the lively Montorgueil district near Rue de Turbigo, is a covered gallery built in 1825. At 12 meters high, it stands out for its metal structure and luminous glass roof. Here you'll find craft stores selling jewelry, furniture and design. To get there, another passageway is hidden in rue Dussoubs. A charming shopping stroll awaits you in the Passage du Grand-Cerf.

label: Jones
comment: Located in the 11th arrondissement, Jones is a warm, neo-bistro, far removed from artifice. With a friendly atmosphere, it offers a selection of surprising, contemporary dishes to accompany a drink. Freshness and quality of produce take pride of place, for an unforgettable culinary experience.

label: Le 6 Paul Bert
comment: Located in the heart of rue Paul Bert, this bistro is a must. Its friendly setting and warm welcome create a very pleasant atmosphere. The open kitchen showcases market-fresh produce for tasty, gourmet dishes. As an added bonus, a grocery corner lets you take home the delights you've discovered on your visit. A culinary experience not to be missed!

label: Le Colectivo Milonga
comment: Colectivo Milango, also known as the "Milango Bus" in Argentinian, is renowned for its Argentinian tango classes for all levels, two-day workshops for enthusiasts, and balls featuring renowned guests. Located in the lively 20th arrondissement, Colectivo Tango stands out for its warm, friendly atmosphere, where learning takes place in good spirits.

label: Le Réservoir - Mary De Vivo
comment: Come and discover the surprises at Le Réservoir! This exceptional venue boasts a concert hall hosting big names such as Ben Harper, Radiohead and Placebo. In the mood for gastronomy? The restaurant offers refined cuisine concocted with seasonal produce. Treat yourself to a delicious cocktail at the bar, prepared by a renowned mixologist. Le Réservoir is a must for music and food lovers.

label: Cook'n with Class Paris
comment: Since 2007, Cook'n With Class Paris, founded by chef Eric Fraudeau, has been offering high-level French cooking courses in English. Located in Montmartre, the school welcomes gastronomy enthusiasts for hands-on sessions, from pastry to bread, taught by professional chefs. A unique opportunity to discover and learn about French cuisine, in a friendly, authentic atmosphere.

label: ParisCityVision
comment: Discover the treasures of Paris and France with PARISCityVISION! Over 90 excursions to Versailles, Giverny, Champagne and the Loire castles. All-inclusive packages, open daily from 7 a.m. to 10 p.m. in summer and 7 a.m. to 9 p.m. from November 1. Day and night tours, departing from and returning to your hotel. Discounts for children available. Reservations essential: tickets on sale on site and at the Paris Tourist Office.

label: Square des Batignolles
comment: The Square des Batignolles, near the Martin Luther King Park, is a haven of peace in the heart of the 17th arrondissement. With its grotto, waterfall, river and pond, it's a jewel of nature in the city. The peaceful atmosphere of Les Batignolles is charming, with its lively streets, majestic church, covered market and organic market. An authentic and charming getaway.

label: Compagnie des Bateaux Mouches
comment: The Compagnie des Bateaux Mouches offers cruises on the Seine with fine dining and a breathtaking view of Paris. A 3-hour night cruise offers the magic of illuminated monuments, with a three-course dinner and wine. For those who prefer daylight, the 1h45 lunch cruise lets you admire Paris in a relaxed atmosphere. With live music in the background, each cruise is a unique gastronomic experience.

label: Haropa Port
comment: Paris, Le Havre and Rouen form the major river-sea port of the Seine axis. Haropa Port, the 4th largest port in Northern Europe, is linked to all continents thanks to its high-quality maritime services. Number 1 in logistics in France, it offers comprehensive, environmentally-friendly services. Paris favors river transport and last-mile logistics. Haropa Port has thus become the leading river port in France and Europe for passenger transport.

label: L'Agapé
comment: The Michelin-starred Agapé restaurant in Paris's 17th arrondissement takes its name from the Greek for "unconditional love". Each plate promises perfectly mastered flavors and elegance. Seasonal produce is sublimated, and temperatures, tastes, textures and spices are harmoniously matched. The pastry chef's desserts will delight even the most demanding palates. Enjoy these culinary delights in a cosy, warm and modern setting.

label: Europa Experience
comment: Europa Expérience is a 3-storey, 1500m2 interactive space on Europe in Paris. Visitors can explore the EU through a multimedia tour, augmented reality installations and a 360° cinema. For groups, there's a role-playing game where they take on the role of Members of the European Parliament. All content is available in 24 languages, and is accessible to the mobility-impaired, hearing-impaired, blind and partially-sighted. An enriching experience accessible to all!

label: Auteuil Brasserie
comment: Travel to the heart of Italian flavors in this atypical bar-restaurant, nestled in the old Auteuil train station. Its unusual setting instantly transports you to an exotic atmosphere. Let yourself be seduced by authentic, tasty Italian cuisine that will awaken all your senses. A unique and memorable culinary experience awaits you in this place full of charm and history.

label: Cimetière du Montparnasse
comment: The Montparnasse cemetery, opened in 1824, is the second largest in Paris after Père Lachaise. Covering 19 hectares, it replaces three former farms and houses a listed tower. Numerous works of art can be found here, including Constantin Brancusi's "The Kiss". Among the personalities buried here are Charles Baudelaire, Guy de Maupassant, Jean-Paul Sartre, Simone de Beauvoir and Charles Garnier. It's a peaceful spot in the heart of Paris's bustling Montparnasse district.

label: L'Orangerie
comment: L'Orangerie, a luminous extension of the Galerie overlooking the Cour de Marbre, was awarded its first Michelin star in 2017 less than a year after opening. A consecration for this restaurant, which perfectly combines elegance and refinement to the delight of gourmets in search of unique experiences.

label: Anne Fontaine
comment: Since her debut, Anne Fontaine has revolutionized the white shirt with designs that combine sobriety and audacity. Crafted from noble, natural materials, her creations are wildly alluring, whether classic or original. A brand that has established itself as a benchmark for style and elegance.

label: Le Tango Paris
comment: This club, with its warm, festive atmosphere, attracts a diverse clientele: gays, lesbians and straights of all ages and styles. The varied music program caters for all tastes, from musette and dance to variety and disco. The spirit of the place is good-natured and friendly, conducive to relaxation and partying.

label: Bonjour Concept Store Paris
comment: Since 2015, Bonjour Concept Store - Paris has offered a mischievous selection of fun objects, home decor and gift ideas for the whole family. Open Tuesday to Saturday in Oberkampf, this concept store showcases exclusive creations by designers from around the world and 100% French items. Close to emblematic venues such as L?Atelier des Lumières, it's a veritable crossroads of creativity. Bonjour welcomes you in French, English, Spanish and Chinese. An oasis of fantasy in the heart of the capital!

label: Boutique Puma - Les produits Ferrari
comment: On the Avenue des Champs-Élysées, the Ferrari boutique offers an exclusive selection of clothing, toys and souvenirs for enthusiasts of the famous Italian brand. Immerse yourself in the mythical world of Ferrari and let yourself be seduced by the iconic red that adorns each product. A unique shopping experience for all lovers of beautiful machines!

label: Galerie Chantal Crousel
comment: Galerie Chantal Crousel, founded by Chantal Crousel and Niklas Svennung in 1980, is a pillar of contemporary art in Paris. Renowned artists such as Sophie Calle, Wolfgang Tillmans, Tony Cragg, Cindy Sherman and Melik Ohanian have exhibited at this prestigious venue. Thanks to this gallery, these artists have gained international recognition. Galerie Chantal Crousel continues to support and promote innovative artistic creations.

label: Théâtre Édouard VII
comment: The Théâtre Édouard VII, close to the Madeleine and Opéra Garnier, is an iconic Paris landmark. Founded in the 20th century, it has welcomed such artists as Sacha Guitry, Sarah Bernhardt, Orson Welles and Vivian Leigh. Its varied program features classic and contemporary works. Since September 2015, the theater has been "English friendly!" with shows surtitled in English, in collaboration with "Theatre in Paris". This opens up French theater to non-French speakers.

label: Bibliothèque Saint-Eloi
comment: The Saint-Eloi library, ideally located between Gare de Lyon and Place de la Nation, offers a wide range of services. With areas dedicated to adults, young people, music, the deaf and languages, it caters for everyone's needs. In addition, 15 multimedia workstations are available for users in search of digital resources. A must for culture and knowledge.

label: Pavillon Carré de Baudouin
comment: Built in the 18th century, the Nicolas Carré de Baudouin pavilion owes its name to its former owner. Its distinctive façade features a peristyle of Ionic columns inspired by an Italian villa. Transformed into a cultural space dedicated to contemporary creation, it offers exhibitions and conferences open to all. Nearby is a former 19th-century orphanage and a landscaped garden. Street art frescoes on the outside wall add a touch of originality.

label: Comité départemental de la randonnée de Paris
comment: The Panamées® are a unique way to discover Paris. Organized by the Comité départemental de la randonnée pédestre, these themed walks are open to all and free of charge. Every third Thursday of the month, from 7pm to 10pm, participants walk 7 km in the company of the Comité's "storytellers". These guides reveal the secrets of the places and monuments they visit. An original way to explore the capital while learning, not to be missed by Paris enthusiasts.

label: Le Dauphin
comment: In a setting of white marble and mirrored walls enhanced with mahogany, a sublime setting is revealed, where a sophisticated atmosphere reigns. Basque chef Inaki Aizpitarte officiates with brio, offering a cuisine that is both traditional and daring. His culinary art, a blend of revisited classicism and unbridled creativity, promises an unforgettable gastronomic experience. A perfect combination of elegance and originality that will delight the most demanding palates.

comment: Immerse yourself in the world of this showcase boutique, where sneakers featuring the emblematic little rooster are presented in an original way. A must for fashionistas and sneaker collectors in search of rarities and novelties.

label: Capelstore
comment: Discover a varied selection of top-of-the-range clothing for taller and heavier men at Capelstore. Prestigious brands such as Hugo Boss, Tommy Hilfiger, Polo Ralph Lauren, Paul & Shark and Lacoste are featured. In addition to the ready-to-wear collections, Capelstore offers made-to-measure suits for a perfect fit. Find the style that suits you, and enhance your elegance with quality clothing.

label: La Flèche d'Or
comment: Formerly a renowned railway station on the Petite Ceinture, the Flèche d'Or has reinvented itself to become an essential socio-cultural venue. Transformed into an underground concert hall until 2016, it now offers a diverse program thanks to nine local collectives and initiatives. Concerts, screenings, theater, exhibitions, workshops, canteen and bar: a space open to all, at the heart of a neighborhood committed to fighting injustice.

label: La Légende bar
comment: Come and discover this charming bar in the Batignolles district, once a brothel converted into a French-style pub. Perfect for evenings out with friends, you can enjoy drinks and snacks while watching a soccer or rugby match. Concerts regularly enliven the evenings. The space can be privatized for special events. A friendly, lively place not to be missed!

comment: The Church of Sainte-Jeanne-de-Chantal is a magnificent example of the imposing churches built along the major boulevards around Paris in the early and first half of the 20th century. Built over a period of 20 years, from 1933 to 1952, it bears witness to the architectural expertise and grandeur of religious buildings of the period.

label: Le Bellerive
comment: Located on the banks of the Canal Saint-Martin, next to La Villette, Le Bellerive is renowned for its friendly, relaxed atmosphere, simple, tasty menu, affordable prices and warm welcome. Attended by a varied clientele, from regulars to pétanque enthusiasts taking an aperitif break, this lively place is ideal for enjoying Parisian life in all its simplicity. Don't miss the Sunday brunch with Swiss or Norwegian flavors. A charming address to discover!

label: Massale
comment: Restaurant Massale offers authentic, refined French cuisine, prepared by chefs trained at the prestigious Le Bristol. Each dish is a delicious ode to French terroir and gastronomy. The restaurant offers a warm and friendly atmosphere, with a refined setting or a sunny terrace for unforgettable gourmet moments. Wine lovers will be delighted with a selection of over a hundred organic and natural wines from the Jura region.

label: Espace de glisse parisien 18e
comment: EGP 18 is the largest skate park in France, with 3,000 m² of indoor space. Located near Porte de La Chapelle, it offers state-of-the-art equipment for all riders, beginners and advanced alike: bowls, vertical wall and street furniture. Introductory, handisport and family sessions are offered on a regular basis, enabling everyone to discover the sport in a safe and fun way.

label: Marché du livre ancien et d’occasion
comment: Since 1987, the Antiquarian and Second-Hand Book Market, set up under the Halles near Parc Georges Brassens, has been attracting book lovers from the 19th and 20th centuries. This Parisian weekend rendezvous offers literary treasures: antiquarian books dating from before 1815, out-of-print works from past centuries and modern illustrated books. A veritable literary Ali Baba's cave, where every visitor can unearth rare and precious literary nuggets.

label: Théâtre Montparnasse et Petit Montparnasse
comment: The Montparnasse theater, built in 1886 by architect Charles Peigniet, is a fixture on the Paris cultural scene. Renowned playwrights such as Éric-Emmanuel Schmitt, Agnès Jaoui, Jean-Pierre Bacri and Florian Zeller have found success here. Le Petit Montparnasse, a modern 200-seat theater, showcases contemporary writing and young talent. In 2016, its 11 shows attracted over 140,000 spectators, confirming its ongoing success.

label: Puces de Montreuil
comment: The Puces de Montreuil, the kingdom of bargain hunters and vintage enthusiasts, is brimming with a variety of treasures: second-hand clothes, bicycle parts, antiques and unusual objects. Retro enthusiasts, dive into this paradise of vintage clothing and curiosities. This atypical market blends past and present for a unique shopping experience. Let yourself be surprised by the many surprising finds. Take your time to explore the wonders of the Puces de Montreuil.

label: Camion à Pizzas
comment: Le Camion à Pizzas, located under the Halle Aubervilliers in Le Centquatre, is a must for street food in Paris. The pizza-maker prepares delicious wood-fired pizzas: Neapolitan, vegetarian or meat. Prepared with fresh ingredients and great care, these pizzas are an efficient, friendly and fast gourmet break. An unforgettable culinary experience in a place dedicated to contemporary art.

label: L'atelier de Donato
comment: Donato's workshop is not your average beauty salon. It's a cozy sanctuary where you're welcomed like family. Located in the former showroom of the famous embroiderer Jean-François Lesage, known for his work with Chanel, this intimate space offers scalp massages, highlights, and elegant updos for any occasion. Experience exceptional service in a warm setting that feels like home. Pamper yourself with luxury and relaxation at Donato's workshop. Welcome to your new haven!

label: Hôtel Bohême
comment: The Hôtel Bohême regularly opens its doors for a weekend dedicated to designers committed to a sustainable approach. On the program: handmade pieces, local production, recycled products and organic food stands. The event takes place near Place de la République, in a bright industrial-style building. Not to be missed by fans of responsible design!

label: Paul & Joe
comment: Sophie Albou's flamboyant, non-conformist style is reflected in her ready-to-wear creations for women, men and children, as well as in her lines of beauty products and small jewelry. Its collections are young, fresh, retro and colorful, offering an original and audacious breath of fresh air in the world of fashion.

label: Théâtre Ouvert - Centre national des dramaturgies contemporaines
comment: The Théâtre Ouvert, nestled in a passageway near the famous Moulin Rouge, stands out as a place of experimentation and creativity. By showcasing original, never-before-seen dramatic texts, it offers audiences the chance to discover unique artistic creations. Each year, the venue also offers artists-in-residence the opportunity to develop their talent and artistic vision.

label: Église Saint-Jean de Montmartre
comment: Located at the foot of the Butte Montmartre, the first reinforced concrete church, built between 1894 and 1904, is a jewel of sacred art. Clad in bricks and ceramics, notably flamé and pastillé stoneware, this architectural work is marked by the influence of the Art Nouveau style. Listed as a historic monument, it bears witness to the innovation and creativity of the period.

label: Stadium Tour Paris Saint-Germain
comment: Dive behind the scenes of the Parc des Princes and explore the places usually reserved for football heroes! From the VIP boxes to the press room, via the changing rooms and the presidential lounge, discover the famous stadium from a whole new angle. A unique experience not to be missed by soccer fans and the curious in search of discovery!

label: Saint Michael's Church Paris
comment: Located in the heart of Paris, Saint Michaels Church is an Anglican place of worship open to all, whatever their origin or culture. This cosmopolitan church brings together believers from the four corners of the globe, offering a space for prayer and sharing that fosters diversity and open-mindedness. A sanctuary of peace and brotherhood in the heart of the French capital.

label: La Rotonde Stalingrad
comment: In the heart of La Villette, the Rotonde Stalingrad is an emblematic Parisian landmark. Built before the Revolution, this cultural hive offers a wide range of activities. The trattoria seduces lovers of Italian flavors, while the sunny Jardin terrace offers a relaxed setting. The Galerie exhibits contemporary art, while the mini club livens up weekend evenings. Bars, a florist, a boutique, games and a co-working space complete this festive and convivial address.

label: La maison Dr Hauschka
comment: Immerse yourself in the heart of nature at the Maison du Dr. Hauschka. This institute, in perfect harmony with the brand's eco-responsible philosophy, offers a haven of well-being surrounded by birch trees. Relax, pamper yourself and rediscover the peace and quiet away from the hustle and bustle of the city. On the program: facial and body treatments, facial gymnastics and natural hair removal. A haven of peace for a gentle, natural interlude.

label: Le Spa, j'Adore !
comment: At the heart of the Paris J'Adore Hotel & Spa*****, the Spa, j'Adore offers an oasis of serenity with its 11-meter pool, Jacuzzi, geysers and waterfalls. Enjoy the marble hammam, cedar sauna, sensory showers, ice fountain and Himalayan pink salt grotto. Unique massages are offered in 3 treatment cabins, including one with an affusion shower. Open from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m., the Spa also welcomes external guests and can be privatized 24 hours a day for absolute relaxation.

label: Grand Central
comment: Discover an atypical place combining industry and gastronomy! In this post-industrial-style refectory, enjoy gastronomic cuisine that's both ethical and inventive. Large tables invite conviviality, while raw concrete adds a raw, modern touch. A unique culinary experience in a warm and original setting.

label: École Militaire
comment: At the end of the Champ-de-Mars park stands the majestic façade of the École Militaire, built under the reign of Louis XV. This institution is now home to the higher military education system. Open to the public during the Heritage Days, it bears witness to French military history.

label: Palais de Chaillot
comment: The Palais de Chaillot, built in 1937 in the 16th arrondissement of Paris for an international exhibition, consists of two pavilions linked by the Parvis des Droits de l'Homme, offering a magnificent view of the Trocadero gardens and the Eiffel Tower. It houses the Cité de l'architecture et du patrimoine, the Musée de la Marine, the Musée de l'Homme and Chaillot - Théâtre national de la Danse, bringing together art, history and dance, a veritable treasure trove of Parisian heritage.

However, the theatre cannot guarantee that seats will be available at the last moment and advises to book and pay as soon as possible."]

label: Francis Klein
comment: For over 30 years, this family-run business has been handcrafting unique frames. Made in France, their collection adapts to every style for a glamorous, original look. For those seeking elegance and subtlety à la Parisienne, these frames will add a sophisticated touch to their look.

label: Sir Winston
comment: The Sir Winston pub, one of the oldest in the capital, welcomes you in a colonial atmosphere with an impressive selection of fifty exceptional whiskies. Make yourself comfortable in club armchairs as you sample. For party-goers, the club lounge in the basement offers house and world music. Cigar aficionados can head to the smoking room. The Sir Winston combines simplicity, chic and elegance for the perfect evening.

label: Egg Factory
comment: The Egg Factory, located in the dynamic 10th arrondissement, is renowned for its gourmet egg bun revisited. The quality of the ingredients, from soft brioche bread to Label Rouge farm eggs, is the secret of their success. The friendly, gourmet atmosphere of the establishment promises an unforgettable culinary experience, a timeless moment for all lovers of good food. Egg Factory, a must for taste buds in search of authenticity.

label: Théâtre Dejazet
comment: Built in 1851, the Théâtre Dejazet embodies the splendor of the Boulevard du Crime, renamed Boulevard du Temple, near Place de la République. Renovated in 1976, this venerable establishment offers an eclectic program in an authentic Italian setting. Come and discover plays by renowned authors as well as young talent, not forgetting the great names of French music who perform on its stages.

label: Assemblée Nationale - Palais Bourbon
comment: The National Assembly has 577 deputies and passes around a hundred laws a year. The Palais Bourbon, built in 1728, is reminiscent of the Grand Trianon at Versailles. Converted by the Prince de Condé, it became the seat of the French National Assembly in 1795. Declared a "national asset" in 1791, it now boasts a Napoleonic colonnade. In the 19th century, it was modified and today houses works of contemporary art.

label: Le Concert de Cuisine
comment: Franco-Japanese fusion is at work in the culinary arts, thanks to the talent of a chef specializing in teppanyaki. This technique of cooking on hot plates is mastered with brio, offering a unique gastronomic experience where flavors blend harmoniously. An exquisite blend of Japanese tradition and French creativity, for tasty, refined dishes that delight the taste buds.

label: Pierre Cardin
comment: In 1950, Pierre Cardin founded his fashion house, becoming a pioneer of futuristic fashion. His innovative creations are distinguished by their audacity and originality. Today, the collections of this fashion visionary are on display in the prestigious Faubourg Saint-Honoré boutique, a symbol of French excellence and refinement.

label: Raoul Maeder
comment: Raoul Maeder, baker-patissier, perpetuates ancestral know-how, enriched by prestigious training courses. Winner of the 1st prize for the Best Baguette in Paris in 2000 and 2002, he draws inspiration from his Alsatian roots to offer authentic creations such as kougelhopf, pretzels, manele, Linzer Torte and streusel. Passionate and talented, he combines tradition and innovation to offer his customers unique products.

label: Studio Massaro
comment: Discover a dance and training center dedicated to South American dances such as Argentine tango, salsa, samba and Brazilian dance. Learn to master these captivating and passionate dances in a warm and friendly atmosphere. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced dancer, our classes are suitable for all levels, so you can progress while having fun. Join us on a journey to the heart of Latin American culture and music!

label: Laser World Paris
comment: Immerse yourself in the apocalyptic world of the Laser Game at Laser World Paris! Explore a 500m2 maze set in a post-apocalyptic Paris. Take on your opponents with precise lasers and experience a thrilling game that demands strategy, coordination and agility. Whether you're a beginner or an expert, our team guarantees you an unforgettable experience. Challenge your friends in our uniquely themed centers: Apocalyptic Paris, Lost Island, Jungle Star and Explorer. Join us at Laser World Paris for an epic adventure!

comment: Uniqlo, Japan's leading ready-to-wear brand, offers colorful, affordable casual collections. Its flagship store in Paris, covering 2,000 m² and three floors, offers a wide choice for men, women and children. The brand collaborates with renowned designers and is committed to sustainable fashion. A global benchmark for style, quality and practicality at affordable prices.

label: Les Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann - Boutique souvenirs
comment: Don't leave the capital without your traditional souvenir! Visit the Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann souvenir store to find the perfect item. From the Eiffel Tower on a key ring to the Arc de Triomphe on a mug, every major Parisian landmark is represented with style and fantasy. Let yourself be seduced by this varied and designer choice of unique objects. Head to floor 6 of the Coupole building to find what you're looking for!

label: Le 3 Bis Paris
comment: Le 3Bis, the capital's largest games bar with 200m2 on 2 levels, offers breathtaking scenery and a wide variety of board games. Main area and 6 private themed lounges for karaoke, quizzes, blind-tests, retro-gaming, darts, projections and dance floors. Food and drink available on site or to take away. The perfect place for gaming enthusiasts.

label: La Galerie Dior
comment: The Galerie Dior, in the emblematic Dior townhouse, plunges visitors into the world of Parisian haute couture. The spectacular staging retraces the history of the house, from Christian Dior to his successors such as Yves Saint Laurent, Marc Bohan and Maria Grazia Chiuri. In 13 thematic rooms, visitors discover iconic models, original sketches and unique archive pieces, offering a privileged glimpse into this exceptional world.

label: Brasserie Fouquet’s Paris
comment: The Fouquet's Paris brasserie, on the Champs-Élysées for over a century, embodies the charm of Parisian brasseries with its bright red awnings. A legendary cinema venue, it offers refined cuisine by Chef Pierre Gagnaire, magnificent terraces and an authentic decor. For an elegant breakfast, gala reception or business meeting, Fouquet's and its team provide impeccable service. An address not to be missed!

label: Dalí Paris
comment: The "Dalí Paris" exhibition features more than 300 works from the private collection of Salvador Dalí and other art enthusiasts. Paintings, sculptures, engravings and surrealist objects offer a fascinating journey into his world. Fascinated by science, antiquity and religion, Dalí brings his visions to life in 3D: soft monsters, strange creatures. In his revisitations of literary works, he adds his infinite palette of colors. Immerse yourself in the captivating universe of this extraordinary artist.

label: Comprendre Paris en Marchant
comment: Architect-urban planners Hervé Judéaux and Dominique Wurtz present their "Comprendre Paris en Marchant" projects for Paris enthusiasts. They take you on a journey of discovery of the history and daily life of Parisians, through urban walks. Their approach is inspired by Jean-Christophe Bailly's ideas on the full experience of cities by their inhabitants. This program is the fruit of a close collaboration to select the sites of interest.

label: Musée d'Orsay
comment: The Musée d'Orsay exhibits Western art from 1848 to 1914, including painting and architecture. A former railway station transformed into a palace for the 1900 Universal Exhibition, it has been reopened after renovation with an additional 400m². The new spaces feature post-impressionism, the Impressionist gallery and a café with an "aquatic" design by the Campana brothers. A must for art lovers.

label: Hotel de Béthune-Sully
comment: Located in the heart of the Marais district, the Hôtel de Béthune-Sully is a sumptuous 17th-century residence that once belonged to Henri IV's Superintendent of Finances. Becoming the headquarters of the Centre des Monuments Nationaux in 1967, this exceptional site boasts a Cour d'Honneur, an information center and a bookshop. Its garden, decorated with plant embroidery, leads to the Place des Vosges, a Paris landmark.

additional_information: ["The Hôtel de Sully is the headquarters of the Centre des monuments nationaux and is not open to visitors. However, it is possible to cross the courtyard and the garden during opening hours to access the Place des Vosges. Conference visits of the duchess's apartments are organised on fixed dates. Opening hours of the bookshop: Tuesday-Sunday, 1pm-7pm."]

label: Le Temps des Cerises
comment: Le Temps des Cerises, a Marseille-based brand specializing in vintage denim, offers collections for women, men (Japan Rags) and children (Little Cerise, Japan R*gs). Inspired by the urban style of thrift stores, the brand's fashion is responsible. To age its jeans, Le Temps des Cerises uses a non-toxic ozone oxidation process that preserves water resources. A great initiative that combines style and respect for the environment.

label: French touche
comment: The "Galerie d'objets touchants" boutique presents itself as a warm and poetic place, featuring a variety of handcrafted creations. Visitors will find jewelry, bags, belts, lighting, ceramic tableware, clothing, children's toys, comforters, cards, notebooks, records and fanzines. A real invitation to discover unique and original pieces for all tastes and occasions.

label: Fluctuart
comment: Fluctuart, the first floating urban art center open to all, brings together street art enthusiasts and renowned artists. A place of inspiration and exchange, it showcases innovative practices, from pioneers to current talents. Fluctuart, an artistic crossroads, offers a constantly evolving space for creation, exhibition and discovery. Each visit is a plunge into a dynamic cultural universe, with a varied and stimulating program.

additional_information: ['Winter: Wednesday-Sunday, midday-midnight. Summer (from mid-April): Sunday-Wednesday: 7 days a week from 12 p.m']

label: Couvent de la Madeleine de Traisnel
comment: Built in 1664 on a 42-hectare site, the Couvent de la Madeleine de Traisnel has served a variety of functions: a boarding house for the nobility, a weaving mill in 1790, an artists' studio in 1871 and a condominium in 1997. Alexandre Dumas and Patrick Süskind found inspiration here. The stone structure with its 1717 bell tower bears witness to its religious past. Refurbished by architect Jean-Sylvain Cartaud in the 17th century, the convent now has a new identity.

label: Boutique Montmartre je t'aime
comment: The Montmartre je t'aime boutique, in the heart of Montmartre, offers a wide selection of souvenirs from the famous Mur des je t'aime. Find magnets, mugs, posters, pens and postcards, made in France or Europe at Paris est toujours Paris, passage Jouffroy in the Grands Boulevards. Offer romantic and original gifts for all occasions: Valentine's Day, birthdays, Christmas... A refined selection to share your love of Paris with your loved ones.

label: Les Ateliers de la Maille
comment: The Ateliers de la Maille collections embody the refined concept of "Nature à porter", combining elegance, sobriety and shimmering colors. By masterfully exploiting noble materials such as cashmere, silk, cotton, bamboo, linen and even soy, the brand offers unique, comfortable creations.

label: Neo Christian Chauveau - École des techniques du maquillage artistique
comment: Want to benefit from professional make-up without emptying your wallet? Head to Christian Chauveau's École des techniques du maquillage artistique, a renowned establishment in the heart of Paris. Students in training are on the lookout for models, offering the opportunity to enjoy quality make-up at lower cost. Don't hesitate, it's time to be pampered at low cost!

label: Église Saint-Paul Saint-Louis du Marais
comment: The Saint-Paul-Saint-Louis church, built between 1627 and 1641 by the Jesuits with the support of Louis XIII, is a Baroque jewel. The first to break with Gothic aesthetics, it impresses with its modernity and elegance. A monument emblematic of architectural innovation, it marks a significant stage in the evolution of religious buildings.

label: Maison Plisson Beaumarchais
comment: In the heart of Paris, on Boulevard Beaumarchais, Maison Plisson blends delicatessen and restaurant to offer a unique experience. Over 6,000 carefully selected products from partner butchers, charcutiers, cheesemongers, greengrocers, wine merchants and grocers are featured. Open 7 days a week, it offers fresh, quality products, cooked with passion by the restaurant's chefs. A must for lovers of good food and good products.

label: Fondation Custodia - Collection Frits Lugt
comment: The Fondation Custodia, located in the 18th-century Hôtel Turgot between the Invalides and the Musée d'Orsay, houses the famous "Frits Lugt" art collection. This collection includes works by Flemish and Dutch masters of the 16th and 17th centuries: drawings, engravings, paintings, correspondence and miniatures. The Fondation Custodia also organizes regular exhibitions, enabling visitors to discover the history of art.

label: Stock B
comment: Stock B invites you to discover its 800 m² space dedicated to top-of-the-range men's ready-to-wear at discounted prices. Find renowned pieces such as Arrow shirts, Azzaro, Courrèges or Scherrer suits with exceptional discounts ranging from 30% to 50% off original prices. Take advantage of this opportunity to treat yourself to quality clothing at low prices.

label: Musée de l’Homme - Muséum national d'histoire naturelle
comment: At the heart of the Palais de Chaillot, the Passy wing houses the Musée de l'Homme. Covering 2,500 m², the Galerie de l'Homme offers a fascinating exploration of our history, identity and future. Its anthropological and paleontological collections are among the most impressive in the world. Don't forget to admire Davioud's superb 1878 glass roof before leaving this amazing place.

label: L'Escarmouche
comment: L'Escarmouche, the perfect restaurant for groups and events, offers private lounges for 15 to 100 guests. An authentic setting with stonework, 12th-century wells and stained glass windows, a warm atmosphere in the Latin Quarter. Enjoy traditional, high-quality cuisine for your events. An address to remember for unforgettable moments of conviviality.

label: Paris Rando Vélo
comment: Every week, Paris Rando Vélo offers free bike rides to help you discover the capital in a different way. A not-to-be-missed event on Friday evenings and the 3rd Sunday of each month, these 2.5-hour rides (between 20 and 25 km) offer a unique experience. Starting points are on the esplanade of the Hôtel de Ville: Fridays at 9.30pm for a 10pm start, and Sundays at 10.30am for an 11am start. An excellent way to enjoy Paris in a convivial atmosphere!

label: Vedettes de Paris
comment: Embark on a unique cruise with Les Vedettes de Paris, at the foot of the Eiffel Tower. 1-hour cruise on the Seine at 20/adult and 9/child. Original boat design with glass deck, upper deck and bar. Champagne option (+9?) or gourmet break with crêpe and soft drink (+5.5?). Departures 11am-9pm daily. Information and reservations at Café des Vedettes. An unforgettable experience aboard the Vedettes de Paris!

label: Sentou
comment: Sentou, an iconic boutique, offers a cutting-edge selection of design including Alvar Aalto, Charles and Ray Eames, Arne Jacobsen and Tsé-Tsé and Isamu Noguchi. In addition to the big names, you'll also find objects from the Gallery, such as the creations of 100drine. A real nugget for lovers of design and exceptional objects.

label: Altermundi
comment: Discover a stylish range of fair trade products at Altermundi. The store showcases ethical fashion with brands such as Article 23 for clothing, Nu for organic jeans, Cyclus or Pampa & Pop for bags, and El Naturalista for vegetable leather shoes. A quality choice that combines style and respect for the environment.

label: La Cantine Russe
comment: In the 16th arrondissement, opposite the majestic Eiffel Tower, this traditional Russian restaurant invites you on a culinary journey to the heart of Russia. Discover the authentic flavors of this country through refined, typical cuisine. A unique experience for lovers of new gastronomic discoveries.

label: Le Restaurant d’Orsay
comment: The Musée d'Orsay restaurant harmoniously blends classicism and modernity, with a décor inspired by the 1900s, featuring superb frescoes by Gabriel Ferrier and Benjamin Constant. The chairs, meanwhile, were created by Italian artist Jacopo Foggini, adding a touch of contemporary elegance to this showcase of history and art. A place where tradition subtly blends with innovation.

label: Théâtre de Verdure du Jardin Shakespeare
comment: Located in the Bois de Boulogne, in the heart of the Pré Catelan, the Shakespeare garden is a romantic haven of peace that evokes the world of the famous English playwright. Every spring, the garden is transformed into a magnificent open-air theater, offering spectators a stage surrounded by greenery and a welcoming lawn for theatrical performances. A unique immersion in an enchanting setting for lovers of culture and nature.

label: Spree
comment: Founded in 2001 by Roberta Oprandi and Bruno Hadjadj, Spree is an international reference in fashion and design. The boutique offers a collection of contemporary creators, designers from the 50s to the 80s and artists. New talents join renowned designers such as Isabel Marant and Vanessa Seward every season. Spree's diverse clientele includes celebrities from the worlds of film, fashion and music, who are seduced by this unique place of passion and influence.

label: Cité Fleurie - Cité d'artistes
comment: La Cité Fleurie, built at the end of the 19th century in the 13th arrondissement, is a collection of 29 studios with a singular charm, reminiscent of typical white cottages. This historic site has played host to such great names in the art world as Paul Gauguin and Amedeo Modigliani. To discover this cultural heritage, it's possible to take part in the open house days usually held in June. An artistic and historical journey not to be missed in the capital.

label: Oxymore - Pizzeria française
comment: Nestled between old stones and a bistro atmosphere, Oxymore is a French pizzeria. Its dough, made with fresh flour and yeast, follows the French baking tradition. With long fermentation, pizzas release a unique aroma and are easily digestible. Charcuteries, cheeses and extra virgin olive oil also come from France, as does the tomato sauce concocted in Provence. A hexagonal culinary escapade in Paris not to be missed.

label: RV Dégustation
comment: Dive into the heart of Paris for a unique culinary experience with RV Degustation. Ateliers are led by cheese and wine enthusiasts. Learn while having fun with games, sensory challenges and gastronomic quizzes. Food Tours let you discover the best of Parisian gastronomy. Book now for a gourmet adventure in Paris, in English and French!

Book now for a gourmet adventure in Paris, in English and French!

label: Le bar du marché
comment: The Bar du Marché, nicknamed the BDM, is a popular spot for young hipsters in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, on the corner of Rue de Seine and Rue de Buci. Its retro charm also attracts those nostalgic for the golden age of the Paris village. With its red-and-white gingham tablecloths, the BDM fully embraces its Parisian ambience. Quality cuisine, local produce and classic drinks at affordable prices. A chic yet relaxed atmosphere, the terrace is perfect for summer evenings.

label: Centre tchèque
comment: Nestled in the heart of Saint-Germain-des-Prés, the Czech Center offers an authentic immersion in Czech culture. Exhibitions, concerts, cinema, literary evenings, conferences, language courses? A rich and varied array of captivating events for curious visitors. And since 2011, don't miss the Paris-Prague jazz club, a not-to-be-missed Friday night event!

label: Le Mouffetard - Théâtre des arts de la marionnette
comment: The Théâtre de la Marionnette becomes Le Mouffetard - Théâtre des arts de la Marionnette after 20 years on the road. Located in the heart of the Latin Quarter in Paris, this theater offers a varied program dedicated to the art of puppetry. A resource center is also open to the public. Le Mouffetard promises quality puppet shows in a friendly venue open to all. Find out more about this cultural offering on the theater's website.

label: Maison de l'Europe à Paris
comment: The Maison de l'Europe in Paris, a non-profit organization, is a space dedicated to European citizenship. As a Europe Direct information center, it offers specialized services and organizes conferences, events and training on the European Union. Open to all, it's the ideal place to find out about and discuss European issues.

label: Eres (Montaigne)
comment: Eres swimwear collections highlight the beauty of the body's lines with sophistication and a unique touch of temporality. These high-quality creations offer refined, durable pieces that are always at the height of fashion. At Eres, elegance and style combine perfectly to sublimate the silhouette with subtlety and class.

label: Hippodrome ParisLongchamp
comment: Following its major renovation in 2018, the Longchamp racecourse has been reopened. Designed by architect Dominique Perrault, this building is a true architectural feat. Founded in 1857, it is home to the famous Qatar Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe. Horse racing enthusiasts and the curious gather here to bet, explore, lunch in one of the three restaurants, enjoy the rooftop or attend events. The Longchamp racecourse offers a unique and varied experience.

label: Le Diamant Bleu - La Croisière Gourmande
comment: The Croisière Gourmande on the Seine aboard Le Diamant Bleu combines indulgence and escape. Take advantage of the panoramic lounge overlooking Parisian monuments and the terrace deck to contemplate "Paris by night". A musical atmosphere with live singers and DJs transforms the lounge into a dance floor. The tasting menu offers 9 flavors prepared on board by the chef and his team. A unique gastronomic experience to share with family, friends or couples.

label: Le petit Keller
comment: Take a trip back in time at Le petit Keller restaurant, immersed in the retro atmosphere of the 50s with its period tiling and Formica tables. Here, chef Kaori Endo prepares a family-style cuisine with world flavors, focusing on fresh, often organic produce. On the menu: daily specials and bentos for lunch, and a variety of small plates to share in the evening. And don't forget the cellar, with its selection of natural wines to accompany your meals.

label: La Scène Thélème
comment: La Scène Thélème, near the Arc de Triomphe in Paris, offers refined cuisine combining Japanese and French flavors, featuring top-quality seasonal produce. In addition to the Michelin-starred restaurant, a theater hosts a variety of shows by renowned and up-and-coming artists. It's the place to be for lovers of gastronomy and culture in Paris, combining the delight of the taste buds with the wonder of the arts.

In addition to the Michelin-starred restaurant, a theater hosts a variety of shows by renowned and up-and-coming artists. It's the place to be for lovers of gastronomy and culture in Paris, combining the delight of the taste buds with the wonder of the arts.

label: Musée des graffitis
comment: Since May 26, 2009, the Graffiti Museum has been welcoming street artists to express their talent on panels that are renewed every two weeks. The most remarkable works are preserved to form a unique collection. This innovative museum is an initiative of the Lilolila neighborhood association, based at 295 rue de Belleville, which has been active in the 19th arrondissement since 2004. A true place of artistic expression in constant evolution!

label: Aux bons crus
comment: The Aux bons crus restaurant, set in a traditional Parisian bistro with red checkered tablecloths and wooden furniture, offers generous, authentic French family cuisine. Dishes, prepared with care and butter, are served in a warm, friendly atmosphere. This Les Routiers-labeled address guarantees a typically French culinary experience, where tradition and simplicity come together to delight diners.

label: Comédie-Française - Studio-Théâtre
comment: Inaugurated in 1996 by director Jean-Pierre Miquel at the Carrousel du Louvre, this venue celebrates the first Moscow Art Theatre Studio. This intimate venue offers a unique theatrical experience on a 50 m² stage for 136 spectators. The Comédie-Française troupe performs here all year round, offering a wide choice of classic and contemporary plays. Performances, lasting around an hour, take place at 6.30pm from Wednesday to Sunday for theater lovers.

label: La Cinémathèque française
comment: The Cinémathèque française, in the Bercy Gardens, is housed in a modern building designed by Frank O. Gehry. Dedicated to cinema, it features the Méliès museum, exhibitions, screenings, meetings, conferences, a library and bookshop. Georges Méliès, film genius, was celebrated by Martin Scorsese in Hugo Cabret for his famous shell in the eye of the moon. Immerse yourself in the life of this unique character at La Cinémathèque for an enchanting journey through the history of cinema.

label: Palais de l’Institut de France
comment: The Institut de France, located in the former Collège des Quatre-Nations in Paris, is an architectural masterpiece. Founded by Cardinal Mazarin between 1662 and 1688, it has been home to five renowned academies since 1795: the Académie française, des inscriptions et belles-lettres, des sciences, des beaux-arts and des sciences morales et politiques. It houses cultural treasures such as the Bibliothèque Mazarine and prestigious museums, contributing to culture and knowledge in France.

label: Paroisse protestante luthérienne Saint-Jean
comment: Located close to the Invalides, in a green setting, Saint-Jean church invites you to come and visit. Every Sunday at 10:30am, the faithful and the curious gather to worship. Events also punctuate the week: enchanting concerts, silent prayers and meditations on Saturdays... The Saint-Jean parish, part of the Église Protestante Unie de France, embodies the warm, welcoming spirit of the Lutheran denomination.

label: Flamme de la Liberté - Stèle commémorative à la Princesse Diana
comment: The Flame of Liberty, restored in 1987 near the Pont de l'Alma in Paris, symbolizes the friendship between France and the United States. A gilded copper replica of the Statue of Liberty's flame, it became a place of remembrance after the death of Princess Diana in 1997. Emblematic and emotionally charged, it attracts visitors from all over the world to pay tribute to her with flowers, poems and engraved messages. A historic icon to discover in Paris.

label: Antoine & Lili
comment: On the Quai de Valmy, three boutiques in acidic hues present the brand's women's and children's collections, brimming with cheerfulness and bright colors. There's also a selection of original ethnic-inspired objects, including jewelry, babouches and babioles. A true paradise for lovers of fashion and exotic curiosities.

label: Zenzan
comment: Located near the Champs-Élysées, the Zenzan restaurant is a must for fans of Japanese cuisine. With its variety of authentic dishes at affordable prices, there's something for everyone: sushi, yakitori, ramen, to suit every taste. The friendly atmosphere makes it an ideal place to enjoy a meal with friends and family. Zenzan offers a true Japanese culinary experience.

label: L'Éclaireur
comment: Discover Martine and Armand Hadida's cutting-edge fashion selection at the stunning L'Eclaireur Sévigné concept store. A place halfway between the organic and the technological, offering a unique experience oscillating between reality and illusion. Voted best concept store in the world by WeAr magazine in 2009, it perfectly embodies the marriage of avant-garde and elegance.

label: Ladurée Royale
comment: Since 1862, Ladurée Royale has embodied French art de vivre. This historic tearoom, adorned with restored woodwork and frescoes, features ceilings adorned with pastry angels. The menu, in perfect harmony with the seasons, reveals an authentic and delicious cuisine that perpetuates the reputation of the Maison. Enthusiasts delight in Ladurée's unrivalled macaroons, refined croissants and emblematic pastries, perpetuating an exceptional culinary tradition.

label: Un guide à Paris
comment: Would you like to discover Paris in a different way? As a passionate tour guide, I offer personalized tours to explore the capital's emblematic and secret places. Whether you're a couple, a family or a group of friends, immerse yourself in the magic of Paris on a private tour. Tailor-made programs for business, association or school groups. Let's discover together authentic neighborhoods, hidden gardens and picturesque passages. I'll share my favorite addresses for a unique experience. Ready to explore Paris with me?

label: Peppe Pizzeria
comment: Located in the charming Saint-Blaise district, Peppe Pizzeria is the project of Peppe Cutraro, voted best pizza maker in the world in Naples in 2019-2020. A former chef at Big Mama, he offers an entirely homemade menu, offering a gustatory journey to Naples through the best Neapolitan pizzas in the world! With its open-plan kitchen and outdoor terrace, the culinary experience is both authentic and convivial. A must for lovers of quality pizzas.

label: Jacadi
comment: Discover timeless, elegant children's fashion à la française. From Liberty blouses to smocked dresses, each piece reflects unparalleled refinement. The brand combines know-how and creativity in its lines for children, birth, shoes and nursery. Immerse yourself in a world where timeless chic meets made-in-France authenticity.

label: Raimo
comment: Parisian ice cream maker Raimo has been renowned since 1947. In 2008, the Raimondo family passed on their know-how to three gastronomic enthusiasts to guarantee quality. With over 120 flavors of ice cream, creams and sorbets, Raimo caters to every craving, some of them seasonal. Ranked among the capital's best ice cream shops by Sortiraparis.com in 2013, Raimo is present in several Parisian neighborhoods. Come and discover their originality at one of their outlets.

label: Rosa Bonheur sur Seine
comment: On the banks of the Seine, the boat-guingette Rosa Bonheur sur Seine warmly welcomes guests, offering a relaxed, sunny atmosphere. Open non-stop, this place offers quality cuisine to be savored while admiring the spectacular view of the Grand Palais from its sunny terrace. A perfect place to relax and enjoy the gentle Parisian lifestyle.

label: Église Saint-Denys de la Chapelle
comment: The current building dates back to 1204, erected without a stone vault on the site of the chapel of Sainte-Geneviève (dating from 475). It rests on three pairs of early Gothic pillars. In the 18th century, under the reign of Louis XV, a neo-Doric façade replaced the 13th-century porch depicting the legend of the saint. The building backs onto the Basilica of Sainte-Jeanne-d'Arc.

label: Max Linder Panorama
comment: The Max Linder Panorama, majestically situated on the boulevards, is a cinematic institution dedicated to grand spectacle. Featuring a 16-meter panoramic screen, THX sound, 600 comfortable seats spread over three levels, and an elegant reception area, this independent cinema offers a unique, immersive experience for film lovers.

label: Kiehl's
comment: Founded in 1851, a modest New York pharmacy decided to diversify by creating cosmetics tailored to the needs of its clientele. Over a century later, Kiehl's has become a benchmark for high-quality beauty products. Immerse yourself in the brand's world by booking a personalized consultation in their Beauty Room. Let yourself be pampered and discover unique treatments that will enhance your natural beauty.

label: Gare d'Austerlitz
comment: The Gare d'Austerlitz, located in the 13th arrondissement, welcomes over 20 million visitors every year. Opened in 1840 and rebuilt between 1862 and 1867, it was listed as a historic monument in 1997. It is divided into two zones: the street level (Seine hall, Museum hall) and the underground section. For last-minute needs, a varied catering offer, including innovative concepts and a mini-market, is available on site.

label: Musée Nissim de Camondo
comment: Built between 1911 and 1914 by architect René Sergent near Parc Monceau, Count Moïse de Camondo's hotel is a magnificent reconstruction of an 18th-century residence. An art enthusiast, he collected antique furniture, paintings, tapestries, porcelain and silverware. It's a testament to his love of art and history, immersing visitors in the refined atmosphere of 18th-century aristocracy. An enriching experience for art lovers.

label: Théâtre des Champs-Élysées
comment: The Théâtre des Champs-Élysées, the jewel of Parisian entertainment, is distinguished by its beauty and history. Designed by architectural greats such as Henry Van de Velde and Auguste Perret, it is an emblem of 20th-century style. The 300,000 annual spectators enjoy a varied program of ballets, operas, orchestras and recitals. An exceptional cultural venue where tradition meets modernity, inviting visitors to enjoy unique artistic experiences.

label: Stock Claudie Pierlot
comment: Discover the "feminine and urban" collections of ready-to-wear, shoes and accessories from this renowned brand, all at 40% off the original price. Take advantage of this opportunity to treat yourself to trendy, quality pieces at reduced prices. Don't miss this opportunity to renew your wardrobe with style and elegance without breaking the bank.

label: Le Carmen
comment: Pigalle's cocktail bar, a tribute to George Bizet, is housed in a listed 19th-century townhouse. Antoine Platteau's decor blends elegance and refinement, with wood panelling, columns, alcoves and Louis XVI armchairs. The absinthe cocktails are original and delicious, accompanied by DJ?s, acoustic concerts and stage performances. A unique venue in the heart of a lively Parisian nightlife district.

label: Madeleine 7
comment: Just a stone's throw from Place de la Madeleine, this brasserie offers traditional French cuisine of the highest quality. Perfect for a gourmet break during your shopping sprees near the department stores. You can also enjoy a coffee or lunch on the sunny terrace. An ideal setting to savor the delights of French gastronomy right in the heart of the capital.

label: Essaïon Théâtre
comment: Nestled in the medieval cellars of an old hotel near the Centre Pompidou, the Essaïon theater has been offering a varied program since 1975. Classics revisited, contemporary creations and musical shows follow one another on its two stages. The first room, transformed into a cabaret, offers an intimate atmosphere with 70 seats, while the second, with 100 seats, hosts theater and music in a stone-walled setting. A must for lovers of live entertainment.

label: Le Fumoir
comment: Le Fumoir, close to the Louvre and Rue de Rivoli, offers a charming colonial atmosphere that attracts a varied clientele. The terrace offers a magnificent view of the Louvre, and the menu features original cocktails and quality scotch. The library is the ideal place to relax with books and board games. Don't miss this unique Fumoir experience!

label: Le Baudelaire
comment: In 2011, the Hotel Burgundy saw its restaurant, Baudelaire, shine with its first Michelin star. In a neo-classical setting, the restaurant invites guests to a "rendez-vous du bon goût à la française". Renowned for its poetic flavors and inventive dishes, Le Baudelaire is an exceptional venue for lovers of fine dining.

label: Passage Brady
comment: The Passage Brady, built in 1828 between the Boulevard de Strasbourg and the Boulevard de Paris, is a Paris landmark with two unique atmospheres: under a glass roof and in the open air. Nicknamed Little India, this passage is brimming with Indo-Pakistani, Mauritian and Reunionese stores offering exotic flavors, spicy products and colorful clothes. A lively spot at 22 or 33 boulevard de Strasbourg and 43 rue du Faubourg Saint-Martin.

label: Pavillon de l’eau
comment: The Pavillon de l'eau in Paris is a place dedicated to raising awareness and providing information on water management. In addition to temporary exhibitions, it houses a permanent exhibition on water in Paris, open to the public free of charge. An enriching visit to better understand the issues surrounding this essential resource.

comment: Serge Bensimon is renowned for his sense of style, and this is reflected not only in his clothes, but also in his boutique. The latter offers a cutting-edge selection of contemporary design objects and curiosities. Right next door, another boutique offers his famous ready-to-wear collection and his must-have tennis shoes. An address not to be missed by fashion and home decor enthusiasts.

label: Escada
comment: Founded in Munich in 1978, Escada is a renowned brand that embodies glamour and finesse. Using high-quality materials, its collections combine chic and casual, offering the possibility of creating unique and elegant outfits through the play of superimpositions. Revealing a modern elegance tinged with glamour, the Escada line celebrates femininity with a sensual touch.

comment: Located between Belleville and the Buttes Chaumont, the Théâtre Clavel offers a varied program ranging from plays to one-man shows and concerts. With its commitment to quality, this venue caters for audiences of all ages, offering shows that are both entertaining and enriching.

label: Le Carreau du Temple
comment: Le Carreau du Temple, a 19th-century industrial-style cultural and sporting venue renovated by the City of Paris in 2014, offers over 230 artistic, cultural, sporting and lifestyle events a year. It is also home to over 50 associations offering a variety of weekly classes open to all. A place for encounters and explorations, it enlivens the cultural landscape of Paris.

label: Mundolingua
comment: Language, a primordial human faculty, has shaped our evolution and today?s social fabric. Mundolingua invites you to unravel its mysteries through an exploration dedicated to Languages, Language and Linguistics. Set off for a unique experience in the Latin Quarter, between the Jardin du Luxembourg and Saint-Sulpice. Mundolingua?s 170m² permanent exhibition promises a playful and intimate immersion in a wide range of themes.

label: Montmartre Enchanté
comment: Discover Montmartre with "Montmartre Enchanté": an unforgettable guided song tour led by renowned singer Veronica Antonelli. This UNESCO-labeled tour combines eco-tourism and historical anecdotes for a total immersion in the unique atmosphere of Montmartre, from the picturesque Place des Abbesses to the emblematic Sacré-C?ur. A memorable social experience awaits you, and you'll be enchanted by the magic of this mythical Paris neighborhood!

label: Gare du Nord
comment: Gare du Nord, in the 10th arrondissement, is Europe?s 1st and the world?s 3rd busiest in terms of visitors. With over 220 million passengers a year, it serves the north of France and international destinations. Inaugurated on June 14, 1846, it features a modern neoclassical style, with a façade adorned with twenty-three statues by renowned sculptors. It comprises four areas: the Eurostar Terminal, the Quai Transversal for catering, and levels -1 and -2 for passengers.

label: Paris on the Way
comment: Paris on the Way, founded in 2010, is a leader in guided tours. Our Ministry of Culture-certified guides offer unique experiences in Paris. Over 100 tours available, including museums, monuments, gastronomy and local life. Multilingual guides: French, English, German, Spanish, Portuguese, Italian, Russian. Enjoy our museum, theme, gourmet, children's and castle tours.

label: Atelier-boutique Sadio Bee
comment: Sadio Bee, at the crossroads of Senegalese and Guinean cultures, skilfully fuses African traditions with European modernity. His designs combine contemporary cuts with traditional materials such as wax, basin and bogolan. A harmonious encounter between heritage and trend, giving life to unique garments imbued with authenticity and style.

label: Marché biologique des Batignolles
comment: Every Saturday, the Batignolles market attracts Parisians in search of quality organic produce. In a warm, peaceful atmosphere, the stalls are brimming with fruit, seasonal vegetables, flowers, olive oil soaps, organic antipasti from Sardinia, cheeses and jams, all direct from the producer. An authentic, convivial experience not to be missed by lovers of fresh, local produce.

label: Ban Sabaï Bastille
comment: Located near Bastille and Porte Maillot, Ban Sabaï is a warm haven of peace. This salon offers a unique experience with Nuad Bo'Rarn, to balance the body's energies. In an authentic setting, treat yourself to a moment of well-being with expert masseurs. Ban Sabaï is the perfect place to recharge your batteries and rediscover harmony and serenity.

label: Comédie & Studio des Champs-Élysées
comment: The Comédie and Studio des Champs-Élysées, located on Avenue Montaigne near the Champs-Élysées, have been offering a varied, high-quality program for over a century. These emblematic venues of the Parisian stage have welcomed the greatest artists and renowned plays. Their unique atmosphere and rich history attract loyal audiences in search of theatrical emotion.

label: Azzaro
comment: The boutique of renowned Franco-Italian perfume designer Loris Azzaro nestles on the prestigious Rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré. This is where lovers of quality fragrances can discover the sublime women's collections of the house, founded in 1967. A must-see address for lovers of olfactory haute couture.

label: Soya cantine bio
comment: Nestled in the heart of a former faucet workshop in Paris's 11th arrondissement is the Soya canteen, a veritable pillar of the capital's organic gastronomy scene. Whether vegetarian or not, the diversity of the menu will satisfy every palate. A must-visit address for lovers of healthy cuisine, in this dynamic, friendly neighborhood.

label: Ducasse sur Seine
comment: Discover a unique cruise on the Seine aboard the first electric boat, combining modernity and French hospitality. Enjoy gourmet lunches and dinners, savoring exceptional cuisine prepared according to the seasons. Le Ducasse sur Seine, moored on the right bank, offers a magnificent view of Paris, the river and its Unesco World Heritage bridges. A harmonious immersion in the city for Paris lovers.

label: Cathédrale Saint-Alexandre-Nevsky
comment: Built in 1861 in neo-Byzantine style, the Orthodox church dedicated to Saint-Alexandre-Nevsky hosted the wedding of Pablo Picasso and a Russian dancer. Prestigious witnesses such as Jean Cocteau, Max Jacob and Guillaume Apollinaire honored this memorable event with their presence. Listed as a historic monument in 1983, this church is both a place of worship of great architectural value and a historical witness to significant events.

label: Cyrillus
comment: The brand offers "bon-chic-bon genre" fashion for the whole family, combining elegance and comfort. In addition to apparel, it has recently extended its expertise to home decoration with its "Cyrillus Intérieur" line. Discover a revisited classic style that will dress up your home as well as your wardrobe.

label: La tête dans les nuages
comment: Come and discover Europe's largest amusement arcade, located right in the heart of Paris. There's something for everyone: bowling, racing simulators, billiards and even games for children. Admission is free, so you can spend an entertaining time with family and friends. A fun experience not to be missed!

label: Galerie Thaddaeus Ropac - Paris Marais
comment: The Thaddaeus Ropac gallery, founded in Salzburg by the famous Austrian gallerist of the same name, moved to the Marais district in 1990. With its 4 floors and 1,000 m² of exhibition space, it showcases the work of the most influential contemporary artists. Among them are such names as Daniel Richter, Gilbert & George, Ilya & Emilia Kabakov, Georg Baselitz and Amos Gitaï. A second space opened on a wasteland site in Pantin in 2012.

label: Les Étincelles du Palais de la Découverte
comment: Les Étincelles, created by the Construire et Charpente Cénomane workshop, offers a temporary activity space during the renovation of the Palais de la Découverte. Evoking the brilliance of the Palais' renowned scientific demonstrations, this environmentally-friendly wooden structure is located near the Jardin Caroline Aigle, in the heart of the Parc André-Citroën. A harmonious blend of modernity and tradition to continue to amaze science and discovery enthusiasts.

label: Auditorium du Louvre
comment: The Musée du Louvre auditorium is an essential part of Parisian cultural life, offering over 300 events per season. Its varied program explores themes such as art history, archaeology, architecture and museography through lectures, films, concerts and international symposia. A diverse offering that brilliantly reflects the current state of the prestigious museum.

label: Bronx Pizzeria
comment: Pizzeria Bronx, ideally located near Porte Maillot in the 17th arrondissement, welcomes you in the warm atmosphere of an Italian trattoria. The decor, designed by Pierre Canot, takes you on a culinary journey through Tuscany, Liguria and Campania. Enjoy your pizzas on the 50-seat terrace, heated in winter, in an authentic and friendly setting.

Enjoy your pizzas on the 50-seat terrace, heated in winter, in an authentic and friendly setting.

label: La Sorbonne - Université
comment: In 1253, Louis IX founded a school for 16 needy theology students, named Sorbonne by Robert de Sorbon, the king's confessor. Since 1885, the Sorbonne has been France's largest university. The Sorbonne church, built from 1635 to 1642 by Jacques Lemercier on Richelieu's orders, houses his tomb, designed by François Girardon in 1694, and a cupola by Philippe de Champaigne.

label: Atelier Brancusi - Centre Georges Pompidou
comment: Constantin Brancusi, a Romanian sculptor who settled in Paris in 1904, left his mark on art history. His studio in the 15th arrondissement is now a national treasure, restored in 1997 at the Centre Pompidou in accordance with his testamentary wishes. This collection of 137 sculptures, 87 pedestals, 41 drawings, 2 paintings, more than 1,600 photographic plates and original prints bears witness to the genius of Brancusi, an indisputable master of modern sculpture. A fascinating immersion in his world.

label: Domaine national du Palais Royal
comment: The Palais Royal, built in 1633 by Cardinal de Richelieu, was once the residence of kings. The sublime gardens are set in impressive architecture, with works of modern art by Buren and Bury. The Buren columns, commissioned from Daniel Buren, stand near the Ministry of Culture. With their 260 black-and-white striped columns, they have become a symbol of Paris, not to be missed during a visit.

label: Église Notre-Dame-des-Champs
comment: Notre-Dame-des-Champs church, built in 1876 on the foundations of an ancient temple dedicated to Mercury, features Romanesque-style architecture. Within its walls are numerous paintings by the artist Joseph Aubert. A place steeped in history and beauty to discover on a rewarding visit.

label: Galerie de minéralogie et de géologie - Muséum national d'histoire naturelle
comment: Launched in October 2014, the 250m² exhibition at the Galerie de Minéralogie et de Géologie unveils a never-before-seen selection from the Museum's mineral collections. Treasures of the Earth presents 600 minerals, meteorites, gems and historic jewels from five continents. The scenography explores the formation of minerals, their diversity of color and form, and phenomena such as fluorescence. Some twenty giant crystals retrace the history of the Earth and the solar system.

label: Philharmonie de Paris
comment: The Philharmonie de Paris, the capital's new musical jewel, combines the talents of Jean Nouvel and Christian de Portzamparc. Explore the Musée de la Musique by day, attend renowned concerts by night. Relax at Gourmandises de l'Atelier or enjoy a meal at Le Balcon restaurant. The Philharmonie offers tours, exhibitions, concerts and workshops. Family activities are planned for weekends. A must for music lovers and the curious alike.
