label: Passage du Caire
comment: Built in 1798, the Passage du Caire is the oldest in Paris. Its name pays homage to the statues of Hathor. Under its fishbone glass roof, ready-to-wear wholesalers set up shop in this narrow Sentier space. The period facades are a delight for architecture enthusiasts. Accessible via several entrances, including Rue d'Alexandrie, Rue Saint-Denis and Rue du Caire, this is a must-see.

With 44,000 m2 dedicated to shopping and personalized services such as personal shopper, it attracts fashionistas in search of elegance. Here you'll find all the major luxury brands, the latest designers and a perfumery area. Printemps offers a personal shopping service in private lounges for an exclusive shopping experience. A must for fashion and luxury enthusiasts.

Renowned artistic director Virginie Viard brilliantly continues the legacy of the illustrious Karl Lagerfeld, bringing modernity and audacity to each collection. A true immersion in the world of fashion, between tradition and innovation.

label: La Caserne
comment: The renovated Caserne will open in June 2021 in the former Château-Landon fire station at 12 rue Philippe-de-Girard. This 4,000 m² incubator showcases eco-responsible fashion Made in France. 40 young brands are supported in their efforts to produce in an environmentally-friendly way. Workshops, exhibitions and events raise public awareness. A vegetated rooftop, a club and a vegetarian restaurant promote local and seasonal products.

This unique venue offers a unique artistic experience, at the crossroads of art and architecture. Reinvented in 2012, it is Europe's largest contemporary art center, offering an exciting journey through artistic creation. Explore emerging art and meet the creators of our time in this place steeped in history.

label: Le Vieux Belleville
comment: Take a trip back in time and discover or rediscover the popular songs of old Paris at Le Vieux Belleville musette restaurant. Accompanied by accordion or barrel organ, guests dine in a warm, authentic atmosphere reminiscent of the traditional bistros of yesteryear. A unique experience to plunge into the heart of Parisian musical culture, and let yourself be carried away by nostalgic, festive tunes.

label: Joe Allen
comment: In the heart of Paris's Etienne Marcel district, Joe Allen has been a New York institution since 1972, offering typical Big Apple brasserie cuisine. Club sandwiches, bagels, pecan pie, brownies and burgers are prepared with fresh ingredients. Weekends and holidays are the perfect time to enjoy a convivial brunch. Allen's Markets, at 33 rue du Château d'Eau, in the 10th arrondissement, is another restaurant to discover.

label: Les Tontons
comment: If you're looking for original flavors, the cantine des Tontons in Paris is the ideal address for tartar lovers. This booming bistro offers an impressive variety of revisited tartars: foie gras, blue cheese and walnuts, goat's cheese... Pair your dish with a quality wine from their exquisite selection. Don't miss this gourmet rendez-vous for a culinary experience full of surprises and delights!

label: Maison Fleuret - The Baking School - Notre-Dame
Lanvin Delphine
comment: Discover Paris on foot, by coach, by car or by bike and explore its emblematic districts such as the Marais, the Latin Quarter, Montmartre, the Palais Royal and the Île de la Cité and Île Saint-Louis. Opt for original tours on different themes such as famous women, crime, revolutions or Napoleon, and don't miss must-see museums such as the Louvre, Orsay, the Eiffel Tower or the Invalides. Take advantage of nearby sites such as Versailles, Giverny or Fontainebleau for a cultural immersion in the City of Light.

label: Le BHV Marais
comment: BHV MARAIS, located in the heart of Paris, is a veritable institution that has been seducing shoppers for 160 years with its diversity of products spread over 8 floors. Fashion, home decoration, DIY, beauty, culture, everything is there to satisfy everyone's desires. From hardware to clothing to cosmetics, you'll find it all at BHV MARAIS. The various themed floors allow you to stroll, relax and even enjoy delicious food. Men are not left out either, with the BHV L'HOMME area specially dedicated to their world. And for those in search of originality, the La Niche space offers a cutting-edge selection of trendy products. The BHV MARAIS, a destination not to be missed for a unique and varied shopping experience.

label: Céline
comment: Founded in 1945, the famous haute couture house Céline is distinguished by its emblematic logo formed by two interlaced "Cs". It offers a range of women's ready-to-wear collections, leather accessories (bags, gloves, shoes) and perfumes. Discover these renowned creations in her boutique on Avenue Montaigne. A must for fashion lovers in search of elegance and refinement.

label: Grand Palais
comment: The Grand Palais, the iconic building of the 1900 Paris World's Fair, is distinguished by its glass dome and French flag. A historic monument divided into the Nave, Galeries nationales and Palais de la Découverte, it offers a varied cultural program. A must-see venue close to the Champs-Élysées, it delights both art lovers with its renowned exhibitions and science enthusiasts with its dedicated children's museum. A unique address in the heart of Paris.

label: Comédie-Française - Théâtre du Vieux-Colombier
comment: The Théâtre du Vieux-Colombier, located in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, was founded in 1913 by Jacques Copeau. Restored by architect Bernard Kohn, it became the Comédie-Française's second theatre in 1993, seating 300. The Comédie-Française troupe offers a varied repertoire, combining classic and contemporary texts. A true institution of the performing arts, this unique historic and artistic venue is well worth a visit.

label: Le Petit Pont
comment: Le Petit Pont, a brasserie located opposite Notre Dame, is renowned for its lively terrace and relaxed atmosphere. Customers are seduced by a wide selection of cocktails, tasty dishes and gourmet desserts. Enjoy a pleasant setting and musical atmosphere for unique moments of relaxation.

label: V'Île Fertile
comment: V'Île Fertile, a market-garden farm in the Bois de Vincennes, practices old-fashioned urban agriculture. Managed by volunteers, it favors bio-intensive, chemical-free techniques. Freshly harvested vegetables are sold on site, and educational workshops are held at weekends. Accessible by RER line A, this green nugget will appeal to nature lovers right in the heart of the capital.

label: Edmond, le restaurant panoramique du Terrass’’ Hotel
comment: The 7th floor rooftop offers spectacular views over Paris. This is where you'll find a restaurant and bar in an artists' loft design, blending arty-chic ambience with breathtaking panoramas. Ideal for travelers in search of tranquility, this 4-star hotel offers a gourmet breakfast, Sunday brunch, delicate lunch or romantic dinner with a breathtaking view of the City of Light. A must for gourmets in search of magic!

label: Hermès (Saint-Honoré)
comment: Hermès has embodied French excellence for over 180 years. Each piece is the fruit of meticulous work, passing on a passion from generation to generation. Craftsmen explore their talents to offer unique and timeless creations. Hermès also organizes exclusive events and exhibitions to share its history and exceptional heritage. An emblematic brand, unrivalled in luxury.

label: Lili Cabas
comment: At Lili Cabas, discover a variety of bags for all your needs: beach, shopping, city strolls or picnics. Choose from elegant flap bags, practical shoulder straps, chic clutches or trendy besaces. Find the perfect bag for your style. Lili Cabas combines originality and practicality in a unique accessory to affirm your personality.

label: Violon d'Ingres
comment: At the heart of his gastronomic restaurant, chef Christian Constant revisits the classics of French cuisine, using carefully selected seasonal produce: soft-boiled eggs, pan-fried duck foie gras, crispy sea bass... emblematic dishes that have made the reputation of this not-to-be-missed address in the 7th arrondissement. With its elegant decor and refined cuisine, this renovated establishment is sure to delight food lovers.

label: Temoa
comment: Discover Temoa's carefully chosen selection of products from around the world, aligned with ethical values. Decorative objects, jewelry and accessories in vibrant colors are sure to win you over. Natural cosmetics and fair-trade delicatessen products complete this varied and responsible offer. A real invitation to travel and discover, to consume ethically and responsibly.

label: Le Gambetta club
comment: This cosmopolitan concert hall is a musical universe of world colors. From reggae and raï to funk and afro, let yourself be carried away by the bewitching rhythms. A friendly, festive atmosphere guaranteed for memorable evenings. And to top it all off, enjoy drinks at unbeatable prices. A unique musical and cultural experience awaits you!

label: Musée national des arts asiatiques - Guimet
comment: The Musée national des arts asiatiques ? Guimet holds the largest collection of Asian art in Europe, and the most comprehensive in the world. A true invitation to travel across Asia, from Afghanistan to Japan, without leaving France. A breathtaking immersion in Asian culture and history awaits you as soon as you step through the doors of the MNAAG.

label: Natalys
comment: Since it was founded in 1953, Natalys has set itself apart by offering clothing adapted to expectant mothers. Over the years, the brand has extended its expertise to children's fashion and nursery equipment. As a result, Natalys has become an essential reference for parents looking for quality, stylish products for their little ones.

label: Le Mesturet
comment: The "Le Mesturet" restaurant in Paris is an emblem of French bistros. Its authentic, high-quality home cooking uses fresh produce. The wine list, chosen by Alain Fontaine, will delight wine lovers. The warm, friendly atmosphere is instantly appealing. With room for 90 guests and a private lounge for 30, Le Mesturet is perfect for any event. The bar is open all day for a gourmet break. An address not to be missed in Paris.

label: Théâtre Michel
comment: The Théâtre Michel, founded by Michel Mortier in 1906, is a remarkable Italian-style Parisian theater. Today, it offers captivating comedies combining humor and emotion. Audiences are transported by stories that are at once funny, touching and incisive, offering them a moment of unforgettable entertainment.

label: Passy Plaza
comment: In 1995, MIPIM Award-winning architect Anthony Emmanuel Béchu rebuilt the Passy Plaza. In 2008, David & Lampros Architectes renovated the building to make it lighter and more modern. Today, Passy Plaza is an ideal venue for high-end shopping, attracting a discerning clientele. Transparent glass roofs and elegant window displays enable brands to fully reflect their philosophy.

label: Le Siga-Siga - La boutique sans argent
comment: Come and discover the Siga-Siga, a unique place dedicated to collaborative giving, located in the former Gare de Reuilly, in the 12th arrondissement. Drop off transportable items (clothes, crockery, games, toys, books, etc.) you no longer need, and leave with new items... all free of charge! You can also relax over a cup of coffee or tea. Make a generous gesture and take part in this wonderful initiative!

label: Caveau de la Huchette
comment: Jazz and Paris, a timeless idyll... Since Saint Germain des Prés, the French capital has attracted jazz artists from all over the world. Discover the magic of the Caveau de la Huchette, a musical oasis near Notre-Dame. Since 1947, this temple to jazz has welcomed legends such as Miles Davis and Duke Ellington. Enchanting evenings combine music, refined beverages and dancing until dawn. A unique experience for jazz lovers.

label: Tootbus Paris
comment: Explore Paris in a practical, eco-friendly way with Tootbus! Discover the jewels of the City of Light aboard double-decker buses equipped with wifi, clean energy and sunroof. Opt for a 24h or 48h package, and take advantage of the Hop-on Hop-off system to get on and off as you please. Thanks to the Tootbus application, follow the buses in real time and discover authentic Paris with Tootwalk. An ideal way to visit the capital in complete freedom and comfort.

label: Pierre Hermé (Bonaparte)
comment: Dubbed "the Picasso of pastry" by Vogue, Pierre Hermé shone at Fauchon before conquering Japan. Back in France, his boutique at 72 rue Bonaparte has become a must for sweet tooths. Hailed worldwide by Paris Match, The New York Times and The Guardian, he pushes the boundaries of taste with his innovative macaroons, pastries and chocolates.

label: Jardin Catherine Labouré
comment: The Jardin de la Vierge, a former kitchen garden steeped in history, pays tribute to a 19th-century nun who witnessed Marian apparitions. It's a popular place for Parisians to relax and enjoy nature in summer. The 7,000m² grounds feature fruit trees, vines, an arbour and a retro atmosphere. It's a haven of peace where families, friends and lovers come together to relax or stroll along the paths.

label: Square Léon Serpollet
comment: Square Serpollet, in the 18th arrondissement of Paris, pays tribute to Léon Serpollet, the famous French inventor. This green space offers calm and relaxation to visitors, providing an opportunity to reflect on the history of industry. A place of tranquility in the heart of the city, inviting contemplation and discovery of nature in the midst of Paris. An ode to the inventor's genius, offering a haven of peace in the midst of urban bustle.

label: Los Guardiola, la Comédie du Tango
comment: Tango dancers Marcelo Guardiola and Giorgia Marchiori, known as Los Guardiola, are world-famous. Winners of the "Nueva Generación" diploma in 2004, they were officially recognized by the National Tango Academy in 2016. Their universally acclaimed show is a light-hearted blend of tango in Argentina, dance and music in Italy, and fluidity in France. Their international success has led them to charm audiences around the world.

label: Le Falstaff
comment: With over 120 beer references, the Faltstaff is a real paradise for beer lovers. This French pub is very popular with students looking for a change of scenery and a friendly atmosphere. In addition to its wide selection of beers, it also offers daily specials, snacks and even moules-frites to accompany the beverages. A great place to quench your thirst and indulge in a warm, lively atmosphere.

label: Square Maurice Gardette
comment: Just off boulevard Richard Lenoir, you'll find Square Maurice Gardette, with its charming bandstand dating from 1899. This green space appeals to children and adults alike, with its play areas and boules pitch. An oasis of relaxation in the heart of the city, ideal for unwinding and enjoying a quiet moment in the open air.

comment: Located close to Roland Garros, the Parc des Princes and the Auteuil and Longchamp racecourses, Le Congrès stands out for its exceptional location. Considered a flagship of good taste, this establishment offers a luxurious and refined setting, without being ostentatious. An address of choice for lovers of comfort and elegance.

label: Le Flamboire
comment: In this renowned restaurant, top-quality meats and fish are grilled over a wood fire, perpetuating the culinary tradition of the Aveyron region. Diners can watch their dish being cooked, adding a convivial dimension to their meal. The tantalizing smell of the fireplace adds a touch of authenticity. Every mouthful is delicious, reflecting the passion of the kitchen's artisans. This establishment is a haven of peace for lovers of good food and sharing.

label: Château de la Muette
comment: The Château de la Muette, built in 1912 near the Bois de Boulogne, is home to the OECD. Commissioned by Baron Henri de Rothschild, this masterpiece by architect Lucien Hesse replaces the former château. The Rothschild coat of arms adorns the pediment, while the façade is embellished with 24 sculptures representing allegories and theatrical masks. The gardens, refurbished in 2009-2010, are home to 25,000 plants, including 139 majestic trees.

comment: Watch in fascination as chefs busy themselves in the kitchen, intoxicating aromas titillating your senses. Immerse yourself in a refined culinary universe where the passion for quality products shines through. Discover surprising combinations of textures and flavors, in original creations. Each bite is an explosion of flavors, a symphony for your taste buds. Let yourself be surprised by this unique taste experience, where culinary art holds a thousand surprises in store.

label: Guerrisol
comment: Guerrisol, a well-known thrift store chain, is present in several locations in Paris. It offers a wide selection of second-hand clothes, shoes and accessories for the whole family, from men to women and children. With its boutiques, Guerrisol offers an ecological and economical alternative for those wishing to adopt a unique and responsible style.

label: Square du Vert-Galant
comment: The Square du Vert Galant, dedicated to Henri IV and his many mistresses, was awarded the "Espace vert écologique" label in 2007 for its remarkable flora and fauna in the heart of the capital. The park has become a favorite spot for romantic strolls, offering boat rides with breathtaking views over the Seine, the Louvre and the Hôtel de la Monnaie. An exceptional green space with incomparable charm.

label: Tappo
comment: Located in Rue Commines, the Tappo bar offers an authentic Italian tasting experience. Discover a selection of cicchetti, those delicious Italian tapas, accompanied by the famous Venetian spritz, the trendy cocktail of the moment. Let yourself be charmed by the wide choice of Italian wines and enjoy a refreshing prosecco. A true invitation to travel to the heart of transalpine gastronomy.

label: Piscine Yvonne Godard
comment: In January 2020, a new, modern swimming pool opened its doors, offering two pools 10 and 15 meters wide and 25 meters long. The sports pool has an adjustable floor, respects the environment by using 33% renewable energy and is accessible to the disabled. A rooftop solarium lets you relax and soak up the sun, providing a haven of peace in the heart of the city.

label: Piscine Rouvet
comment: A veritable institution among Parisian pools, this emblematic establishment offers the chance to relax and refresh in the very heart of the capital. With a breathtaking view over the Bassin de la Villette, this historic swimming pool is a unique place to swim, combining charm and conviviality. A little corner of aquatic paradise where you can recharge your batteries.

label: Boom Boom Villette
comment: Boom Boom Villette, formerly Vill'Up, will open in summer 2023. With 25,000 m², it will offer 4,000 m² for restaurants and 21,000 m² for leisure activities. There will be 20 kiosks and 3 bars for dining, as well as an escape game, bowling lanes, trampolines, arcade games, a children's area and cultural events hosted by Live Nation. Meanwhile, Pathé and iFly remain open.

label: À la Biche au Bois
comment: Nestled in the countryside, this restaurant stands out for its quality, generous portions and warm atmosphere. Game lovers will love the doe, the star dish. Refined flavors and meticulous presentation for a memorable culinary experience. Ideal for a convivial gourmet moment, this place will satisfy discerning palates. An authentic gastronomic getaway not to be missed by epicureans in search of gustatory pleasure.

label: Fontaine Igor Stravinsky
comment: The Igor Stravinsky Fountain, created in 1983 by artists Jean Tinguely and Niki de Saint Phalle, stands at the foot of the Centre Pompidou. The 16 colorful sculptures, animated by jets of water, recall the work of the famous Russian composer. The fountain, located on a peaceful square away from traffic, is surrounded by restaurants, IRCAM and the Saint-Merri church. A popular place to stroll and relax, it offers a haven of peace in the heart of the city.

label: Tours de Notre-Dame de Paris
comment: After climbing the 422 steps to the towers of Notre-Dame Cathedral, visitors discover one of the most beautiful views of Paris. Three stages mark the tour: the Upper Hall and its Gothic architecture, the Chimera Gallery with its famous gargoyles, such as the Stryge, and finally the Belfry and the Emmanuel Bumblebee, a 13-ton masterpiece. A fascinating experience for history and architecture buffs.

label: Angelina Rivoli
comment: Founded in 1903 opposite the Jardins des Tuileries, the Angelina tea room attracts an aristocratic clientele with its historic setting and sweet treats. Angelina has been renowned for its sweet and savory dishes for over a century, offering a refined menu created by a talented chef. From salmon pavé to veal medallions with morel mushrooms, the delicate dishes will delight the taste buds, while the pastries will delight those with a sweet tooth.

label: La Casa del Tango
comment: Take a trip to the heart of Argentina by joining the tango classes at Casa del Tango, directed by Frédérique Behar, in the 19th arrondissement. Whether you're an enthusiast or a beginner, discover workshops, balls and introductions to this spellbinding dance. Saturday tango evenings and tea dances offer unforgettable moments of music and movement.

label: Saint-Lazare Paris
comment: Located at the Saint-Lazare train station, St.Lazare Paris shines with its 10,000 m² on 3 levels. With no fewer than 80 stores, this commercial space features renowned names such as Muji to Go, Starbucks, Sephora, Burger King and many others. Enough to satisfy all the shopping and dining desires of visiting travellers. With the added bonus of the Lazare restaurant, run by the talented chef Éric Frechon, the offer promises an unforgettable experience.

label: CoCo Paris
comment: Nestled in the Opéra Garnier, CoCo Paris combines refinement and gastronomy. In a design décor blending 19th-century and contemporary, this restaurant offers authentic cuisine, combining tradition and innovation with fresh, seasonal produce. Its vast 1,500 m² terrace, for up to 230 guests, becomes an oasis of calm and elegance in the Paris sunshine. An intoxicating experience for the senses, an enchanted interlude for gourmets in search of unique sensations.

comment: Gaëlle Barré imagines her collections like poems, for women and children. Her signature creations are delicate, feminine and original, characterized by unique cuts and structures. A harmony of sensitivity and inventiveness emanates from her designs, offering a refreshing vision of fashion.

label: Ferme du jardin d’Éole
comment: In 2020, Les fermes d'Espoir opened an urban farm in the heart of the Jardin d'Éole. Home to sheep, goats, rabbits and chickens, this space appeals to visitors in search of nature in the city. Guided tours are offered, providing an enriching immersion experience. Beyond its playful aspect, this social project also aims to promote integration and education in sustainable development. An initiative that combines fun, sharing and awareness-raising.

label: Hippodrome d'Auteuil
comment: Auteuil, a world-renowned racecourse, specializes in obstacle racing. With emblematic obstacles such as "le juge de paix" and the Rivière des Tribunes, it's a place where France's best show jumpers come face to face. Auteuil embodies the quintessence of obstacle racing, sublimated by the breeding of exceptional horses on 33 hectares of greenery on the edge of Paris.

label: Restaurant Les 3 Frères
comment: Tucked away in an unassuming alleyway in the Goutte d?Or district, Les 3 Frères is a popular spot for couscous lovers. Every Thursday evening, starting at 8:30pm, gourmets flock here to savor succulent, home-cooked couscous at affordable prices. The atmosphere is friendly and animated by a varied clientele. Arrive early to secure a table for this affordable Mediterranean feast. An unmissable gastronomic experience in this charming Paris neighborhood.

label: Port de la Rapée
comment: The Port de la Rapée, located between the Charles de Gaulle and Bercy bridges on the right bank of the Seine in Paris, is an idyllic spot in the 12th arrondissement. Close to the Gare de Lyon, the Ministry of Finance and the AccorHotels Arena, this lively district is bursting with life. A few moored boats offer the chance to relax while admiring the view of Les Docks - Cité de la Mode et du Design. A true haven of peace in the heart of the City of Light.

label: Le Bar Botaniste
comment: The Shangri-la Paris, a renowned palace, is ideally located near the Trocadero gardens. Designed by Pierre-Yves Rochon, the Bar Botaniste is an elegant refuge inspired by Napoleonic tents. A tribute to Prince Roland Bonaparte's botanical passion, the bar offers a unique mixology experience with a selection of refined spirits. A veritable jewel in the crown of western Paris, the Bar Botaniste is the place to be for lovers of exceptional cocktails.

label: Le Viaduc des Arts
comment: Le Viaduc des Arts, near the Place de la Bastille in Paris, showcases the talents of French artisans. Jewelry, decorations, antique automata, each creator contributes to the elegance of the place. Exhibitions on Métiers d?Art, Mozart or Africa offer a rich cultural experience, accompanied by enchanting musical notes. A must-see for lovers of creativity.

label: Théâtre Edgar
comment: Since its creation between 1973 and 1975, the Théâtre Edgar, nestled in the lively Montparnasse district, has been dedicated to bringing new talents to the fore: whether they be authors, directors or actors. A veritable artistic incubator, it has forged a solid reputation in the Parisian cultural landscape.

label: Spa Energymer
comment: Spa Energymer offers a total escape in the heart of the capital with its body treatments, thalasso and beauty area. Featuring hydromassage baths, marine wraps and jet showers, it perfectly embodies the essence of thalassotherapy. Relaxation continues with a hammam and sauna for a complete relaxation experience.

label: Herbéus
comment: Herbéus sells natural beauty products from well-known brands such as Laboratoire de Combes d?Ases, Phyt?s, Dr Hauschka and Douces Angevines. Their range includes quality hair, face and body care products, floral waters and plant elixirs, with an emphasis on authenticity. Herbéus is committed to offering products that respect the environment, thanks to their expertise and passion for plants, for a unique sensory well-being experience.

label: Pathé Parnasse
comment: Pathé Parnasse, part of the Gaumont Pathé cinema network, nestles a stone's throw from Montparnasse station, in the heart of a lively street packed with attractive restaurants. With its 12 screens equipped with reclining seats, this establishment offers an upscale cinematic experience unlike any other in Paris. The perfect address for cinema lovers in search of comfort and exclusivity.

label: Le Quincy
comment: Immerse yourself in the heart of the countryside right in the middle of Paris at this genuine inn, promising delicious local cuisine, checkered tablecloths and a warm welcome from the owner. A culinary escapade rich in flavors and authenticity, ideal for lovers of tradition and conviviality. A rustic, gourmet interlude that will delight the taste buds of even the most discerning palates.

label: 25° Est
comment: 25° Est shines among the cafés on the Bassin de la Villette. With its relaxed, typically Parisian ambience, panoramic views, affordable prices and two-level terrace, it attracts visitors on sunny days. A not-to-be-missed venue, it also offers a variety of DJ sets and concerts (jazz, world music...). A perfect place to enjoy a good time with friends.

label: Hugo Boss
comment: The famous German brand HUGO BOSS diversifies its style through different ranges. There are classic (Black), luxurious (Selection), sporty (Orange and Green) and creative (Hugo) collections. Since 2009, Boss Selection has offered a new line, Tailored Line, by appointment. This is the second largest HUGO BOSS boutique in the world and the first in Europe.

label: Eden Park
comment: Founded in 1987 by five former Racing Club de France rugby players, the Eden Park brand offers chic sportswear collections for the whole family. Recognizable by its famous pink bow tie, a symbol of the eccentricity of its founders, the brand embodies elegance and fantasy in equal measure. With a refined, casual style, Eden Park perfectly blends the worlds of sport and fashion, offering quality pieces for a look that's both casual and sophisticated.

label: Arts factory
comment: Arts Factory, an artistic oasis founded in 1996 by Effi Mild and Laurent Zorzin in the former loft of the Lavignes-Bastille gallery, dedicates its 250 m² on four levels to the graphic arts scene. Exhibitions, a bookshop, workshops and events make this space a must for discovering emerging talents and established artists in drawing, illustration, graphic design and comics. Unique in Europe, Arts Factory offers a captivating panorama of contemporary artistic creation.

label: Nathalie Garçon
comment: Located in one of Paris's most prestigious galleries, this boutique offers an enchanting setting, a true haven of peace in the heart of the urban bustle. The warm, attentive welcome makes you feel almost at home. Take the time to explore a collection that stands out for its originality and unique style, far removed from today's standardized fashion trends. A true oasis of serenity, where elegance and authenticity are the watchwords.

label: La Fab.
comment: Located near the Bibliothèque F. Mitterrand in the 13th arrondissement, "La Fab." is a must-see address for agnès b. and SOA Architectes. The gallery exhibits a diverse collection of 5,000 works, including photos by S. Keïta and N. Golding, street art by Banksy, paintings by A. Warhol and J-M Basquiat, sculptures by J-M Othoniel, installations by C. Lévêque and videos. Quarterly exhibitions are held at agnès b.'s Galerie du Jour, where everything is for sale. A captivating artistic experience awaits you!

label: Bobino
comment: Located in the lively Montparnasse district, Bobino is an iconic venue offering a wide variety of performing arts: concerts, one-man shows, dance, theater, comedy and much more. After enjoying an unforgettable show, spectators can discover the many restaurants in the area for a gourmet break before or after the show. A must for culture and entertainment lovers in Paris.

label: Square d'Anvers
comment: The Square d'Anvers occupies a portion of Montmartre's former abattoirs. With a lively bandstand on sunny days and a breathtaking view of Montmartre's Sacré C?ur, this square has a charming, peaceful atmosphere. A pleasant stopover in the heart of the city to enjoy the tranquility and beauty of this place steeped in history.

label: Piscine Pontoise
comment: The swimming pool on rue de Pontoise, in the heart of the Latin Quarter, boasts unique Art Deco architecture dating from 1933, and is a listed building. Several sports activities are offered, including yoga, cardio-muscu and squash. With opening hours until 11:45pm on weekdays, you can take advantage of this space at any time of day to relax or work out. A charming and authentic place, ideal for sports and relaxation enthusiasts.

label: Armor Lux
comment: Armor Lux draws its inspiration from the values and traditions of Brittany, which are reflected in its authentic creations. The brand embodies French know-how in textiles and clothing, offering products of incomparable quality. With a rich heritage and creative vision, Armor Lux stands out for its unique, timeless style, perfectly symbolizing the French art of living.

label: Musée du Luxembourg
comment: The Musée du Luxembourg, the first museum in France to open in 1750, presents two annual exhibitions from Rmn-Grand Palais. It highlights the Renaissance, the links between art and power, and the role of Paris as a capital of the arts. Located close to the Palais and Jardin du Luxembourg, the Senate Museum enjoys an exceptional setting in the heart of the Latin Quarter, with spaces redesigned by architect Shigeru Ban, including the Angelina restaurant/tea room and educational workshops.

label: Azabu
comment: The Azabu restaurant, nestled on the left bank of the Seine near the Pont Neuf, offers a quality Japanese culinary experience. Its sober, contemporary setting appeals to diners, who can savor their meal at the table or comfortably seated at the counter, enjoying the spectacle of teppan-yaki. An address to remember for discovering Japanese gastronomy in elegant, refined surroundings.

label: Chez Jeannette
comment: Jeannette has transformed an old bistro into a trendy spot for Parisian night owls. With its retro ambience, young clientele and attractive prices, this bar on rue du Faubourg Saint-Denis is very popular. From the aperitif onwards, crowds flock here. From 10.30pm onwards, the music swells and the guinguettes improvise. You feel like you're at a friend's house, perhaps Jeannette herself. The plates of charcuterie and cheese are delicious, decorating the zinc and Formica tables.

label: Chez Hé
comment: Chez Hé offers a unique experience in two distinct areas: a convivial dining area, equipped with large tables ideal for group lunches, and a play area dedicated to children. Children can enjoy tasty Asian dishes before having fun with their friends, all under the supervision of caring adults. A perfect combination for an enjoyable time with family and friends.

label: Le Rex Club
comment: Formerly a temple to disco and rock, the Rex Club, nestled in the basement of the famous Grand Rex cinema, is now a bastion of techno and electro in Paris. This Parisian party mecca regularly plays host to the most prestigious national and international DJs. Ideally located on the Grand Boulevards, the Rex Club remains an essential reference on the electronic music scene.

label: Le Bazaristain
comment: Discover Le Bazaristain, a 70 m² concept store in Paris, combining tradition and innovation. Fashion and decoration blend harmoniously in this unique and inspiring space, where creativity reigns supreme. Whether you're a design enthusiast or simply curious, let yourself be seduced by the warm atmosphere and treasures from around the world. Every object has a story, and every detail counts. Le Bazaristain, a place of peace for lovers of beautiful things and in search of inspiration.

Whether you're a design enthusiast or simply curious, let yourself be seduced by the warm atmosphere and treasures from around the world. Every object has a story, and every detail counts. Le Bazaristain, a place of peace for lovers of beautiful things and in search of inspiration.

label: Les Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann - Expériences uniques
comment: Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann plunges you into the worlds of gastronomy and fashion. Attend the Fashion Show to discover the latest trends in just 30 minutes. Learn how to make macaroons at the Macaron Course and taste your creations on the spot. Take part in the Cours Ferrandi to master the sweet and savory recipes of renowned chefs. A unique experience awaits you at Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann!

label: Do Eat Better
comment: Do Eat Better offers gastronomic tours to discover a city through its culinary specialties. Accompanied by a local expert, you'll sample local dishes as you stroll the streets. Present in France, Italy and Spain, our tours offer authentic immersion. The Paris Food Tour of Montmartre lets you savor traditional dishes, learn about local history and enjoy breathtaking views of the capital.

label: New Morning
comment: Since 1981, Le New Morning has been a jazz and world music club renowned for its cutting-edge, high quality programming. Legends such as Miles Davis, Prince and Chet Baker have performed here, offering fans a unique musical experience. Located in the République district of Paris, this legendary venue encourages exchanges between artists and audiences. Whether visiting or resident, jazz enthusiasts are sure to find their way to the New Morning.

label: Stella McCartney
comment: Paul McCartney's daughter, a renowned fashion designer, has imposed her unique style, combining impeccable cuts, irreverence and sexy femininity. In addition to her ready-to-wear collections for children, shoes and accessories, in 2012 she was chosen to dress British athletes at the London Olympics. A success story that confirms her talent and her place in the fashion world.

label: Aux Belles Poules
comment: Listed in the supplementary inventory of historic monuments, "Aux Belles Poules" is an exceptional brothel. Its mosaics, ceramics and erotic frescoes are a precious testimony to Art Deco. Closed in 1948, it was reopened in 2017 thanks to Caroline Senot. Now, the public can discover this marvel during guided tours retracing its fascinating history, as well as that of brothels in Paris.

label: Opera a Palazzo - Music Opera Events
comment: The Fondation Simone et Cino Del Duca organizes an exceptional opera evening, plunging you into the heart of the love story of Violetta and Alfredo in Verdi's La Traviata. Enjoy a unique immersive experience in an exclusive setting. Opera a Palazzo offers a condensed 1h30 version featuring the principal roles, for a strikingly close encounter with the artists. Discover opera in a totally new way during this unforgettable evening.

label: Cour carrée du Louvre
comment: The Cour Carrée, an emblematic part of the Musée du Louvre, was built by renowned architects. Decided by François I in 1545, its Renaissance façade, the work of architect Pierre Lescot, is the oldest in the museum. The magnificent decor by Jean Goujon is a vibrant tribute to the French sovereign.

label: Marché Mortier
comment: Located in eastern Paris, on the outskirts of Bagnolet, this charming neighborhood market opens its stalls twice a week. The stalls are brimming with fresh fruit, local vegetables and tasty fish, as well as colorful bouquets from two artisan florists. A pleasant interlude for residents in search of quality, local produce.

label: Marché Bercy
comment: Nearby Bercy Village is a must-see market for lovers of fresh, local produce. This charming market offers a wide selection of organic fruit and vegetables, perfect for healthy eating. Whether you're shopping or strolling through the colorful stalls, Bercy Village is an oasis for your taste buds. With its many stalls and traders, there's something for everyone. Come and discover this friendly market for a gourmet experience.

label: Le Severo
comment: Looking for the best steak tartare in Paris? Head for this colorful bistro renowned for its tasty cuisine. And if steak tartare isn't your thing, you can opt for a delicious andouillette, a tasty rib of beef or a creamy stew. A must for lovers of refined gastronomy.

label: Herzo Paris
comment: Founded decades ago, Herzo excels in the creation of quality jewelry. Each piece is the result of meticulous craftsmanship, where nothing is left to chance. Herzo's craftsmen combine tradition and innovation to create one-of-a-kind jewels made from exceptional materials. Each creation tells a story and is synonymous with excellence. Herzo's commitment to unrivalled customer satisfaction makes it a major player in the jewelry world.

label: La Scala Paris
comment: La Scala Paris, a renowned private theater, opened its doors in September 2018. Led by Mélanie and Frédéric Biessy, this cultural institution offers remarkable artistic diversity: theater, dance, music, contemporary circus, visual and digital arts. Designed by scenographer Richard Peduzzi, this modular space welcomes up to 900 spectators, in a warm atmosphere thanks to its bar and restaurant.

label: Parc Floral de Paris - Jardin botanique de Paris
comment: Opened in 1969, the Parc Floral de Paris is a popular destination for nature and floral art lovers. Nestled in the heart of the Bois de Vincennes, this 28-hectare garden offers four unique atmospheres, rest areas, activities for children and an original mini-golf course depicting the city's monuments. In summer, the park hosts cultural events such as the Paris Jazz Festival. An enriching getaway in a true open-air capital!

Savor authentic delights and share convivial moments around mouth-watering specialties, exquisite sweets and, of course, the famous vodka. Let yourself be seduced by this warm address where the bewitching flavors of Russia take center stage.

comment: Located in the 20th arrondissement, near the Nation, Les Pères Populaires is an original bistro with a surprising decor: salvaged sofa, school chairs, etc. The atmosphere is relaxed, perfect for enjoying delicious market cuisine at lunchtime. label: Galerie Olivier Castaing Team School Gallery
comment: La School Gallery, opened in January 2008, showcases contemporary art in all its forms: installations, videos, sculptures, paintings, drawings, photos, design and architecture. Under the direction of Olivier Castaing, the gallery exhibits renowned artists and young talents from all over the world, from France to Argentina, Sweden, Algeria and Austria. A must-see venue for discovering the diversity of the world's artistic creation.

label: Le Collectionneur
comment: The Hôtel du Collectionneur restaurant welcomes you in a contemporary, festive and trendy atmosphere. The menu, created by chefs Joël Veyssière and Nicolas Amelin, is a symphony of flavors that evolves with the seasons. Discover creative, revisited and daring dishes for a generous and modern culinary experience. Let yourself be transported by this festive place in the heart of the capital for an unforgettable moment of gustatory pleasure.

label: Juvia
comment: Le Juvia, nestled in the prestigious Faubourg Saint-Honoré district, offers French cuisine revisited in a post-colonial setting. Its peaceful, shady 25-seat terrace is one of the most pleasant in the region. A speakeasy-style cocktail bar completes the experience. A place where elegance rhymes with refinement.

label: Éric Bompard
comment: Eric Bompard, a renowned brand, offers sweaters and accessories of rare quality, made from the delicate wool of a Mongolian goat. Combining comfort and elegance, this French brand has become a benchmark for cashmere. Discover their 600 m² boutique, a veritable showcase for these exceptional pieces.

label: Le Merle Moqueur
comment: Le Merle Moqueur, located in the 20th arrondissement near Père-Lachaise, offers a wide choice of reading material in pleasant surroundings. This bookshop has a general section (literature, essays, comics, cookery, guidebooks...), another dedicated to young people, as well as an area devoted to art. An ideal place for lovers of varied reading and literary discoveries.

label: Marché sur l'eau
comment: The floating market in Paris offers local fruit and vegetables from Seine-et-Marne, delivered by barge on the Ourcq canal. With its emphasis on short circuits, the market promotes environmentally-friendly agriculture. By subscribing to a basket or buying by the piece, fans of local produce can stock up in Pantin and Paris. Support sustainable, responsible agriculture.

label: La Colline - Théâtre national
comment: La Colline, one of France's five national theaters, is located in eastern Paris and is supported by the French Ministry of Culture. With the Grand Théâtre (700 seats) and the Petit Théâtre (200 seats), its programming is varied. Designed by Valentin Fabre and Jean Perrottet, the building has a glass façade and well-thought-out spaces. The interior design by Annie Tribel Heinz completes this cultural showcase.

label: The Broken Arm
comment: Launched in 2013, The Broken Arm is a concept-store blending fashion and gastronomy. Its boutique offers a cutting-edge selection of original creations, while its café delights the taste buds with homemade pastries and hot drinks. The Scandinavian ambience invites you to relax. At lunchtime, guests can enjoy dishes concocted from fresh, seasonal ingredients. An address where fashion and gourmet delights come together with elegance.

label: Le Dix
comment: The "Le Dix" restaurant, located within the 4-star Crowne Plaza République hotel, offers refined traditional French cuisine, highlighting the authentic flavors of French gastronomy. At the same time, its bar offers a relaxing setting in which to enjoy exquisite cocktails in a warm, friendly atmosphere. Whether you're looking for a gourmet meal or a moment of relaxation, "Le Dix" will meet all your expectations.

label: Paris greeters
comment: Greeters are Parisian volunteers who offer free tours of the City of Light. Each walk is an opportunity to discover Parisian neighborhoods through the eyes of local residents, in a warm and friendly atmosphere. A great way to experience the City of Love in a different way, sharing unique and authentic moments with those who know it best.

label: Liza
comment: Enjoy delicious contemporary Lebanese cuisine, subtly blending Western and Eastern flavors. Enjoy an exceptional brunch on Saturday and Sunday, in a setting where tradition meets modernity. label: Façonnable
comment: Façonnable, founded in 1950 on the Riviera, is the embodiment of sportswear chic. Its collections, with their clean cuts and bright colors, reflect the sunny landscapes of the Côte d'Azur. With carefree elegance, the brand offers unisex clothing that combines the relaxed style of the South of France with French refinement. Every season, Façonnable revisits the classics of the sports wardrobe with a modern twist for a loyal clientele in search of sophisticated style.

label: Tribunal de Paris
comment: The Tribunal de Paris, designed by the famous architect Renzo Piano, is an exceptional 160-metre-high, 38-storey building in the Batignolles district of Paris. This impressive building is an architectural feat, offering the public access to the first 4 levels, including an atrium, a salle des pas perdus and a cafeteria. A remarkable achievement that testifies to the talent and vision of this renowned architect.

label: LV Dream par Louis Vuitton
comment: The LV Dream exhibition at La Samaritaine highlights the collaboration between Louis Vuitton and renowned artists. Through nine thematic rooms, visitors explore the luxurious universe of the house, from ready-to-wear to perfumes, with creations by Frank Gehry, Marc Jacobs and Yayoi Kusama. An exclusive boutique offers one-of-a-kind pieces, and a Maxime Frédéric chocolate shop delights the taste buds. An artistic and gourmet escapade for lovers of fine things.

Quality, originality and elegance come together to enhance your wardrobe.

label: The American Cathedral in Paris
comment: Paris's American Cathedral, built in 1886, has been a historic monument since 1997. Located on Avenue George V, it is dedicated to Anglican worship and attracts visitors from all over the world for its stained glass windows and neo-Gothic style. A landmark in Paris, it symbolizes the friendship between France and the United States.

label: Il Goto
comment: Immerse yourself in the warm ambience of It Goto, an Italian trattoria nestled in the heart of Paris's 12th arrondissement. Run by an Italian couple with a passion for gastronomy, this little gem offers a sunny menu featuring antipasti, carpaccios, gnocchi and many other transalpine delights. All this in a sober but friendly setting, where Italian flavors take pride of place at very reasonable prices. A gourmet getaway not to be missed!

Its creative and refined cuisine will delight the most discerning palates. With a breathtaking view of the Eiffel Tower, this establishment promises a unique culinary experience in a warm and cosy atmosphere.

label: Faggio
comment: Faggio, ranked among the best pizzerias in Paris, stands out for its fresh pizzas made with authentic Italian ingredients. Faggio's chefs add a touch of originality to traditional recipes such as the Margherita or the Reine, offering pizzas that are both crisp and tasty. A must for discerning Italian food lovers.

label: Interkultur Paris
comment: Interkultur offers a variety of guided tours, videoconferences, cultural events and excursions to discover France's rich heritage, history and architecture. Some tours are regular and individual, others for private groups. High-end tours allow you to discover unusual places in the Paris region. Immerse yourself in France's cultural diversity with Interkultur.

comment: At the Musée de la Poste store, you'll find a wide selection of products related to the postal world: elegant stationery, original postcards, specialist books, collectors' items and unique gift ideas. label: Carré Rive Gauche
comment: Every year, the Carré Rive Gauche association attracts art lovers with its unique itinerary. 111 art galleries and antique dealers take part in this not-to-be-missed event along Rue du Bac, Rue de l'Université and Rue des Saints-Pères, bordered by the majestic Seine on Quai Voltaire. You'll hear fascinating stories from the owners of these unique treasures. Plunge into the heart of art and history during this enriching immersion!

label: Le Procope
comment: Le Procope, a legendary restaurant in Paris's 6th arrondissement since 1686, has played host to such illustrious figures as Voltaire, Robespierre, Molière, Diderot and Benjamin Franklin. A symbol of history and prestige, Le Procope offers traditional cuisine with emblematic dishes such as Coq au vin and Tête de veau. A place full of memories, where gastronomy and historical heritage come together.

label: Swarovski
comment: Founded in 1895 by Daniel Swarovski, the renowned crystal company remains a market leader. The "Crystal Forest" boutique, designed by the talented Tokujin Yoshioka, offers sparkling jewelry, accessories and decorative objects, captivating visitors with stories of beauty and elegance. A true paradise for lovers of luxury and crystal, offering a unique sensory experience. A must for those who appreciate the magic of crystal.

label: Cirque d'Hiver Bouglione
comment: Inaugurated in 1852, the Cirque d'Hiver is one of Europe's oldest permanent circuses. Every winter, the Bouglione family presents an original show featuring artists from all over the world: clowns, acrobats, trapeze artists, tightrope walkers, trained animals, acrobats, jugglers... All set to spellbinding music, with dancers and orchestra. A magical event not to be missed, to discover the magic of the circus in all its splendor!

label: L'As du Fallafel
comment: Discover authentic falafel, a genuine chickpea dumpling, in the Jewish quarter of rue des Rosiers, in the heart of the Marais district! Despite the influx of gourmands, let yourself be tempted by this real falafel, cooked according to the rules of the art. Once you're past the hustle and bustle of the street, you'll finally be able to enjoy this delicious sandwich, prepared with care. Looking for a change? Opt for the lamb shawarma... Takeaway or eat-in, this little restaurant is well worth a visit.

label: Marché Barbès
comment: Every Saturday, the boulevard de la Chapelle market under the overhead metro attracts a varied clientele. African women in boubous, young mothers, lost night owls and men in burnous rub shoulders to buy watches, scarves and fresh fruit and vegetables at attractive prices. The place is a melting pot of smells, colors and languages, offering a unique multicultural experience.

Taste a selection of 60 imported Spanish vintages. Bellota-Bellota Saint-Germain is located at 64 rue de Seine, 75006 Paris. A culinary voyage to delight your taste buds!

label: Muji
comment: Muji, a brand advocating simplicity with functional, elegant products that are deliberately basic and timeless. Its Forum des Halles flagship perfectly embodies the minimalist spirit, offering a unique shopping experience that puts product quality first. Each item, practical and aesthetic, reflects a brand philosophy focused on the essential. A variety of products, from stationery to furniture, attract customers in search of purity and well-being, in a setting of pure design.

label: Église Notre-Dame du Bon Conseil
comment: Notre-Dame-du-Bon-Conseil church stands on the site of the former chapel of the Maison de l'?uvre des frères de Saint-Vincent-de-Paul, near the Saint-Ouen flea market. Built in the late 19th century, it was consecrated as a parish in 1948. Its rich history and remarkable architecture make it a real treasure to discover.

label: Emporio Armani
comment: Giorgio Armani's high-end ready-to-wear collection combines a youthful aesthetic with a resolutely fashionable edge. The Saint-Germain-des-Prés boutique offers a selection of clothing, sunglasses, perfumes, accessories and fragrances to satisfy the most discerning fashionista. This line embodies the savoir-faire and timeless elegance of the famous Italian designer.

label: Crypte du martyrium
comment: In the 5th century, the inhabitants of Paris built a chapel on the Butte in honor of Saint Denis, the city's first bishop. Rebuilt in the 9th century to accommodate pilgrims, this chapel bears witness to local Christian history. Archaeological digs on the hilltop have uncovered numerous Christian burials grouped together in a quarry known as Martyrium. These discoveries reveal a rich and moving history.

label: Cool Japan
comment: Discover traditional Japanese craftsmanship from the city of Kanazawa in Paris! This boutique offers a variety of products, from traditional clothing to decorative objects, not forgetting Bohcha tea, a favorite in Japanese temples. Immerse yourself in Japanese craftsmanship without leaving the French capital!

label: Maison de la Radio et de la Musique
comment: The Maison de la Radio, nicknamed the "Maison Ronde", is located in the 16th arrondissement of Paris along the Seine. Designed by architect Henry Bernard in 1963, this venue dedicated to radio, music and creativity offers more than 3,000 seats over 4,000 m². It features concerts, live broadcasts, guided tours and family workshops. It's a must-see cultural venue in Paris, offering a rich and varied experience.

label: Palais de justice
comment: In the heart of Paris, on the Île de la Cité, the Palais de Justice covers more than 4 hectares, with a surface area of almost 200,000 m² spread over several floors. Once the residence of sovereigns, the Palais embodied legislative, executive and judicial power. Steeped in history, it still holds many mysteries about its early years, particularly during the Merovingian and Carolingian reigns. Considered a monarch by divine right, the king held all power in his hands.

label: Cité Internationale - Centre du patrimoine
comment: Discover the Cité internationale universitaire de Paris! Covering 34 hectares, this garden-city welcomes international students in houses with a variety of identities. Guided tours on architecture, art and biodiversity are offered by the Heritage Center. Immerse yourself in the history of this 90-year-old site, exploring three of the 40 pavilions, including Argentina, Japan and Canada. Discover the 5 buildings protected as historic monuments, including the Fondation Suisse and the Maison du Brésil designed by Le Corbusier.

label: Piscine des Amiraux
comment: Designed by architect Henri Sauvage between 1922 and 1927, the Amiraux swimming pool and building are a masterpiece of Art Nouveau architecture. The building's stepped facade conceals a 33-meter pool where swimmers move between tiled walls and corridor cabins. Classified as a historic monument in 2003, the facility offers a unique experience combining architectural beauty and aquatic relaxation.

label: Pottoka
comment: Immerse yourself in a unique taste experience and discover a menu rich in flavors, inspired by the gastronomy of the Basque Country. Traditional dishes revisited with a modern touch for an explosion of flavors in your mouth. Whether you like classic cuisine or are looking for something new, this restaurant is sure to satisfy all your expectations. Come and tickle your taste buds and experience a moment of pure culinary bliss in this warm and welcoming place.

label: Le Camion qui fume
comment: Discover the emblematic Camion qui fume, forerunner of street food in Paris. Since 2011, this food truck has been serving up homemade burgers with a solid reputation. Accompanied by home fries, crispy onion rings or fresh coleslaw, these tasty dishes are available in limited quantities. To round off the meal in style, mouth-watering cheesecakes and cookies are also on the menu. A not-to-be-missed gourmet rendezvous for street food lovers!

label: Bob's Bake Shop
comment: Discover Bob's Bake Shop, the latest addition to the Bob family, at Halle Pajol! Inspired by the organic cuisine of Brooklyn, this Parisian spot offers a tempting menu: fresh bagels, tasty sandwiches, gourmet tartines, fresh salads and sweet "health cups". And don't forget the typical desserts: fluffy carrot cakes, melting brownies, crunchy crumbles, creamy cheesecakes and crunchy cookies. A culinary journey through the heart of Paris not to be missed!

label: Coloré par Rodolphe
comment: Rodolphe, famous Parisian colorist, pampers the hair of celebrities such as Sophie Marceau, Jodie Foster and Johnny Hallyday. His salon, located near Place Vendôme, reflects his talent: colorful and golden. Each client benefits from exceptional treatments (balayage balnéothérapique, blow-dry, anti-hair-loss care) and a personalized color, symbolizing the expertise of this master of hair color.

label: Paroisse Saint-Serge de Radonège
comment: In the 19th century, a Protestant parish became the Saint-Serge Orthodox Church, nestled in the Buttes-Chaumont. A former refuge for German and Russian emigrants, the church's seductive wooden porch and Stelletsky frescoes make it a unique place to visit. Its 35,000-book library and religious bookshop make it a unique place to visit. The Institut de Théologie Orthodoxe Saint-Serge offers courses in French, making it a true Parisian cultural treasure to explore!

label: Jardin du Ranelagh
comment: The 60,500 m² Ranelagh Garden was designed by Baron Haussmann in 1860. Inspired by Lord Ranelagh, a ball was planned in his honor, but in the end it was Haussmann who created this magnificent park. Embellished with statues and trees, it welcomes families and children with a bandstand and an old wooden carousel. Three playgrounds and weekend puppet shows delight visitors of all ages.

label: Chaumet
comment: The famous Chaumet jewelry house made history by embellishing Napoleon and his empresses. Today, it continues to sublimate women with exceptional creations such as "Les liens", "Attrape-moi si tu m'aimes" and "ABC". Chaumet also exhibits its unique treasures in its museum, celebrating elegance and ancestral know-how in the service of beauty. A prestigious brand that always shines thanks to its refinement.

label: Julien de Savignac
comment: Celebrated sommelier Julien de Savignac offers a selection of 250 southern wines for a unique sensory experience. Regular tastings are organized for a demanding and curious clientele, enabling the discovery of new ?nological nuggets. Passionate, Julien brings out the flavors of each wine with expertise, making his cellar a treasure trove for connoisseurs in search of sensory emotions. A must for wine and French art de vivre enthusiasts!

From perfumery to cabin treatments, spa and skin diagnostics, discover the complete world of the brand. A majestic chandelier adorned with 8,000 rose petals catches the eye as you enter. A must-see address for beauty enthusiasts in search of excellence and innovation.

comment: Located in the heart of the French capital, this Alsatian restaurant offers traditional cuisine from Eastern France. In a sober and warm setting, visitors can savor authentic and original flammenkueches. A great opportunity for Parisians to discover the delights of Alsatian gastronomy, prepared with fresh produce.

label: Jardin Serge Gainsbourg
comment: Inaugurated in June 2010, this contemporary 1.4-hectare urban park, perched above the ring road, stands out for its innovative approach to sustainable development and water management. Featuring shared gardens and play areas, this peaceful setting is linked by a gently sloping winding path, offering a pleasant stroll to the heart of nature in the heart of the city.

These fragrances break with traditional codes to offer bold, sensual seduction with surprising notes. Whether you're surprised, excited or repulsed, État Libre d'Orange fragrances never leave you indifferent, for an unparalleled olfactory experience.

label: Église Saint-Laurent
comment: Located near the Gare de l'Est railway station, Saint-Laurent church, built in the early 15th century, is an architectural gem in the flamboyant Gothic style. Consecrated on June 14, 1429, it boasts an impressive structure with penetrating vaults, high windows and an ambulatory adorned with sculpted keystones. Despite subsequent modifications, the authenticity and beauty of its Gothic architecture remain remarkable.

label: Spa Villa Thalgo
comment: Villa Thalgo is renowned for its popular aquagym classes. But this 1,000 m² marine spa in the city offers much more. In partnership with Thalgo, it offers beauty treatments and wellness activities inspired by thalassotherapy. The sensory pool, iodized hammam and high-tech fitness area offer a relaxing and revitalizing experience. A haven of peace close to the Musée de la Marine.

Whether you come with friends or family, this entertainment venue is sure to provide you with light-hearted, joyful moments. Don't hesitate to push open the doors for an evening full of good humor.

label: Dalva

In summer, you can enjoy your favorite dishes al fresco, on their welcoming terrace. It's a warm and welcoming address not to be missed, ideal for sharing a convivial gourmet moment with friends or family. Let yourself be tempted by an authentic culinary experience in this little corner of gastronomic paradise.

label: Jamin Puech
comment: Talented designers Isabelle Puech and Benoît Jamin create one-of-a-kind bags and accessories, combining different styles and materials in surprising ways. Their inventiveness is reflected in their use of mother-of-pearl, rhodoid, fur and raffia, resulting in original and precious pieces. A true invitation to boldness and originality in the world of fashion.

label: Promenade de l'avenue de Breteuil
comment: Avenue de Breteuil is a charming avenue in Paris, shaded by plane trees and lined with elegant bourgeois buildings. Strollers will find serenity and magnificent views of the Invalides dome. The green spaces are enriched by playgrounds, ponds with fountains and a monument to Pasteur by Falguière. An ancient well in the square adds to the historic atmosphere.

label: Les Folies Gruss
comment: Enjoy an exceptional show combining equestrian performance, aerial acts and breathtaking acrobatics, all sprinkled with comic touches. Les Folies Gruss, with 24 talented artists and 50 majestic horses, offers unique entertainment. Accompanied by a live orchestra and an enchanting singer, this show takes place in the heart of Paris's Bois de Boulogne. An unforgettable experience not to be missed!

label: Librairie-boutique du musée d’art et d’histoire du Judaïsme
comment: The Musée d'Art et d'Histoire du Judaïsme bookshop-boutique offers a wide range of books, objects, textiles, jewelry and a selection for children. Books cover a wide range of subjects, including fine art, Judaica, philosophy, mysticism, contemporary history, ethnography and more. Discover also monographs by contemporary artists and essays by intellectuals. A rich diversity to explore for all enthusiasts of Jewish culture and history.

label: Paroisse Notre-Dame du Travail
comment: The Notre-Dame du Travail church, built between 1899 and 1902 by Jules Astruc to an idea by Father Soulange-Bodin, stands out for its exceptional steel-framed nave. With 135 tons of iron and steel, this structure gives the building a modern, industrial look. Created to unite the neighborhood's workers and celebrate labor, the church has stood the test of time and is now a historic monument, testifying to its importance in architecture.

A touch of exclusivity in a world of simplicity and refinement.

label: Basilique Notre-Dame des Victoires
comment: In 1628, Louis XIII ordered the construction of Notre-Dame des Victoires. Work was halted for lack of funding, but resumed in 1656. The church, blessed in 1666, remained unfinished until the intervention of Jean-Sylvain Cartaud, who created the sumptuous portal between 1737 and 1740. Requisitioned during the Revolution, it housed the Loterie Nationale, then the Bourse des Valeurs under the Directoire. Its religious vocation was restored in 1802.

This oasis of tranquility in Paris's 2nd arrondissement features siesta cabins with integrated massage programs. Leave your fatigue behind in a jade stone massage bed or levitating armchair. Lulled by soft music and subdued lighting, ZZZ...Zen takes you away from the hustle and bustle of Paris for a restorative siesta. In addition to the nap cabins, the center offers a wide range of treatments.

A true architectural pearl that never fails to arouse the admiration of passers-by.

With several locations in Paris, Grom offers a sunny, Italian-style taste experience.

label: M. Musée du Vin Paris

With Ba&sh, elegance becomes a way of life, symbolizing a woman who is free, daring and passionate about fashion.

The 22,000m² building houses a museum, library, auditorium, architecture school, bookshop and restaurant. Explore a 1h30 architectural tour of France, from the Middle Ages to the present day, through models and reproductions. Three galleries invite you to discover architecture through casts, paintings, stained glass and models of modern architecture. Immerse yourself in the history and future of architecture!

label: Fondation Le Corbusier, Appartement-Atelier de Le Corbusier- Immeuble Molitor
comment: Le Corbusier's apartment-studio, located in the Molitor building, dominates the city. Built between 1931 and 1934 by Le Corbusier and Pierre Jeanneret, it illustrates the "radiant city". The first glass building, it offers luminosity and transparency. Witness to the architect's experiments, this space housed his painting studio until 1965. Listed as a Unesco World Heritage site in 2016, it symbolizes the innovative genius of its creator.

comment: Les Bonbons, nestled in the Montparnasse district of Paris, is a mini-confiserie with plenty of surprises in store. Despite its small size, the variety of products is impressive: vintage tins, jars of pastel marshmallows, licorice, Leone Italian pastilles and even marshmallows. But the real stars of this confectionery are the sugar fondants. A true art of confectionery, a must-see!

label: Paroisse Notre-Dame du Liban à Paris
comment: Nestled in the heart of the Latin Quarter, Notre-Dame-du-Liban, an Eastern Catholic Maronite-rite church, captivates visitors with its artistic richness. Philippe Andrieux's contemporary stained-glass windows, created between 1993 and 1994, brilliantly illustrate the emblematic saints of this tradition: Saint-Maroun, Saint-Ephrem, Saint-Charbel, Sainte-Thècle, Sainte-Marina, Sainte-Rafka and the Virgin Notre-Dame du Liban, all depicted with finesse and devotion. An invitation to contemplation and spirituality.

With Tea Time 1789, share a tea with Marie-Antoinette & Robespierre to relive the French Revolution. Or opt for Tea Time 1812, and take tea with Bonaparte and Josephine to discover one of the most fascinating destinies in French history. An unusual and enriching experience that literally transports you to a bygone era.

A true wonder to be discovered on a rewarding stroll.

Inspired by Romanesque art, the artist created an immense relief on the Avenue Marceau façade. The majestic figure of Christ the King takes center stage, surrounded by finely crafted motifs and details. This work is a testament to Bouchard's talent and creativity, making this church a true artistic gem not to be missed.

It offers a variety of activities in a magnificent building designed by Jean Nouvel in Paris. Today, the IMA plays a crucial role in promoting a better understanding of the Arab world and strengthening Franco-Arab dialogue. As a think tank, it brings together different players to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two communities.

comment: The Georges Vallerey swimming pool, a key venue for the French championships, attracts renowned swimmers every year. With its Olympic-size pool and modern infrastructure, it's an iconic venue for swimming enthusiasts. With its stands filled with enthusiastic spectators, it is the scene of exceptional performances and broken records, embodying the excellence of this demanding sport.

label: FAT bar
comment: Located in the Haut Marais district, near the Carreau du Temple, the FAT bar, for French Art Touch, is a must-visit venue dedicated to urban culture and the hip hop scene. This 250m² den of friends boasts a street art decor, a tempting cocktail menu, tasty finger food, a beer pong area, a retro arcade, hilarious stand-up sessions and frenzied DJ sets. A rendez-vous for lovers of good vibes and urban art!

label: Camélia
comment: The Camélia restaurant by Thierry Marx offers an exceptional setting and subtle flavors with fresh, seasonal produce. Local producers are featured and a wide selection of breakfasts is available. The "Daily Marx" formula, with dishes of the week for lunch during the week, is a must. Take advantage of the magnificent landscaped garden to relax and discover a gastronomic experience that respects the environment!

label: Le Printemps du Goût
comment: The exceptional Le Printemps du Goût market offers a varied selection of quality products. La Reine Mer offers responsibly caught seafood, while Supernature offers healthy, tasty dishes. Regain offers quality French meats, while Laurent Dubois delights cheese lovers. Byzance offers top-of-the-range seafood and Maison Balme showcases truffles. Malo, artisan crêpier, invites you to take a gourmet break. The Bar à Vins offers French wines and cocktails with a view of the Eiffel Tower.

label: Marché Place des Fêtes
comment: Located high up in the 19th arrondissement, the Place des Fêtes market attracts residents three times a week. With a diverse range of traders including market gardeners, organic florists, bakers, butchers and creameries, it delights the taste buds and pupils of visitors in search of fresh, quality produce. A veritable explosion of flavors and colors to discover in the heart of this lively Paris district.

comment: In the heart of the dynamic Marais district, on the popular Rue Sainte-Croix-de-la-Bretonnerie, stands Passage du Désir. The perfect place to spice up your life together in a warm, intimate atmosphere.

label: Marché Ordener
comment: Located in Paris's 18th arrondissement, near Square Clignancourt, the Marché Ordener is a must for Parisian food market fans. You'll find a wide variety of fresh, local produce, from seasonal fruit and vegetables to artisanal cheeses and charcuterie. A friendly, lively place where the flavors and colors of French gastronomy mingle.

label: Le Nid du Phénix
comment: In the heart of Paris, Le Nid du Phénix takes you into the enchanting atmosphere of Japan. This unique institute combines the traditions of tea and massage for an incomparable experience, with a range of treatments to relax and revitalize. After your wellness interlude, enjoy a tea from a varied selection to complete your escape. Nestled in the Latin Quarter, Le Nid du Phénix offers you a true voyage into the heart of Japanese culture, without leaving the City of Light.

label: Bert’s
comment: Bert's offers upscale fast food in a major Paris cinema complex. Cinema-goers can enjoy freshly prepared recipes on a formula or à la carte basis: sandwiches, salads, toast, drinks, desserts... A gourmet break before or after the film. You can eat in or take away. With 7 locations in Paris, Bert's offers a real culinary treat before a movie.

label: Septime la cave
comment: Not far from the famous Septime and Clamato restaurants is Septime la Cave. An intimate venue run by the same team, this wine bar offers an interesting alternative when the first two addresses are fully booked. With 90 wines to choose from, wine lovers will be delighted. What's more, you can enhance your tasting experience with delicious plates prepared in the Septime's kitchens. An ideal address for food and wine lovers.

label: L’Arôme
comment: Located in the 8th arrondissement, L'Arôme is a Michelin-starred restaurant run by chef Thomas Boullault. Since 2008, it has offered inventive cuisine in a refined, convivial setting, with an open kitchen. Passionate owner Eric Martins shares his expertise in food and wine pairing, acquired alongside Alain Senderens. The cellar overflows with great vintages to sublimate Boullault's creations. An address not to be missed by lovers of haute gastronomy.

label: Amorino
comment: Founded in 2002, Amorino is a benchmark for ice cream fans in Paris, with its organic and natural products, free from artificial additives. Enjoy classic flavors such as bacio, mango, biscotto and frutto della passione. In addition to our ice creams, discover a selection of Italian pastries and confectionery to satisfy your sweet tooth. A sensory experience not to be missed during your visit to the capital.

label: Art Journey Paris
comment: Discover Paris with unique private tours of museums, monuments and castles such as the Sainte Chapelle, Notre Dame and Versailles, in English or French. Choose the artist or period that fascinates you for personalized tours. Our discussions aim to enlighten you about the significance of the works. Immerse yourself in Impressionism and understand its controversies. Embark on an artistic journey through Paris.

label: Vivant Table
comment: The decoration of this former bird house, adorned with magnificent, colorful earthenware, surprises and delights visitors. Every detail reflects the talent of local craftsmen. The kitchen, in harmony with the picturesque setting, delights the senses with simple, tasty dishes cooked with fresh produce. A gustatory escapade through regional culinary traditions, to satisfy the most demanding palates in an enchanting setting.

label: Le Georges
comment: In 2000, Restaurant Georges reached new heights at the Centre Georges-Pompidou, overlooking the treasures of the Musée National d?Art Moderne. In this exceptional setting, the spectacular architecture designed by the talented Jakob and MacFarlane blends harmoniously with the original structure by Renzo Piano and Richard Rogers, offering a reinvented and unique space.

comment: Immerse yourself in a warm and friendly atmosphere as you discover an inn that delights the taste buds with classics of traditional French cuisine. Located close to the Invalides, this establishment promises a tasty and authentic experience. Let yourself be surprised by gourmet and refined dishes, in a charming and welcoming setting. A culinary experience not to be missed.

comment: Founded in 1948, the renowned Michel Cluizel chocolate factory combines family know-how and gustatory excellence. This exceptional brand cultivates the art of chocolate through unique creations, sublimating the best of cocoa beans. Discover their vast range of products in elegant, refined packaging. An unmissable address for lovers of top-of-the-range chocolate!

label: Le Comptoir des Canettes - Chez Georges
comment: In the Saint-Germain-des-Prés district, even small bars offer affordable prices. Le Comptoir des Cannettes, nicknamed "Chez Georges", has been an institution since 1952. This authentic venue attracts a varied clientele in a convivial setting. With a fireplace in the basement for winter evenings, you can start with a pint of beer for just two euros. A must in this chic neighborhood!

label: Café Charlot
comment: In the lively Marais district of Paris, Café Charlot captivates with its authentic charm. A former bakery converted into a bistro, this establishment offers a classic menu and tasty cocktails. With its coveted terrace facing the Marché des Enfants Rouges, it's a must for Parisians in search of a convivial atmosphere. Early arrival is recommended to fully appreciate the unique atmosphere of this popular Parisian spot.

label: Centre Bouddhique Kagyu-Dzong - Grande Pagode de Vincennes
comment: The Grande Pagode de Vincennes, the jewel of Buddhism in Paris, is home to Europe?s most colossal Buddha, majestic under its gilding and over 9 metres high with its pedestal. Spread over 8,000 m², this sacred sanctuary, comprising two splendid buildings left over from the 1931 Colonial Exhibition, shines during major Buddhist rituals. A unique spiritual haven in the tranquil countryside of the Bois de Vincennes, close to Lac Daumesnil, for an unforgettable spiritual experience.

label: Paroisse de Notre-Dame de l'Assomption de Passy
comment: The church of Notre-Dame de l'Assomption, located in the Passy district of the 16th arrondissement, is an eye-catcher with its superb neo-classical cupola. Its organ, designed by the famous Parisian organ builder Aristide Cavaillé-Coll, adds a remarkable musical dimension to the edifice. Concerts regularly enliven this emblematic venue, offering unique musical moments to devotees and visitors alike.

label: Maison Plisson
comment: In the heart of Paris, on Boulevard Beaumarchais, Maison Plisson combines a food hall with a restaurant. Its market-fresh cuisine showcases carefully selected local produce. For your business or personal events, enjoy made-to-measure services in this convivial venue. Tasting workshops are also available to liven up your receptions in a gourmet and convivial way.

label: La tour Eiffel
comment: The Eiffel Tower, built by Gustave Eiffel for the 1889 Universal Exhibition, is an iconic symbol of Paris. From its 276-metre height, the view is breathtaking. With a glass floor on the 1st floor and an incredible view of Paris's architectural treasures on the 2nd floor, the Eiffel Tower is a jewel not to be missed. In addition to renowned restaurants like Le Jules Verne, there are exclusive boutiques representing French culinary excellence.

label: Musée du Parfum - Fragonard
comment: Just a stone's throw from the Opéra Garnier, the Fragonard perfume museum transports visitors into the spellbinding world of olfactory history. Housed in a luxurious mansion, the museum fascinates perfume enthusiasts with its collection of antique bottles. As you explore three millennia of perfume history, you'll discover the secrets behind the manufacture and evolution of this precious product. A unique sensory experience that immerses us in an atmosphere worthy of the Second Empire. An olfactory adventure not to be missed.

label: Le Baiser Salé
comment: In the heart of Rue des Lombards, Baiser Salé is distinguished by its passion for jazz. Specializing in musical mixes, this café-concert venue combines jazz, soul, hip hop and electro. Artists express their creativity and delight audiences until dawn. A must for music lovers in search of daring, spellbinding discoveries.

label: Le Paysan urbain - La Ferme de Charonne
comment: The urban farm located above the Charonne water reservoirs is a place that combines education and the production of micro-fruits, available for purchase. At the heart of the facilities, a 660 m² bioclimatic greenhouse sits alongside wooden technical buildings and an urban ecology pavilion open to the public. Container-grown areas and wilderness zones promote biodiversity and enrich this instructive visit.
