label: Pink Flamingo Marais
comment: Nestled in the heart of the lively Marais district, this pizzeria focuses on quality, using the finest fresh ingredients. Whether it's organic flour, Guérande salt, toppings from a small market-gardener or grated cheese of the day, everything is meticulously selected to guarantee authentic, tasty pizzas, prepared with care. A must for lovers of traditional, gourmet Italian cuisine.

Whether it's organic flour, Guérande salt, toppings from a small market-gardener or grated cheese of the day, everything is meticulously selected to guarantee authentic, tasty pizzas, prepared with care. A must for lovers of traditional, gourmet Italian cuisine.

label: Théâtre Mogador
comment: The Théâtre Mogador, opened in 1913, is located near the department stores and the Palais Garnier, offering a sumptuous setting with elegant salons, warm foyers, convivial bars and top-quality restaurants. Since its acquisition by Stage Entertainment in 2005, it has presented hit musicals such as The Lion King, Mamma Mia! and Sister Act, making it a little piece of Broadway in the heart of Paris.

label: Spa Mosaïc - Hôtel du Collectionneur Paris Arc de Triomphe
comment: Located close to the Champs-Élysées, this prestigious palace boasts a luxurious 400 m² spa. In a Greco-Roman-inspired decor, the Décléor and Carita brands offer a complete range of treatments in one of the ten cabins available. The establishment also features a balneotherapy area with massaging jets, an oriental hammam, a sauna and a jacuzzi. An exceptional wellness interlude in the heart of the capital.

label: Paroisse de la Trinité
comment: The Eglise de la Trinité, designed by architect Théodore Ballu between 1861 and 1867, stands majestically next to Paris City Hall. In this building, metal blends perfectly with Renaissance style. Visitors can admire the works of talented artists such as Elie Delaunay and Félix Barrias. The adjacent square offers a magnificent view of the monumental façade of this magnificent church, close to famous department stores.

comment: paris with Yachts de Paris, founded in 1993 for unique cruises on the Seine. Aboard the Don Juan II, enjoy an exceptional dinner cruise with refined cuisine by Guy Krenzer. label: Andréa Rodrigues (VGP)
comment: Discover Paris with a certified guide. Explore emblematic districts and monuments, and enjoy tales of culture, art and history. Tailor-made tours await you, from the Marais to Montmartre, from the Louvre to Versailles. Discover Paris and its wonders with Visitas Guiadas em Paris.

label: Boutique La Monnaie de Paris
comment: The Monnaie de Paris boutique will delight all numismatic enthusiasts with its wide range of products: collector coins, medals, jewelry, objets d'art, decorations and fascinating historical archives. It's a veritable paradise for lovers of art and numismatic treasures, whether seasoned or curious. Come and discover this unique place where history and art meet to the delight of all.

label: Astier
comment: Founded in 1956, this restaurant in Paris' 11th arrondissement is a renowned institution, combining conviviality and refinement. The dishes highlight the terroir of the Ile-de-France region, offering gourmets a sublime culinary experience. The creative menu revisits the treasures of French cuisine. Ideal for lunch with friends, dinner for two or an evening with the family, this not-to-be-missed address celebrates gastronomy.

label: Hommes aux mille mains - Sur les traces d’Arsène Lupin : entre magie et mentalis
comment: Discover Arsène Lupin, the gentleman burglar, in a captivating adventure. Jean-Michel Lupin, master of magical phenomena and mentalism, sets off in search of a precious treasure. Using mind-reading, numerology and predictions, he questions and awakens the mind. This talented mentalist carries on Arsène Lupin's legacy by skilfully penetrating your thoughts, combining mystery, magic and poetry.

label: Musée national Eugène-Delacroix
comment: Housed in Eugène Delacroix's former home and studio from 1857 to 1863, the Musée National Eugène-Delacroix offers a unique immersion in the artist's world. Its studio and peaceful garden in the heart of Paris make it a special place to discover. The museum's regularly enriched collection of paintings, drawings, prints and letters sheds light on the many facets of Delacroix's work. An exceptional exploration of nineteenth-century artistic creation.

The museum is open to groups Monday to Friday, 10am to 12pm, except Tuesdays and public holidays.']

label: Caron
comment: Ernest Daltroff, founder of the House of Caron, is a pioneer of haute parfumerie. His creations, based on rare essences, reveal incomparable elegance and sensuality. His perfumes are an invitation to a unique olfactory voyage, where each note reveals a subtle art of composition. Thanks to him, the world of perfume has reached new heights of excellence and refinement, offering fragrance lovers an exceptional sensory experience.

label: Librairie Gay-Lussac / Fenêtre sur l'Asie
comment: Nestled in the heart of the Latin Quarter, Fenêtre sur l'Asie is a bookshop specializing in Asian cultures. With over 12,000 titles, it's a treasure trove for fans of India, South Asia, the Himalayas, Central Asia and the Far East. A unique literary immersion that invites discovery and wonder, a must for lovers of the Orient in search of new sensations and knowledge.

label: Le Congrès Maillot
comment: Ideally located just a stone's throw from the Palais des Congrès, hotels and the heart of the business district, Congrès Maillot is the perfect place for a business lunch, dinner or simply to share a meal with friends. The "Club Affaires" menu, also available in the evening, will satisfy the taste buds of gourmets and business people in a hurry. In April, the verdant, flower-filled terrace adds a touch of elegance to this haven of Parisian peace.

label: Opéra national de Paris - Opéra Bastille
comment: The Opéra Bastille, designed by architect Carlos Ott, was inaugurated on July 13, 1989 after an international competition. Its architecture is characterized by transparent facades and the use of uniform materials. With 2,700 seats, exceptional acoustics, unique stage equipment and rehearsal rooms, it is a modern theater of the first rank. Guided tours take you behind the scenes of this grandiose venue.

label: Thierry Le Roi & Les Nécro-Romantiques
comment: Père Lachaise attracts over 3 million visitors every year, thanks to its famous residents such as Marcel Proust, Jim Morrison and Edith Piaf. Thierry Le Roi, a local guide for over twenty years, offers a unique tour through his "NécroRomantique" safari. Explore the tombs of illustrious personalities with anecdotes and secrets. A visit acclaimed by the Tourist Office for a fun family discovery.

label: Parc de Choisy
comment: Parc de Choisy, located in the heart of Paris's Chinatown district, has a classical allure. Rectangular in shape, it is built around an imposing pond and a wide central esplanade. On either side of the latter, relaxation and play areas invite you to stroll. In addition, a variety of tree species, including ash, lime and ginkgo biloba, enrich this haven of greenery.

label: Holland Bikes Tours and Rentals
comment: Looking for an authentic way to discover Paris? Opt for our Dutch bike tours! Our enthusiasts reveal the secrets of the City of Light, far from the usual tourist circuits. Choose between the Secret tour, the Highlights tour or the Christmas tour for a unique experience. Take advantage of our bike rental service to explore the city at your own pace. Book by phone or online, with flexible hours and attentive customer service. Paris awaits you for a cycling adventure!

label: La Perle
comment: Ideally located in the lively Marais district, opposite the Musée des Archives Nationales, La Perle is a bar with a singular charm. Its kitsch decor mixed with designer touches attracts a varied clientele. Its relaxed, festive atmosphere makes it a must, day or night. Glass of wine and house "miam-miam" for 1 euro each. A friendly, gourmet address in the heart of Paris.

label: Marché Saint-Germain
comment: Located in the heart of the emblematic Saint-Germain district, the eponymous market is packed with international boutiques under its famous arcades. There's a Uniqlo boutique, a 1,300 m² Apple Store, as well as a swimming pool, a gym, an auditorium and a conservatory to offer visitors a multitude of services. A must for shopping and leisure enthusiasts.

label: Galerie de la Madeleine
comment: In the heart of the 8th arrondissement, the 19th-century Galerie de la Madeleine is an architectural marvel linked to the history of the square and the church of the same name. With its two superb caryatids adorning the entrance, it offers strollers an authentic visit. A symbol of elegance, this gallery is brimming with luxury brands and gourmet shops for an enchanted break. Come and discover this emblematic Parisian landmark at 30 rue Boissy d?Anglas.

label: PA Design
comment: PA Design is a publishing house specializing in the creation of simple, useful and poetic objects. This boutique is full of surprises, with original creations from renowned brands such as Atypyk and Ibride. A haven for lovers of unusual and inventive objects.

label: La Ferme urbaine Flora Tristan
comment: The urban farm at Flora Tristan secondary school, a 2300 m² educational gem managed by Veni Verdi, introduces students to innovative agriculture. Projects in the pipeline include a greenhouse and a workshop for transforming crops into homemade jams and sauces, cultivating the seeds of sustainability.

label: Superstars Hairsalon
comment: Superstars is the perfect embodiment of the Japanese hair spa concept. This hair salon doesn't simply offer cutting sessions, but a genuine experience of well-being for your hair and scalp. The white, uncluttered atmosphere is 100% Tokyo, offering total relaxation far from the hustle and bustle of traditional salons. Reclining seats ensure optimum comfort for a truly relaxing interlude in the heart of the capital's Japanese district.

label: Église Saint-Sulpice
comment: Saint-Sulpice Church in Paris, a 17th-century monument, lies in the heart of the 6th arrondissement. Its grandeur and beauty captivate visitors. Inside, the chapel of the Virgin, the works of Eugène Delacroix and the Cavaillé-Coll organ fascinate. Outside, the imposing facade, with its two towers, is a real eye-catcher. This place steeped in history inspired Dan Brown to write "The Da Vinci Code", offering a fascinating visit to a unique artistic universe.

label: Théâtre Atelier de la Bonne Graine
comment: Since its creation in 1999, Atelier de la Bonne Graine has been offering children contemporary puppet shows. On the menu: theater for the very young, sensory stimulation, animated film, storytelling for babies, and a variety of playful workshops. A universe rich in creativity and wonder for children in search of new artistic experiences.

label: Fondation Henri Cartier-Bresson
comment: The Fondation Henri Cartier-Bresson, located in the Marais district of Paris, exhibits the precious collections of the famous photographer and his wife. Emblematic works by Cartier-Bresson are presented in temporary exhibitions, both on site and elsewhere. The museum also showcases other national and international photographic greats. A captivating journey to the heart of visual art awaits you.

label: Mur des Fédérés
comment: The precise spot within the Père Lachaise cemetery where the last Communards were executed by Versailles troops on May 28, 1871, at the height of the Paris Commune, has become a place steeped in history. The bodies of the combatants were thrown into a trench at the foot of the wall. Since 1880, the site has been dedicated to the memory of these events, symbolizing the people's resistance for freedom.

label: Record Station
comment: Record Station is THE place to be for any vinyl enthusiast. This little store is brimming with musical treasures that will delight even the most demanding collectors. Whether you're a music enthusiast or simply curious, a visit to Record Station is a must. Let yourself be seduced by a unique experience at the heart of music.

label: Willi's Wine Bar
comment: Founded in 1980 from the remains of a night bar, Willi's Wine Bar is a must for wine lovers. Under British management, it boasts a distinctive Parisian brasserie atmosphere. The quality bistro cuisine is designed to enhance the tasting of the wines on offer. Specializing in Rhône wines, the establishment is now extending its selection to other European wine regions. A gourmet and ?nological experience not to be missed.

label: Théâtre 14
comment: The Théâtre 14 in Paris, renovated in 2020 and directed by Mathieu Touzé and Edouard Chapot, offers an eclectic program combining contemporary and classical plays. With a team of young associate artists, it offers a demanding and rich theater. Club 14, sometimes transformed into a concert hall, offers a varied artistic experience. Théâtre 14 is also home to the Université populaire du théâtre, an eco-responsible training center open to all.

label: La Tour d'Argent
comment: At the top of the Tower, the Restaurant Tour d'Argent offers a breathtaking view of the Seine, Notre-Dame and the Ile Saint-Louis. Chef Yannick Franques revisits emblematic dishes and offers original creations, combining tradition and modernity. La Tour d'Argent's generous cuisine is seductive, while the service combines French precision. Discover the prestigious wine cellar with 15,000 references for an unforgettable gastronomic experience. A must for food lovers.

comment: Come and discover a trendy bistro renowned for its tasty, inventive cuisine. In a relaxed atmosphere, this restaurant offers dishes of great finesse. In the evening, let yourself be seduced by an extremely elaborate menu, concocted by a modest yet acclaimed chef. A not-to-be-missed culinary experience for food lovers!

comment: Come and discover an experience full of surprises and conviviality in this charming bistro with a retro 70s feel. You'll be delighted by the variety of tapas and delicious gourmet small plates that await you. The warm, authentic atmosphere of this place will seduce you for a unique moment of sharing and culinary pleasure.

label: PEP 75
comment: For over 10 years, PEP75 has been organizing stays in Paris, with a team of ten people on hand to help with planning. They have an extensive network of accommodation centers in France, including Mon Abri in Le Pouliguen and Paris-Mandres in Mandres-les-Roses. Guided tours of the art and history of Paris are available for everyone, including people with disabilities. An enriching experience to discover France's heritage.

label: Les Disquaires
comment: Discover Les Disquaires, a music bar in the heart of Paris's lively Bastille district. Enjoy free concerts of Soul, Funk, Jazz and Hip Hop from 8pm, followed by DJ sets from 10pm onwards for a frenzied atmosphere! Enjoy a friendly, relaxed atmosphere as you sip affordable drinks, savor quality music and dance the night away. An ideal place for lovers of good music and wild parties!

label: Tours Duo
comment: The Duo Towers, designed by architect Jean Nouvel, rise majestically at 125 and 180 meters near the Avenue de France. Their asymmetrical, gently sloping silhouette, with a V-shaped top, offers spectacular views. Designed to house offices, shops, a hotel decorated by Philippe Starck, a panoramic restaurant-bar, verdant terraces and a belvedere garden, these towers combine functionality and innovative design.

comment: Saint-Leu Saint-Gilles church, built in 1235, stands proudly at the heart of rue Saint-Denis, one of the capital's liveliest thoroughfares. Its Gothic architecture and splendid stained glass windows make it a real historical gem to discover. A must-see for lovers of history and sacred art.

The salon offers a unique experience where shaving and beard trimming become timeless rituals, immersing those seeking authenticity and tradition in a past rich in know-how.

comment: Renowned Michelin-starred chef Michel is a key figure on the Parisian gastronomic scene. His restaurant, Dessirier, located in the 17th arrondissement, focuses on seafood. Lovers of oysters, shellfish and crustaceans flock to the adjoining Oyster Bar to enjoy a delicious tasting experience, either on the premises or to take away. An irresistible invitation for lovers of quality seafood cuisine.

label: Biscuiterie la Mère Poulard
comment: Discover La Mère Poulard and its sweet delights for young and old alike! Galettes, sablés, palets, cookies, caramels, confectionery, jams, chocolates, ciders and apple juice, everything is here to delight lovers of authentic flavors. Traditional cookies to die for, from the savoir-faire of the famous chef. A guaranteed treat for the taste buds!

label: Cultival
comment: Immerse yourself in French history and heritage with Cultival. Go behind the scenes at the Stade de France, discover the art of the Gobelins craftsmen, or enjoy an immersive show at the Dôme des Invalides. Play "Arsène Lupin et le secret de l'Opéra" at the Palais Garnier. Cultival offers you a variety of unique cultural experiences. Let yourself be carried away by adventure!

label: Le Centre de Russie pour la science et la culture
comment: Located in the heart of the 16th arrondissement of Paris, the Russian Center for Science and Culture is a must-see between the Place du Trocadéro, Place de l'Étoile and Place Victor Hugo. Every year, it offers over 100 cultural events, including exhibitions, forums and film screenings. Russian language courses are also offered. A true crossroads of Russian culture in the heart of the French capital.

label: L'Office
comment: Exciting news! The Japanese chef brings his unique precision and sensitivity to a menu already renowned for its creativity. His mastery of flavors and textures adds a touch of elegance and authenticity to every dish. Customers acclaim his talent and delight in every bite. Thanks to him, the restaurant attracts a curious and demanding clientele, delighted by the bold creations of this exceptional chef. A fusion of culinary cultures for a memorable experience!

Artists, scientists, architects and sociologists come together for workshops, exhibitions, conferences and performances. A fusion of ideas and skills for a varied program. Students, teachers, local residents and businesses all take part in this artistic effervescence.

label: Théâtre de la Michodière
comment: Located close to the Place de l'Opéra, the Théâtre de la Michodière offers 700 seats for spectators in search of entertainment. Specializing in comedy plays, this establishment offers a varied program to delight a wide audience in search of laughter and good humor. A must for comedy lovers in Paris.

label: Legrand Filles & Fils
comment: A true jewel of the capital, this Parisian cellar is renowned for the quality of its fine wines at affordable prices. Its wine-tasting sessions are convivial and enriching, appreciated by all connoisseurs of fine wines. A place of exchange and passion, where exquisite flavors and sensory discoveries come together.

label: Le Brise Miche
comment: Enjoy refined, traditional French cuisine at this café-brasserie, where delicious dishes are prepared with fresh ingredients. Settle down comfortably on the terrace to admire the fountains of Igor-Stravinsky Square and enjoy a moment of relaxation and conviviality. It's the ideal place to enjoy a delicious meal and a charming view right in the heart of the city.

label: Saint Laurent Paris (Montaigne)
comment: The famous couturier, who died of cancer in 2008, left his mark on women's fashion with audacious creations that have become a benchmark for many designers. His fashion house, founded in 1961, remains one of the most prestigious in the world. Under the artistic direction of Anthony Vaccarello, the brand continues to inspire fashion enthusiasts with its blend of modernity, audacity and excellence, perpetuating the founder's vision and maintaining its position as a leader in the industry.

label: UGC Montparnasse
comment: Discover the diversity of film screenings at UGC Montparnasse! With 7 cinemas offering screenings in both original and French versions, you'll be spoilt for choice. Fancy a gourmet break? A food court and sweets counter are at your disposal. Don't wait any longer at the cash desks, thanks to our time-saving quick-purchase terminals.

label: Kaïten
comment: Located just off the Champs-Élysées, Kaïten is a must-visit sushi bar. Renowned for its deliciously fresh and flavorful dishes, the establishment offers a high-quality culinary experience. An address to discover for all discerning lovers of Japanese cuisine in search of authentic flavors.

Immerse yourself in an enchanting universe where exquisite scents blend to create a refined, intoxicating atmosphere. A true invitation to a sensory voyage, to sublimate your home in total elegance.

label: Le Pré Catelan
comment: In the heart of the Bois de Boulogne lies a splendid Napoleon III pavilion, steeped in history and ideal for weddings, receptions and business events. The restaurant, run by renowned chef Frédéric Anton, offers inventive, refined cuisine. Awarded 3 Michelin stars, a rating of 19/20 and 5 toques in the GaultMillau guide, this establishment is a benchmark for lovers of high-end gastronomy.

label: Semilla
comment: Matthieu Roche, a Michelin-starred chef trained at the Pré Catelan and the Ritz, has been running this restaurant since 2012. His cuisine, a blend of Mediterranean influences and bold flavors, is sure to win you over. Despite the uncluttered decor, the refined, flavorful dishes will transport you. Come and enjoy exceptional products in a warm and friendly atmosphere.

label: Église Saint-Joseph des Carmes
comment: The Saint-Joseph des Carmes church, at the heart of the Institut Catholique de Paris, and the Carmes garden form an emblematic ensemble in the Latin Quarter. This place steeped in history harmoniously combines university life, culture and spirituality within a singular heritage. A veritable nugget in the heart of the capital.

label: Espace Niemeyer - Paris
comment: Designed by architect Oscar Niemeyer, this emblematic building is located in the 19th arrondissement of Paris. In collaboration with other talents such as Jean Prouvé, Jean Deroche and Paul Chemetov, its construction was completed in 1971. Classified as a historic monument in 2007, its curved, glazed facades contrast with the rough-cast concrete and timber interior. Former headquarters of the French Communist Party, this modern building is a real eye-catcher.

label: L'Auberge Aveyronnaise
comment: Come and enjoy a little piece of Aveyron in the heart of Paris, in a warm and rustic setting. This restaurant offers traditional cuisine featuring aligot and Aubrac meats, to the delight of your taste buds. You can also enjoy your meal on the terrace in summer, in a friendly atmosphere. An authentic culinary experience not to be missed!

label: Martine Lambert
comment: Founded in 1975 in Deauville, Normandy, Martine Lambert's ice creams are distinguished by their use of high-quality raw materials. Raw milk and fresh cream, sourced exclusively from Normandy, give their sorbets and ice creams incomparable smoothness and balance. This unrivalled expertise makes Martine Lambert's creations simply unclassifiable. An invitation to taste for lovers of authentic flavors.

label: Restaurant David Toutain
comment: Located near the Invalides, David Toutain's gourmet restaurant is a culinary nugget. In a sober, elegant setting, the Michelin-starred chef offers refined, inventive cuisine, with an explosion of flavors in every bite. Since December 2014, a dining room named Identi-T welcomes guests for culinary delights in a convivial atmosphere. Perfect for groups of friends, it's a gourmet interlude not to be missed.

label: Paris Visites
comment: Discover Paris through its emblematic districts on guided tours by minibus or electric tuk tuk. Explore the covered passages, the Marais, Montmartre, Saint-Germain-des-Prés, the Louvre, Notre-Dame, the Latin Quarter, Les Halles-Montorgueil, Les Invalides, the Camondo Museum, the Garnier Opera House, Parisian cemeteries... Each visit reveals stories, anecdotes, architecture, characters and hidden treasures. An enriching experience combining history, anecdotes and visual pleasure. Enjoy additional services such as dinner in a restaurant, a private concert or wine tasting. An exciting immersion experience awaits you!

comment: Located on rue de Picardie, in the heart of the Haut-Marais district, the EMPREINTES concept store is the place to go for fine crafts. Decoration, tableware, sculptures & murals, furniture, lighting, jewelry & accessories? On 2 floors bathed in light, thousands of sensitive objects, entirely imagined and crafted by the designer in his workshop in France, are offered for sale.

label: Angelina Bac
comment: The famous Maison Angelina opens a new boutique-pâtisserie on rue du Bac, decorated by Bambi Sloan. Ideally located near Le Bon Marché and the Chapelle de la Médaille Miraculeuse, it's the perfect place for a gourmet break. Discover Mont-Blanc, Babylone and fine grocery products. A gustatory experience not to be missed!

label: Librairie Flammarion - Centre Pompidou
comment: The Centre Pompidou, in the heart of Paris, is dedicated to modern and contemporary art in all its forms. Its diverse programming includes the visual arts, theater, music, cinema, books and the spoken word. With a team of 30 experts, Librairie Flammarion offers a constantly updated selection of documents, in line with current artistic trends. An invitation to discovery for art and culture lovers.

comment: Located in Oberkampf, La Caravane is a must for Parisian nightlife. This rock and electro bar-restaurant, with its relaxed staff, offers a warm, colorful setting for tasting a variety of international cuisine: American, Asian fusion, French, Italian and more. Perfect for a lively evening in Paris's 11th arrondissement.

Come and enjoy a magical culinary experience and discover Indian cuisine.

label: Base nautique de la Villette
comment: Fancy rowing or canoeing in the heart of Paris, away from the tourist boats? Then head for Base Nautique de La Villette! Accessible to all, young and old, all you need is the ability to swim and a certificate. There's no need to travel far to indulge your passion for water. So let yourself be tempted by this sporting experience north of the capital!

During the school vacations, the water sports center is open at the same times from Monday to Friday as part of the Centres d?Initiation Sportive http://www.paris.fr/services-et-infos-pratiques/sports-et-loisirs/comment-faire-du-sport/les-activites-sportives-encadrees-toute-l-annee-2268 program or, during certain school vacations, for one-week courses from 9:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. as part of the Écoles Municipales des Sports program - registration one month before each school holiday +33 (0) 1 42 76 30 00 (Écoles Municipales des Sports office); the program is available at http://ems.paris.fr/']

label: Passage Choiseul
comment: Since summer 2013, the emblematic passageway in the Opéra district has been renovated and is once again open to the public. The restored glass roof captivates strollers. Food lovers can enjoy the many restaurants on offer, while stressed-out city dwellers can relax at the Bar à sieste. An unusual stroll not to be missed, with two other entrances to discover: 23 rue Saint-Augustin and 40 rue Dalayrac.

label: Le Trianon
comment: Located at the foot of the Butte Montmartre, the Trianon is a 19th-century architectural gem, a rare example of Napoleon III-inspired Italian-style theater. With its 3,000 m² divided into four distinct areas - the theater, ballroom, winter garden and ancillary spaces - it is a versatile venue for shows, concerts and private events. A must for anyone wishing to experience the magic of art and culture in Paris.

label: Whatizis
comment: Discover Paris in a different way with Whatizis, an innovative app that lets you visit the capital at your own pace, 7 days a week. Take a photo of over 450 monuments and let the app reveal the name of the place, along with audio commentary from experienced guides. Free of charge and usable without a connection, Whatizis lets you explore Paris's architecture, sculptures and street art with ease. Whether you're a tourist or a local, enjoy a new experience of the City of Light with Whatizis.

comment: Discover the city with Sonali, a passionate tour guide who offers tours in several languages. Explore neighborhoods, museums and local gastronomy on her food tours. Enjoy tailor-made half-day or full-day tours, according to your preferences. An enriching and convivial experience not to be missed!

label: Le Grand Rex
comment: The Grand Rex, Europe's largest cinema since 1932, is a historic monument with Art Deco architecture unique on Parisian boulevards. During a 2-hour visit, a guide will reveal all its secrets, from decoration to terrace, and plunge you into the world of cinema with an audio-guided tour of Rex Studios. A must-see for film buffs, it's a jewel in the crown of Parisian heritage.

label: Matières à réflexion
comment: Unique accessories and bags are created by recycling vintage clothing. Whether you're a man or a woman, you'll find what you're looking for in our collections. The little extra? The possibility of having a piece made to measure from an old jacket. It's a great way to give a second life to your clothes, while keeping up with the latest fashion trends.

label: Marie-Andréa Zammit
comment: Discover the artistic treasures of Paris with a passionate guide on unique tours of the capital's artistic highlights. Meet the artists of Montmartre, visit the museum and immerse yourself in the surreal world of Dali. RDV Métro Abbesses. Explore the intimacy of Eugène Delacroix in Saint-Germain des Prés, with a visit to his studio and home. RDV Saint-Germain des Prés metro station. Admire the treasures of the French School and Islamic Art at the Louvre. RDV in front of the Richelieu Eagle. Price:""

label: Église réformée de l'Étoile
comment: The Église Protestante Unie de l'Étoile in Paris is famous for its neo-Gothic temple dating from 1874. It combines Reformed tradition with modern preaching, attracting families with a dynamic catechism program. Its organ, a 32-stop masterpiece by Cavaillé-Coll, remains in its original state. Every first Sunday of the month, a free concert is offered from 5pm to 6pm.

Throughout the year, the establishment offers those who wish to benefit from quality hairdressing services at reduced prices. It's the perfect opportunity to be pampered while contributing to the training of future industry professionals.

label: Librairie de l’hôtel de Sully
comment: The bookshop stands out for its commitment to promoting France's national heritage through a collection that is unique in France, notably with the Editions du Patrimoine. Readers will find remarkable regional diversity, highlighting confidential publishers unavailable elsewhere. In addition, a section dedicated to Paris completes this rich and varied panorama. A must for lovers of heritage and reading.

label: Jardin Anne Frank
comment: In the heart of Paris's Marais district lies the 2,200 m² garden of the Musée d'Art et d'Histoire du Judaïsme, created in the 17th century. A tribute to Anne Frank, it comprises three areas: a contemporary garden with rare species, a Versailles-inspired mineral arbour, and an orchard with apple and cherry blossom trees. This place combines nature and history in a soothing atmosphere.

comment: Square Alex Biscarre, nestled between Notre-Dame de Lorette church and Montmartre, offers welcome tranquility in the heart of a lively neighborhood. This little haven of peace is home to a magnificent purple beech, Austrian black pines and magnolias. There's also a well-equipped playground for local children. A true bubble of nature and play amidst the hustle and bustle of Paris.

label: La Cordonnerie
comment: Looking for an affordable bar? At La Cordonnerie, a pint of beer costs just 4? Other drinks are also very reasonably priced in this friendly establishment, much appreciated by Parisians. What's more, on Thursdays and Saturdays, customers are offered a generous helping of couscous! A great way to relax without breaking the bank.

comment: Located in the Halles district of Paris for over twenty years, Bistrot Beaubourg has the timeless charm of a traditional bistro. comment: Take to the skies in Paris aboard the world's largest balloon, a unique experience at an altitude of 150 meters to discover the capital from a whole new angle! Enjoy this breathtaking view depending on the day's weather conditions. Visit www.ballondeparis.com before your visit to make sure you don't miss out on this magical moment!

Perfect for all occasions, Solis invites you to share warm moments around generous sunny tables.

label: Restaurant Le Dalí
comment: Le Dalí restaurant, created by Philippe Starck at the Le Meurice hotel in Paris, offers authentic, inventive French cuisine in perfect harmony with Dalí's surreal world. Chef Amaury Bouhours sublimates seasonal produce for an unforgettable taste experience. Desserts by Cédric Grolet and François Deshayes are veritable works of art to be savored with pleasure. Each plate offers an explosion of flavors and textures to delight gourmets. Le Dalí offers a unique culinary experience where gustatory pleasure and aesthetics come together harmoniously.

label: Le 9b
comment: Located in Belleville, just off the Couronnes metro station, 9b offers a warm and friendly atmosphere. With its light-filled dining room and pleasant terrace, it's the ideal place to enjoy a meal or a drink, day or night. In the basement, a small club welcomes music lovers for DJ sets, lives and performances in an intimate atmosphere. The perfect place to enjoy the Parisian music scene in an original and festive setting.

label: Passage Jouffroy
comment: Built in 1836, the Passage Jouffroy is a Paris landmark, with its iron and glass architecture, ogival glass roof and marble paving. Here you'll find the famous Musée Grévin, the Salon des Miroirs, now a club on Saturday nights, and the Hotel Chopin for an unusual night out. Unique boutiques offer treasures such as antique canes and rare books, with colorful window displays and gourmet stops. A must-see in Paris. Address: 9 rue de la Grange-Batelière.

label: Maison David
comment: Located in the heart of the Marais district, this kosher butcher-caterer offers an atmosphere reminiscent of a New York delicatessen. Whether it's tasty grilled meats, pastrami or bagels, you can enjoy the experience seated or standing at the counter. A true gustatory voyage in the heart of Paris, between Jewish culinary traditions and a contemporary atmosphere. A place to discover for lovers of authentic cuisine and varied flavors.

label: Le Bar des Maillets d'Argent
comment: The bar on the first floor of the Tower is inspired by polo and Claude Terrail's Maillets d'Argent team. In a reinvented 1930s ambience, the Bar des Maillets d'Argent welcomes you all day long, adapting to your desires, whether for a coffee in the morning or a cocktail in the evening, for lunch, dinner or tea time. With its vintage furniture, green walls and comfortable armchairs, let yourself be charmed by the creations of Head Barman Mathieu Velmir.

label: Musée Marmottan Monet
comment: The Musée Marmottan Monet exhibits a rich Impressionist collection with over 100 works by Monet, including "Impression Soleil Levant" and the Water Lilies, as well as paintings by Gauguin, Guillaumin, Renoir, Sisley, Degas and other artists. Berthe Morisot, a major figure in female Impressionism, is also featured. With its regular temporary exhibitions, the museum is a fixture on the Paris cultural scene, offering a fascinating immersion in the world of the Impressionists.

label: Stade Jean Bouin
comment: The Jean Bouin stadium, symbol of the Stade Français, is located in the 16th arrondissement of Paris. Refurbished in 2013 by architect Rudy Ricciotti, it can accommodate 20,000 spectators. In addition to Stade Français matches, it hosts other clubs and sporting events, such as the Paris Rugby 7s tournament. A potential venue for the 2024 Olympics, it is a must for rugby fans and sports event enthusiasts in Paris.

label: Café de Flore
comment: Café de Flore, in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, attracts a varied clientele with its art deco room and terrace on Boulevard Saint-Germain. Celebrities, locals and tourists alike gather here to enjoy a delicious hot chocolate, a house specialty. A symbol of intellectual Paris, every year the Café de Flore awards the Prix de Flore to a young literary talent, initiated by Frédéric Beigbeder. This historic café is a must for lovers of literature and gastronomy.

Decorated with simplicity but taste, this modest bar attracts with its affordable drinks and sandwiches sold by the metre. Packed almost every evening, especially after exams, Pantalon's relaxed atmosphere and efficient service are a winning combination. A perfect place to relax with friends without breaking the bank!

The concert hall, with its eclectic and dynamic program, welcomes emerging artists to discover as well as established artists such as Yael Naim, Herman Dune, Beth Dito and Fauve. A vibrant, lively venue for music lovers in search of new discoveries.

Let yourself be seduced by exquisite flavors, for an unforgettable taste journey.

A timeless place to enjoy exquisite ice creams and sorbets, perfect for ice cream lovers on any occasion.

comment: The Russian Orthodox Spiritual and Cultural Center of Paris, near the Eiffel Tower, is elegant. It includes a cultural, administrative and educational center and the Cathedral of the Holy Trinity. Designed by Wilmotte & Associés Architectes, the cathedral with its 5 smooth golden bulbs is an architectural feat. The noble materials and sober colors harmonize perfectly with the prestigious neighborhood.

label: Hôtel de Béhague
comment: The Romanian Embassy moved into the Hôtel de Béhague in 1939, a historic building constructed in 1867 for Countess Amédée de Béhague. Nicknamed the "Byzantium of the 7th arrondissement", it is brimming with architectural and artistic treasures, including a magnificent staircase, a painting by François Boucher, a ballroom and a 19th-century library. A private theater regularly hosts a variety of cultural events. Restoration work will begin in autumn 2017 to preserve this architectural gem.

Located in the lively Grand Boulevards district, De Clercq is open from early morning until late at night. Discover their two other Parisian addresses: 184 rue Saint-Jacques (Paris 5e) and 103 rue de Tolbiac (Paris 13e).

label: Horloges et pendules François Hubert
comment: François Hubert, expert clockmaker, operates from his workshop in Saint-Germain-des-Prés. Specializing in the restoration and sale of antique clocks and pendulums, he excels in his field. Whether it's a Louis XIV cartel, an "8-day" clock or an ATMOS clock, no model can resist him. Trained at the Ecole d'Horlogerie de Paris and by Michel Journe, this passionate craftsman puts all his know-how into bringing these precious objects back to life.

comment: Want to discover Paris in a different way? Opt for our running tour with RunRun Tours! A choice of 6, 10, 12 or 21km circuits, departing at dawn or by night. Enjoy a unique sporting and cultural experience in Paris!

label: Paris Canal

A private area is also available on request. And at weekends, don't miss our all-you-can-eat buffet brunch!

label: Mémorial de la Shoah, Paris
comment: The Shoah Memorial in Paris, Europe?s leading information center on the subject, offers an educational tour of the history of the Shoah. Covering over 5,000 m2, it offers tours and activities to help visitors understand the genocide of Jews during the Second World War. Since 2005, the memorial has also addressed the genocides of the Tutsis in Rwanda and the Armenians, reinforcing its essential role in the fight against racism and intolerance.

label: Le bar Long
comment: The Long bar, located at the Royal Monceau hotel in Paris, is one of the city's trendiest spots. Designed by Philippe Starck, this sophisticated bar attracts attention with its backlit table and aluminum furniture. Close to the Arc de Triomphe, it's the ideal place to go out with friends or for a business meeting. Come and enjoy original cocktails accompanied by delicious gourmet bites. An address not to be missed!

label: Le Verre Volé
comment: In the heart of Jacques Bonsergent, near the Canal Saint-Martin, Le Verre Volé is a wine bar appreciated for its "Dish + Glass of Wine" evenings and its demanding selection. Its authentic menu offers delicious dishes in perfect harmony with the wines: charcuterie, smoked fish salad, ham, homemade desserts... A warm atmosphere for lovers of quality food and wine.

label: Salle Cortot
comment: The Salle Cortot, adjacent to the École normale de musique de Paris, is an Art Deco jewel classified as a historical monument. With its 400 seats and remarkable acoustics, it hosts 160 concerts a year, ranging from piano recitals and chamber music to events organized by the Paris music school. A veritable nugget for classical music lovers in search of intense emotions.
description: The Salle Cortot, adjacent to the École normale de musique de Paris, is an Art Deco jewel classified as a historical monument. With its 400 seats and remarkable acoustics, it hosts 160 concerts a year, ranging from piano recitals and chamber music to events organized by the Paris music school. A veritable nugget for classical music lovers in search of intense emotions.

label: A journey in Paris / Paris Tabi Tours
comment: Founded in 2014, A Journey in Paris offers unique guided tours for foreign travelers, revealing a different Paris. From Art Nouveau to Art Deco, our atypical itineraries take you to Bastille, Montmartre, the Latin Quarter, as well as the Louvre, Orsay and the Eiffel Tower. Opt for personalized tours in Japanese with Paris Tabi Tours or in French with Avant Paris for an authentic and memorable experience. A unique escapade not to be missed.

label: Association des guides interprètes de langue russe - AGILR
comment: Founded in 1995, AGILR brings together 71 qualified Russian-speaking guide-lecturers. This non-profit association under the French law of 1901 defends the interests of Russian-speaking guide-lecturers. Each guide must be contacted individually for their services; no commercial services are offered. Consult the list of members on their website. Affiliated with the FNGIC, AGILR offers guided tours in several languages, including French, Russian, Ukrainian and Bulgarian.

label: Conran Shop
comment: In the heart of a former Gustave Eiffel warehouse, Sir Terence Conran's Parisian boutique attracts design enthusiasts with a selection of objects signed by renowned designers. Furniture, decorations, lighting, tableware, textiles... this authentic space is an essential destination for lovers of beautiful things. Discover it for a unique shopping experience.

label: Comme des Garçons
comment: Founded in 1969 by Japanese designer Rei Kawakubo, Comme des Garçons is a revolutionary brand renowned for its bold, unique style. Combining craftsmanship and innovation, it pushes back the boundaries of fashion. With its original cuts, innovative materials and avant-garde patterns, the brand inspires fashion enthusiasts. Its slogan, "Fusion of", perfectly sums up its innovative approach.

label: Tsé & Tsé associés
comment: Catherine Lévy and Sigolène Prébois made their name with "Vase d'avril". Their creativity shines through in all their creations, from lighting fixtures to tableware and everyday objects stamped Tsé & Tsé. Their original universe appeals to a wide public in search of objects that are both practical and aesthetically pleasing, adding a touch of whimsy to our everyday lives. Each Tsé & Tsé object is a genuine work of art combining design and poetry, confirming the brand's exceptional talent on the international scene.

label: Orchestre Hélios
comment: The Hélios association orchestra is a reference in the French orchestral landscape. Founded in 2014, it brings together young talents and experienced orchestral musicians, conductors and soloists, all of whom have graduated from major French conservatories. The multiplicity and complementarity of its talents allows it to tackle a very rich repertoire, ranging from Baroque to contemporary music. The orchestra performs in prestigious halls and religious buildings, thus highlighting French excellence in musical and architectural heritage.

label: Marché Jean Jaurès
comment: Discover the Jean Jaurès market, located in the heart of the lively Villette district, with its popular, cosmopolitan atmosphere. You'll find a variety of shops selling fresh fruit, vegetables and quality fish. A true immersion in the diversity and richness of flavors, for the pleasure of both taste buds and eyes.

label: Nodaiwa
comment: The Japanese restaurant Nodaïwa, located near the Palais-Royal, offers refined and creative cuisine, blending tradition and modernity. Its specialty? Grilled eel, a delicious signature dish. Lovers of Japanese cuisine will be delighted by this address, which offers a unique and disorienting culinary experience. A true invitation to a gustatory voyage to the heart of Japanese gastronomy.

label: Les Mots à la Bouche
comment: In the heart of Paris, between Place de la République and the famous Père-Lachaise cemetery, lies the oldest LGBTQ+ bookshop. Opened in 1980, it offers a wide selection of gay and lesbian literature, specialized magazines, DVDs and cultural exhibitions. A must for discovering committed works and promoting diversity.

comment: "Discover at "DP... AM" a variety of clothing and equipment for children aged 0 to 14. label: Golf ParisLongchamp
comment: Since October 2010, the Bois de Boulogne golf course has been located on the Hippodrome de Longchamp. With a 240m-long driving range, golf enthusiasts can practice by hitting irons and woods. The site boasts 80 stations, including 30 covered ones, for practice in optimal conditions. In addition, several putting green areas are available for fine-tuning technique. A choice destination for golf enthusiasts in the heart of nature.

label: Tse Yang
comment: The Tse Yang restaurant combines elegance with the excellence of Chinese gastronomy. Its chic black décor creates an intimate atmosphere ideal for an exceptional dinner. The dishes on offer, blending flavors and textures, will delight the finest palates. Impeccable service satisfies a discerning clientele. A must for lovers of fine Chinese cuisine in search of an exceptional gastronomic experience.

comment: Since 1995, l'Échappée Belle has been offering a variety of cultural and tourist services in Paris: guided tours of museums, monuments, neighborhood strolls, themed and historical tours. With bilingual and trilingual guide-lecturers, the agency caters for everyone: individuals, companies and associations. Contact them on +33 (0)1 45 51 64 29 for enriching experiences.

label: L'Âne qui rit
comment: Located near the old Château des Ternes is L'Âne qui rit, a Parisian cabaret offering a humorous dinner show in a festive atmosphere. Every evening, the mascot "l'âne jojo" greets the audience with a lively welcome. The Philippe Starck-designed room offers a unique proximity to the artists, both famous and up-and-coming. Guests can enjoy a refined menu for an entertaining and unforgettable evening, far from the ordinary.

label: Collège des Bernardins
comment: The Collège des Bernardins, renovated by the Paris Catholic Church, is a place for sharing and discovery. The Cathedral School offers courses for all and encourages reflection. Its varied program attracts a wide audience with exhibitions, concerts, debates and lectures. A testament to the medieval University of Paris, the site offers a convivial atmosphere with a bookshop, café-restaurant and garden. Fun concerts are also organized to introduce children to art and music.

label: Etna
comment: Immerse yourself in the retro atmosphere of 50s Sicily when you step through the door of this atypical bar. Here, only natural wines are given pride of place, highlighting the terroir and exclusive know-how of the winemakers. Accompany these nectars with a selection of sweet and savoury delicacies. For chocolate lovers, the menu of grands crus will delight your taste buds. A unique sensory experience awaits you at Etna, where tradition and quality combine to perfection.

label: Pierre Marcolini
comment: The Belgian master chocolatier meticulously selects and roasts his own cocoa beans from the four corners of the globe. His innovative creations with unique flavors seduce the palate, including the famous and much-loved six-gram chocolate squares. Each season, an exclusive collection is unveiled for special occasions such as Christmas and Valentine's Day. Les Éphémères also offers regular surprises.

label: BiLiPo - Bibliothèque des Littératures Policières
comment: Nestled in the heart of the Latin Quarter, the Bibliothèque des Littératures Policières (BiLiPo) is a little-known treasure trove in France and around the world. Specializing in detective and espionage literature, it houses 80,000 works and plays an essential role in preserving this unique heritage. Themed exhibitions regularly enliven the premises, offering visitors a fascinating insight into this captivating universe.

label: Théâtre Les Blancs Manteaux
comment: The Théâtre des Blancs-Manteaux, in the heart of the Marais district near the Hôtel de Ville, offers two cosy theatres for 80 and 60 spectators respectively. Its convivial bar adds to the theatrical ambience, conducive to relaxation and light-heartedness. Evenings full of laughter and good humor promise unforgettable moments, inviting audiences to let themselves be carried away by the magic of live performance.

Stores dedicated to women and children are also nearby, in a similar spirit. Let yourself be seduced by Hartford's chic yet relaxed ambience.

label: Les Pâtes Vivantes
comment: The Chinese restaurant offers authentic, exotic cuisine, with fresh pasta prepared in front of you. Let yourself be seduced by our traditional dishes, prepared with quality ingredients by our talented team. Come and enjoy a unique culinary experience in a warm atmosphere. A gustatory escapade to create lasting memories and awaken your senses. Join us to discover the richness of Chinese gastronomy!

label: Delage
comment: Discover the refined world of Delage, artisan creator of luxury women's shoes. Each pair is unique and can be customized to your exact specifications. Visit our boutique in the heart of the sumptuous gardens of the Palais Royal to find the shoe of your dreams. A must-have for fashionistas in search of elegance and originality.

label: Daum
comment: Since 1878, Daum has embodied the perfect harmony between art, nature and color. This exceptional company realizes the dreams of the greatest artists, from the Art Nouveau movement to contemporary creation, thanks to its famous pâte de cristal. Each unique piece is hand-crafted, numbered and bears witness to the brand's incomparable expertise. Daum is a legend in the world of decorative art, jewelry and art publishing.

label: Le Coupe Chou
comment: Restaurant Le Coupe-Chou, in the heart of the Latin Quarter, is housed in a 17th-century mansion with antique fireplaces. Each room, like the Abbé and the Bibliothèque, has its own unique atmosphere, thanks to period decor and antique furniture. A hushed atmosphere reigns, with jazzy music for an intimate ambience. In the kitchen, Le Coupe-Chou offers traditional dishes and French wines for a memorable sensory experience.

label: L'Ébauchoir
comment: The local bistro offers tasty cuisine with carefully selected market produce. The service is friendly, offering a pleasant culinary experience. A selection of quality organic wines accompanies the dishes, ensuring perfect harmony. It's an authentic address for quality, where every bite is a treat for the taste buds. Discover it for an unforgettable gastronomic experience.

label: Clamato
comment: Le Clamato, the new address from the Septime restaurant team, is a seafood bistro run by chef Bertrand Grébaut. Inspired by New York fish bars, this establishment promises a gastronomic experience rich in freshness and conviviality. A perfect combination for seafood lovers in search of authentic flavors.

label: Moulin de la Charité - Montparnasse
comment: In the heart of the Montparnasse cemetery stands the last of the thirty mills that once surrounded the Montrouge plain. Built in the 17th century by the Brothers of Saint-Jean de Dieu or of Charity, it was transformed into a guinguette during the French Revolution. Incorporated into the cemetery in 1824, it became the janitor's dwelling. Today, this historic mill has been abandoned, becoming a silent witness to its eventful past.

label: Librairie Jousseaume
comment: Immerse yourself in an extraordinary collection of unique literary treasures. This bewitching place, worthy of a Paris in black and white, conceals over 40,000 rare works that will delight bibliophile enthusiasts. Come and discover them, contemplate them, or even acquire them to enrich your own library with genuine literary gems.

label: Soirée Bus
comment: Experience a unique evening in Paris with Soirée Bus! Embark on a unique experience aboard a converted bus for a cocktail party or dance. Enjoy a festive atmosphere, complete with sound system, videos and checkroom. Form groups of 30 to 50 for the ultimate experience. Capacity limited to 60 guests. An original and memorable evening!

label: Odéon - Théâtre de l’Europe
comment: The Odéon - Théâtre de l'Europe, a historic monument still in operation, combines tradition and modernity. With its second auditorium since 2003, it offers new theatrical forms. A landmark of French culture, the Odéon offers a varied program, from the classical to the avant-garde. Thanks to its constant renewal, this theater attracts a diverse audience, contributing to the cultural dynamism of Paris.

label: Fondation Cartier pour l'art contemporain
comment: The Fondation Cartier pour l?art contemporain moves to the Palais Royal in Paris. In a building designed by Jean Nouvel, it offers exhibitions, performances and encounters focusing on contemporary creation and major cultural, social and environmental issues.

label: Temple du Port-Royal
comment: The Temple du Port-Royal, a renowned Protestant church of the Reformed Church of France, combines tradition and modernity. Built in the 17th century, this architectural gem is a place of meditation steeped in memory and symbolism. Its reputation extends beyond the local area, attracting worshippers from all over the city. Still a gathering place for Protestants, it perpetuates a centuries-old tradition.

label: Musée de la franc-maçonnerie
comment: Discover a rich collection of Masonic documents and objects tracing the history of the Order in France, its symbols, grades and historical background. Prestigious acquisitions from renowned museums such as the Château de Versailles and the Musée de Montluçon enrich and complete this unique collection.

label: Galerie Véro-Dodat
comment: Galerie Véro-Dodat, near the Louvre, is unique, with its black-and-white marble corridor creating an illusion of depth. Engraved motifs and stained-glass ceiling windows add to the Parisian charm. Elegant boutiques offer furniture, decorations, art, musical instruments and antique dolls. Don't miss Christian Louboutin's atelier-boutique for luxury shoes. Take a stroll down Rue du Bouloi for a break.

label: Bassanti
comment: Located in the dynamic Montparnasse district, Bassanti is a gourmet Indian restaurant that delights the senses. An explosion of exquisite, refined flavors awaits diners, for an unforgettable culinary experience. A must for lovers of authentic, high-quality Indian cuisine.

label: Micadanses
comment: Micadanses' five dance studios on rue Geoffroy l?Asnier welcome over 1,000 people every week. Created in August 2001, Micadanses' mission is to support, promote and encourage artistic creation, particularly in the field of dance. At the heart of its activities are the production and organization of shows, workshops and training courses. A veritable cultural breeding ground that enlivens and enriches the Parisian artistic scene.

label: L'Envol
comment: Le Balcon, on the 6th floor of the Philharmonie de Paris, offers panoramic views over the Parc de la Villette and Paris. Its chic, minimalist decor, with colorful touches, creates an enchanting ambience. The tasty, seasonal cuisine will delight your taste buds. Charcuterie boards and quiches are also available for a quick break. Open to Philharmonie spectators and the general public, this restaurant offers an exceptional culinary experience.

label: Église Saint-Germain l'Auxerrois
comment: Saint-Germain-l?Auxerrois church, founded in Merovingian times, has undergone numerous destructions and reconstructions. Additions were made between the 11th and 13th centuries, with work in the 12th century. The choir and Virgin Chapel date from the 14th century, the nave and porch from the following century, and the transept and choir chapels from the 16th century. Opposite the Musée du Louvre, this church bears the marks of its tumultuous past, particularly during the St. Bartholomew's Day.

label: Aquaboulevard de Paris
comment: Immerse yourself in an incredible experience at Aquaboulevard de Paris, Europe?s largest urban water park! With 2 wave pools, 11 waterslides, Jacuzzis, rivers and a sandy beach, you?ll enjoy a moment of family fun. Hygiene and safety are paramount: the water is continuously treated, lifeguards watch over you, cameras and discreet staff keep an eye on you. Enjoy the Aquaboulevard with complete peace of mind!

label: L'Escargot Montorgueil
comment: This listed Parisian establishment has been delighting snail lovers for 2 centuries. With its preserved Second Empire décor, it offers exceptional gastronomic cuisine. Dishes such as croustillants de cèpes, brioche de quail au foie gras and 12 escargots de Bourgogne en colimaçon are sure to delight gourmets. An institution in the heart of the capital, this restaurant perpetuates quality culinary savoir-faire.
description: This listed Parisian establishment has been delighting snail lovers for 2 centuries. With its preserved Second Empire décor, it offers exceptional gastronomic cuisine. Dishes such as croustillants de cèpes, brioche de quail au foie gras and 12 escargots de Bourgogne en colimaçon are sure to delight gourmets. An institution in the heart of the capital, this restaurant perpetuates quality culinary savoir-faire.

label: Atelier de reliure Céline Beutain
comment: Céline Beutain, expert bookbinder and restorer, operates from a conveniently located workshop near the Luxembourg Gardens. She brings old or damaged books back to life, specializing in leather and parchment bindings, photo albums, children's books and antique cardboard games. Her expertise is dedicated to the preservation of literary and artistic heritage, reflecting a passion for the conservation and enhancement of cultural heritage.

label: Le Pain Quotidien - Victoires
comment: Founded in Brussels in 1990, Le Pain Quotidien focuses on authenticity, quality and conviviality. With its handmade organic bread and fresh, seasonal ingredients, this restaurant offers a unique culinary experience. Le Pain Quotidien Victoires, near the Opéra Garnier, offers a warm setting with a large table made of recycled wood and a glass roof overlooking the arches of the Jardin du Palais Royal. A must for lovers of authentic cuisine.

label: Naturalia
comment: Naturalia, the leading organic products store in Paris, offers a wide selection of environmentally-friendly food and cosmetics. Choosing Naturalia means opting for responsible and ethical consumption, for your health and the planet. Committed to social equity and respect for the environment, Naturalia is your ally for healthy eating and quality natural skincare.

label: Satellite
comment: Satellite jewelry, crafted from noble materials such as crystal, Venetian glass, enamel and mother-of-pearl, stands out for its mystery and elegance. Inspired by ethnic cultures and passionate about travel, the brand's designer infuses her creations with a touch of exoticism and authenticity. Each piece reflects exceptional craftsmanship and boundless creativity, for one-of-a-kind jewelry.

Each piece reflects exceptional craftsmanship and boundless creativity, for one-of-a-kind jewelry.

label: Noglu
comment: Located in the chic 7th arrondissement, close to the Musée Maillol, Noglu offers refined cuisine that's 100% gluten-free and, for some recipes, lactose-free. In a sumptuous setting, guests can enjoy exquisite dishes with complete freedom and no constraints. For those in a hurry, a "Take away" area is also available on site. A must for lovers of healthy, gourmet gastronomy.

label: Oxte Restaurant
comment: Nestled in the 17th arrondissement, near Place de l'Étoile, Oxte Restaurant shines with its Michelin 2021 star and two Gault & Millau toques. Under the direction of Mexican chef Enrique Casarrubias, French cuisine is subtly flavored with Mexican accents. Let yourself be seduced by delicately spiced and refined dishes in a warm and friendly atmosphere. Original and tasty flavors will delight your taste buds.

label: La Régalade
comment: Located near the Louvre, La Régalade restaurant offers authentic French cuisine led by chef Bruno Doucet. The dishes, based on fresh seasonal produce and regional specialties, are homemade and of the highest quality. The restaurant's chic, elegant ambience is much appreciated, as are its affordable prices. Praised by numerous gastronomic guides, La Régalade is a must for lovers of French cuisine.

label: Sarah Guetta
comment: Immerse yourself in the glamorous world of Sarah Guetta, the hairdresser to the stars who has become a true star hairdresser! Visit her salon, just a stone's throw from the Tuileries Gardens, for a privileged experience. This cinema expert brings a unique touch to your hair, working on dry hair for an ultra-chic, natural result. A beauty interlude not to be missed!

label: La Maroquinerie
comment: La Maroquinerie, in the 20th arrondissement of Paris, is a 500-seat concert venue not to be missed. Its eclectic programming and role as a festival producer make it a unique venue. In addition to concerts, its restaurant hosts readings, debates, showcases and exhibitions. A vibrant place for music and culture.

label: Galerie Perrotin Matignon
comment: Galerie Perrotin, renowned for its prestige, recently inaugurated a new space on the chic Avenue Matignon, close to the Champs-Élysées. This intimate 70 m² space, nestled on the first floor of a building dating from 1900, offers visitors immersion in a selection of works by the gallery's renowned artists. A true artistic experience in the heart of Paris.

label: Cotélac
comment: Cotélac garments are distinguished by their fluid, unstructured design, but also by their originality and sophistication. Each piece is unique, with details such as gathers, pleats and prints adding a special touch. The brand succeeds in combining modernity and elegance for resolutely unique collections.

label: Paris 4 Lovers
comment: Paris 4 Lovers, a must for lovers of the City of Light. With over thirty years' experience in Paris, Gilles, a Guide and Lecturer with a diploma from the Ecole du Louvre, reveals the city?s secrets on unusual tours combining history and anecdotes. From Passy to Montmartre, let his passion guide you as you discover an authentic Paris, far from the beaten track. A unique experience to (re)discover the City of Love. Follow him on Facebook: Gilles GUIDE / Gilles CAKE.

label: Yam’Tcha
comment: The Yam'Tcha restaurant, run by Adeline Grattard and Chi Wah, fuses French and Chinese flavors. Dishes, based on local produce and Cantonese cuisine, are steamed and accompanied by carefully selected teas. The tea boutique at 4 rue Sauval in Paris offers a wide selection of teas. For a gourmet break, the café Lai'Tcha at 7 rue du Jour offers creative cuisine close to the Canopée des Halles. A unique culinary experience not to be missed!

label: Le Quincampe
comment: Located on Rue Quincampoix in the heart of Paris, Le Quincampe is a charming bistro with a typically Parisian, cosy atmosphere. With its authentic decor of stonework and exposed beams, this place exudes French charm. The tasty bistro cuisine will delight gourmets, and lovers of French craft beers will be delighted. An address not to be missed for a convivial and delicious culinary experience.

label: Cinéma Les Fauvettes
comment: Located opposite the Manufacture des Gobelins in the 13th arrondissement, Les Fauvettes cinema boasts a magnificent setting, renovated by architects Miguel Chevalier, Françoise Raynaud and Jacques Grange. Before plunging into one of the theaters, take the time to appreciate the ambient luminosity and enjoy a drink at the bar. The program features restored cult films to the delight of film buffs.

label: Biocoop
comment: Biocoop, a network of organic stores present in various Parisian neighborhoods, has a vast 300m² facility in the 12th arrondissement, one of the largest in the capital. With a wide range of products, from food and skincare to beauty and home care, Biocoop is the benchmark for eco-responsible, fair-trade consumption. It's the place to go for a healthier, more environmentally-friendly lifestyle.

label: Théâtre des Marionnettes du jardin du Luxembourg
comment: Since 1933, Guignol has brought the Luxembourg Gardens to life. Founded by Robert Desarthis, the theater has been passed on to his son, Françis-Claude Desarthis, who takes care of everything. The Théâtre des Marionnettes du Jardin du Luxembourg is modern, air-conditioned in summer and heated in winter. With a capacity of 275 spectators, it's the largest puppet theater in France. Enjoy performances on Wednesdays, Saturdays, Sundays, public holidays and school vacations.

label: Causses, Sud Pigalle
comment: Chez Causses, the delicatessen focuses on healthy, tasty and simple products. Quality, local and varied products are on offer: fruit, vegetables, charcuterie, cheeses, wines, preserves and more. In addition to food, Causses offers fast food with soups, salads and hot dishes. Culinary workshops are also organized in collaboration with Only&Co for cooking enthusiasts.

label: Boutique-atelier Márcia de Carvalho
comment: Márcia de Carvalho, a passionate Brazilian designer, draws her inspiration from the cultural richness of her country. Her dazzling creations reflect her boundless creativity and love of diversity. Each piece tells a unique story, whether it's a colorful dress, an original sweater or a positive T-shirt. Her radiant fashion invites you to express your personality and celebrate your uniqueness, in a whirlwind of good cheer. An invitation to share and enjoy life!

label: Église Notre-Dame de Lorette
comment: The church of Notre-Dame-de-Lorette, nestled between the Opéra Garnier and Montmartre, was begun in 1823 and completed in 1836. Classified as a historic monument in 1984, it is a colorful jewel of Paris. Not to be missed: the superb Gobelins carpet under the main altar, as well as the Virgin Mary and the oak pulpit. A must-see for art and history lovers in search of architectural marvels.

label: Galerie Kamel Mennour
comment: In the heart of Saint-Germain-des-Prés, gallerist Kamel Mennour exhibits French and international artistic diversity in a variety of media. Among the renowned artists represented are David LaChapelle, Daniel Buren, Camille Henrot, Claude Lévêque, Huang Yong-Ping, Larry Clark and Anish Kapoor. In addition to his main address, his works can be found at 6 rue du Pont de Lodi and 28 avenue Matignon in Paris. A must for contemporary art lovers.

label: Entrée to Black Paris
comment: Discover Entrée to Black Paris guided tours: Black history around the Jardin du Luxembourg as a group (1h30) and the Black exhibition at the Louvre as a private tour (maximum 5 people, 1h30). Consult the calendar, book online or request a private visit to the Louvre 15 days in advance at paris@entreetoblackparis.com. Explore Paris in a unique way with Entrée to Black Paris!

label: Fluctuart - Food & Drink
comment: Discover Fluctuart, a floating urban art center offering a unique experience overlooking the Seine. Ideal for a moment with friends, this venue offers formulas for groups of 10 or more, with free reservation. Enjoy free admission, free guided tours and relaxation areas in summer, with 486 seats, including 272 on the rooftop. In winter, 94 places are available. Enjoy food & cocktails at the main bar and on the rooftop. Perfect for lively evenings surrounded by urban art.

label: Masha Paris
comment: Located close to the Place du Trocadéro, Masha Paris is sure to appeal to lovers of fine dining. Designed by Stefanie Renoma and Fan Sack, this 1,000 m² space combines luxury and modernity in its decor. The cuisine, a veritable alliance of French tradition and Japanese subtlety, will delight the most demanding palates. Whether you're a gourmet or simply looking for a refined drink at the cocktail bar, Masha Paris is sure to meet your expectations.

label: Immeuble-cathédrale de la rue Réaumur
comment: At 61 and 63 rue Réaumur stands an exceptional facade combining Art Nouveau and neo-Gothic styles, created at the end of the 19th century by architects Edouard Singery and Philippe Jouannin, and sculptor F.-A. Jacquier. Adorned with numerous details, it features an imposing clock, representations of the seasons, the months of the year and the signs of the zodiac. This unique architectural masterpiece is a must-see in this district.

label: Paris-visiteguidee
comment: Paris-visiteguidee offers tailor-made tours for all publics. As national tour guides, we specialize in walking tours of the capital. Choose from classic or unusual themes. With some forty different circuits, tours can be scheduled by the hour or even by night. Tours by boat or coach are also available.

label: Église Saint-Honoré-d'Eylau
comment: At Saint-Honoré-d'Eylau, visitors have the privilege of admiring an exceptional work of art: Tintoretto's Adoration of the Shepherds. This magnificent painting by the famous Venetian artist is captivating in its beauty and intensity. Every detail, every play of light, immerses us in this biblical scene with a unique emotional depth. A true artistic nugget not to be missed during a visit to Saint-Honoré-d'Eylau.

label: The World of Banksy
comment: The World of Banksy offers a unique artistic immersion near the Palais Garnier, department stores and the Musée Grévin. The exhibition features some one hundred works by Banksy, the global icon of street art. Discover the Walled Off hotel, a Parisian replica of the Bethlehem establishment, for a complete artistic experience inspired by Banksy's world. Immerse yourself in this captivating universe around every corner.

label: Banana Café
comment: Located in the Châtelet district of Paris, the Banana Café is a fixture on the capital's gay nightlife scene. Renowned for its gogo-dancers, its yellow storefront attracts an eccentric clientele. The relaxed atmosphere, "happy low cost" happy hour from 6pm to 11pm and original theme nights such as "Banana Fever" or "Lady Boy" make it a very popular venue.

label: Les Voûtes
comment: The Voûtes, near the Frigos, resonate with experimental melodies, creating a unique atmosphere. Each note awakens the senses and emotions of visitors. A sensory journey awaits the curious, between stone vaults and artistic installations. The artists offer original performances, pushing back the boundaries of musical creation. An artistic laboratory blending unexpected sounds, an unforgettable experience for music lovers in search of strong emotions.

label: Les Glaneuses
comment: Located in the 11th arrondissement, Les Glaneuses is much more than just a zero-waste boutique. In addition to offering workshops and conferences on ecology, this convivial space also provides a place to rent everyday objects, ideal for limiting our environmental footprint. What's more, there's a relaxing area where you can enjoy a cup of coffee. The perfect place to do your shopping while doing your bit for the planet.

label: Les Caves du Louvre
comment: Les Caves du Louvre, central Paris, created by a passionate team. Dating back to the 18th century, built by Trudon, sommelier to Louis XV, this space is dedicated to French wine. Immerse yourself in the world of wine with a free app during a playful visit. Each room transports you to the French terroir, from vine to tasting. Take part in a blending workshop to create your own wine. A unique experience for amateurs and connoisseurs alike.

label: Burberry
comment: In 2010, the famous English brand known for its timeless trench coat opened its flagship store in Paris, in the heart of the Saint-Germain-des-Prés district. Founded in 1856, the brand offers a wide range of ready-to-wear for men and women, as well as accessories and fragrances. Discover the world of this emblematic brand in a 300 m² space dedicated to fashion and elegance.

label: Make Up for Ever Boutique
comment: Make Up for Ever, created by French make-up artist Dany Sanz, was first appreciated by professionals for its excellent products. Now it is also attracting the general public. Located near Saint-Augustin church, the rue de la Boétie boutique offers a wide range of make-up, accessories and skincare products. Expert staff provide personalized advice. The brand has its own school, the Make Up for Ever Academy Paris.

label: Marché couvert des Ternes
comment: The Marché des Ternes, nestled in the 17th arrondissement of Paris, is a charming and friendly place where stalls abound with quality products. Variety is the order of the day, with a renowned poultry shop, a tempting fishmonger's, a gourmet cheese shop, and even non-food stalls adding to the diversity on offer. A must for lovers of fresh produce!

label: Spa Nuxe - Hôtel Square
comment: The Nuxe spa, located in the Hôtel Square with a breathtaking view of the Eiffel Tower, offers a 200 m² space with a warm, contemporary design. Dominated by noble materials such as wood, elegant curves and ivory and gold tones, it offers a complete range of Nuxe treatments, including the exclusive "Kashmir", an energizing massage inspired by Indian traditions. Enjoy a unique well-being experience in an exceptional setting.

label: Arboretum - Jardin botanique de Paris
comment: The Paris Arboretum is home to 1,200 trees in preserved natural environments such as a wetland, a reedbed and a limestone meadow. With its 650 marked tree species, discover exceptional trees such as the Korean fir, the metasequoia or the Chinese tulip tree. You might also come across hedgehogs, weasels, squirrels or rabbits on your stroll. An enriching nature experience right in the heart of the capital.

label: Le Ruisseau
comment: Right next to the famous Butte Montmartre, there's a place offering delicious French-style burgers at very attractive prices. The ingredients used are fresh and sourced from local producers, guaranteeing impeccable quality. In a friendly atmosphere, you can enjoy a delicious meal in a warm and welcoming setting.

comment: The concept-store is distinguished by its flagship, a place combining finesse and diversity. Dedicated to renowned brands, it also houses an editorial bookshop and an art gallery. Active collaborations with various artists continually enrich the experience offered to visitors, from graphic designers to musicians.

label: Isabel Marant
comment: Isabel Marant, a designer adored by modern urban women, skilfully combines femininity with casual elegance. Her pieces subtly combine comfort and sophistication, offering wearers the perfect balance between feminine allure and masculine touches. A high-end ready-to-wear brand that seduces with its unique, timeless style.

label: Chapelle de la Sorbonne
comment: In the heart of the Latin Quarter stands the Sorbonne chapel, part of the prestigious architectural ensemble of the university of the same name. Designed by architect Jacques Lemercier at the request of Richelieu in the 17th century, the chapel's singular façade and elegant dome make it a real eye-catcher. A true architectural gem in the heart of a university renowned for its history and prestige.

label: La Halle Saint-Pierre
comment: The Halle Saint Pierre, in superb Baltard style, offers an exceptional view over the gardens of the Butte Montmartre. Featuring a museum, gallery, bookshop, auditorium and café, this luminous space offers a variety of exhibitions and artistic activities. Explore some thirty works from the permanent Max Fourny collection of naive art, as well as temporary exhibitions on art brut, popular, singular and contemporary art. A unique place dedicated to the most surprising creativity.

label: Diva's Kabaret
comment: Come and discover Diva's Kabaret, a transformist cabaret in a 12th-century vaulted cellar in the heart of the Marais district. Open Fridays and Saturdays from 8pm to 2am, this burlesque and humoristic show promises new talent every week. Enjoy the piano bar, sing along and relax in a friendly atmosphere. Enjoy a drink or a meal on site. A warm and lively evening awaits you at this Parisian landmark!

label: Chez Omar
comment: Hidden behind its old Parisian bistro look, Chez Omar remains a must for lovers of Oriental cuisine. Its specialty? Divinely prepared couscous that instantly transports you to the heart of North African flavors. A warm welcome awaits you at Chez Omar, promising a convivial and delicious moment to share with friends or family.

label: Théâtre 13 / Jardin
comment: Théâtre 13 is distinguished by its commitment to showcasing promising young companies. Its varied program includes classical and contemporary plays, original creations and themed musical evenings. It is also the initiator of the Prix Théâtre 13 competition for young directors. Since 2011, a second theatre has been built near the Bibliothèque François Mitterrand, offering a greater diversity of performances.

label: La Maison de la Conversation
comment: Located in a priority district of the 18th arrondissement, our third-party social innovation space promotes living together. With values of equality and inclusion, this space encourages exchanges between all. Our aim is to become a major player in the transition by involving local residents. Workshops, shows, debates, yoga, dance... Our varied program attracts a wide audience and encourages them to take an active part.

label: Drouant
comment: The Drouant restaurant, a Parisian icon created in 1880 near the Opéra Garnier, combines literary prestige with Art Deco decor. Romain Van Thienen offers refined French cuisine, accompanied by a wide selection of wines, notably from the Rhône Valley. Open all day, Drouant offers a lively atmosphere for breakfast, lunch or dinner, as well as a popular Sunday brunch. A must for gourmets in search of conviviality.
