label: Jardin des serres d'Auteuil - Jardin botanique de Paris
comment: The Jardin des Serres d'Auteuil, in the Bois de Boulogne, is a botanical garden belonging to the City of Paris, founded in 1761 under Louis XV. It features a magnificent parterre à la française and five 19th-century greenhouses housing rare plants. Guided tours are available all year round, and a classical music festival is held annually. In June 2019, six contemporary greenhouses were added near the Simonne Mathieu court of the Roland Garros stadium, enriching this exceptional site.

label: Badaboum
comment: Le Badaboum, in the heart of the Bastille, is a unique concert, club and cocktail bar. Emerging and renowned artists perform here, with a top-quality sound system. Affordable prices and finger food to accompany cocktails make this a convivial place to be. A must for night owls in search of originality and good music!

label: Kiliwatch
comment: In a stretched-out space, an impressive variety of clothing and accessories is displayed: from Hawaiian shirts to sequined dresses and military jackets. Books, shoes, international magazines and a selection of men's and women's ready-to-wear are also on display. A veritable melting pot of styles and trends to discover without delay!

label: Le Cox
comment: Le Cox is a must for Parisian gay nights, where bearded and mustachioed men are welcome. Its friendly, fetish atmosphere attracts a clientele in search of interesting encounters. The crowded terrace is appreciated for its relaxed setting. Happy hours from 6pm to 10pm attract regulars with attractive prices. Whether you're looking for a drink with friends or to meet new people, the Cox meets the expectations of Parisian night owls.

label: Université d’été en Sorbonne
comment: This summer, Sorbonne Université's Faculty of Arts is organizing the Université d'été en Sorbonne, from June 24 to July 19, 2024. Courses in the humanities, in French or English, and French as a foreign language courses for all levels are planned, attracting participants from all over the world for a unique cultural experience. Discover French culture with Sorbonne University teachers and immerse yourself in the intellectual effervescence of Paris!

label: Dilettantes
comment: In the heart of St Germain des Prés, Dilettantes offers over 150 rare champagnes from Grand Cru terroirs in its 17th-century vaulted cellar. Discover 3 different champagnes every two weeks, with detailed explanations and food pairings. Join us for special events and tastings on Saturdays to discover four champagnes from the Champagne region. Don't miss our exclusive events for champagne enthusiasts!

With its exhibitions, private collections and two auditoriums, it offers a diversified, high-quality program for both professional and private event-goers. A true place of culture and creativity in the heart of the capital.

The cafeteria offers a variety of dishes, perfect for a gourmet break. The Wi-Fi connection lets you stay connected while enjoying the pleasant surroundings. Whether you're going for a swim or relaxing in the sun, it's the perfect place for a convivial moment. Come and enjoy this unique and rejuvenating place in complete serenity.

label: Svetlana
comment: Immerse yourself in the warm atmosphere of the Russian restaurant "Svetlana", ideally located near the Théâtre de l'Atelier and the Montmartre district. Let yourself be enchanted by this unique culinary experience, where every mouthful sounds like an invitation to travel.

label: Patrick Roger
comment: Discover the delicious creations of Patrick Roger! This talented chocolatier stands out for his art of sculpting chocolate and innovating with flavors. Patrick Roger pushes the boundaries to offer unique taste experiences to his customers. His boutique is a sensory voyage not to be missed!

comment: The Ma'Lucia restaurant, nestled behind its red façade, celebrates the delights of Southern Italy with fresh ingredients. Authentic, delicious gastronomy takes center stage. Homemade dishes are displayed in a showcase, then enjoyed in a convivial atmosphere in the dining room. A real treat for the taste buds and a total immersion in traditional Italian cuisine.

label: La Vie Claire
comment: Since 1948, La Vie Claire has been dedicated to the distribution of organic products in France. In addition to its own brand, it offers the leading brands in the organic sector. La Vie Claire stores offer a wide selection of food, wellness and beauty products, and even an exclusive range of cleaning products. A varied choice to help you go organic every day, while respecting the environment.

comment: Specializing in private guided tours in Paris, Best of France Tours offers unique experiences in France. With skilled English-speaking driver-guides, the company offers walking tours, day excursions and tailor-made trips. A variety of tours are available, including museum visits and gastronomic tastings. Passionate guides reveal France's hidden treasures for an authentic, personalized experience.

label: Restaurant Laïa

Housed in a former distillery, this unique venue hides at the end of a verdant garden, complete with rooftop vegetable patch. Laïa invites you on a cosmopolitan culinary journey blending flavors from the south of France, Spain and Italy. Let yourself be seduced by its warm and welcoming atmosphere, perfect for a gourmet getaway in Paris.

Located in the 11th arrondissement near Square Gardette, this restaurant offers perfectly cooked meats accompanied by natural wines. An authentic gastronomic experience not to be missed.

In an elegant yet relaxed atmosphere, enjoy champagne or cocktails in a chic decor by Christophe Pillet. Pleasant music and petal-shaped alcoves add to the romanticism. View of the Eiffel Tower, blending elegance and refinement for an unforgettable experience.

label: Pozzetto Paris
comment: Located in the Marais district of Paris, Pozzetto is an Italian ice-cream parlour offering just 12 flavours, traditionally made every day in accordance with Italian recipes. Ice creams are not served in scoops, but in cones or small pots, accompanied by a small spatula. For an Italian-style gourmet break, head to 16 rue Vielle du Temple, 75004 Paris, to discover this renowned ice cream parlour.

label: Eataly Paris
comment: Eataly, the famous Italian gourmet chain, is making its debut in Paris, joining other major cities around the world. Located in the Marais district of Paris, this exceptional 3-storey, 4,000 m² store features a 2,500 m² delicatessen on the first floor, over 1,000 Italian wines, seven food and beverage outlets, a fruit and vegetable courtyard and a café. A must for lovers of transalpine cuisine.

label: Compagnie des Bateaux Mouches
comment: Come aboard the Bateaux Mouches in Paris for a unique cruise along the Seine. In just one hour and ten minutes, discover the monuments and multilingual commentaries of the City of Light. Enjoy a breathtaking view of the quays and historic sites, from the shelter of the bay windows or from the upper deck. A peaceful getaway for unforgettable memories, far from the hustle and bustle of the city. An exceptional experience to share.

comment: Founded by Catherine Mennad, l'Habit Français promotes French textile manufacturing by offering an exclusive selection of pieces. The boutique offers a unique experience in discovering original pieces, sometimes distributed for the first time in stores. L'Habit Français is a showcase for the talents and know-how of French fashion, offering a unique and authentic style. A must for fashion lovers and advocates of Made in France.

label: Le Mouton à cinq pattes
comment: Le Mouton à cinq pattes, a cult Parisian store founded in 1960, is a popular spot for bargain-seeking fashionistas. Men and women alike flock to the store to find discounted clothing from leading brands. With its vast selection of original, off-price clothing, everyone can create unique looks without breaking the bank. For those who want to stand out from the crowd in Paris, Le Mouton à cinq pattes is the place to go.

Fruity and refreshing, they will awaken the taste buds of Parisians in search of new ice cream experiences.

comment: Frog at Bercy Village, ideally located in the wine cellar district of Paris, is perfect for all your events. With its 400m2 on 2 levels and 2 terraces, this venue offers multiple possibilities for a cocktail party, a corporate dinner or an evening out with friends. You'll receive a warm welcome and enjoy a variety of entertainment including a DJ, photobooth and beer tasting. An address not to be missed for unforgettable moments in Paris!

Its typically Parisian ambience blends tradition and modernity, appealing to lovers of good food. Come and enjoy tasty, generous dishes prepared with fresh produce in a place steeped in history. Let yourself be transported by the warm atmosphere of this emblematic place and enjoy an unforgettable culinary experience.

comment: Enjoy an exceptional bowling experience at our 20-lane facility. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced player, you'll enjoy challenging your friends and family in a friendly, dynamic atmosphere. For fans of Reunion cuisine, this is the perfect place to explore the island's varied culture.

comment: Estelle Ramousse, a talented and inspired milliner, creates spectacular hairstyles and unique hats with a strong personality in her atelier-boutique. A universe where originality and creativity meet to sublimate the scene and seduce lovers of exceptional pieces.

label: Piscine Hébert
comment: The Hébert pool, in the heart of the La Chapelle district, is distinguished by its glass façade, which bathes the interior in light. It features two pools, one of 25 meters and the other of 14 meters. In summer, the magic happens when the roof opens to let in the gentle caress of the sun's rays on the pools. An exceptional aquatic experience!

label: Diesel
comment: The Italian brand with its provocative, offbeat style is still very popular with young rebels for its worn jeans. Known for its daring collections, the brand appeals to a clientele in search of originality, and renews its success by focusing on emotion. Her rebellious heritage gives her a timeless aura, making her an icon of contemporary fashion. This promising success story seems assured of a bright future.

label: La Gare / Le Gore
comment: Located near the Parc de la Villette, La Gare is an atypical concert venue housed in a former station on Paris's "petite Ceinture" railway line. Every evening, it offers jazz, hip-hop, groove and jam concerts, with free admission. Its 2,000 m² of gardens and terraces offer a warm atmosphere for drinks and snacks at low prices. After midnight, La Gare transforms into Gore, the place to be for wild clubbing evenings.

label: Salle Gaveau
comment: The Salle Gaveau, in the heart of Paris's 8th arrondissement, owes its name to the eponymous piano factory. Great artists such as Marguerite Long, Richter and Jessye Norman have performed here. Privatizing this historic venue for special events offers a unique opportunity, in an ideal location in the heart of the capital. It's the perfect choice for memorable cultural or business events.

label: Hôtel de Brienne - Ministère de la Défense
comment: Dating from the 18th century, the Hôtel de Brienne became the residence of the French Ministers of Defense in 1817. The tour on the 1st floor reveals the history of the Bonaparte family, Clemenceau's restored study and the place where De Gaulle established his base after the liberation of Paris in 1944. After discovering this place of power, a surprising anecdote in the garden brings this immersive, historical experience to a close.

label: Scoop me a cookie
comment: Scoop me a cookie has opened its second boutique in Batignolles, following its success in Ménilmontant. Originally from the United States, this star cookie from Boston is seducing Parisians with elaborate creations featuring butter from the Charentes region, organic eggs from Ile-de-France, vanilla from Madagascar, hazelnuts from Piedmont... Cookies with soft cores and crispy edges for a succulent taste experience.

label: Bloom Garden
comment: Come and enjoy an exceptional taste experience at the Bloom Garden restaurant, where the soothing ambience promises a moment of delectation. Discover refined, gourmet cuisine, crafted with passion to awaken your taste buds and delight your senses. Let yourself be tempted by a culinary escapade where each dish is an invitation to a gastronomic journey.

label: L'Autobus
comment: In the heart of rue Oberkampf, l'Autobus, a bar-PMU located at number 1, is full of charm. No fuss, no muss, just a home-from-home feel. You can order directly from Pierrot, the inimitable owner. The terrace is lively, as is the interior. Music from the jukebox, laughter from students and young executives, the atmosphere is electric. Don't miss l'Autobus, this little gem of Parisian conviviality!

label: Le Richer
comment: Come and discover an exceptional café-restaurant with a bistronomic ambience, where the menu is both concise and tempting. The wine selection is as impressive as the décor. In a convivial atmosphere, enjoy creative, delicate cuisine, with expert advice on food and wine pairing. Tip: Le Richer is open from dawn until late at night. Attentive service and reasonable prices guaranteed.

label: Repetto
comment: Created by Rose Repetto and loved by the likes of Bardot and Gainsbourg, Repetto is famous for its high-quality ballerinas, which are as comfortable as slippers. Adopted by renowned dancers such as Roland Petit, Nureyev and Béjart, these shoes embody French elegance and craftsmanship. A true timeless fashion legend, Repetto attracts fans of elegant footwear, remaining unchanging, unavoidable and as seductive as ever.

label: Coco de mer
comment: Le Coco de Mer in Paris offers a unique Seychelles gastronomic experience. From the moment you enter, you're transported to a tropical paradise, far from the hustle and bustle of the city. The ambience is carefully designed, with rattan furniture and teak tables. The menu is packed with emblematic Seychelles dishes: black pudding terrine, exotic "crab-nems", lentil sausage rougail, Cajun lamb, free-range chicken with coconut and turmeric... A feast to savor in the heart of Paris.

label: Le Monde de Noé
comment: Le Monde de Noé reinvents urban leisure with a unique immersive experience for families. In the heart of fantastic settings, visitors embark on a 1? hour adventure with real refuge animals. Accompanied by Rangers, they explore the secrets of the wilderness while learning about ecology. Giant rabbits, aquatic animals, flying creatures... for just 15 explorers. An urban oasis to bring humans closer to biodiversity and animals.

comment: The prestigious l'Arpège restaurant nestles close to the Invalides. This temple of gastronomy, led by talented Michelin-starred chef Alain Passard, celebrates vegetables in all their forms. In elegant, contemporary surroundings, guests are treated to a feast of refined cuisine where vegetables are the real stars. A unique taste experience not to be missed.

comment: Immerse yourself in the enchanting world of Turkish specialties, a delightful blend of Balkan and Oriental influences. Let yourself be seduced by a tasty cuisine with a thousand flavors. The warm welcome of the locals will add a touch of conviviality to your culinary experience. A taste experience rich in discovery awaits you!

label: Librairie polonaise
comment: Founded in 1830, Librairie Polonaise is now located on Boulevard Saint-Germain in Paris. Specializing in Polish books and cultural products, it is a reference for lovers of Polish literature and art. The bookshop offers a wide selection of books in Polish, as well as works from neighboring countries, giving you the chance to discover the culture of Eastern Europe. It's a convivial meeting place for fans of Slavic culture.

label: Basilique Notre-Dame du Perpétuel Secours
comment: The Church of Notre-Dame-du-Perpétuel-Secours, nestling in Paris's 11th arrondissement, has a captivating neo-Gothic architecture, erected in 1898. Elevated to the status of minor basilica in 1966 by Pope Paul VI, it joins the prestigious Basilica of Santa Maria Maggiore in Rome. Famous for its exceptional organ, this parish houses one of the capital's most renowned instruments.

label: L'Entrepôt
comment: L'Entrepôt, close to the Montparnasse train station, is a lively cultural venue offering a variety of activities: films, lectures, exhibitions, literary workshops and concerts. Open to all, it's also child-friendly. Between events, visitors can enjoy simple, fresh cuisine at the bar or restaurant. The garden and veranda invite you to relax, while the bar offers a lively musical atmosphere in the evenings.

label: Chocolaterie de Puyricard
comment: Since 1967, Chocolaterie de Puyricard has been renowned for its top-of-the-range chocolate, made without freezing or preservatives. In 2010, it was awarded the "Entreprise du Patrimoine Vivant" label. With 3 boutiques in Paris and the south of France, chocolate lovers can visit the workshop or take part in gourmet workshops. For further information or to place an order, please contact the France and Europe Shipping Department on +33 (0) 4 42 28 18 16.

label: Marché couvert Saint-Germain
comment: Come and discover the Saint-Germain covered market, set under magnificent arcades. Open 6 days a week, this market is packed with colorful stalls: fruit and vegetables, delicatessen, fresh fish, rotisseries, international products from Spain, Italy, Greece... Don't miss a visit (or several) to the counter of the famous cheesemaker Michel Sanders. A culinary escapade not to be missed!

comment: Discover this charming boutique dedicated to well-being and beauty, offering a selection of organic and all-natural soaps, skincare products and cosmetics. Top brands include Lilas Blanc, Patyka, Marius Fabre... And let's not forget our handcrafted soaps. A veritable paradise for fans of quality products that respect the skin and the environment.

label: La Palette
comment: The bistro "La Palette" is a must-see in Paris's 6th arrondissement, with its sunny, flower-filled terrace, a haven of peace in Saint-Germain-des-Prés. Listed as a historic monument, it boasts period decor, with paintings and ceramics from the 1930s. A haven for Parisian artists, it welcomed Picasso, Braque, Jim Morrison, Hemingway, Roberts and Ford. Its simple, authentic menu delights gourmets looking for a tasty break.

label: Institut Giacometti
comment: The Institut Giacometti in Paris allows visitors to explore the world of Swiss sculptor Alberto Giacometti (1901-1966). Housed in Paul Follot's former studio, it features a permanent exhibition of Giacometti's original work. Temporary exhibitions compare his work with that of other artists, and a library specializing in modern art is available. The Giacometti Lab offers educational activities. Tickets for an enriching visit.

label: Église Saint-Antoine de Padoue
comment: Saint-Antoine de Padoue church, designed by architect Léon Azéma, stands out for its singular architecture in the Porte de Versailles district. Its imposing reinforced concrete frame, combined with red brick, gives it a unique allure. Its 46-meter high bell tower is crowned by a cement cross. A remarkable building that combines modernity and architectural tradition.

label: Le Bistro Parisien
comment: Le Bistrot Parisiens, located at the foot of the Eiffel Tower, boasts a privileged location and a breathtaking view through its bay windows and two terraces. Open for lunch, dinner and Sunday brunch, this establishment offers the ideal setting for enjoying French gastronomy to the full. A must for lovers of fine cuisine and views of Paris.

label: Gare de Paris-Est
comment: At Gare de l'Est, travelers can enjoy 49 shops spread over 2 levels, with well-known names such as Sephora, Etam, Camaïeu, Mango, Rituals, Swarowski, Desigual, Dim, Kiko, Hema, Mac Donalds, Paul, Maison Pradier, Kusmi Tea, Jeff de Bruges, M&S Food, Fnac, Relay, as well as 2 restaurants and a pharmacy. It's a shopping and dining paradise for travelers passing through this iconic station.

label: Centre Pompidou
comment: The Centre Pompidou, designed by Renzo Piano and Richard Rogers, is an architectural icon of the 20th century, housing the Musée National d?Art Moderne with works by Matisse, Picasso and Warhol. Renowned exhibitions take place on the top floor, offering panoramic views over Paris. A full visit can take half a day, including time for refreshments, a visit to the Bibliothèque publique d?information, or shopping.

label: Un Jour, un regard
comment: Ideally located on Rue Saint-Honoré, Un Jour, un Regard specializes in eye beautification. Whether you're looking for reshaping, enhancement, semi-permanent make-up or eyelash extensions, we've got everything you need to make your eyes shine. The salon also offers treatments for hands and feet, for a complete beauty experience. Treat yourself to a wellness break at Un Jour, un Regard.

label: Square des Épinettes
comment: In Paris's 17th arrondissement, the Épinettes district boasts a vast green space: the Square des Épinettes. At its heart stands a bandstand. Among its arboreal treasures, a remarkable purple beech planted in 1879 stands proudly alongside a majestic Virginia tulip tree reaching a height of 20 meters. A peaceful place where nature and tranquility come together to the delight of walkers.

label: Le bar du Noham Café
comment: At the heart of this elegantly glamorous lounge bar is an imposing double rhinoceros head. Yet this establishment, located near the Arc de Triomphe, offers a unique atmosphere, blending rock and refinement. The head bartender, an expert in mixology, skilfully prepares a variety of delicious cocktails, combining classic recipes with exclusive creations. An address not to be missed for an exceptional moment.

Around a warm central bar, customers sit on stools, creating a convivial atmosphere worthy of the best pizzerias.

The sunny terrace opens in April for an unforgettable culinary experience.

An innovative approach that promises to surprise and delight perfume lovers in search of originality.

label: Pavillons de Bercy - Musée des Arts Forains
comment: Immerse yourself in the world of the Musée des Arts Forains, an unusual venue in Paris. Discover a collection of 19th-century objects housed in former wine cellars. No labels, just guided tours led by actors. Experience magical moments with rides and mechanical instruments. A magical experience for all, not to be missed! And don't miss the Festival du Merveilleux during the festive season, a colorful and enchanting show.

label: Le Cabaret sauvage
comment: The Cabaret Sauvage, created by Méziane Azaïche in December 1997 at La Villette, has a warm, inviting atmosphere. Red velvet, wood panelling, light effects and mirrors create an atmosphere conducive to escape. On the dance floor, a unique show unfolds, blending music, dance and emotion. This atypical venue offers a varied program: concerts, cabarets, balls... An immersive experience not to be missed!

Red velvet, wood panelling, light effects and mirrors create an atmosphere conducive to escape. On the dance floor, a unique show unfolds, blending music, dance and emotion. This atypical venue offers a varied program: concerts, cabarets, balls... An immersive experience not to be missed!
street: Parc de la Villette - 211 avenue Jean Jaurès

label: Église Saint-Jean-Baptiste de Belleville
comment: Nestled in the heart of Paris's lively Belleville district, the Saint-Jean-Baptiste church stands out for its striking neo-Gothic architecture. Built between 1854 and 1859, it is 68 m long and 25 m wide, with spires reaching 57 m in height. An emblematic monument of the capital, it is a vibrant testimony to Paris's history and architectural heritage.

label: Paroisse protestante luthérienne de Bon Secours
comment: Founded in 1854 in the heart of the dynamic Faubourg Saint-Antoine, the Protestant Lutheran parish of Bon-Secours is a veritable religious heritage. Threatened with destruction in 1994, the church was saved thanks to an exceptional mobilization of the community. Today, restored to its former glory, it sits majestically and proudly on the Monuments Historiques list. A wonderful story of solidarity and preservation of architectural heritage.

label: Port du Gros Caillou
comment: Stroll along the Port du Gros Caillou, a pedestrian haven on the banks of the Seine, linking the Pont des Invalides to the Pont de l'Alma. An integral part of the Parc Rives de Seine, it offers magnificent views of the Grand Palais and the Eiffel Tower. Between art and nature, discover Fluctuart on its barge and the floating gardens dedicated to Niki de Saint Phalle.

label: Musée de la Préfecture de police
comment: Immerse yourself in French history, with key events, conspiracies and famous people. Discover historical archives, weapons and uniforms. Explore famous criminal cases through exhibits on display. Immerse yourself in the atmosphere of the capital's former prisons and daily life. A fascinating immersion in French history, from arrests to urban issues.

label: Le Djoon
comment: The Djoon, a not-to-be-missed club in Paris, is renowned for its soul and world music evenings. Young talents perform here regularly, attracting a hip clientele. Located close to the François Mitterrand Library, this dynamic venue offers a popular restaurant serving delicious soul food. Private events can also be organized in this prestigious setting.

label: Jaja.
comment: In the heart of the Marais, Paris' historic LGBT district, Le Jaja offers a bucolic break in a charming passageway, far from the hustle and bustle of the street. Its flower-bedecked terrace creates a pastoral ambience for enjoying bistronomic cuisine featuring fresh, organic and seasonal produce, accompanied by a selection of over 80 wines. A children's menu is available, and a vaulted room in the basement can be reserved for private events. A peaceful address in the heart of the capital.

label: Nord Marais
comment: Located in the trendy Nord Marais district, this bar-restaurant perfectly combines tradition and modernity. At lunchtime, let yourself be seduced by tasty home cooking. In the evening, the establishment transforms into a bar, offering a variety of tapas and platters to share, all in a warm and friendly atmosphere. The perfect place to discover the art of Parisian living.

label: Pavillon de l'Arsenal
comment: The Pavillon de l'Arsenal in Paris is a veritable mine of information on urban planning and architecture. Its permanent collection, giant model and temporary exhibitions trace the evolution of the City of Light and the impact of history on its urban development. Explore news galleries, a photo library and conference rooms on three floors. Take part in the "Archivélo" bike tours to discover Greater Paris. An enriching experience not to be missed!

label: Basilique du Sacré-Coeur de Montmartre
comment: The Basilique du Sacré-C?ur, a Paris landmark inaugurated in 1919 on the Montmartre hilltop, fascinates with its Romanesque-Byzantine architecture and dazzling whiteness. Inside, the largest mosaic in France (480m²) and a visit to the crypt are not to be missed. The more adventurous can climb up to the dome for a panoramic view. Nearby, the Place du Tertre and the Abbesses district offer charming strolls. An evening at the Moulin Rouge promises unforgettable moments. A must for fans of the City of Lights!

label: Paroisse du Saint-Esprit
comment: Located in the Daumesnil district, the church, designed by architect Paul Tournon, unveiled its crypt in 1929. Built in reinforced concrete, it features a square nave topped by a majestic dome measuring 22 metres in diameter and 33 metres in height. Inside, mosaics, stained-glass windows, paintings, sculptures and ironwork form a decor that has been classified as a historic monument. Organ and classical music concerts regularly enliven these walls steeped in history.

label: L’Usine - Club de sport
comment: L'Usine, nestled near the Opéra and Beaubourg, is an emblematic venue for intelligent sports activity. Designed by architect Christophe Delcourt, this urban club combines design and training. After the effort, the spa invites you to take a relaxing break, with a massage area and steam rooms for an anti-stress moment.

label: L'Argonaute - Cité des Sciences et de l'Industrie
comment: Discover the Argonaute, a 50s fighter submarine open to the public at the Parc de la Villette. Equipped with audioguide headsets, immerse yourself in this mythical machine, from the crew station to the torpedo tube. A unique immersion in the history of submarines awaits you in this captivating setting. An unforgettable experience for maritime history buffs!

additional_information: ['Tuesday to Sunday, 10 a.m. to 11:30 p.m. Closed Mondays']

label: Marché couvert les Enfants Rouges
comment: The Marché des Enfants Rouges, opened in 1615, remains an emblematic Paris landmark, offering fresh, local produce in a multicultural atmosphere. Among the varied stalls, you'll discover a diversity of world cuisines, from Italian groceries to Lebanese delicatessen. On Sundays, you can enjoy a gourmet brunch at l'Estaminet or La Petite Fabrique. A gustatory experience not to be missed in Paris!

label: Montmartre en chansons
comment: Discover another facet of Montmartre with the "Montmartre en chansons" tour led by local guide and singer Anne-Sophie. Immerse yourself in the legends of French chanson, from Édith Piaf to Jacques Brel and Charles Aznavour. Anecdotes and a cappella performances will transport you into the spellbinding atmosphere of Montmartre. Stroll through unusual places, discover iconic landmarks such as the Sacré-C?ur and the Moulin de la Galette, all the while humming the cult tunes of this mythical district. A unique experience not to be missed!

label: Jardin de l'hôtel Salomon de Rothschild
comment: The "Folie Beaujon" mansion, built by banker Beaujon, is today represented by the Hôtel Salomon de Rothschild and its adjoining garden. Nestled in the 8th arrondissement, close to the Champs-Élysées, this peaceful spot was the site of an amusement park after the banker's death. Offering a calm, country atmosphere, it is a true oasis of tranquility in the heart of the capital.

label: Centre culturel canadien
comment: The Canadian Cultural Centre in Paris is located in the prestigious 8th arrondissement, just off the Champs-Élysées. A key player in cultural exchanges between Canada and France, it offers a rich program of activities: exhibitions, concerts, shows, film screenings, conferences... A true showcase of Canadian culture in the heart of the French capital.

label: Nakatani
comment: The Nakatani's Japanese chef, a disciple of Hélène Darroze, cultivates a strong passion for French gastronomy. His cuisine adapts to the seasons and local produce, offering a refined, authentic culinary experience. The sober, elegant ambience of the dining room, bathed in light and white, enhances the bond created between guests and the chef, whose open kitchen reveals all his savoir-faire.

label: Sensitive et fils
comment: Explore the exotic world of Sensitive et Fils, specialists in Asian decorations. Fall for our silk velvet garments from Vietnam, Burmese necklaces, colorful vases and cushions, and authentic furniture from China and Mongolia. Let yourself be charmed by these unique pieces that evoke a warm and exotic atmosphere. A design escapade through Asia for a touch of originality and elegance in your home.

label: Café Beaubourg
comment: Opposite the Centre Georges Pompidou, Café Beaubourg is a favorite for its ideal location. Its large terrace offers a magnificent view of the unique architecture of Europe's largest museum of modern art. Opened in 1987 by Gilbert Costes, this café with its contemporary design by Christian de Portzamparc offers an elegant setting in which to relax or work. With a daily brunch, it's the ideal place to meet up with friends or enjoy a break from the urban hustle and bustle.

label: Uncouture by Béatrice Ferrant
comment: Since 2003, Béatrice Ferrant's luxury label has been offering collections of mutant garments carefully crafted from noble French and Italian materials. Each piece reflects artisanal know-how and an eco-responsible approach. Attracting a clientele in search of elegance and originality, her timeless creations reflect deep reflection.

label: Galerie Karsten Greve
comment: For over 40 years, Galerie Karsten Greve has been showcasing the work of renowned artists such as Louise Bourgeois, Lucio Fontana and Piero Manzoni. But it also supports promising young talents such as Claire Morgan and Georgia Russell. Paintings, drawings, prints, photographs, installations... A rich and varied artistic panorama that continues to fascinate art lovers the world over.

label: Cyril Lignac - Aux Prés
comment: Chef Cyril Lignac has opened a new restaurant in Saint-Germain-des-Prés. Featuring authentic bistro cuisine in a retro-chic ambience, the establishment recaptures the spirit of the 50s with the leather banquettes of the "Claude Sainlouis". What's more, the chef has also launched "Le Bar des Prés" at 25 rue du Dragon, in a former tanning salon. A not-to-be-missed address for tasty cocktails in an elegant and convivial setting.

label: Fédération française de la randonnée pédestre
comment: The Fédération française de la randonnée pédestre (French Hiking Federation), a non-profit organization, promotes and develops hiking by creating, marking and maintaining hiking trails throughout France. In Paris, these signposted itineraries let you discover the capital's diversity on foot. Walking enthusiasts can explore the City of Light through routes detailed in the federation's topo-guides, combining urban riches with nature.

label: Les Petits Plats
comment: This bistro, full of charm and conviviality, stands out as the perfect place for hesitant lovers of good food. No more dilemmas, here every dish can be tasted in half portions! Not to mention a fine selection of wines to delight even the most demanding palates. A place to indulge without restraint, to be discovered without delay.

label: Longines
comment: In June 2015, Longines opened its first dedicated boutique in France. The 120 m², beige and wood-toned venue celebrates tradition, elegance and performance. Located in the 6th arrondissement of Paris, the boutique was inaugurated in the presence of Stefanie Graf. In addition to the 500 models on display, visitors can enjoy a museum area and a personalized welcome in the VIP lounge. A must for lovers of exceptional watches.

label: Visites guidées : Les secrets des Galeries Lafayette Haussmann
comment: Discover the fascinating history of Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann, founded in 1893. Visit this iconic Paris shopping destination on exclusive tours to explore its evolution from novelty store to architectural masterpiece. Admire the majestic dome, elegant balconies and monumental staircase. Book your guided tour on Saturday at 9am in French or Sunday at 10am in English to unlock the mysteries of Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann.

label: Grande Halle de La Villette
comment: The Grande Halle, next door to the Cité des Sciences et de l'Industrie, is the former cattle market of La Villette. Built between 1865 and 1867, this historic monument is a magnet for architecture enthusiasts. Masterfully renovated by Bernard Reichen and Philippe Robert from 2005 to 2007, it has become a major cultural venue, hosting shows, concerts, exhibitions and festivals in the heart of the capital.

label: Galerie Jocelyn Wolff
comment: Galerie Jocelyn Wolff, founded in 2003, is located in the lively Belleville district of Paris. It offers a year-round program of exhibitions featuring renowned contemporary artists. A must for art lovers in search of varied, high-quality artistic discoveries.

label: S.T. Dupont
comment: Renowned for introducing the gasoline-powered pocket lighter, this renowned brand has been offering a variety of luxury items since its creation in 1872. From Chinese lacquer to guilloché lighters, leather goods and jewelry, it designs and manufactures accessories of exceptional quality.

label: Musée Clemenceau
comment: In 1896, George Clemenceau moved into an apartment overlooking the Eiffel Tower and a private garden. Despite his many posts, he kept the same address. His home has been preserved, and in 2015, the vestibule and study were restored. In 2017, the first-floor gallery was renovated to celebrate his centenary in power. His garden, where he loved to stroll and raise chickens, remains a haven of peace.

label: Jardin du Luxembourg
comment: The Luxembourg Gardens, created in 1612 by Queen Marie de Médicis, are a historical and botanical jewel in the heart of Paris. Its 25-hectare grounds combine French and English gardens, lush greenery, a varied orchard, apiary, orchid greenhouses and rose garden. Statues, the Médicis fountain, the Orangerie and the Davioud Pavilion enhance this magnificent setting. Children: rides, puppets and slides; adults: chess, tennis, bridge, remote-controlled boats. Dynamic cultural program.

label: Jardin de Reuilly - Paul Pernin
comment: The Jardin de Reuilly - Paul Pernin, along the Coulée Verte René Dumont, is a green gem. This gently sloping 4,200 m² garden, lined with themed gardens and female statues, replaces a former goods station. Designed between 1992 and 1998 by Pierre Colboc et Paysage, it features a public fountain, the only one of its kind in France, offering fresh or sparkling water free of charge. An oasis of relaxation in the city.

label: Église Saint-Georges de la Villette
comment: Saint-Georges-de-la-Villette church, built at the end of the 19th century in the Villette district, is distinguished by its neo-Romanesque style. Characterized by its sobriety and rare openings, it dazzles visitors with its magnificent stained-glass windows, richly decorated with religious stories. A true invitation to contemplation and wonder.

label: Free Lance
comment: Vendée-based brand Free Lance offers limited-edition collections combining traditional craftsmanship and creativity. From pumps to biker boots to riding boots, Free Lance stands out for its unique style, each pair designed with meticulous attention to detail. Opt for elegant, hard-wearing footwear, perfect for all your adventures. Discover this singular universe for lovers of fine footwear.

label: La Pâtisserie Cyril Lignac (Chaillot)
comment: Chefs Cyril Lignac and Benoît Couvrand have combined their talents to create a unique culinary experience in their boutique on rue de Chaillot. With its wooden facade and earthenware tiles, the place exudes authenticity. Here, you can savor refined breads, viennoiseries and pastries, including the delicious Equinoxe signature creation and revisited classics such as éclair, baba au rhum and tarte au citron. A true gourmet's paradise.

label: Le Villaret
comment: Restaurant Villaret, located in the Oberkampf district of Paris, is a gourmet address not to be missed. With its chic Parisian bistro decor, the atmosphere is warm and friendly. Meat takes pride of place on their plates, with tasty dishes based on lamb, game and many other delicacies. And let's not forget the superb cellar, sure to delight wine lovers. An ideal place for lovers of good food and good times with friends and family.

comment: Near Montmartre, Bio c' Bon Pigalle stands out as one of the largest organic supermarkets in Paris. Renowned for its quality and affordable prices, this store offers a wide range of certified organic products. From fresh fruit and vegetables to dairy products, bread and cheese, there's something for everyone. A must for organic food lovers looking for variety and quality.

label: Cité de la musique - Philharmonie de Paris
comment: The Cité de la musique - Philharmonie de Paris offers concerts, a museum and musical activities. Located in the Parc de la Villette, it is a unique architectural landmark. The Musée de la Musique exhibits over 7,000 instruments and works, while the Philharmonie offers concerts, tours and workshops. A new permanent exhibition space testifies to its heritage ambitions.

label: Le Progrès
comment: In the heart of the Marais district, Le Progrès is the place to meet friends. Located at the intersection of three lively streets, this Parisian bar-tabac offers a convivial atmosphere. Enjoy a glass of wine and a charcuterie board on the terrace. Popular with fashion, advertising, arts and media professionals, Le Progrès is ideal for a lively aperitif. Come and enjoy the unique atmosphere of this emblematic venue in the upper Marais.

label: YellowKorner
comment: Since 2006, YellowKorner has made fine art photography affordable. These high-quality, affordable prints are limited editions and numbered. Choose from a wide selection of works by renowned artists of the past, such as Nadar and Man Ray, as well as contemporary artists. Treat yourself to a unique piece from this rich and varied collection.

label: Square Paul Painlevé
comment: In the heart of Place Paul-Painlevé, between the Sorbonne and the Musée de Cluny, nestles a small 758m² green space created in 1900 by Jean-Camille Formigé. Redesigned in 2000 by Eric Ossart and Arnaud Maurières, this haven of peace recalls the medieval charm of Cluny's gardens. Embellished with works such as "La Louve Romaine" and the fountain "Monument à Octave Gréard", this garden offers a relaxing break in the heart of Paris, far from the hustle and bustle of busy boulevards.

comment: With the return of the warm weather, the small stadium, nestled in the heart of a green setting, offers a pleasant setting for sports enthusiasts. Equipped with top-quality facilities such as a shot-put area, a high jump, a long jump and a 250-meter track, it is sure to delight lovers of running and jumping. An ideal setting for sports activities in a naturally soothing environment.

label: La Maison de la Poutine
comment: Taste delicious Poutine québécoise in Paris's East End or in the Sentier district. A unique culinary experience for lovers of authentic and original cuisine. Savor every bite of crispy fries, melting cheese and creamy sauce. These addresses will tantalize your taste buds and take you on a gustatory journey to the heart of Quebec culture, without leaving Paris. A gourmet getaway not to be missed on your next visit.

label: L’Assaggio Restaurant
comment: Hotel Castille Paris is home to L'Assaggio restaurant, where since 2017, Chef Ugo Alciati has been elevating Italian cuisine. With excellent ingredients such as Sicilian tomatoes, and homemade pasta, each dish is a tribute to the flavors of Piedmont. Discover the seasonal creativity of our Chef and his brigade, true to Alciati's gastronomic craftsmanship.

label: Tour Saint-Jacques
comment: The Saint-Jacques tower, a flamboyant Gothic bell tower built between 1509 and 1523, is the only vestige of the Saint-Jacques-de-la-Boucherie church, destroyed in 1797. It marks the start of the pilgrimage to Santiago de Compostela via Turonensis. Since 1891, a weather station has been operating under the Montsouris Observatory. Symbols of the evangelists and eighteen statues of saints adorn this restored jewel.

label: Virtual Room
comment: Discover Virtual Room, the first collaborative virtual reality room in Paris! In teams of 2 to 4 players, immerse yourself in immersive adventures combining thinking and communication. Explore 4 thrilling missions including Time Travel 1 & 2, Are we dead and Press Start. Travel from prehistory to the future, battle zombies or explore a retro gaming universe. A unique experience to share with family and friends!

label: Librairie du Mémorial de la Shoah
comment: Located in the heart of the Shoah Memorial, our bookshop offers over 15,000 references on the history of the Shoah and Jewish Worlds. As a specialist bookshop, our catalog goes beyond these subjects with a varied selection: literature, thrillers, theater, poetry, essays, humanities, history, youth, comics, audio and video. Come and discover our cultural space, passionate about reading.

label: Pitanga
comment: Dive into the heart of Latin America at this Parisian restaurant, a stone's throw from the Palais Royal. Discover the culinary richness of Brazil through tasty tapas, refreshing cocktails and sunny, exotic dishes. A tasty immersion that will delight your taste buds and transport you into a warm and friendly atmosphere. A must for lovers of world cuisine in search of a change of scenery.

comment: The Paris Ma Belle team offers to discover Paris of yesterday and today in a fun and offbeat way thanks to treasure hunts. Petanque tournaments are also organized in the best places of the capital. Each activity is designed for young and old and takes place in a friendly atmosphere. A passionate team, in love with the city, elaborates tailor-made events with challenges for companies.

comment: This brand seduces with its timeless, sober and slightly trendy style, perfect for moms and their daughters. label: Marché Anvers
comment: The Anvers food market, established in 2004, nestles at the foot of the famous Butte Montmartre, between Pigalle and Barbès. Every Friday afternoon, some twenty traders take over the premises, offering a variety of fresh, local, quality produce. Among the colorful stands, a few stalls of organic produce delight fans of healthy, responsible cooking. An unmissable weekly rendezvous for gourmets in search of authentic flavours.

label: Le Pataques
comment: Le Pataquès restaurant, ideally located in the 12th arrondissement near the AccorHotels Arena de Bercy, boasts an original Provencal menu. Under the direction of Rose Kébir, the traditional cuisine offers authentic, tasty dishes. You can also take advantage of the pleasant tree-lined terrace for convivial moments on sunny days. A gastronomic haven of peace in the heart of the capital.

label: Mystery cuisine
comment: Immerse yourself in the mysterious world of Mystery Cuisine, where intimacy is the order of the day with just 3 tables. Muffled ambience, soft lighting and candles create an enchanting atmosphere. Enjoy Vietnamese cuisine revisited by chef Thu-Ha, blending tradition and modernity with surprising molecular touches. A unique sensory experience, combining the discovery of flavors and the pleasure of the senses. An original and affordable address for a memorable romantic dinner.

Pastry workshops, birthday creations and elegant, playful culinary accessories are also on offer. A gourmet and creative place to delight taste buds and pastry enthusiasts in search of inspiration.

label: Les comptoirs du Médoc
comment: Located in the Haussmann district, this chic restaurant showcases the prestigious Médoc wine and gastronomy region of Bordeaux. The menu features a meticulous selection of local produce, sourced directly from the region's producers. The refined dishes attract both local regulars and tourists in search of an authentic culinary experience. Ideal for a gourmet break between two shopping sessions or before a performance at the Garnier opera house.

label: Le Bataclan
comment: Following several transformations, Le Bataclan has become a renowned concert venue. Formerly a music hall, then a theater and finally a cinema, it now plays host to major national and international artists. From Alain Bashung to Prince, not forgetting IAM, Oasis, NTM and Robbie Williams, this legendary venue, ideally located between Place de la Bastille and Place de la République, has played host to renowned artists from a wide range of musical backgrounds.

label: Quiveutpister
comment: Discover Paris in an original way with Quiveutpister's treasure hunts! Explore the City of Light, from popular neighborhoods to secret places, equipped with your detective's tools. Explore Montmartre, Saint-Germain-des-Prés, the Marais or the Opéra Garnier in search of suspects, witnesses or culprits. Solve the riddles, collect points and become the best team of investigators. A fun and educational way to discover the capital!

label: Jardins du Trocadéro
comment: Don't miss the Jardins du Trocadéro when you visit the Eiffel Tower! These 93,930m² of greenery, created in 1937, offer a breathtaking view of the Tower. Don't forget your camera to capture this unique moment. The Warsaw Fountain and its 20 water cannons offer an exceptional aquatic spectacle. A number of sculptures also adorn the garden, making it an ideal place to stop and take in the beauty of Paris and its surroundings.

This team of pros will redefine your eyebrows and magnify your lashes with innovative techniques such as micro-pigmentation and semi-permanent mascara. An elegant, friendly atmosphere guaranteed for radiant eyes! Other addresses in Paris, open even on Sundays, for your complete satisfaction.

A source of healthy, responsible eating, the products are certified 100% organic, sourced from French organic farming and in season. What's more, every month a producer is featured, highlighting the diversity and quality of the ingredients on offer at LadiBIO.

Fertile ground for artists such as Cézanne and Picabia, it is open to the public during the annual open house, an eagerly awaited opportunity to immerse yourself in artistic Paris.

comment: Located near Place des Vosges, Librairie du Globe specializes in Russian culture. A wide choice of works in Russian, books on Russia, learning methods, dictionaries, newspapers, DVDs, CDs and audio books. Numerous events on offer: Russian courses, lectures, activities for children, literary meetings, concerts and film club. A must for Russian culture enthusiasts, combining enriching readings and fascinating encounters.

comment: Founded in 1963, École Gobelins is a renowned institution in the field of images. Specializing in training for careers in photography, communications, graphic design, animation and digital design, it offers both full-time and apprenticeship programs. The school also regularly organizes exhibitions to showcase the talents of its students. A benchmark for artistic and creative professions.

label: Café Jacques
comment: Café Jacques, nestled in the heart of the ?garden in motion? of the musée du quai Branly ? Jacques Chirac, offers a breathtaking view of the Eiffel Tower and the Seine. This contemporary café offers natural, gourmet cuisine featuring seasonal produce. The pastries are to die for! Enjoy a light, delicious break with no obligation to buy a ticket. A place not to be missed, recommended by the Bonne Table Les Collectionneurs gastronomic guide.

label: Grande Mosquée de Paris
comment: Built between 1922 and 1926, the Mosquée de Paris is located in the Latin Quarter, next to the Natural History Museum. Its Hispano-Moorish architecture, with a 33-metre minaret, is reminiscent of the Alhambra in Granada. The arcaded patio creates an enchanting atmosphere, and the prayer room is decorated with magnificent motifs and sumptuous carpets. In addition to its religious function, the Mosquée de Paris offers hammam services, a restaurant, a tea room and an exotic boutique reminiscent of oriental markets. A unique place that combines culture and relaxation.

label: La Tarte Tropézienne
comment: Created by Alexandra Micka in 1955, Tarte Tropézienne opened its first store in Paris, on rue de Montfaucon in the 6th arrondissement. This emblematic dessert is a delicious brioche filled with crème pâtissière, a secret recipe that is the key to its success. A pure delight to be savored in a chic, refined setting.

label: L’Arbre à Sens
comment: The Arbre à Sens spa, near the Palais-Royal in Paris, offers a unique sensory experience inspired by the Orient, India and the Maghreb. Specializing in natural, hand-crafted treatments, this place of relaxation offers a range of services: body and facial treatments, traditional massages and a hammam. L'Arbre à Sens invites you on a journey of the senses in the heart of Paris, with its warm, refined decor conducive to relaxation.

label: Stade Sébastien Charlety
comment: Located in the heart of Paris's 13th arrondissement, the 20,000-seat Stade Charléty is the city's second-largest sports venue. Every day, over 2,000 visitors enjoy its top-quality facilities. At the same time, the stadium organizes prestigious events such as Charléty sur neige, national and international championships (rowing, rugby, etc.), and broadcasts of major events such as the soccer World Cup.

label: Hôtel Guimard
comment: Built between 1909 and 1912 by architect Hector Guimard, this Art Nouveau-style townhouse is a work of art. It housed Guimard?s agency on the first floor, his private apartments on the 1st and 2nd floors, and his wife?s studio on the 3rd floor. Listed for its stone and brick facade featuring curved forms and bow windows decorated with floral motifs, this building is a testament to Guimard?s talent.

label: Sénat - Palais du Luxembourg
comment: The Palais du Luxembourg, built in 1625 by Salomon de Brosse for Queen Marie de Médicis, has undergone a number of changes over the years. Used as a prison during the Revolution, it became the meeting place of the Senate under Napoleon Bonaparte in 1800, then of the Chamber of Peers after his fall. Alphonse de Gisors extended the building in 1836 to accommodate the Senate of the Fifth Republic, made up of 321 senators divided into six commissions who debate legislation in the company of experts.

label: Betino’s Record Shop
comment: Betino's Record Shop is a must-visit address in the 11th arrondissement, entirely dedicated to vinyl records. With an impressive selection of 12,000 items, music lovers have a lot to look forward to! A true paradise for collectors in search of rare nuggets and musical treasures.

label: Sainte-Chapelle
comment: The Sainte-Chapelle, a jewel of the Radiant Gothic style, fascinates with its 1113 stained-glass windows. Built in the 13th century by Louis IX as part of the Palais de la Cité in Paris, it was originally intended to house Christ's Crown of Thorns. Featuring fifteen glass windows and an impressive rose window forming walls of light, it embodies the splendor of the Gothic style. Listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Sainte-Chapelle is a masterpiece not to be missed.

label: Frédéric Simonin
comment: Frédéric Simonin's restaurant, near the Arc de Triomphe, is a culinary nugget. Headed by Michelin-starred chef Frédéric Simonin, formerly of Le Meurice and George V, it offers creative, refined cuisine. Awarded a Michelin star and three toques by Gault & Millau, this elegant, Art Deco-inspired establishment offers an exquisite menu that revisits the classics to delight the taste buds.

Headed by Michelin-starred chef Frédéric Simonin, formerly of Le Meurice and George V, it offers creative, refined cuisine. Awarded a Michelin star and three toques by Gault & Millau, this elegant, Art Deco-inspired establishment offers an exquisite menu that revisits the classics to delight the taste buds.

label: Culture Rapide
comment: Culture Rapide, the place to be for slam fans, is in Belleville. This bar with a popular soul offers original decor, a convivial terrace and lively evenings. Open stage" sessions reveal young talents such as Grand Corps Malade and Abd Al Malik. A buffet aperitif is offered every Friday. A must for lovers of urban poetry, in a warm and diverse atmosphere.

label: Bong 15eme
comment: Discover Bong, an authentic restaurant celebrating Korean tradition! Located between Montparnasse and the Eiffel Tower, this restaurant transports you to the heart of Korean gastronomy. Enjoy tasty dishes, rich flavors and delicately prepared delicacies. Let yourself be seduced by the warm and friendly atmosphere of this unique establishment. An unforgettable culinary experience awaits you at Bong!

label: Cité internationale universitaire de Paris, son parc et ses pavillons
comment: Founded in 1925, the Cité internationale universitaire de Paris comprises 40 residences in a variety of architectural styles. Among them, the Fondation Suisse and the Maison du Brésil, designed by Le Corbusier, are historic monuments. Every year, 12,000 students of 140 different nationalities enjoy the Cité U's rich cultural program of events, shows and exhibitions. This intellectual space reflects the diversity of student life in Paris.

label: Centre sportif des Poissonniers
comment: The sports center features a 1,000-seat grandstand stadium, two gyms with disabled access, three tennis courts and a popular 21-meter outdoor climbing wall. A complete infrastructure to satisfy athletes of all levels and encourage the practice of a variety of activities in a modern, adapted environment.

label: Square Louis XIII
comment: The square, nestled in the heart of the Place des Vosges, is home to around a hundred lime and horse chestnut trees, accompanied by four fountains. In the center, the majestic equestrian statue of Louis XIII is a real eye-catcher. In summer, the verdant lawns are much appreciated by visitors in search of calm and freshness.

label: Immeuble Home
comment: Designed in 2015 by the agencies Hamonic + Masson & Associés and Comte Vollenweider, the Home building is a landmark development in Paris Rive Gauche. The first residential building over 50 metres in height in Paris since the 1970s, it symbolizes an architectural revival with its evolving stepped structure leading to a tower with unstructured balconies. Combining social housing and home ownership, the Home project is resolutely modern and innovative.

label: Jardin Casque d’Or
comment: The Jardin Casque d'Or, near the Père-Lachaise cemetery, is a haven of peace in the city. With its manicured lawns, shaded terraces and quiet corners, it's an ideal place to recharge your batteries. What's more, there's a 1,400 m² shared garden where you can grow your own food together. An invitation to relax in the heart of the capital.

label: Galerie de paléontologie et d’anatomie comparée - Muséum national d'histoire na
comment: Housed in a 19th-century building, the Comparative Anatomy gallery presents the world of vertebrates and invertebrates. Skeletons of fish, birds, reptiles and mammals are on display. This immersive visit continues upstairs with the Paleontology gallery, where impressive fossilized skeletons, such as dinosaurs and mammoths, come to life. An exploration rich in discovery at the heart of nature's wonders. (384 characters)

label: Paroisse Saint-Vincent-de-Paul
comment: Located near the Gare du Nord station, the Église Saint-Vincent-de-Paul is a Parisian architectural gem. The capital's last great "classical" church, it is inspired by Roman basilicas, with its two imposing square towers framing the façade. An imposing monument to Paris's religious history and heritage.

label: Tour Jean-sans-Peur
comment: Classified as a historical monument in 1884, this legendary building is now open to the public. Its spiral staircase, inspired by the Louvre, and its vaulted ceiling adorned with unique plant motifs, offer a breathtaking view of the Palace. Discover the bedroom of John the Fearless, immersing visitors in the life of a medieval ducal palace. Temporary exhibitions enrich this plunge into medieval Paris, offering a fascinating discovery of the capital and its ancient buildings.

label: Mobicity au BHV Marais
comment: Discover Solex, Matra and Easybike electric bikes near BHV Marais. Find folding, lightweight and comfortable models with a range of accessories on 140 m². Ideal for the city, whether you're an urbanite or a fan of soft mobility. Take advantage of our team's advice to choose your ideal model. Come and discover our unique selection and the freedom of a quality electric bike. Visit our store for a unique shopping experience in Paris.

label: Parc Georges Brassens
comment: Parc Georges Brassens, named after the famous artist, is the perfect place to relax near Paris Expo Porte de Versailles. Its slopes, river, bridge, towering trees and statues make it an ideal place to recharge your batteries. Families and children can enjoy swings and pony rides. A must for a day out combining relaxation and outdoor culture. (261 characters)

label: Man'ouché
comment: Come and discover a delicious Lebanese snack for a quick and affordable gourmet break. Here, the bread for your sandwiches is carefully prepared in front of you, guaranteeing freshness and flavor. All you have to do is select your favorite filling for an explosion of flavors in your mouth. An authentic and tasty culinary experience not to be missed!

label: Retro Tour
comment: Discover Paris in a vintage sidecar with Retro Tour! From Montmartre to the Île de la Cité, explore the capital in a unique way. Admire the architecture and atmosphere day and night on organized tours. Share Retro Tour's values of originality and authenticity while discovering the unusual aspects of the City of Light. Opt for a romantic nighttime sidecar ride or explore Montmartre with our passionate team for an unforgettable human experience!

label: Maison du Jardinage
comment: La Maison du jardinage in Paris, founded in 1997, is a place of excellence in the heart of Bercy. Evolving with the seasons, it features plants, flowers, fruit and vegetables. Its documentation center is open to all, and specialists give weekly practical advice on caring for indoor plants, decorating windowsills, choosing new planting... Exhibitions and fun activities for younger visitors regularly enliven this authentic setting.

label: Spa Le Bristol by La Prairie
comment: The luxury palace Le Bristol, opened in 1925 near the Champs-Élysées, boasts a spa bathed in natural light. The Spa Le Bristol by La Prairie offers a wide range of treatments for total relaxation in a refined setting. Unique in Paris, La Prairie's range of facial treatments is available at Le Bristol, notably in the "Russian Room". After this wellness interlude, relax in the indoor garden accessible from the spa.

label: Parc de La Villette - Plein Air
comment: The Parc de la Villette, designed by Bernard Tschumi on former abattoirs, is the largest urban cultural park in Paris. Its 55 hectares, 35 of which are open-air, offer a harmonious blend of nature and contemporary architecture. Families and art lovers alike can enjoy the park's leisure areas, cultural spaces and theaters. Between the Cité des sciences, the Géode, the Zénith, the Musée de la Musique and the Philharmonie, culture has pride of place.

label: Église protestante unie de Pentemont Luxembourg
comment: Nestled in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, close to the Luxembourg Gardens, the Pentemont-Luxembourg Reformed Church is part of the Église Réformée de France. Designed by architect Valcourt, this modern church opened its doors in 1857, offering a serene place of worship in the heart of the capital. A building that attracts with its emblematic architecture and rich spiritual history.

label: Musée Yves Saint Laurent - Paris
comment: The Yves Saint Laurent museum, which opened on October 3, 2017, features a 450-square-meter tour highlighting the couturier's iconic creations. Housed in a Second Empire-style townhouse, this historic space traces 30 years of work by the designer's teams. With its period fitting rooms, over 5,000 prototype dresses and the Collections Studio, the museum offers a fascinating immersion into the world of Yves Saint Laurent for fashion enthusiasts.

comment: Discover the gardens and cemeteries of the Mairie de Paris by visiting the blog blogs.paris.fr/casepasseaujardin and the Facebook page www.facebook.com/Paris.Jardins.Environnement. All the information you need to organize your walks and discover the capital's most emblematic sites. A must for lovers of nature and Parisian history.

label: ACCORD Langues
comment: Founded in 1988, ACCORD is a recognized school for teaching French to foreigners, close to the most emblematic sites in Paris. Awarded the "Qualité FLE" label and approved for continuing education, it is located between the Champs de Mars and the Eiffel Tower. With more than 15 courses for adults, language stays in summer and packages for school groups all year round, the school offers true immersion in the French language and culture. Accommodation options range from host families to hotels. An enriching experience in Paris.

label: Le Café du Commerce
comment: Hidden since 1920 in the very quiet 15th arrondissement, the Café du Commerce is located on three floors around an interior patio. This Art Deco brasserie is bathed in light thanks to a superb sliding glass roof. The traditional brasserie cuisine is prepared with products from small producers.

label: Kok Ping
comment: Kok Ping is a renowned Asian restaurant offering typical Chinese and Vietnamese dishes. The menu features tasty dim sum, crispy Peking duck, shrimp ravioli and delicious Phuket kebabs. Nestled close to the Champs-Élysées avenue, on the prestigious rue Balzac, this establishment is a choice address for lovers of refined Asian gastronomy.

label: Cinéma Le Balzac
comment: Close to the Champs-Élysées, the Balzac is a renowned Parisian cinema dedicated to art house films. Opened in 1935, it is a delight for film buffs. In addition to the usual screenings, there are original events such as opera evenings, ballets on the screen and the famous "Pochette surprise du dimanche matin". Saturday evenings are also filled with concerts at this not-to-be-missed cultural venue in Paris.

label: Vedettes du pont Neuf
comment: Discover the treasures of Paris with Les Vedettes du Pont Neuf cultural cruises on the Seine. In French and English, discover emblematic monuments such as the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre. Embark on a romantic one-hour cruise from the Pont Neuf, aboard panoramic boats. A guaranteed change of scenery, day or night. Departures every 30 minutes, all year round. An unforgettable experience in the heart of the City of Light!

label: Cirque Phénix
comment: Circus Phénix, one of the biggest in the world with 5,500 seats, offers optimal visibility to all its spectators thanks to its lack of internal structure. With no animals, this spectacular circus offers high-flying acts that have delighted spectators throughout its 20 years of existence, which will be celebrated in 2019! An unforgettable experience for the whole family.

label: Square Jean Perrin
comment: Located next to the Galeries Nationales du Grand Palais, Square Jean Perrin is a haven of peace close to the Jardin de la Nouvelle-France. This French-style garden, emblematic of the capital, offers a relaxing space with a magnificent central pool surrounded by greenery. Parisians gather here to enjoy the fine weather. A place dedicated to Jean Perrin, winner of the Nobel Prize for Physics in 1926, chemist and politician.

comment: Discover a boutique full of choice and bargains! Dive into the world of fashion for the whole family, with brand-name clothing for women, men and children. Find your style at mini prices in this sale store, where the quality and diversity of items will satisfy all tastes. There's something for every member of the family, at very attractive prices. The perfect place to renew your wardrobe without breaking the bank!

label: Médiathèque Hélène Berr
comment: The Hélène Berr media library, commonly known as the Picpus library, is located in the 12th arrondissement of Paris. Its 3 sections are packed with thousands of books: the adult section, the music section with CDs and sheet music, and the youth section. In addition, 32 multimedia workstations are available to users. A wealth of knowledge and entertainment to discover in a welcoming, modern setting.

label: Menard Institute Paris
comment: Located near the Opéra, this institute offers exceptional facial and body treatments. Specializing in shiatsu techniques, double cleansing and the green tea ritual, Ménard perfectly embodies Japanese tradition. In a soothing, uncluttered setting, skin is sublimated, massages provide deep relaxation and well-being is incomparable. A true parenthesis of gentleness and relaxation.

At weekends, let yourself be surprised by the 250 varieties of plants scattered around this secret spot. Ideal for teaching children (and yourself) about plant diversity and escaping to the heart of Paris.

label: La Flûte de Pan
comment: Founded in the 19th century, La Flûte de Pan is a must for music lovers. With 3 stores in Paris's music district, it offers a wide selection of sheet music, teaching aids and instrument accessories. It's a veritable sanctuary for all music lovers. What's more, an online store service is also available for music lovers the world over.

label: Harry's New York bar
comment: Located near the Palais Garnier, this cocktail bar is an institution in the Opéra district, founded in 1911 by an American fleeing Prohibition. It's Europe's oldest cocktail bar, with a typically New York atmosphere. The menu offers a wide variety of cocktails, beers and whiskies served by bartenders in white jackets. In the evening, a convivial atmosphere reigns with a piano bar in the basement. A historic and authentic address for a unique experience in Paris.

label: Cercle Suédois
comment: Le Cercle Suédois, located near the Tuileries Gardens and Place de la Concorde, houses a restaurant serving Swedish and French cuisine. Above all, it promotes Swedish culture through a variety of events. Every Wednesday, a Jazz evening with Swedish buffet delights music lovers and authentic flavors.

label: Éternelle Notre-Dame
comment: Discover Notre-Dame Cathedral in virtual reality with Éternelle Notre-Dame. Explore this architectural gem in a small group, equipped with a backpack and VR headset. Accompanied by a specialist guide, immerse yourself in the fascinating story of the construction and restoration of this iconic monument. Produced by Amaclio Productions and Orange, this 45-minute immersive experience transports you to the heart of Notre-Dame's majesty. Participate in the preservation of this world heritage treasure by supporting its restoration. Don't miss this unique expedition!

label: Vincennes Hippodrome de Paris
comment: The Paris-Vincennes racecourse, "the temple of trotting", in the Bois de Vincennes since 1863, attracts enthusiasts with its 2,000m track and capacity for 40,000 spectators. France's most prestigious races and world-class equestrian events, such as the Grand Prix d'Amérique, are held here. Modern and convivial, it offers 150 boxes, 3 catering areas, a bar, a 3,000m² hall and a 160m² giant screen. A must for horse racing fans.

label: Jardin naturel - Pierre-Emmanuel
comment: Inaugurated in 1995, this 6,300 m² garden showcases the wild flora of Paris in days gone by. A pond, an undergrowth and a meadow offer refuge to insects and birds. The Mairie de Paris doesn't do the watering or mowing, leaving nature to manage plant growth and protect wildlife. A neighbor of Père-Lachaise, this square offers educational workshops on biodiversity. The preservation of nature is here an educational spectacle for all.
description: Inaugurated in 1995, this 6,300 m² garden showcases the wild flora of Paris in days gone by. A pond, an undergrowth and a meadow offer refuge to insects and birds. The Mairie de Paris doesn't do the watering or mowing, leaving nature to manage plant growth and protect wildlife. A neighbor of Père-Lachaise, this square offers educational workshops on biodiversity. The preservation of nature is here an educational spectacle for all.

label: Institut des Cultures d’Islam
comment: The Institut des Cultures d'Islam, located in the 18th arrondissement of Paris, offers a variety of artistic events to showcase the cultures of Islam. Exhibitions, concerts, conferences and workshops are organized to foster intercultural dialogue. As a creative and exhibition space, the ICI supports artists inspired by these cultures. With two buildings and a charming inner courtyard, ICI offers a pleasant and dynamic setting for visitors and artists alike.

additional_information: ['Open Tuesday to Sunday, 11am to 7pm. Open Fridays from 4pm to 8pm.']

label: Montblanc
comment: Since 1906, Montblanc has embodied excellence with its emblem, the white star. Thanks to its prestigious writing instruments, such as the famous Meisterstück fountain pen, the brand has made history. Montblanc has successfully expanded to include collections of fine jewelry, watches, leather goods and fragrances. It also stands out for its limited editions, highly prized by luxury connoisseurs.

label: Musée des moulages de l'hôpital Saint-Louis
comment: This unique collection of almost 5,000 medical wax casts is a veritable treasure trove for medical learning and the history of dermatology since the 19th century. These casts offer a precise and detailed overview of the various skin pathologies, making a major contribution to the understanding and evolution of this medical discipline. A true visual immersion in the world of dermatology through the ages.

label: Épicure
comment: The renowned Épicure restaurant, in the prestigious Parisian Palace du Bristol, shines its star in the gastronomic guides. Chef Eric Fréchon delights food lovers with his delicious dishes. In a luxurious setting, the restaurant overlooks a delightful garden, ideal for relaxing in the heart of the city. From dawn to dusk, Épicure promises an unforgettable culinary experience.

label: Visite du quartier Javel "Avec Les Yeux de Julie"
comment: Discover the 15th arrondissement of Paris in a unique way with "Avec les Yeux de Julie". Julie, a passionate resident of Javel for the past 10 years, takes you on a cultural stroll far from the tourist trails. Immerse yourself in an unusual and authentic Paris, full of surprises and good humor. Let yourself be guided and explore the capital in an original way with Julie.

label: Palais de l’Élysée
comment: The Palais de l'Élysée in Paris, formerly owned by the Marquise de Pompadour, was renamed in 1797. Transformed over time, it even hosted popular balls under the Duchesse de Bourbon. Today, it houses the headquarters of the French President at 55 rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré. A true architectural gem, with its salons, library, dining room and garden, the Palais de l'Élysée is a must-see during the European Heritage Days.

label: Salle Pleyel
comment: Located near the Arc de Triomphe in the 8th arrondissement, the Salle Pleyel, built in 1927, is a prestigious venue dedicated to music and events. With its exceptional acoustics and elegant design, it attracts numerous artists. A versatile venue, it can host concerts, conferences, fashion shows and private parties. The Salle Pleyel offers a unique experience to every visitor, thanks to its modern facilities and its adaptability to all types of events.

label: Petit Palais - Musée des Beaux-Arts de la ville de Paris
comment: The Petit Palais, between the Seine and the Champs-Élysées, is an architectural gem designed by Charles Girault for the 1900 Universal Exhibition. It became the Musée des Beaux-Arts de la Ville de Paris in 1902, and boasts an extensive art collection from Antiquity to the early 20th century. Its peaceful interior garden is ideal for a break during your visit.

label: Les Fleurs
comment: Discover Les Fleurs, a veritable paradise for lovers of designer jewelry and accessories. In addition to Lucie's magnificent creations, this concept store is packed with over two hundred brands, including Cocobohême, Adolie Day and La Tonkinoise in Paris. An invitation to browse for unique and original pieces.

label: Le Coq Rico
comment: In a lively neighborhood, this bistro attracts gourmets in search of traditional, quality flavors. The poulard, guinea fowl and roast chicken are delicious, as are the candied gizzards, simmered eggs and homemade broths. Renowned for its freshness and expertise, this restaurant offers authentic, refined cuisine in a friendly atmosphere. Come and enjoy a unique culinary experience at the "bistrot des belles volailles".

label: Square de la Roquette
comment: Square de la Roquette, also known as Square Marcel Rajman, lies in the immediate vicinity of the famous Père-Lachaise cemetery. Enjoy a pleasant stroll through the flower beds, admire the cascading fountain, relax under the palm trees and enjoy the view from the belvedere. A true haven of peace in the heart of the city.

label: Désordre Urbain
comment: Some fifty talented designers contribute to this pretty boutique, offering a variety of fashion accessories, home decor and jewelry. Between refinement, flowers, baroque and romanticism, the treasures to be found in this boutique come in limited series or unique pieces. A veritable organized "mess" that will delight lovers of creativity and originality.

label: Copenhague
comment: Located on the 1st floor of the Maison du Danemark on the Champs-Élysées, the Copenhagen restaurant embodies elegance and intimacy. Designed by the duo Stine Gam and Enrico Fratesi, the place exudes a serene Nordic atmosphere. Chef Andreas Møller treats guests to a signature tasting menu, accompanied by wines. Inspired by the New Nordic movement, Møller combines pleasure and authenticity, creatively sublimating products.

Thanks to our interactive methods, you'll make rapid progress, whatever your level. Whether you're a beginner or an expert, our team will guide you efficiently. Payments by bank transfer accepted. Join us for an enriching learning experience!

comment: Café Campana transports us into an imaginary world where the colors of the sea and coral, chosen by the eponymous designers, permeate the space. Modern and soothing, it offers a welcome break after a visit to the Musée d'Orsay's Impressionist gallery. A unique atmosphere in which to unwind in complete serenity.

label: Ossek Garden
comment: Located near Place de la République, Ossek Garden offers a gustatory voyage to Korea. Its authentic, flavorful cuisine promises to satisfy all your culinary desires. Delicious exotic dishes to awaken your senses. A not-to-be-missed culinary experience for lovers of Korean gastronomy or for the curious in search of new discoveries. Ossek Garden, a must for a gastronomic experience with a change of scenery.

label: À La Folie Théâtre
comment: In Paris's 11th arrondissement, you'll find the dynamic À la Folie Théâtre, offering interactive shows for toddlers from age 1 and for all ages. Classic plays, contemporary creations, comedies and original performances are all on offer. Theater courses are available all year round, with workshops during the school vacations. Rental available for private events. À la Folie Théâtre: a magical place to create dreams and memories.

label: HéDONIE
comment: Specialist in organic and natural food, HéDONIE offers its customers fresh seasonal products and groceries: breads and pastries (including gluten-free), organically grown fruits and vegetables, dairy products and frozen foods, but also teas and coffees, jams, savoury products, biodynamic wines and champagnes... The shop organizes tastings and makes gift sets.

label: Le WorkshoW
comment: WorkShoW, whose motto is "Eat, Drink & Socialize", is a hybrid of bar-club, bistro, restaurant and concept store. Its warm, friendly atmosphere is enhanced by a decor featuring vintage furniture and unusual accessories. Thursday evenings are animated by DJs, adding a festive touch to the nights of this atypical place.
