label: L’École des Arts Joailliers
comment: Founded in 2012, the École des Arts Joailliers offers training in the field of jewelry accessible to the general public. Located on Place Vendôme, this institution came into being with the support of the House of Van Cleef & Arpels. Its aim is to demystify this captivating world, offering everyone the chance to discover the world of jewelry. Open to all those with a passion for the art of jewelry, the school is also aimed at aesthetes in search of knowledge.

label: Chez Nénesse
comment: Nestled on a lively street, this charming bistro attracts passers-by with its traditional recipes. The beautifully laid tables and colorful tablecloths add a touch of authenticity. In the evening, it becomes an elegant restaurant where you can enjoy refined dishes in an intimate atmosphere. Lovers of rustic cuisine will be won over by the quality of the dishes and the attention paid to ingredients. An address not to be missed for a unique and memorable culinary experience.

label: Sun Limited
comment: In the heart of Paris, Sun Limited guarantees you perfect skin all year round or optimal preparation for tanning. Enjoy 20 solariums open until 10pm, competitive rates and unlimited packages. A smile bar is available for teeth whitening sessions. Relax and enhance your beauty at Sun Limited with iPads and self-service massage chairs.

comment: La Rôtisserie d?Argent, a not-to-be-missed bistro in the Vème arrondissement, captivates with its warm decor, renowned rotisserie and emblematic dishes. Explore the Chef's revisited creations: world champion ?uf mayonnaise, roast duck, pike quenelles... As for wine, an exceptional selection awaits you to accompany your dishes. In this friendly, generous setting, gastronomy takes center stage, just a stone's throw from Notre-Dame.

label: Les Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann
comment: For over 100 years, Galeries Lafayette has offered a luxury and accessible shopping experience, featuring fashion, beauty and prestigious brands. A new space is dedicated to well-being, beauty and sport, while the Gourmet building offers a gastronomic experience with a floor dedicated to street food. Original activities such as fashion shows, culinary workshops and private tours are also on offer. An unforgettable experience awaits you at Galeries Lafayette.

comment: Discover art accessible to all in this concept store located in the heart of a shopping center. You'll find a refined and original selection of artworks, reproductions, merchandising, decorative objects and fashion accessories at affordable prices. A unique opportunity to discover and acquire unique and trendy pieces without breaking the bank. Let yourself be seduced by the diversity and creativity of these artistic creations, accessible to all.

label: Lalique
comment: Lalique, renowned for its crystal works, has established itself as a world-renowned brand thanks to the variety, excellence and refinement of its collections. From tableware to decorative pieces, Lalique sublimates crystal in jewelry, leather goods, perfumes and watches. A diversity of objects that testifies to the brand's unrivalled excellence and expertise.

label: Bercy Village
comment: A former Bercy warehouse, the Cour Saint-Emilion blends a variety of materials in its architecture. Famous for its wine market, it now offers a 26,000 m² living space with stores, restaurants, leisure activities and a variety of events, including the Science Expériences museum. Free activities such as tours, concerts and workshops are offered regularly. Bercy Village, with its 3,000-space parking lot, is open from 10 a.m. to 2 a.m. every day, making it a must-see.

label: Le Bal de la rue Blomet
comment: Founded in 1924 at the heart of the Roaring Twenties, the Bal de la rue Blomet combined music and politics. This cabaret welcomed Joséphine Baker, Man Ray, Ernest Hemingway, Sidney Bechet, Sartre and Camus. Located in Montparnasse, it offers musical comedy, cabaret, jazz and classical music, with a restaurant, La Table du Bal. A legendary address where art and gastronomy come together perfectly.

label: La Place - Centre Culturel Hip Hop
comment: La Place, the first cultural center dedicated to hip-hop, brings together all the disciplines of this movement in a single venue. Its original programming highlights five essential pillars - dance, rap, deejaying, beatboxing and graffiti - offering total immersion in the artistic diversity of hip-hop. With La Coursive, the warm welcome and the bar, enjoy an exceptional view of the Canopée des Halles, the Jardin des Halles and the Bourse du Commerce - Pinault Collection.

label: Cité des sciences et de l'industrie
comment: Discover the Cité des Sciences et de l'Industrie, the largest landscaped park in Paris. The secrets of science, unusual experiments and the infinite possibilities of images await you. Explore the thousand pleasures of discovery, for young and old alike. Two interactive exhibits allow children aged 2 to 7 and 5 to 12 to learn while having fun. Build, play and discover scientific concepts. Parents too will be captivated by this fascinating place!

label: Centre sportif Paul Faber
comment: Located between Porte Maillot and Porte de Champerret, the Paul Faber sports center boasts a 400-meter athletics track, ideal for hosting a variety of sporting events. Its strategic location makes it a popular venue for running enthusiasts and athletes seeking quality training. With its modern facilities and dynamic atmosphere, the Paul Faber sports center is a real asset for outdoor sports in the capital.

label: Élysée Montmartre
comment: Since 1807, the Élysée Montmartre, the jewel in the crown of the Butte Montmartre, has been lighting up Parisian nights. The venue, birthplace of the French cancan, boasts majestic Gustave Eiffel architecture. This legendary venue offers an eclectic and demanding musical program, ranging from rock to electro to French chanson. A must for music lovers in search of discovery and emotion.

label: L'Embuscade - Rhumerie du Cap Vert
comment: Every Saturday evening, don't miss l'Embuscade - Rhumerie du Cap Vert for a unique sensory experience: spellbinding concerts, cuisine with a thousand flavors, traditional Cape Verdean dishes and exotic cocktails. In this lively restaurant, let yourself be carried away by the magic of music and spices for an unforgettable evening.

label: Au Lapin Agile
comment: Le Lapin Agile in Montmartre keeps the tradition of French chanson alive. Every evening, this historic cabaret offers an authentic musical journey, without artifice. Music and vocals mingle in a natural atmosphere, with the audience taking an active part, creating a convivial atmosphere. New talents also get their chance, for an experience close to the evenings of yesteryear. Come and discover this unique, charming venue, ideal for a romantic rendezvous.

label: Parc André Citroën
comment: The Parc André Citroën, opened in 1992 on the site of the former Citroën factory in Paris, is one of the capital's newest parks. Designed by renowned landscape architects, it offers magnificent views over the Seine. Divided into three parts - Jardin Blanc, Jardin Noir and Parc Central - it is home to a wide variety of exotic trees and rare plants. Leisure facilities include playgrounds, table tennis, children's games and a tethered balloon up to 150 meters high.

label: Marché couvert La Chapelle
comment: This food market is nestled in a charming Baltard-style pavilion. Open six days a week, it's brimming with gourmet treasures: caterers, tearooms, creameries, florists, fruit and vegetables... A veritable concentration of flavors and colors to tantalize the taste buds and delight the eyes. A warm and friendly place to discover and taste fresh, quality products.

label: Fondation Louis Vuitton
comment: The Fondation Louis Vuitton, opened in 2014 in the Bois de Boulogne near the Jardin d'Acclimatation, exhibits contemporary art from the 20th and 21st centuries. Designed by Frank Gehry, its unique and bold glass design creates a luminous and exceptional edifice. Visitors can admire art treasures while enjoying breathtaking views from the terraces of this remarkable site.

label: Chai 33

With its restaurant, historic 300-wine cellar, bistro, bar, wine store and terraces, Chai 33 offers a unique experience. Its cuisine blends French tradition and world flavors to satisfy every palate. A place steeped in history that reinvents wine tasting.

A perfect place to share gourmet moments in a convivial atmosphere.

label: Le Balajo
comment: Since 1935, rue de Lappe, close to Bastille, has been home to Balajo, one of Paris's leading nightclubs. This legendary club offers a variety of evenings, from rock to salsa, in a period ballroom decor. Enthusiastic dancers keep the night alive until the early hours. A tea dance is also organized every Sunday and Monday. Le Balajo is a must for Parisian party-goers looking for a memorable experience.

label: Théâtre des Nouveautés
comment: The Théâtre des Nouveautés, located in the heart of Paris in the Grands Boulevards district, is a 600-seat Italian-style theater. A historic landmark for vaudeville and comedy, it continues to offer shows featuring the genre's most talented authors. A must-see experience for lovers of quality entertainment in Paris.

label: Yasube
comment: Rue Sainte-Anne is a benchmark for Japanese restaurants, and Yasube is a fine example. Enjoy traditional, authentic cuisine in a zen, uncluttered setting. Bento, tempura, sushi, grilled meats, brochettes... All the must-haves of Japanese gastronomy. And for an even more exotic experience, there's nothing like settling down comfortably on Japanese-style tatami mats for a memorable dinner!

comment: Nocibé, a multi-brand perfumery, has 12 stores in Paris with well-known brands. Some stores (e.g. avenue du Maine) offer beauty salons, Clarins treatments, parapharmacy and organic corners. Cosy boutiques offering a wide range of products for everyone. Advantageous loyalty program for discounts and benefits throughout France. A benchmark in beauty and well-being.

label: Passage des Panoramas
comment: The Passage des Panoramas, Paris's first covered passageway, has been attracting the curious since 1799. Situated between the Bourse and the Grands Boulevards, this historic site blends the charm of yesteryear with commercial activity. Historic stores, listed as historical monuments, retrace the evolution of the capital. Shops, craftsmen and collectors rub shoulders over 133 meters. The period decorations of chocolatier Marquis, reminiscent of the 18th century, add to the charm. The Théâtre des Variétés, open since 1807, enlivens this famous passageway.

Comprising some 15 stalls (cheese, butchery, bakery, patisserie, fishmonger's, etc.), this medium-sized market offers a wide variety of fresh, quality produce. A pleasant place to shop and discover local flavors. A must for lovers of good food and local produce.

label: La Mère Catherine
comment: Founded in 1793 on the Place du Tertre, the restaurant La Mère Catherine is steeped in history. It was an important meeting place during the Revolution, where the word "bistro" was born thanks to the Cossacks. Ideally located in Montmartre, near the Sacré C?ur Basilica, it offers traditional French dishes and a fine selection of wines. A warm setting for savoring French cuisine in all its splendor.

label: BeMyLove
comment: Be my love in Paris offers unique services for couples who want to celebrate their love in the city of love. The program includes a tour of romantic sites, a proposal in front of a monument, champagne, macaroons and a photo session. The guide, who speaks French, English or Spanish, captures every moment. Three flexible formulas are available: half-day, full-day or two-day. A magical moment for two in Paris.

Close to the Seine and rue Saint-André-des-Arts, a unique experience. For film buffs, this is the place to be in Paris.

label: Cimetière du Père Lachaise
comment: Père Lachaise cemetery owes its name to François d?Aix de La Chaise, confessor to Louis XIV. It is the most prestigious necropolis in Paris, covering 44 hectares and 70,000 concessions. Its architecture blends English parkland and contemplation, with a diversity of funerary styles. Famous names such as Molière, Edith Piaf, Oscar Wilde and Jim Morrison are buried here. A stroll through its verdant alleys plunges you into French history and culture.

label: CGR Paris - Lilas
comment: The Étoile Lilas cinema, located between Paris and its suburbs, is a popular cultural venue. This 20 m-high cube spans the Paris ring road and offers a varied program of "Art et Essai" films. The 7 screens, accessible by elevator, offer optimum comfort. A vast 300m² terrace planted with trees extends the cinematic experience. And for those not in the mood for a film, the terrace is perfect for simply enjoying a good time in company.

label: Urban Challenge
comment: Want to discover Paris in a different way? Opt for an outdoor training session supervised by professionals (firefighters, military personnel, top athletes). An hour of intense sport that combines discovering the city and getting back into shape in emblematic locations. A unique experience that lets you explore the City of Lights in a whole new way!

label: Le 1807
comment: Le 1807, located in the Hôtel Napoléon, is an elegant bar with a Parisian flair. Open from morning to night, it welcomes a varied clientele for coffee, lunch, French tea or aperitifs. Its 1930s Art Deco decor is reminiscent of Napoleon, with a linear, symmetrical style. Brightness and discretion characterize this intimate terrace, ideal for observing Parisian life.

label: Conciergerie
comment: Immerse yourself in the history of the medieval royal palace through its Gothic rooms, remnants of the Conciergerie. The Salle des Gardes and the Salle des Gens d?armes, built under Philip the Fair, evoke the palace's glorious past. Transformed into a prison, this historic monument was the scene of the French Revolution, housing the revolutionary court and Marie-Antoinette. Listed as a UNESCO World Heritage Site, it offers an emotional immersion in an eventful past.

label: Parc de Bercy
comment: In the heart of Paris's 12th arrondissement, Parc de Bercy is a former industrial site transformed into a green space. It features a vineyard, rail tanker tracks and the Bercy Arena. Close to the Gare de Lyon, it's a popular spot for walkers all year round. The park is home to the Cinémathèque française, a romantic garden with lake and island, as well as the Maison du Lac and the Maison du Jardinage. Ideal for families, sports enthusiasts and those seeking tranquillity.

label: Galarie le Minotaure
comment: Discover an exceptional gallery highlighting the art of Eastern Europe and Russia, particularly from the first half of the 20th century. Considered one of the most significant spaces dedicated to Russian art in Paris, it offers a unique immersion in an often overlooked artistic wealth. A genuine invitation to explore and appreciate the diversity and creativity of these regions through authentic and fascinating works.

label: Temple de la Rédemption
comment: The Temple de la Rédemption, near Boulevard Haussmann, is an imposing neo-classical Lutheran building. It hosted the funeral of Baron Haussmann, underscoring its historical importance. The site attracts many visitors in search of emotion and history, preserving its charm over time. Its captivating history makes it a must-see for lovers of architecture and religious heritage.

label: Fondation Carla Sozzani
comment: Carla Sozzani, former editor of Italian Vogue and founder of the transalpine Elle, opens her Paris gallery in October 2019. In a former industrial building in the 18th arrondissement, this fashion and art icon offers a vibrant space blending design, fashion, architecture and photography. At the crossroads of creation and discovery, the Carla Sozzani Foundation showcases little-known artists, offering a unique place of expression in Paris.

label: Marché Monge
comment: The legendary Monge market, nestled in the heart of the Latin Quarter, has been delighting Parisians' taste buds since 1921. An exquisite variety of meats, fish, fresh fruit and vegetables, organic produce, mature cheeses, tasty wines and bright flowers are offered by some forty passionate traders. A not-to-be-missed gustatory experience in a warm, authentic setting.

Its refined setting and delicate cuisine reflect the Mediterranean influences that inspired the chef. What's more, affordable prices make this restaurant a must for an exceptional culinary experience in Paris.

label: Berluti
comment: Since its creation in 1895 by Alessandro Berluti, the eponymous house has seen four generations of bootmakers succeed one another. Known for the invention of the lace-up pump, Berluti continues to combine tradition and innovation. The brand continues to excel in crafting leather shoes of exceptional quality, combining ancestral know-how with contemporary creativity.

label: Jardin du Pré Catelan
comment: Nestled in the heart of the Bois de Boulogne, the Pré Catelan is a delightful botanical garden between the Lac Inférieur and the Parc de Bagatelle. Founded under the reign of Louis XIV, it is home to the dairy, restaurant and theater de verdure of the Shakespeare garden. Perfect for a romantic getaway, it's brimming with majestic trees ideal for strolling. Accessible by bus (line 244), a stroll through the Pré Catelan is an invitation to relax and marvel.

An ideal place to recharge your batteries and enjoy a unique wellness experience.

An ideal choice for fans of ethical and natural fashion.

label: Le bar-bibliothèque du Saint James Paris
comment: Located near the Bois de Boulogne, the library-bar of the Saint James Paris hotel offers calm and relaxation in a neo-classical atmosphere reminiscent of a London mansion. With its wood panelling, you can settle comfortably into a leather club chair to enjoy a whisky while admiring the 12,000-book library. The magnificent terrace allows you to enjoy a club sandwich while taking in this little corner of England in Paris. One of the capital's most welcoming hotel bars.

label: Les Potins de Paris
comment: Dive into little-known history with our guided tours of Les Potins de Paris! Follow the Marquise des Potins of the 18th century as she takes you behind the scenes of great historical moments. From Voltaire to the mysteries of the Sun King, to the incredible stratagems used to save drowning men, each anecdote will captivate you. An enriching and entertaining experience not to be missed! Visit the Potins de Paris website for more information.

label: Musée national de la Marine
comment: The Musée National de la Marine is reborn at the Palais de Chaillot in Paris after a six-year transformation. Discover nearly 900 restored maritime treasures on a unique immersive tour. Witnessing 250 years of naval history, this museum raises public awareness, particularly among young people, of current maritime issues. Embark on a journey of three themed "crossings" and four "ports of call" to explore its collection. An unforgettable maritime adventure awaits you in the heart of the capital.

comment: Since 1977, La Maison du Chocolat has been sharing its passion for creation and excellence. With boutiques across Paris, the company carefully selects the finest products for its ganaches, pralines and pastries. Known for its "haute-couture" creations exhibited at the Salon du Chocolat, La Maison du Chocolat surprises with unique works in chocolate: dresses, necklaces, Louis XVI chairs. A must for chocolate lovers and gourmet creatives.
description: Since 1977, La Maison du Chocolat has been sharing its passion for creation and excellence. With boutiques across Paris, the company carefully selects the finest products for its ganaches, pralines and pastries. Known for its "haute-couture" creations exhibited at the Salon du Chocolat, La Maison du Chocolat surprises with unique works in chocolate: dresses, necklaces, Louis XVI chairs. A must for chocolate lovers and gourmet creatives.

label: Église Sainte-Élisabeth de Hongrie
comment: The Church of St. Elizabeth of Hungary, built in 1646 in the picturesque Marais district of Paris, is brimming with artistic treasures. Dating from the 19th century, its paintings and frescoes bear witness to a rich artistic past. It also houses a series of one hundred 17th-century woodcarvings and exceptional stained-glass windows from the 1830s. In addition, the presence of two organs makes it an ideal venue for spellbinding concerts.

label: Magic Ways
comment: Magic Ways offers excursions from Paris and Disneyland® Paris, including round-trip transportation and entrance tickets. For Disneyland® Paris visitors, opt for our "Paris Essentials" day trip with round-trip transportation from Disney® hotels and a visit to "Paris from the Eiffel Tower to Notre-Dame". Discover royal history with our excursion from Paris to the Château de Versailles. Choose Magic Ways for unique and unforgettable experiences!

label: La Maison du Zéro Déchet
comment: The Maison du Zéro Déchet launched by Zero Waste France in 2017 is a convivial space committed to zero waste. With a store offering alternatives, a free library and an associative café, it encourages action. Its full program includes conferences, roundtables, screenings-debates, practical workshops and training to accompany everyone towards an environmentally-friendly lifestyle.

label: Notre-Dame de la Croix de Ménilmontant
comment: Dominating the Ménilmontant district, the Notre-Dame-de-la-Croix church, built between 1863 and 1880, attracts visitors with its imposing size and panoramic location. Measuring 87 metres in length, it is famous for its 70-metre-high tower and monumental 49-step staircase. Its architectural style is an elegant blend of neo-Romanesque and neo-Gothic elements. Inside, you'll discover veritable artistic and religious treasures, including an organ by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll and 19th-century paintings. A visit steeped in emotion and history.

label: La REcyclerie
comment: La REcyclerie, a former Ornano station near the Marché aux Puces at Porte Saint-Ouen, combines conviviality and ecology. Canteen, grocery store, do-it-yourself shop all come together in this unusual place. A refreshment bar, where you can enjoy drinks and simple dishes, on old rails overgrown with vegetation. Need repairs? Experts and DIY courses available. And don't forget to bring your own wine and organic produce. An eco-responsible getaway to discover!

label: Cercle Delacre
comment: Located on avenue Georges V, Institut Marc Delacre is a place dedicated to men's beauty, offering a wide range of services including back and eye treatments, tanning, waxing and tinting. Its exclusive Asie-Energie massage combines shiatsu, Thai massage and Chinese belly massage, for a unique experience of well-being. The perfect place to pamper yourself in an atmosphere of luxury and relaxation.

label: Chantal Thomass
comment: Chantal Thomass sublimates the female body with lingerie that's both sensual and impertinent. With her inimitable style, her boutique-boudoir is brimming with corsets, guêpières and other chic finery that will delight lovers of refined lingerie. A must for those in search of elegance and charm.

label: Le Little
comment: Ideally located near Place de la République, Le Little is a vintage establishment popular with young Parisians, both quiet by day and lively by night. With its frenzied DJ sets, it attracts a clientele in search of festivity and conviviality. Its retro decor and warm ambience make it a must for evenings out with friends. Whether you want to enjoy a drink on the terrace or dance the night away, this atypical venue is sure to please party-goers and people-watchers alike.

label: Spa Mont Kailash
comment: The Spa Mont Kailash, one of the capital's largest Zen temples, offers 500 m² of well-being near the Opera House. Treatments and services inspired by Tibetan rituals are offered, as well as a yoga and meditation experience. For a more intimate atmosphere, another spa is available at 19 rue Pierre Leroux, in the 7th arrondissement.

label: Kitchen
comment: Enjoy healthy and tasty preparations at Kitchen, a friendly vegetarian canteen. On the menu: smoothies, soups, salads and dishes made with fresh, high-quality vegetables. All at affordable prices. Enjoy tasty, organic food without breaking the bank. An ideal address for lovers of healthy, balanced cuisine.

label: Meert
comment: The reputation of Lille-based chocolatier, patissier and confectioner Meert extends as far as Paris, where a boutique has been set up in the Saint-Germain-des-Prés district. Enthusiasts delight in the famous vanilla waffle, emblematic of the house. A must for gourmets in search of refined sweets.

label: La Balle au Bond
comment: Located on the Left Bank, opposite the Louvre Museum and close to the Musée d'Orsay, the La Balle au Bond barge offers a wide range of cultural activities, including exhibitions, concerts and literary events. A café lounge open Tuesday to Saturday, with brunch at weekends. Its 120 m² terrace overlooks the Seine and the Louvre, ideal for cocktails or local produce. Check availability, as the barge is often privatized.

comment: This innovative and ethical boutique offers a collection of unique garments and accessories, veritable works of textile art. Created by talented young designers, these rare and natural pieces are handmade. An original selection that invites you to discover exceptional creations, combining creativity, quality and respect for the environment. An authentic shopping experience for fashion and craft lovers.

label: La Cigale
comment: La Cigale, a historic monument since 1981 and redesigned by Philippe Starck, welcomes renowned artists all year round. This historic venue, once a cabaret and then a cinema, is now a concert venue not to be missed. Its eclectic program mixes avant-garde artists and rockers, offering unique musical evenings.

label: La Main au Panier
comment: In the heart of the Saint-Victor district is La Main au Panier, a famous cabaret where Patrick Sébastien, Gérald Dahan, Pascal Bruner and Daniel Herzog got their start. Since 1962, spectators have been able to enjoy an exceptional dinner prepared by a renowned chef. Led by charismatic master of ceremonies Michel Forever, the evenings are filled with humor, song and even magic tricks, promising unforgettable entertainment.

label: Le Grand Restaurant Jean-François Piège
comment: In the heart of Paris's golden triangle, between the Madeleine and Concorde, Michelin-starred chef Jean-François Piège opened his establishment on September 10, 2015. Le Grand Restaurant, just a stone's throw from Rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré and the Champs-Élysées, offers refined gastronomy with 25 covers. In this showcase of creativity, the chef deploys all his talent with his famous Signatures creations and his Mijotés Modernes, a festival of flavors and elegance.

label: Ministère de l’économie, des finances et de la relance
comment: Discover the Ministry of Finance during the European Heritage Days to explore this imposing hive of activity above the river. Moved to Bercy between 1983 and 1989, it comprises three modern buildings, named Colbert, Vauban and Necker. With its two monumental 72-metre arches, a veritable gateway to the capital, the Ministry of Finance attracts visitors with its internal workings and remarkable architecture. Not to be missed, to appreciate all its splendor.

label: Bowling Mouffetard
comment: Discover a unique entertainment venue with 8 bowling lanes, lively bars, a variety of games, pool tables and a dynamic musical atmosphere. Perfect for a convivial evening out with friends or family. Come and enjoy a fun and festive experience in a warm and original setting!

label: Taxis parisiens - Préfecture de Police
comment: On its website, the Préfecture de Police highlights essential information about the cab trade in Paris. News, general information and frequently asked questions are covered to provide a clear and comprehensive overview of the profession. A rich and informative content for all those wishing to learn more about this key sector of Parisian urban life.

label: Centre de documentation du Mémorial de la Shoah
comment: The CDJC, founded by Isaac Schneersohn in 1943, is the originator of the Shoah Memorial, dedicated to the memory of the genocide of Jews in Europe. This museum, documentation center and place of remembrance gathers evidence of Jewish persecution during the war. The archived documents were used at the Nuremberg trials to demand justice.

label: Salon Dessange Elysées
comment: The Dessange salon is a true jewel, blending white, black and champagne in an elegant decor. At the heart of this space, a renowned hair and beauty salon rubs shoulders with a spa dedicated to hair health and overall beauty. From hair extensions to Foot Spa, everything is designed to offer a complete and refined beauty experience.

comment: Discover the art of gastronomy in a modern, chic setting. This palatial restaurant offers an exceptional culinary experience with Michelin-starred dishes and a selection of prestigious wines. Attentive, refined service completes this unique experience. An address not to be missed by lovers of fine dining.

label: Théâtre Darius Milhaud
comment: Located near the Parc de la Villette, the Théâtre Darius Milhaud offers a rich and varied program. Theater, music and children's shows are all on offer. In addition to these performances, the venue offers practical theater courses for adults and children. A cultural and artistic offering to suit all tastes and ages!

label: Brüning Ursula
comment: Discover Paris and the surrounding region with guided tours in several languages (French, German, English). Groups limited to 6 people for an intimate experience. A qualified tour guide offers coach tours of Paris, the Paris region, the Loire, Normandy and Champagne regions. Explore museums, exhibitions and historic monuments on exciting guided tours. Create customized tours with original themes such as the "Da Vinci Code" or the "scandals" at the Musée d'Orsay. A unique experience!

label: Grand Palais Immersif
comment: An exceptional city, Venice has thrived thanks to the sea. "Venice Revealed" takes a behind-the-scenes look at this city-state on the water, highlighting the flourishing trade shaped by the Grand Canal and its sumptuous palaces. As visitors explore the city, they will discover the mysteries behind the Venetian walls. A fascinating opportunity to unravel the secrets of Venice, a dream for history and art enthusiasts.

label: Le piano vache
comment: Le Piano Vache, famous in Paris for its timeless charm, is a vintage piano bar immortalized on screen in cult films such as "Le Péril jeune" and "Sex Boys". Its warm, quirky atmosphere, with its antique piano, original rooms, worn tables and lively decor, attracts a clientele in search of originality. In the evening, it's a festive and convivial place where good humor reigns, all at affordable prices. An authentic and joyful experience in the heart of Paris!

label: Scotch & Soda
comment: Founded in Amsterdam in 1985, Scotch & Soda offers collections for men, women (Maison Scotch) and boys (Scotch Shrunk). The new Scotch R'Belle line also allows little girls to dress in casual-fusion style. A brand that offers a variety of look possibilities for the whole family.

label: Studio 13/16
comment: Studio 13/16 at the Centre Pompidou is dedicated to teenagers aged 13 to 16. It offers workshops in music, video, graphic and digital arts. Led by professionals, these activities encourage creativity and artistic discovery. This dynamic space offers young people a stimulating introduction to a variety of disciplines.

label: Halle Georges Carpentier
comment: The Halle Carpentier, part of a sports complex, offers a range of facilities including a gymnasium, soccer pitches, rugby pitches and athletics fields. With bleachers for over 4,000 spectators, it offers comfortable accommodation. Practical, it offers catering, infirmary, press and meeting rooms. Every year, various national and international sporting events make it a must-see venue for sports enthusiasts.

label: Gare de l'Est
comment: Located in the 10th arrondissement, 10 minutes from the Gare du Nord, the Gare de l'Est welcomes 37 million visitors a year. Inaugurated in 1850 by Napoleon III, it is the oldest Parisian railway station, rich in history and architecture. Serving the east of France and international destinations, it offers a journey through time and space, as well as a varied offer of gastronomy, shopping and a rooftop overlooking Paris. Don't miss the "xxx" bunker.

label: Ogoura
comment: Located not far from the Opéra, in the bustling theater district, Ogoura is a welcoming sushi bar steeped in tranquility. It offers a soothing, friendly atmosphere, perfect for enjoying exquisite sushi in the most pleasant of surroundings. It's a haven from the hustle and bustle of the city, where you can relax and enjoy in complete tranquillity. Come and experience serenity amidst the hustle and bustle of the city.

label: La Fée maraboutée
comment: This talented fashion designer excels in designing unique collections, combining contemporary elegance with refined feminine touches. Each piece is the result of meticulous work to sublimate the silhouette. She skilfully transforms her creations into timeless, modern works of art. Her dressing room is brimming with sophisticated pieces, perfect for any season. Her exceptional craftsmanship astonishes and delights her public with unique and magnificent creations.

label: La Cave du 38Riv'
comment: Paris's emblematic Marais district is home to hidden treasures such as the Cave du 38RIV? This intimate club offers jazz, baroque and classical concerts, theater, entertainment and chansonniers. It can also be booked for private events. With bar service provided 30 minutes before each concert, this atypical venue blends culture and conviviality to perfection. A must-see address for fans of original artistic discoveries.

label: Galerie Openspace
comment: Since 2012, Openspace gallery has been a mecca for contemporary urban art in Paris. Created by Samantha Longhi and Nicolas Chenus, it offers 240 m² of exhibition space between Bastille and République. From collages to stencils, canvases to sculptures, figurative to abstract, the works on display reflect the diversity and evolution of urban art. It's a must-see for art lovers in search of varied and inspiring discoveries.

label: Le Café des Chats
comment: Café des Chats near Bastille is a must for feline fans. With its warm atmosphere and free-roaming cats, it's a soothing place for a coffee break. Customers can enjoy their drink surrounded by these adorable furballs who love to cuddle. This original concept is especially appealing to children, who can discover the world of cats in a friendly, secure setting. A unique experience for animal lovers.

label: Boutique Bourjois
comment: Bourjois, the famous make-up, perfume and cosmetics brand, has opened its first boutique in Paris, Passage du Havre. It features the entire Bourjois range, as well as an "open bar varnish" area for express manicures and a "beauty room" offering waxing, manicure and make-up services. A must for beauty lovers looking for quality products and personalized service.

label: Virtus
comment: This restaurant in the heart of the city offers Mediterranean cuisine in a chic setting. Its Art Deco decor creates a calm atmosphere, perfect for dinners with friends. The chef's authentic flavors transport you to the heart of the Mediterranean, with fresh fish, grilled vegetables and typical dishes. The varied menu, accompanied by a selection of wines, is sure to satisfy all your expectations. A must for a gourmet getaway in a warm and friendly atmosphere.

label: L'Olympia Bruno Coquatrix
comment: The Olympia, between the Opéra and the Madeleine, has been a temple to music since 1893. A place of artistic excellence, it has seen the likes of La Goulue, Piaf, the Rolling Stones and Madonna. Stars and humor rub shoulders, with comedy shows. Since April 2019, the original billiard room has been refurbished for stand-up evenings, bringing the Olympia into the modern age.

label: Cimetière de Passy
comment: Located in Paris, this small necropolis offers a magnificent view of the Seine, the Palais de Chaillot and the Eiffel Tower. The extravagant, often monumental tombs bear witness to the splendor of 19th-century Parisian aristocrats, financiers, industrialists and politicians. Artistic figures such as Édouard Manet, Tristan Bernard and Claude Debussy can also be found here The site, adorned with century-old chestnut trees, exudes a peaceful atmosphere conducive to contemplation.
description: Located in Paris, this small necropolis offers a magnificent view of the Seine, the Palais de Chaillot and the Eiffel Tower. The extravagant, often monumental tombs bear witness to the splendor of 19th-century Parisian aristocrats, financiers, industrialists and politicians. Artistic figures such as Édouard Manet, Tristan Bernard and Claude Debussy can also be found here The site, adorned with century-old chestnut trees, exudes a peaceful atmosphere conducive to contemplation.
additional_information: ['Early November to mid-March: Monday-Friday, 8am-5:30pm; Saturday, 8:30am-5:30pm; Sunday and holidays, 9am-5:30pm.']

label: L'éclair de génie - La Fabrique
comment: Christophe Adam, renowned pastry chef, revisits French pastry classics with talent. Known for his gourmet creations and expertise in chocolate truffles, he offers revisited sweets in his factory near the Palais Brongniart, between the Palais-Royal and the Grands Boulevards. His delicious creations are also available in several Parisian boutiques.

label: Jovoy Paris
comment: Halfway between Place Vendôme and the Tuileries Gardens, this 175 m² concept store is a veritable olfactory treasure trove. It houses an exclusive selection of rare fragrances, often never before seen in Paris, from some sixty renowned brands such as Clive Christian and Heeley Parfums. In addition to this exceptional collection, a variety of accessories complete this unique sensory experience.

label: Printemps du Goût
comment: Jules Jaluzot founded the Printemps department store to offer fresh, original products in tune with the season. Today, at Printemps Haussmann, this ambition continues. Le Printemps du Goût offers a 900m² selection of delicacies, with French specialties such as chocolates, truffles, caviar and smoked salmon, as well as renowned brands such as Reine Mer, Supernature, Regain, Laurent Dubois and Lomi. A true ode to the flavors of the French terroir, to the delight of customers.

label: Librairie Ulysse
comment: Established on the Île Saint-Louis since 1971, the Ulysse bookshop is a temple dedicated to travel. Managed by a passionate, globe-trotting bookseller, it offers a wide selection of over 20,000 works, including new and old books, maps, magazines and other literary treasures. A true haven for lovers of escape and discovery.

label: Le Pain Quotidien – Marais
comment: Founded in Brussels in 1990, Le Pain Quotidien embodies authenticity, quality, simplicity and conviviality. With its hand-kneaded organic wheat bread and fresh, seasonal ingredients, this restaurant advocates a healthy, gourmet lifestyle. Le Pain Quotidien Marais, nestled in the heart of the Marais district, offers a warm, historic setting. Its shaded terrace and basement dining room make it an ideal place to enjoy gourmet moments in complete conviviality.

label: Jardin des Pâtes
comment: Le Jardin des Pâtes is located opposite the Jardin des Plantes, in the 5th arrondissement of Paris. This pasta-specialized eatery has a friendly atmosphere, with exposed beams, a small terrace and plenty of natural light. Pasta, made from whole-grain organic cereals, comes in all shapes and sizes. The wine and dessert list is also top-notch. Perfect for a family outing - kids love pasta! Not to be missed.

label: Roller parc du square du Serment de Kouffra
comment: Located in the 14th arrondissement, the roller park in the Square du Serment de Kouffra offers skaters an ideal place to express themselves. With its 570 m² track, skaters of all ages can engage in jumps, slalom and other tricks. Access to the site is totally free, open to all, and offers a pleasant setting in the heart of a verdant park.

label: Abbaye royale du Val-de-Grâce et musée du Service de santé des armées
comment: Built in the 17th century by François Mansart, the church and convent of Val-de-Grâce are historic jewels donated by Queen Anne of Austria for the birth of Louis XIV. Since the Revolution, the convent has become a military hospital. The church houses sculptures and paintings by Philippe de Champaigne, while a museum in the cloister traces the history of the military health service through its artistic and medical missions. A must-see for history and architecture buffs.

label: Cinquième Sens
comment: Founded in 1976 near the Eiffel Tower, this perfumery expert offers creative workshops for everyone. Whether you're an enthusiast or a novice, you'll find a course to suit your needs. With an all-female team, Cinquième Sens emphasizes professionalism and passion. In addition to tours of Paris, the company also offers workshops on ?nology and coffee to provide a varied and enriching experience.

Immerse yourself in the authentic atmosphere of Belleville with the Balade Paris à Belleville. Explore the charm of Sud Montmartre on the Paris Gourmet tour. And don't miss an evening with Thomas, journalist and winner of the Prix Elysée de la Photographie in 2016. Paris a Dream offers tailor-made events for all groups.

A wide range of choices to satisfy all the desires and needs of travelers passing through this emblematic Parisian station.

comment: In the emblematic Moulin de la Galette, next to the Sacré-C?ur and the Moulin Rouge, the chef sublimates inventive, refined French cuisine. On the terrace in the heart of Montmartre, guests are invited to enjoy a romantic escape, shaded in summer and subdued in the evening. The dynamic, seasonal food and wine list is served by an exceptional young team.

label: Mamie Gâteaux
comment: At the heart of the 6th and 7th arrondissements is the Mamie Gâteaux tea room, in a historic building dating back to the French Revolution. The friendly, family atmosphere is reminiscent of the flavors of our ancestors. The menu features traditional soups, salads, tarts, savory cakes and pastries. Delicious cuisine that appeals to taste buds young and old alike.

label: Rose Bakery
comment: Enjoy a unique culinary experience at Café-Terrasse Rose Bakery, whether it's breakfast with the family, lunch with colleagues or drinks with friends. In an idyllic setting, enjoy fresh salads, tasty pastries, delicious hot dishes and a wide selection of hot and cold drinks. Let yourself be tempted by our all-organic cuisine, creatively revisiting English gastronomy.

label: Clasico Argentino (rue Madame)
comment: Gourmets of Argentinian cuisine can indulge themselves on the Left Bank of Paris, near the Luxembourg Gardens. At Clasico Argentino on rue Madame, the atmosphere combines the authenticity of Argentine stools with Nordic lighting design. Alone or with friends, enjoy empanadas and homemade ice creams. Takeaway service is also available. Not to be missed: the El Carrito food truck at Clasico Argentino, for a unique South American culinary experience.

label: Galerie Frédéric Got
comment: The Frédéric Got art gallery presents a diverse range of French and international contemporary artists, including Gonzalez Bravo, Rémi Bourquin, Stallman, Patrick Rubinstein, Jacques Le Bescond, Carlos Mata, Quentin Garel, Harry Benson, Steve McCurry and Denis Felix. With three locations in Paris, including one on the Île Saint-Louis and two in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, Galerie Frédéric Got is a must for contemporary art lovers.

label: Le Café Marly
comment: Located under the arcades of the Louvre, close to the Carrousel and the Tuileries, the Café Marly enjoys an ideal position. Its Napoleon III ambience, designed by Olivier Gagnère, elegantly blends modernity and classicism. Its terrace offers a breathtaking view of the Louvre's glass pyramid. This trendy spot offers creative cuisine blending French and international flavors, for a unique culinary experience.

label: Église Saint-Pierre de Montmartre
comment: Built in 1147, Saint-Pierre-de-Montmartre blends Romanesque and Gothic influences. Its architecture reflects the evolution of artistic styles over the centuries. Since 1953, it has housed a magnificent stained-glass window by artist Max Ingrand, depicting the life of the Apostle Peter. Every detail of this work is meticulously crafted, immersing visitors in Christian history. In this way, the church remains a treasure trove of symbols and emotions for all.

label: L'Assiette
comment: A magical place for food lovers: an enchanting atmosphere and French dishes magnified with talent, in a renowned address. Appreciate the elegance of the setting, the subtlety of the flavors and the boldness of the recipes for a memorable culinary adventure. Every bite transports you to a world of refinement and pleasure. Experience the essence of French cuisine in this exceptional restaurant, where every plate is a work of art to be savored in wonder. Let yourself be enchanted by the magic of French gastronomy revisited with genius.

Immerse yourself in the history of chocolate, meet our talented chocolatiers, indulge in tasty tastings, make your own sweets, share fun family moments, let your gourmet imagination run wild, and meet other chocolate enthusiasts. label: Jean Imbert au Plaza Athénée
comment: Chef Jean Imbert heads the gourmet restaurant at the Palace Plaza Athénée on Avenue Montaigne. His French cuisine is sublimated in a sumptuous room decorated with 20,000 gold leaves by designer Rémi Tessier. The 12-metre marble table is impressive. The Relais Plaza, the hotel's brasserie, also offers the chef's delights. An unmissable address for tasting the best of French gastronomy in an exceptional setting.

label: Racines
comment: This charming bar-restaurant, a former wine den, offers refined cuisine featuring fresh, high-quality produce. Gourmets will delight in a variety of tasty dishes prepared by a talented chef. Wine lovers will be delighted by the selection of organic wines from renowned vineyards. A warm place to savor delicate dishes and discover exceptional vintages, all in a friendly, elegant atmosphere.

label: Coulée verte René-Dumont
comment: The Coulée verte René-Dumont, formerly the Promenade Plantée, opened in 1988 by Philippe Mathieux and Jacques Vergely, follows the former Bastille-Varenne-St-Maur railroad line. From the Opéra-Bastille to the Jardin de Reuilly, via the Viaduc des Arts, the Allee Vivaldi offers shops before reaching the Porte Dorée and the Bois de Vincennes. Over 4.5 km, this varied route offers views over the 12th arrondissement, with lush vegetation and contemporary landscaping, ideal for a rewarding stroll.

label: Notre-Dame de la Compassion
comment: Built in the 19th century, Notre-Dame-de-Compassion church combines neo-Byzantine and Gothic styles. Its biblical frescoes, colorful stained-glass windows and sculpted furnishings bear witness to the talent of its artists. A place of prayer and passage, it attracts art and history lovers for its beauty and its location close to the Palais des Congrès and the Hôtel Méridien in Paris.

label: Goethe-Institut de Paris
comment: The Goethe-Institut de Paris offers a wide range of cultural events highlighting German culture through film, visual arts, theater, dance, literature and encounters with authors. Its library provides access to a wide range of media and information on Germany's cultural, social and political life. An enriching immersion in the diversity and creativity of the German art scene.

label: Hôtel Drouot
comment: Since 1852, Hôtel Drouot has been an emblematic venue, with some 70 auctions and over 230,000 works of art and collectibles. Visitors can admire the unique pieces on show and talk to the auctioneers. This fascinating venue features vintage furniture, jewelry, fine wines and fashion accessories. Hôtel Drouot hosts a variety of events throughout the year: exhibitions, urban art fairs and screenings.

label: El Ganso
comment: Founded in 2004, Spanish brand El Ganso is renowned for its elegant, preppy collections for men, women and children. In 2012, it opened a second boutique in Paris, strengthening its presence in the fashion market. Thanks to its know-how and creativity, El Ganso offers quality pieces in line with current trends. Its chic yet casual spirit appeals to a clientele in search of elegance and modernity, winning over many customers around the world.

label: Boutique PSG Champs-Élysees
comment: The Paris Saint-Germain boutique on the Champs-Élysées will delight soccer fans. Spread over 370 m² on 2 levels, fans will find a wide selection of clothing for men, women and children, as well as a varied range of accessories. Souvenirs such as player figurines, plush toys and mugs are also available among the 17,000 products on offer. A must-visit destination for proudly displaying your colors and supporting your favorite team.

label: Marsan par Hélène Darroze
comment: Michelin-starred chef Hélène Darroze offers an exceptional gastronomic experience in her 30-cover dining room, a private table in her 6-cover kitchen and a 22-cover table d'hôtes opening onto the creative workshop. Her other establishment, Restaurant Joia, is located at 39 rue des Jeûneurs in the 2nd arrondissement, also offering a terrace to enjoy delicious dishes in a unique setting.

label: Raffles Spa & Wellness
comment: The Royal Monceau - Raffles Paris, the capital's prestigious luxury hotel, is home to an exceptional spa: the Spa My Blend by Clarins. In an immaculate setting, this sanctuary of well-being extends over 1,500 m², with seven treatment rooms, a hammam, a laconium, a sauna, a Turkish bath and a 23-metre swimming pool (the largest in Parisian palaces). Treat yourself to the Royale Energie treatment, a unique Clarins experience for total relaxation and revealed beauty.

label: Pathé Aquaboulevard
comment: The Gaumont Aquaboulevard cinema has 14 screens, including one with digital projection. All tiered and air-conditioned, these theaters offer optimal sound quality. With spacious red club seats, wide armrests and cup holders, as well as 1.10m aisle spacing, moviegoers enjoy the ultimate in comfort.

label: Tartine et Chocolat
comment: Founded in 1977, Tartine et Chocolat is a French brand renowned for its high-quality children's clothing. Soft, poetic collections every season, with noble materials and delicate colors. Chic, comfortable pieces to dress your little ones elegantly. Opt for style and quality with Tartine et Chocolat. Discover the world of refinement and succumb to these unique creations. An invitation to dream and escape.

label: Au Petit Tonneau
comment: Ideally located in the heart of Paris's 7th arrondissement, near the Invalides, the "Au Petit Tonneau" restaurant continues the tradition of authentic Parisian bistros. Managed by Arlette and chef Vincent Neveu, this establishment offers authentic, generous gourmet cuisine, featuring quality produce prepared according to the season and the market. The famous Commissaire Maigret used to enjoy his favorite blanquette de veau here.

label: Versace
comment: The prestigious boutique of Gianni Versace, the famous Italian designer, sits majestically on Avenue Montaigne, a stone's throw from the Champs-Élysées. Renowned for its baroque style and luxurious designs, the brand embodies Italian extravagance. A must for lovers of fashion and refinement.

Guerlain Signature facials offer pure relaxation, with natural products such as Orchidée Impériale. The program includes hydrotherapy, divine massages, body treatments and make-up. A sensory escape to the land of beauty and serenity.

comment: The Paris City Council launched a project to create a "Rue de la Mode" in the Goutte d'Or district to revitalize the area. Many European, American and Asian designers have set up shop here. Flagship addresses include Marcia de Carvalho at 2 rue des Gardes, Dognin at 4 rue des Gardes, and Lily Latifi at 11 rue des Gardes. It's an opportunity to discover international talent in a unique and lively environment.

label: Comédie Caumartin
comment: Located in the Opéra Garnier district, the Comédie Caumartin opened in 1901 under the name Comédie-Royale. This renowned theater is best known for hosting major comedies such as "Boeing-Boeing". Prestigious comedians such as Franck Dubosc have performed on its stage, leaving their mark on the history of this iconic venue. A must for comedy fans in Paris.

label: Musée Maillol
comment: The Musée Maillol offers a unique immersion into the artistic world of renowned modern sculptor Aristide Maillol. Through his sculptures, paintings, drawings, terracottas and tapestries, visitors can appreciate the diversity and depth of his work. In addition to the permanent collections, the museum offers two temporary exhibitions each year, highlighting contemporary artistic trends. A rich and captivating cultural experience not to be missed.

label: Maxime Simoëns
comment: In 2006, Maxime Simoëns distinguished himself by graduating top of his class from the Chambre syndicale de la couture parisienne. With experience working for big names such as Gaultier, Ghesquières and Galliano, he founded his own house in 2009. His style is characterized by geometric dresses with fluid cuts, bringing a breath of fresh air and innovation to the world of Parisian haute couture.

label: École nationale supérieure des Beaux-arts
comment: Founded in the 19th century on the site of the Petits Augustins convent, the École nationale supérieure des Beaux-Arts continues the tradition of the royal academies of the great century. Not to be missed: the Cour d'Honneur, the Petits Augustins chapel and the Cour du Mûrier. Temporary exhibitions regularly enrich this emblematic site of art and culture. A must for history and art lovers.

label: Galerie Eric Dupont
comment: Founded in 1997, the Marais contemporary art gallery showcases the work of cosmopolitan artists such as Taysir Batniji, Fouad Bouchoucha, Pascal Convert, Yazid Oulab, Mathieu Pernot, Regina Virserius, Nicholas Nixon and the duo Gil & Moti. Its vast, light-filled space is home to these talents, and actively participates in renowned fairs such as Paris Photos, Art Brussels and Scope Miami. An international showcase for these extraordinary artists.

label: Au Cadet de Gascogne
comment: Chef Georges Guinot invites you to savor traditional French cuisine at Le Cadet de Gascogne in Montmartre. Enjoy classic dishes such as Soupe à l?oignon, B?uf Bourguignon and Magret de canard, accompanied by homemade delicacies. Enjoy breakfast on the terrace, lunch in the sun or dinner with live music. Our waiters are at your service from 7 a.m. to 2 a.m. in an authentic setting. Capacity up to 266 guests, privatization possible for special events. Discover French gastronomy at Cadet de Gascogne!

label: Paris Hockey Club
comment: Founded in 1913, the Paris Hockey Club is a veritable institution in the world of speed skating. In addition to its recognized expertise, the club offers introductory and preparatory courses for roller touring. These sessions are supervised by qualified instructors, guaranteeing quality learning and an enriching experience for all skating enthusiasts.

label: Jardin d'agronomie tropicale René-Dumont
comment: Founded in 1899, this exotic garden has a captivating history: originally, agronomists used it to study the reproduction of plants from the colonies (coffee, cocoa, vanilla, banana, etc.). In 1907, it became the site of the five villages of the Colonial Exhibition, some of which are still standing today. Today, the garden is a pleasant and surprising place to stroll, immersing visitors in the history of exchanges between the world's different cultures.

label: Cabaret-Club Madame Arthur
comment: Discover Pigalle's emblematic cabaret, Madame Arthur, for an offbeat Parisian experience. On stage, original artists revisit the classics of French chanson to enchant you. In a convivial atmosphere, attend a dinner show or enjoy the show with a drink. There's also a blind test and a dance floor to prolong the magic. Come and discover this authentic and unique venue today!

label: Bateau Concorde Atlantique
comment: Moored on the Seine, between the Assemblée Nationale and the Musée d?Orsay, the Concorde Atlantique boat offers after-work and clubbing evenings all year round. With 3 levels open to the public (450 m²), including an outdoor deck offering a breathtaking view of Paris and the banks of the Seine, a UNESCO World Heritage site, this is an unusual evening on this mythical river not to be missed.

label: Ambassade d'Auvergne
comment: Just a stone's throw from the famous Centre Pompidou, in the heart of Paris, discover a charming restaurant offering traditional cuisine featuring fresh produce. The rustic ambience adds a touch of authenticity to this culinary experience. An ideal setting for a tasty gastronomic getaway in the heart of the French capital.

label: Temple de Pentemont
comment: Built in 1747 for the Bernardines, the building became a barracks in the 19th century, before being reassigned to the Ministry of Veterans? Affairs. In 1844, Victor Baltard transformed the chapel into a Reformed place of worship, and the nuns' choir became the nave of the temple. Today, this place steeped in history combines heritage and administrative function.

label: Jardins d'Éole
comment: Located 1.5 km from the Buttes-Chaumont and La Villette parks, Les Jardins d'Éole offers a green oasis in a neighborhood lacking in green spaces. They are home to a rich biodiversity, with a gravel garden, planted canal, meadow, flowering lawns, copses, shrub beds, perennial garden and grass garden. A haven of peace with a shared garden, a convivial place for sharing.

Featuring a 25-meter pool, it offers a variety of aquatic activities such as aquagym and group classes. An ideal opportunity to recharge your batteries and pamper your body in the heart of Paris.

The chef, who trained at the Atelier du Peintre in Colmar, the Vague d'Or in Saint-Tropez, the K2 in Courchevel and the Pyramide in Vienna, concocts dishes of remarkable subtlety and finesse. In the elegant setting of a Parisian bistro, guests are treated to exquisitely refined cuisine.

label: Ma Bourgogne
comment: The Ma Bourgogne restaurant, renowned for its Burgundian cuisine, offers a typical atmosphere with beams, wood panelling and a vaulted cellar. The menu features emblematic dishes such as escargots, b?uf bourguignon, jambon persillé, veal kidneys with chablis and ?ufs pochés en meurette. From Monday to Friday, in brasserie or restaurant versions, or on the terrace in fine weather, Ma Bourgogne offers fresh, authentic products for a unique gastronomic experience.

label: Librairie de la Cinémathèque française
comment: The Cinémathèque bookshop, on the mezzanine, offers a wide selection of books, DVDs and recordings on cinema, film music, images, cinema architecture, new technologies, posters, photography and foreign works. We also offer essays, novels, plays and poetry, in conjunction with exhibitions and programs. The bookshop offers publications from the Cinémathèque and the BiFi, a treasure trove for cinema and culture enthusiasts.

label: Le Monteverdi
comment: Located on a charming street in the Latin Quarter, Le Monteverdi is an Italian restaurant with undeniable charm. Founded by a descendant of the famous composer Monteverdi, this romantic establishment offers refined Italian cuisine in a pleasant piano-bar atmosphere. For a unique culinary experience, remember to reserve your table in advance.

label: Au Paradis du gourmand
comment: In the heart of the 14th arrondissement is Au Paradis du gourmand, a must for lovers of good food. Created by Ridha Khader, head baker, pastry chef and caterer, it won the Premier Prix de la Meilleure Baguette de Paris in 2013. In addition to a variety of breads such as Intégral bio and campagne au levain naturel, the establishment excels in macaroons, its sweet specialty. A delicious address not to be missed!

label: Musée des Archives Nationales - Hôtel de Soubise
comment: The hôtels de Soubise and de Rohan, jewels of the Marais district, feature sumptuous salons designed by Germain Boffrand, and decorated with works by Boucher, Van Loo and Trémolières. The Musée des Archives Nationales showcases rare documents, presents captivating exhibitions and organizes events such as the Journées du patrimoine and the Nuit des musées. Not to be missed: the Nomades Festival, Jeunes Talents concerts, Baroque Lunchtimes and the Prince's Piano bring this historic venue to life.

label: Benoit Paris
comment: Founded in Paris in 1912, Restaurant Benoit is an authentic bistro where gourmets from all over the world enjoy lunch and dinner. The only establishment of its kind to hold a Michelin star, it is located close to the Hôtel de Ville, the Centre Pompidou and the Tour Saint-Jacques. Since the beginning of the 20th century, Benoit has been delighting lovers of traditional French cuisine in a warm and friendly atmosphere.

label: Zo

Its cuisine knows no borders, taking you on a journey from Japan to Italy, via France. Simple, tasty and beautifully presented dishes are the hallmark of this popular Faubourg Saint-Honoré address, where politicians and fashion enthusiasts meet in a relaxed atmosphere.

From stuffed cabbage to exquisite truffles, diners delight in the richness of the wine list. An address not to be missed, where the warmth of the welcome and the quality of the dishes attract a loyal and conquered clientele.

label: Théâtre Marigny
comment: Under Offenbach in 1855, the theater reached its apogee. Garnier's circular architecture of the 1880s marks its history. After Abel Deval in 1910, Léon Volterra rebuilt the theatre in 1925 to create a more spacious auditorium. Since 1965, Elvire Popesco and Jean Bodson (from 1978) have successfully continued this tradition. The Molières and "Au Théâtre ce soir" awards contribute to its renown.

label: Au bonheur du jour
comment: The Au Bonheur du Jour art gallery, located near the Palais-Royal in Paris, offers two distinct spaces: one dedicated to historical and modern photography, as well as thematic exhibitions, and the other exhibiting drawings, paintings and singular antique objects, accompanied by a selection of books. This unusual venue offers erotic works of art for a discerning and curious public, offering a unique artistic immersion in the heart of the French capital.

label: Passage Verdeau
comment: The Passage Verdeau, named after its creator, is one of the most charming covered passages in Paris. Built in 1847, it forms a perfect trio with the passages des Panoramas and Jouffroy. Here you'll find antique shops and unusual boutiques offering vintage books, postcards and vintage cameras. The magnificent storefronts, illuminated by the fish-ribbed glass roof, attract visitors. A second entrance is at 31 bis rue du Faubourg Montmartre.

The spacious terrace overlooks the lively boulevard. A must before or after a show, La Rotonde embodies the charm of Montparnasse.

The layout allows guests to enjoy a view of a magnificent fresco inspired by French gardens, while the open kitchen adds a touch of conviviality to the dining experience.

comment: Maison Valmont, a symbol of Swiss beauty, combines scientific expertise and natural ingredients in its face and body treatments. At the Valmont spa in the Le Meurice palace in Paris, this 340 m² space offers four luxurious cabins, a landscaped terrace and a boutique with anti-aging treatments and Storie Veneziane fragrances. Its fluid architecture and soothing hues make it a haven of sophistication and relaxation.

Its fluid architecture and soothing hues make it a haven of sophistication and relaxation.

You can also take advantage of the hotel's covered garden terrace, a warm and peaceful space in all seasons.

label: A la Mère de Famille
comment: Founded in 1761, À la mère de famille is an emblematic Parisian chocolaterie-confiserie. It offers a wide range of sweet treats: ice creams, pastries, nougats, caramels, pralines and even famous marrons glacés. Her historic store, on the corner of Rue du Faubourg Montmartre and Rue Richer, is a must-see with its listed façade. A paradise for gourmets in search of the delights of yesteryear. An unforgettable sweet experience in Paris.

An educational immersion that will arouse the curiosity of all visitors!

Its work strengthens links between Spanish-speaking countries and other cultures, promoting diversity throughout the world.

A mobile trattoria that delights lovers of authentic Italian cuisine.

label: Le Palace
comment: Le Palace, a landmark building on the Grands Boulevards, has a rich history. Opened in 1912, it became a cinema in 1946 before returning to its original vocation. After a retro '30s renovation, the Palace welcomed Grace Jones and became the chic spot of the Parisian night, attracting an elite clientele. Closed in 1996, it was reborn in 2006 to offer exceptional shows, confirming its status of excellence.

label: Observatoire de Paris
comment: Built between 1667 and 1672 by architect Claude Perrault, the Paris Observatory is an emblematic historic building housing a collection of astronomical instruments. It is also the oldest observatory in operation. The meridian of France, established in 1729 by Jacques Cassini, was created here, enabling the first map of France to be drawn. In 1884, an international convention chose the Greenwich meridian as the universal geographic reference.

label: Tour de la biodiversité - M6B2
comment: The Biodiversity Tower - M6B2, built in 2016 by Maison Edouard François in Paris Rive Gauche, reaches a height of 50 meters. Its social housing units with charming balconies and planted facades contribute to urban biodiversity. Wild species settle in naturally, enriching the urban ecosystem. In addition to the housing, there's a hostel for young workers, shops, a crèche and a garden, promoting sustainable well-being.

Each year, prestigious prizes are awarded to women writers. A place where history and glamour meet in harmony.

label: Tornabuoni Art Paris

Specializing in contemporary Italian art and Italian Novecento artists such as De Chirico, Balla and Fontana, it also exhibits 20th-century greats such as Picasso, Mirò, Dubuffet, Christo, Warhol and Basquiat. Nestled close to the Champs-Élysées, the Parisian gallery offers a wide range of captivating exhibitions.

label: Paroisse Saint-Germain de Charonne
comment: Saint-Germain de Charonne, a listed historic monument, dominates the streets of Bagnolet and Saint-Blaise with its imposing bell-tower. Incorporated into Paris in 1860, it is a rare piece of history. Legend has it that Saint Germain and Sainte Geneviève met here in 429. Built between the 12th and 13th centuries, the church underwent modifications in the 15th and 18th centuries. The churchyard contains an ancient cemetery, a unique treasure in Paris.

Here you'll find clothing boutiques, tea rooms, wine cellars, grocery stores, antique bookshops... Access is via Rue de la Banque and Rue Vivienne. An unmissable getaway in the heart of Paris!

label: Le Café Caché
comment: In the heart of Le Centquatre, this café with its clean, modern style is a must for a gourmet break. Its simple, refined cuisine offers fresh, tasty dishes. In a warm, contemporary setting, you can enjoy your meal in peace and quiet, far from the hustle and bustle of the city. Don't miss our Sunday brunch for a delicious, convivial experience. An address to discover for a moment of pleasure and relaxation.

Fridays are dedicated to private events, while other days offer the possibility of privatizing this space for up to 350 guests. A must for quality entertainment in a warm and friendly setting.

label: Boutique Comédie-Française
comment: Located in the heart of Paris, between the Louvre and the Opera, the Comédie-Française theater is the oldest in France. Its boutique offers a varied collection of objects and books related to the theater and its rich heritage. From tableware and stationery to jewelry and textiles, discover exclusive creations and a unique selection of theatrical objects. An invitation to plunge into the exciting world of the stage.

label: Marché aux timbres
comment: Philatelic enthusiasts meet regularly near the Champs-Élysées. This weekly meeting brings together enthusiasts and collectors, whether professionals or amateurs. An extensive collection of stamps, phone cards and postcards is available for sale, to suit all budgets. A must for postal history enthusiasts and collectors of rare objects.

comment: The Ecomusée de la Goutte d'Or is a multi-purpose art gallery and cultural space. Set in an inspiring artistic environment, it brings together workshops, exhibition and performance spaces. Renowned artists have already taken part. Exhibitions, lectures, shows and workshops are all on offer. Open to all, this space invites everyone to discover an exciting artistic universe.

label: Montmartre aux Artistes
comment: In the heart of Paris's 18th arrondissement, "Montmartre aux Artistes" is a haven dedicated to artistic creation. Comprising three Art Deco buildings, it houses 177 studios where artists from all horizons give free rein to their imagination. Each year, these creators open their doors to the public, offering an opportunity to discover their world and their works. It's an enriching way to talk to contemporary art enthusiasts.

label: École normale supérieure
comment: Located in the heart of the Latin Quarter, the École normale supérieure is a true center of excellence for undergraduate and doctoral studies. With fourteen teaching and research departments, this renowned institution covers a broad spectrum of disciplines, both literary and scientific. As a leading centre of French research, the ENS is renowned for its multidisciplinary expertise and international renown.

label: Citadium
comment: The Carrousel du Louvre is a must for street culture enthusiasts. On three floors, you'll find the hottest sportswear brands, offering a selection of fashionable clothing and accessories. In addition to the stores, events and exhibitions enrich the visitor experience. It's the perfect opportunity to discover new trends and talents on the urban art scene. A total immersion in street culture in the heart of Paris.

label: Le Pain Quotidien - Lepic
comment: Since its creation in Brussels in 1990, Le Pain Quotidien has stood for authenticity, quality, simplicity and conviviality. The place offers organic wheat bread and fresh, organic ingredients around a large table made of recycled wood. Le Pain Quotidien Lepic, in the heart of Montmartre, offers organic breads, brunches, a tea room and a delicatessen. Its shaded terrace and convivial dining room are the perfect place to get together all day long.

comment: Café Zéro Zéro is a popular spot for young adults, bringing together vinyl aficionados for sales every Friday, as well as fans of minimal house, hip-hop and funk. This vibrant, friendly venue is the ideal meeting place for music lovers in search of musical discoveries and a trendy atmosphere.

label: Aquarium de Paris
comment: In the heart of Paris, the Aquarium de Paris offers an unforgettable spectacle with 60 tanks, over 7,500 fish, French invertebrates and 50 sharks. Explore France's largest shark tank, pet Koi carp and enjoy interactive animations. In 2019, discover the Medusarium, Europe's largest, with 2,500 jellyfish in 15 tanks. A magical family day awaits you!

comment: Chef Michel Rostang's renowned restaurant offers a luxurious setting adorned with wood panelling and collectors' items. His classic French cuisine will delight the most discerning palate. Not to mention an impressive wine list to satisfy even the most demanding connoisseurs. An unmissable address for an exceptional culinary experience.

label: Corpus Christi
comment: In a setting inspired by Swedish hunting lodges, the boutique presents the glamrock creations of Thierry Gougenot. Between provocation and humor, his collection of jewelry and accessories features skulls and sacred symbols, carefully sculpted in noble materials. A subtle blend of originality and audacity that enchants fashion lovers in search of unique and singular pieces.

label: Le Paon Qui Boit
comment: Le Paon Qui Boit, France's first "alcohol-free cellar", opened in Paris in April 2022. More than 400 quality drinks for adults are on offer: sparkling wines, cocktails, de-alcoholized wines, beers, all alcohol-free and mostly ORGANIC. Made in France, with a low sugar content, they are available for takeaway or delivery to events and companies. Private tastings and reservations available for a unique experience! Online store available.

label: Hammam de la Mosquée de Paris
comment: Nestled behind the Jardin des Plantes, the hammam of the Mosquée de Paris features a décor inspired by Byzantine art. Shimmering mosaics, elegant marble and sumptuous porphyry create an enchanting atmosphere. In its steam baths, the heat gradually rises to purify the body according to Eastern traditions. After this relaxing escapade, unwind in the tea room or on the patio, to prolong the sweetness and relaxation.

label: Le Trabendo
comment: Located in the Parc de la Villette, the Trabendo is a unique Parisian concert venue with its red "folie" designed by Bernard Tschumi. Renovated in 2012, it can accommodate up to 700 spectators for concerts ranging from rock to electro and hip-hop. Renowned artists such as Justice and Tyler The Creator have already performed here. With its terrace and friendly atmosphere, Le Trabendo is a must for music fans in the Paris region.

label: Prada
comment: Established in 1913 as a saddlery, Prada underwent a major turning point under the impetus of Miuccia Prada, daughter of the founder, who launched the brand's ready-to-wear line. Today, Prada is a must-have brand for intellectual fashion enthusiasts around the world, carving out a place for itself on the covers of trendy magazines.

label: Spa Nuxe
comment: In 2002, Nuxe inaugurated its first Parisian spa at the prestigious addresses of 32 and 34 rue Montorgueil. Housed in a former wine storehouse with a unique décor of vaulted cellars and stonework, this space invites you to immerse yourself in the hidden treasures of Paris. With thirteen treatment rooms, including two for couples, and a superb sensory pool heated to 35°, this 300m² space offers exceptional moments of relaxation just a stone's throw from Les Halles.

label: Bassin de La Villette
comment: The Bassin de la Villette, an imposing 800 meters long and 70 meters wide, is the largest artificial water feature in Paris, cleverly connecting the Canal de l'Ourcq to the Canal Saint-Martin to promote river transport. This aquatic space offers a rich array of entertainment and cultural activities, such as shows, concerts and theater, making it a festive venue much appreciated by Parisians.

It's an oasis of well-being in the heart of the city, perfect for lovers of aquatic sensations.

A walk rich in discoveries and moments of relaxation in the heart of nature.

A friendly, festive place where everyone can enjoy a warm, lively atmosphere.

label: Maison Fleuret - The Baking School - Saint-Germain-des-Pres
Square Georges Cain
comment: Located near the Musée Carnavalet in the Marais district, Square Georges Cain is a 2,128m² haven of peace. Its discreet atmosphere attracts lovers of tranquillity or regulars seeking to preserve this secret spot. Two astonishing works of art are on display: "L'Aurore", a 17th-century bronze statue, and Eric Samakh's "Le Rossignol Electrique" (1990), an electronic bird singing in the wind. Ideal for a picnic or a game of cards under the trees.

label: Musée national Gustave Moreau
comment: Nestled in the 9th arrondissement of Paris, Gustave Moreau's studio house carefully preserves the painter's artistic treasures. With 1,300 paintings, watercolors and cartoons, plus 5,000 drawings, visitors can admire major works on the first floor and discover the intimacy of the artist's apartment on the 1st floor. An enriching visit into the world of this great master.

comment: Le Village Suisse Paris, an artistic jewel in the heart of the capital since 1920, seduces lovers of art, jewelry and antiques. Galleries and boutiques abound with unique pieces. Its hanging gardens and tree-lined patios invite you to take a soothing stroll, ideal for immersing yourself in the history of art. Just a stone's throw from the Eiffel Tower and the Grand Palais Éphémère, this pedestrian zone is a haven of peace. An unforgettable experience for art and design enthusiasts.

label: Mémorial de la guerre d’Algérie et des combats du Maroc et de la Tunisie
comment: Inaugurated in 2002, the Memorial to the Algerian War and the Fighting in Morocco and Tunisia pays tribute to the soldiers, auxiliaries and civilians who died for France between 1952 and 1964. Located quai Branly in Paris, it honors the memory of the victims of the conflicts in North Africa.

label: Auditorium Edmond J. Safra du Mémorial de la Shoah
comment: The Edmond J. Safra amphitheater, which seats 120, is the ideal venue for symposia, conferences, screenings and debates on the history of the Holocaust and its current repercussions. These events, linked to the temporary exhibitions, cover a wide range of historical subjects, personal accounts, genocide studies and literary analyses. This space for dialogue and reflection is essential to understanding the challenges of our contemporary history.

label: Musée de la Sculpture en plein air
comment: The Musée de la Sculpture en Plein Air, located on the Quai Saint-Bernard, offers a pleasant stroll along the Seine, between the Pont de Sully and the Pont d'Austerlitz. Since 1980, the Square Tino-Rossi has been exhibiting works by great sculptors such as César, Brancusi, Nicolas Schöffer and Gilioli. The sculptures, with no barriers, allow visitors to admire them from all angles, offering a unique cultural getaway to discover contemporary art.

label: Présence africaine
comment: Discover Black Africa and its diaspora through fascinating and informative articles. Explore the cultural diversity, ancestral traditions and artistic talents that characterize this part of the world. From music and dance to gastronomy, plunge into the heart of a vibrant, ever-evolving universe. A journey through Africa and its diaspora that will captivate and amaze you.

label: Pierre Sang in Oberkampf
comment: Celebrity chef Pierre Sang, revealed in 2011 on Top Chef, opens his first restaurant in Paris, on rue Oberkampf. Trained by some of the world's greatest chefs, he offers a refined blend of flavors, traditions and colors. His innovative concept features a 6-course surprise menu that changes daily, offering a unique culinary experience. A popular address for gourmets in search of original taste discoveries.
