label: Pizza Chic
comment: The ambiance is chic and refined down to the smallest detail, from the checkerboard tiles to the immaculate tablecloths and elegant silverware. Antipasti are both sophisticated and delicious, sweet Italian specialties delight the taste buds, and pizzas are prepared with virtuosity. This exquisite setting promises an exceptional culinary experience where good taste takes center stage.

label: Maison La Roche
comment: Built between 1923 and 1925 by Le Corbusier and Pierre Jeanneret, the Maisons La Roche and Jeanneret are icons of 1920s architecture. Only the Maison La Roche is open to the public, classified as a Historic Monument in 1996. This unique house combines an art gallery with Raoul La Roche's reinforced concrete apartments. Le Corbusier applied his "Five Points of New Architecture" to the building. The Maison Jeanneret houses the Fondation Le Corbusier and holds the architect's original drawings. Listed as a Unesco World Heritage site in 2016, this is a must-see for architecture enthusiasts.

comment: The chic and intimate Secret Square cabaret, not far from the Champs-Élysées, offers a sensual and exclusive dinner-show experience. Its original menu, a subtle blend of refined flavors, goes perfectly with a selection of vintage wines. As a bonus, a captivating show combining stripping and pole dancing, unique in Paris, will delight guests in search of an exceptional evening. Not to be missed for an unforgettable, spellbinding experience.

label: Colonne de Juillet
comment: The Colonne de Juillet, built on the site of the Bastille, honors the heroes of the 1830 revolution. Inaugurated in 1840, this emblematic monument dominates the Bastille district, with the Génie de la Liberté at the top, now an icon of Paris. The lower sections of this triumphal column are open to guided tours at weekends, offering a fascinating experience with a guide-lecturer. A not-to-be-missed historical and architectural landmark of the 19th century.

label: Musée Bourdelle
comment: Come and discover the Musée Bourdelle, in the former studio of sculptor Antoine Bourdelle. Admire over five hundred works in plaster, marble and bronze, revealing his talent. A collaborator of Rodin, Bourdelle influenced artists such as Giacometti. The museum, renovated by architect Christian de Portzamparc, offers a contemporary experience. Discover the sculpture garden and temporary exhibitions to explore Bourdelle's world.

label: Institut finlandais
comment: The Institut Finlandais, nestled in the heart of the Latin Quarter, is a veritable showcase for Finnish culture. This must-see venue showcases Finnish creativity, heritage, craftsmanship, language and cuisine. Come and discover the richness and diversity of this Nordic country through exhibitions, cultural events and culinary tastings. A complete immersion in the fascinating world of Finland awaits you at the Institut Finlandais.

label: Square Jules Verne
comment: In the heart of Belleville, the Square Jules Verne is a veritable green refuge in the middle of the city. This space offers residents the chance to recharge their batteries and enjoy nature. As well as being a place to relax, the square is home to a shared garden that fosters social ties between residents. This initiative strengthens conviviality within the local community, creating a real sense of solidarity.

comment: Specializing in music, cinema and theater, L?Archipel offers a variety of concerts ranging from classical to jazz and world. Its high-quality film and theater programming will delight fans of these arts. In addition, special attention is paid to film music, offering a rich and diverse cultural experience.

label: Palais des Thés
comment: For years, the experts at Le Palais des Thés have been scouring the globe in search of the finest teas. Green, black, white and smoked teas from Africa, South America and Asia. Among them, the highly prized "grands crus", testifying to rare and exquisite flavors. To help you find what you're looking for, our boutiques offer the possibility of tasting on site. Treat yourself or your loved ones to quality gift boxes and gourmet baskets.

comment: Housed in the prestigious Ritz Paris, the Ritz Escoffier School celebrates the art of French cuisine and patisserie. A teaching ground for culinary excellence, it is open to professionals and gastronomy enthusiasts alike, from beginners to aspiring chefs. Each lesson, taught in French, is translated into English, guaranteeing a high-end learning experience accessible to an international audience.

comment: Discover a shopping paradise at Westfield Forum des Halles! Leading fashion brands for men and women, as well as specialist beauty, health and wellness boutiques await you. Enjoy a unique experience combining shopping, relaxation and leisure in the heart of Paris. Don't miss out on the many advantages offered by your favorite shopping center!

label: Chapelle Notre-Dame de la Médaille Miraculeuse
comment: Nestled in the heart of a small, discreet courtyard, not far from the famous Bon Marché, lies one of Paris's most important places of worship. It was in 1830 that the Virgin Mary appeared to Catherine Labouré for the second time, asking her to strike a protective medal. Miracle after miracle followed, and the craze continued, attracting crowds of pilgrims from all over the world almost two centuries after this prodigious event.

label: Ciné-Balade
comment: Since 2011, Ciné-Balade has been showcasing Paris through the cinema. The capital, beloved of filmmakers, has inspired many cult films. Follow in the footsteps of Truffaut, Varda or Méliès on our tours. Immerse yourself in iconic neighborhoods with famous films such as Amélie Poulain in Montmartre or Minuit à Paris in the Latin Quarter. Discover mythical film locations at the Opéra and La Villette thanks to our innovative concept featuring photos and video extracts on a tablet. A unique experience to travel with the great directors.

In addition to quality treatments, customers can enjoy a cocktail bar, a comfortable smoking room and even a private cinema in the basement. Tradition, refinement and elegance come together to offer a unique experience in Paris.

Every dish at Yen is prepared with care and passion to delight the taste buds.

Immerse yourself in a friendly atmosphere and enjoy traditional French cuisine. Discover the chef's signature dishes, such as Pied de Cochon stuffed Périgourdine-style or Double côte de cochon Ibaiama to share. An unforgettable culinary experience awaits you.

label: Musée national de l’histoire de l’immigration
comment: The Palais de la Porte Dorée, an Art Deco historic monument, was built for the 1931 colonial exhibition. Transformed into the Musée national de l'histoire de l'immigration in 2007, it highlights the impact of immigrants on French society. The current tour retraces eleven key moments from 1685 to the present day, and looks at contemporary issues. Documents, photos, artwork and interactive tools provide an essential exploration of the history of immigration in France.

label: Au diable des lombards
comment: Le Diable des Lombards, in the Marais district, is a resto with a vintage American look, complete with Harley Davidson minis, neon lights and wooden stools. You can enjoy burgers, pancakes and US dishes while watching music videos. The waiter puts on a show with original dances. The daily brunch is an experience not to be missed. A relaxed and gay-friendly atmosphere for a unique and warm culinary experience. An unmissable taste experience!

comment: Located in the heart of Paris, the Nicolas Stohrer patisserie, founded by King Louis XV's pastry chef, offers a gastronomic experience not to be missed. Reputed to be the oldest in the capital, it seduces gourmets with its delicious sweet and savory pastries. Its sumptuous decor, listed as a historic monument, adds a touch of elegance to this not-to-be-missed address for lovers of fine flavors.

Renowned for its traditional French cuisine, it offers emblematic dishes such as frog legs, sweetbreads and snails. With its warm atmosphere and tempting menu, the establishment is perfect for spending a pleasant moment with the family, delighting young and old alike.

A unique opportunity to delve into the world of art, far from the beaten track of art galleries.

comment: Originally from the Auvergne region of France, this talented chef excels in the art of marrying flavors to create exceptional dishes. Each plate is an explosion of delights, a symphony of tastes and textures that instantly transports guests on a unique culinary voyage. His creativity and savoir-faire make him a gastronomic artist, capable of surprising and delighting with every bite. An incomparable gustatory experience, to be savored absolutely.

This design space offers a collection of original and innovative creations, highlighting emerging and established talent in interior design and decorative trends. An ideal place for design enthusiasts in search of unique, avant-garde pieces in an artistic and inspiring setting.

comment: The Centre culturel algérien à Paris, opened in 1983, occupies a prestigious position in the largest arrondissement of the French capital. A veritable showcase for Algerian culture in France.

comment: Founded in 1932 by Joseph Louville, La Rhumerie is a café-brasserie specializing in rum, located in the heart of Saint-Germain-des-Prés. Today, its tradition is carried on by his granddaughter and great-granddaughter. Enjoy exquisite cocktails and West Indian dishes in an intoxicating atmosphere. Don't miss the jazz concerts on Sunday and Monday evenings. A must for lovers of spirits and exotic music.

Fresh, local and homemade products are used in the cuisine, such as the côte de b?uf to share or the Poulet Bio des Landes roast. The chef revisits classics with quality. Festive atmosphere with piano, perfect for an authentic evening in Paris." (373 characters)

comment: The Palais de la Découverte, a Universcience site, offers an interactive approach to science. Astronomy, biology, chemistry, mathematics, physics and earth sciences are explored through experiments with scientific mediators. New permanent rooms enhance the experience: the Lumière room combines chemistry, biology and physics, while the Hydrogène space explores the applications of this energy. Scientific immersion for all!

The café offers artisanal products for an original culinary experience. Whether with family, friends or lovers, this is a warm and inviting place to discover.

label: L'Académie du climat
comment: The Académie du climat, near the Hôtel de Ville, is a key venue for raising young people's awareness of environmental issues. Close to the Saint-Gervais Saint-Protais church, it offers a variety of weekday activities: cooking, DIY, gardening, sewing, eco-construction, tree nursery, etc. Free environmental conferences, workshops and exhibitions are also available in the evenings and at weekends. A complete offer to train and mobilize young people aged 9 to 25.

additional_information: ['The Academy: Monday-Friday, from 9am. La Buvette: Wednesday-Saturday, 11am-midnight; Sunday, 12pm-5pm.']

label: Bar 228
comment: Bar 228, at Le Meurice in Paris, is an emblematic place where guests can enjoy exquisite cocktails in a hushed atmosphere. Every evening, live jazz accompanies this exceptional moment. A popular spot for a refined break, the bar offers tailor-made cocktails by mixology experts. The decor, by Philippe Starck, is modern and elegant, attracting a chic clientele. Bar 228 embodies luxury à la française, inviting you to savor unique moments.

label: Atelier Maître Albert
comment: L'Atelier Maître Albert, an extension of the famous Guy Savoy house, is a rotisserie located in a quiet street in the Latin Quarter, close to the Seine. Modern yet traditional, the establishment offers different areas to suit all tastes: the Vinothèque for a quick break, the Bibliothèque lounge for a warm atmosphere, and the Salle Cheminée for an intimate, romantic setting. In the kitchen, generous and delicious market cuisine awaits guests.

label: Piscine Keller
comment: The Keller pool is the ideal place for sports enthusiasts and keen swimmers! With its 50-meter pool, it's perfect for sporty swimming. In summer, its ceiling opens up for swimming under the Paris sky. In addition to swimming laps, you'll find a variety of activities such as gentle gymnastics, aquagym and baby swimming. A sauna is also available for recuperation. This pool is reserved for serious swimmers, away from the dabblers!

label: La Monnaie de Paris
comment: La Monnaie de Paris, founded in 864, moved to 11 quai de Conti in Paris in 1775. Since 2017, its museum has welcomed the public to discover its manufacturing secrets, collections and crafts. Visitors can explore treasures and know-how in a playful setting. The building also houses a boutique, Guy Savoy's three-starred restaurant and a Café Frappé serving fresh local dishes. A captivating dive into the world of La Monnaie de Paris.

additional_information: ['Tuesday to Sunday from 11am to 6pm with a night-time event on Wednesday until 9pm']

label: Piscine Suzanne Berlioux
comment: Aquatic activities are suitable for all members of the family, whether you're a fan of flipper fitness, toning aqua aerobics or looking for a variety of workouts. Swimming lessons for beginners or those wishing to improve their technique are also available. Cycling enthusiasts can enjoy aquabiking, an original way of exercising in the water. There's something for everyone, with a complete range of activities to keep your body in shape and have fun at the same time.

label: History Group Store
comment: History Group excels in designing unique visitor experiences, such as PARIS BY VR. This experience allows visitors to teleport from the second floor of the Eiffel Tower to the main surrounding monuments to discover Paris in an immersive way. We are an innovative company, constantly adding value to the tours we offer.

label: Odori
comment: In the heart of La Motte-Picquet, in the 15th arrondissement of Paris, Odori offers authentic, refined Korean cuisine. Traditional flavors and dishes typical of this Asian country are served in a warm atmosphere and meticulous decor. The diversity and quality of the dishes will delight lovers of Asian cuisine, with each dish prepared with care and generosity. Odori is a must for Asian food lovers in search of an authentic experience.

label: Le Boulanger de la Tour
comment: At the foot of the Tour d?Argent, our bakery offers a variety of organic breads baked in our workshop, visible from the store. Baguettes, pies, wholemeal or corn breads, our artisan breads will seduce you. In the window, pure butter pastries, delicious cakes and travel cakes will delight your taste buds. Experience authentic craftsmanship in a marble and solid wood setting.

label: Institut suédois
comment: Immerse yourself in the history and artistic exchanges between France and Sweden through emblematic 18th- and 19th-century souvenirs. Discover also contemporary Swedish paintings that testify to the richness and diversity of today's art scene. A captivating immersion into the heart of two constantly evolving artistic worlds.

label: Gare de Paris-Bercy-Bourgogne-Pays d'Auvergne
comment: The Paris-Bercy-Bourgogne-Pays d'Auvergne station, built in the 70s, offers connections to Burgundy (TER), Clermont-Ferrand (Intercités), Italy (night trains) and OUIBUS buses to many destinations in France and Europe. You can also take the auto-train to cities such as Biarritz, Avignon, Bordeaux, Nice, Marseille and Lyon. The station is open daily from 6 a.m. to 10 p.m., including public holidays.

comment: Discover an exceptional gourmet address, nestled between the Maison de l'Amérique Latine and the Musée Maillol. At DéSIGN2, talented chef Marcelo Joulia brilliantly revisits the great classics of French gastronomy. Enjoy refined dishes such as langoustine mayo, skate wings meunière or a generous seafood platter. An exquisite culinary voyage not to be missed, in a warm and elegant setting.

comment: Artisans du Monde is committed to responsible consumption with fair trade products. They offer a wide range of products from the South: handicrafts, groceries, confectionery, cosmetics... Their online boutique offers a varied choice: cosmetics, jewelry, tableware, home decor and fashion. A great way to make meaningful purchases and support fair trade consumption.

label: Day by day
comment: Launched in May 2003, Day by Day is the first grocery store network entirely dedicated to bulk sales. With 750 products and no superfluous packaging, the chain is revolutionizing the way we consume. Committed to combating food waste and reducing waste, Day by day favors French products. By informing consumers, this network aims to be a responsible player in today's consumer issues.

You'll find sports and leisure clothing, winter and mountain sports equipment, as well as water and underwater sports equipment. Enjoy safe adventures with quality mountaineering and climbing equipment, and a wide range of products for all your outdoor activities.

label: La Bibliothèque du Film
comment: The BIFI, part of the Cinémathèque Française, brings together films from all over the world, from the beginnings of cinema to the present day. It offers a rich collection on key periods in cinema: the avant-garde of the 20s, French cinema of the 50s, the Nouvelle Vague... BIFI has a video library, two reading rooms, a research area and an icon library.

label: Chez Prune
comment: Come and enjoy a convivial moment at Prune for an aperitif with friends! Make yourself comfortable and enjoy a glass of wine with a delicious plate of charcuterie in this charming bistro overlooking the Canal Saint-Martin. The warm ambience and retro charm of the establishment will transport you back to the Paris of yesteryear.

label: Les Cocottes - Tour Eiffel
comment: In his restaurant, renowned Michelin-starred chef Christian Constant offers tasty cuisine presented in cast-iron casseroles or verrines. With a modern decor and affordable prices, customers can enjoy refined dishes without breaking the bank. A culinary experience combining quality, originality and affordability.

label: Le Barboteur
comment: Le Barboteur, a cultural barge, sails the canals of Paris and the Ile-de-France region, bringing new life to the riverbanks of Paris, Bobigny and Pantin. On the quay, an open-air terrace attracts the curious. On the foredeck, a floating stage offers free shows, while on the aft deck, a bar welcomes visitors for a drink and a bite to eat. A cultural and convivial experience not to be missed along the banks of the Seine.

label: Musée Curie
comment: Founded in 1911, the Institut du Radium brings together the laboratories of Marie Curie in physics and chemistry, and Claudius Regaud in medicine and biology. The Musée Curie, located in the former institute's Pavillon Curie, traces the history of radioactivity and its medical applications through historical instruments and photos of the Curie family, winners of five Nobel Prizes. Refurbished in 2012, the museum features an exhibition on the Curie family, radium, the Curie laboratory and the Fondation Curie's fight against cancer, offering a visit that combines science and history.

label: Le Point Virgule
comment: Le Point Virgule, a café-théâtre in the Marais district, was founded in 1975 by comedians Martin Lamotte and Gérard Lanvin. Housed in a former carpentry workshop, this intimate venue has become a benchmark for comedy and one-man shows. It has seen the emergence of many now-famous comedians, making the venue a veritable breeding ground for talent.

label: Église Saint-Léon
comment: Built in 1934, Saint-Léon church in the Grenelle district of Paris is distinguished by its Romanesque-Byzantine style. Renowned for its luminosity and harmony, Saint-Léon is one of the most remarkable modern churches in Paris. The building's chapels are embellished with statues by Henri Bouchard, and imposing mosaics add to its splendor.

label: Taxi PMR parisien
comment: The Parisian cab service TAXI PMR provides transportation for people with reduced mobility in Paris and the Ile-de-France region. Specializing in transfers to and from train stations, as well as airports such as Roissy-Charles-de-Gaulle, Orly and Beauvais, it offers its customers a customized, secure transport solution.

label: Square Saint-Lambert
comment: Square Saint-Lambert, designed by George Sébille in 1933 to replace the Vaugirard gasworks, is home to works such as René Paris's Chien (1928) and Victor Peter's Oursons. There's also a bas-relief by Auguste Guénot (1939) and a pleasant setting with a pond, lawns and a terrace overlooking the Eiffel Tower. Children enjoy playgrounds, outdoor shows and activities in the shared garden. A green haven of peace for all.

label: Bellota-Bellota Champs-Élysées
comment: In the heart of Paris, this exceptional venue offers a gastronomic plunge into Spain and Byzantium. Taste Iberian delights, from wines and charcuterie to cheeses and the famous Bellota-Bellota ham. Explore Byzantine delicacies such as prestige Russian-style smoked salmon and fresh caviar, all in a typical Byzantine setting. A unique culinary experience for lovers of exquisite flavors and authenticity.

label: Sunset-Sunside
comment: The Sunset-Sunside, Paris's must-see jazz club on rue des Lombards, welcomes music lovers. Two rooms, each seating around 100, offer a unique experience. The Sunside offers acoustic jazz, while the Sunset, in the basement, features electric jazz, electro-jazz and world music. An address for exceptional musical evenings.

comment: Discover our wide selection of used sheet music for all instruments and musical styles. With over 7,000 references available, find the ideal sheet music to enrich your repertoire. label: Auburn
comment: Enjoy the best of both worlds in one place: the coffee shop in the morning, then the wine bar in the evening. Discover a variety of freshly brewed coffees at dawn, from intense espressos to smooth cappuccinos. After dark, the café gives way to an elegant wine bar. Enjoy a selection of cheeses, charcuterie and delicacies carefully chosen to accompany each wine. A sophisticated culinary experience awaits you.

label: Piaget
comment: The prestigious Swiss brand, specialized in luxury jewelry and high-end watches, has opened its largest boutique in the world in Paris. The 510 m² showcase, designed by architect Christine Querlioz, is located on the famous Rue de la Paix. The brand's magnificent creations, including the emblematic Possession ring, are showcased in this flagship store. A must for lovers of exceptional jewelry.

label: Passy Mandarin
comment: In the heart of Paris, near the Opéra Garnier, this prestigious restaurant promises a culinary experience worthy of the greatest Chinese emperors. The exquisite dishes, prepared by talented chefs, combine tradition and creativity. Enjoy an unforgettable gastronomic experience in elegant surroundings at 6 rue d'Antin, 75002, Paris. This Michelin-starred temple to Chinese haute cuisine has an exceptional evening in store for you. Book now to savor these delights.

label: Le Comedia
comment: The Comedia, a theater on the Grands Boulevards in Paris, offers a varied program: cabaret, concerts, comedy, dance... Its auditorium can accommodate 1,000 spectators for an immersive experience. The smaller, more intimate auditorium seats around 200. Relax after the show in the mezzanine bar overlooking Boulevard de Strasbourg. A must-see address for unique cultural moments in Paris!

label: Piscine Joséphine Baker
comment: The Joséphine Baker floating pool on the Seine in Paris offers a unique setting. Moored near the François Mitterrand library, it features a 25m x 10m pool with four swim lanes. In summer, the barge unveils its roof, offering an unusual view over the Seine. There's also a 250m² sports pool, a 50m² paddling pool, solariums, saunas, hammam, jacuzzi and fitness room. A unique aquatic experience in the capital.

label: L'Arbre à Café
comment: In the heart of the Sentier, you'll find l'Arbre à Café, much more than just a store. Founded by the passionate Hippolyte Courty, this place tells the story of a man dedicated to sourcing, importing and roasting the finest vintages directly in Paris. Elevating coffee to the status of haute gastronomie, he offers tasting sessions in a dedicated lounge, all with a resolutely biodynamic approach. A unique experience for discerning coffee lovers.

label: Cœur Sacré
comment: Nestled at the foot of Montmartre's Sacré Coeur basilica, C?ur Sacré is a unique place filled with local treasures. An ethical boutique offers creations made in France, a delicatessen offers regional products to savor on the spot or to take away, and a rooftop on the 1st floor offers a breathtaking view. Embellished with works of art, this venue organizes temporary exhibitions on the theme of Paris, offering a total immersion in the capital's local crafts and culture.

Conviviality and gourmet delights reign supreme here. Perfect for family lunches, romantic dinners or evenings with friends, Chalet du 8e combines authentic flavors and a welcoming atmosphere for a unique culinary experience.

A brand of excellence that shines in the world of haute couture for the home.

comment: Wanderlust, in the heart of Paris's Cité de la Mode et du Design, is a multifaceted venue. Its terrace on the banks of the Seine offers a variety of activities: yoga, art workshops, DJ sets and film screenings. The club, very much in vogue at night, offers an electro ambience. On Sundays, the terrace becomes the Brunch Bazaar, with artists and entertainment. A place where gastronomy, art and music come together to satisfy every visitor.

label: Le mur des je t'aime
comment: The famous Mur des Je t?aime, designed by Frédéric Baron and Claire Kito, attracts lovers from all over the world to Paris, the city of love. Covering 40 m², 612 glazed lava tiles display 311 "je t?aime" in 250 languages. The scarlet hues symbolize a broken heart, trying to reconcile a fragmented humanity. Located on Place des Abbesses, in the heart of Montmartre, this monument to love moves and unites visitors from all over the world.

label: Le Bonne Nouvelle
comment: Located in the trendy Xe arrondissement, Bonne Nouvelle is a brasserie with retro 1950s charm. Its large mirrors, neon lights and old tables give the place an incomparable ambience. At lunchtime, a brasserie menu offers tartines and set menus at 15 euros. In the evenings, the place caters mainly to a clientele in their thirties and forties, without being exclusively reserved for the gay community.

label: Église Saint-Philippe du Roule
comment: On the site of a former chapel destroyed in 1739, stands the church of Saint-Philippe-du-Roule, the fruit of Louis XV's desire to provide the district with a new place of worship. Nestling on the rue du Faubourg Saint-Honoré, close to the Place de la Madeleine and Place Vendôme, its architecture evokes Roman temples, with their ancient columns. The stained glass windows on the second floor, bathed in shades of blue, are the work of Émile Hirsch.

label: Courant d'art
comment: Marie-Josée Grandjean offers a vast collection of 150,000 works on art, including painting, sculpture, photography, design, architecture, theater... Rare, unobtainable or out-of-print books are on offer, to the delight of enthusiasts and collectors alike. A real treasure trove for visual and performing arts enthusiasts, whether novice or expert. This address is a must for literary treasure seekers.

comment: H.A.N.D., an acronym for Have A Nice Day, is a must for fans of American specialties. Bon appétit and Have A Nice Day!

comment: Discover the Spa Terraké, a luxury oasis at the Hôtel Bowmann Paris. Sapphire pool, golden mosaic, Carrara marble, Jacuzzi, hammam, sauna and fitness room promise absolute relaxation. Terraké offers personalized treatments in a setting of harmony and gentleness, for deep relaxation and absolute bliss.

label: Galerie Triple V
comment: Since September 2010, Galerie Triple V has become a fixture on the Paris contemporary art scene, with exhibitions by artists such as Michael Scott, Emmanuelle Iainé and Jens Haaning. Its varied program highlights audacious creations, attracting young talents and discerning art lovers alike. Triple V is a unique platform for the discovery and promotion of contemporary art.

label: Le Dancing underground
comment: Located in the Tolbiac district of Paris's 13th arrondissement, Dancing Underground is a relaxed bar with affordable prices. Nestled in a former hotel, this 200 m² establishment boasts walls adorned with works by street artists. An ideal place to spend a pleasant moment between the Butte-aux-Cailles, the Bibliothèque François Mitterrand and the Place d'Italie.

label: MK2 Beaubourg
comment: The MK2 Beaubourg cinema is right next door to the famous Centre Pompidou, offering cinephiles a wide range of films, often in the original version. A must-see for film lovers in search of authentic discoveries and emotions. Enjoy a varied, high-quality program in a modern, friendly setting.

label: La Dame de Pic
comment: Anne-Sophie Pic, three-star chef from Valence, has opened a new restaurant in Paris. Bruno Borrione has perfectly combined white and raw wood to create a sober, warm setting. Pic's cuisine is characterized by exquisite aromas, offering a unique culinary experience with every menu. An unmissable address for lovers of haute gastronomy.

label: Jardin Atlantique
comment: Next to Montparnasse station, this garden is a haven of peace, with its century-old trees, shady paths and colorful flowerbeds. Ideal for a break before catching the train, or for relaxing and admiring nature, it offers calm and serenity. Far from the hustle and bustle of the city, you feel transported to a peaceful world. An enchanted interlude in the heart of the capital.

label: Bateaux Parisiens
comment: Embark on a cruise on the Seine with Bateaux Parisiens, the leading boat rental company in Paris. Enjoy an exceptional view of the capital's monuments and savor quality French cuisine made with fresh produce. Opt for an all-inclusive dinner cruise menu with aperitif, starter, main course, cheese, dessert, wine, mineral water and coffee. Contemplate the Eiffel Tower, Les Invalides, Notre-Dame and many other Parisian treasures during this unique experience.

label: Bonton Filles du Calvaire
comment: Come and discover Bonton's high-end, colorful world for 0-3 year olds over 800 m². You'll find ready-to-wear, furniture, toys, household linen... And that's not all! This unique place also offers a café, a hairdressing salon and a care area dedicated to toddlers. A must for parents in search of quality and originality for their children.

label: Skin Marceau
comment: Discover Skin Marceau, expert in dermatology and aesthetics, near the Place de l'Étoile in Paris. The team offers treatments such as HydraFacial and CO2 laser. To combat signs of aging, acne and other skin problems, you'll also find hair removal, injections and laser treatments. Skin Marceau guarantees personalized, safe and precise care to sublimate your skin.

label: Studio Hébertot
comment: Located in the Batignolles district of Paris, in the 17th arrondissement, the Studio Hébertot has a history dating back almost two centuries, to 1830. This performance venue offers a rich program of contemporary expression: texts, concerts, meetings and readings. Open to foreign companies, it offers a variety of shows that will captivate an international audience in search of artistic discoveries.

label: Duke’s Bar
comment: The Duke?s Bar, located between the Palais Garnier and Place Vendôme, is seductive with its hushed atmosphere and authentic style. With its Westminster Abbey woodwork and leather armchairs, it's the perfect place to enjoy a cocktail. Open from 4pm to 6pm for tea time, this iconic venue also serves meals. On weekdays, relaxing music accompanies guests, while weekends are enlivened by jazz. An elegant and refined stopover in Paris.

label: Café Charbon
comment: Café Charbon, open since 1900, welcomes night owls until 4am. On a lively street in the 11th arrondissement, this emblematic establishment with its Second Empire-style decor offers a unique ambience. Classic cuisine and finger foods to share are on the menu. Despite its small terrace, it enjoys excellent sunshine. Guests can also enjoy live music at the neighboring Nouveau Casino. A friendly, musical atmosphere awaits you.

label: Espace de glisse de la Muette
comment: On the edge of the Bois de Boulogne, the La Muette skatepark underwent a metamorphosis in 2012, expanding to 750m². With its giant bowl, it's THE place to be for fans of rollerblading, skateboarding, BMX and scootering. It's the place to be for thrill-seeking riders, in front of a curious public and family outings.

comment: In the heart of the Pigalle and Blanche districts, Les Trois Baudets nestles discreetly, an emblematic venue where theater and concerts by independent artists come together. Behind its art deco facade lies a friendly, intimate atmosphere that appeals to Parisians in search of cultural discoveries. A real hidden gem that's energizing the capital's artistic landscape.

label: Binet-Papillon Parfums
comment: The house of Binet-Papillon, in Paris' Galerie Vivienne, offers unique fragrances inspired by the tradition of French perfumery. Each fragrance, created by a talented "nez maison", seeks to awaken deep emotions and express your identity through evocative names such as Akemist Pepper, Ambre Demi Deuil, Patchouli Monarque and Cologne Curieuse. Travel back to the 17th century with these exceptional fragrances that will magnify your personality.

Enjoy total immersion with a variety of courses: tea ceremony, origami, calligraphy, floral art. Explore the diversity of Japanese culture!

Overlooking the Place des Fêtes, this park offers a concentrate of leisure and relaxation. Children will love the play areas, while music lovers will be charmed by the bandstand. An invitation to discovery and wonder right in the heart of the capital.

With its modern facilities and friendly atmosphere, the Drigny pool attracts a wide audience in search of well-being and vitality. A destination of choice to immerse yourself in a unique aquatic universe right in the heart of Paris.

label: Les Cognées
comment: Need to relax and let off steam? Discover Les Cognées, France's first axe-throwing center, located in the 18th arrondissement. This fun activity can be enjoyed by colleagues, friends, couples or families, for an original and exciting moment. With its ten targets and experienced instructors, the center offers a unique experience requiring skill and concentration. Let us guide and advise you for an unforgettable experience!

comment: The German brand, a pioneer in natural cosmetics, has created a haven of peace dedicated to nature. Behind its façade, a wall of plants and stone sculptures offer a relaxing experience. On the program: massages, facials, workshops on cultivating well-being, gift ideas and beauty products. Every Thursday, the "apéro bien-être" features an organic buffet and self-massages. A unique place for a gentle interlude in the heart of the city.

label: Fondation GoodPlanet / Domaine de Longchamp
comment: In the heart of the Bois de Boulogne in Paris, the GoodPlanet Foundation covers 3.5 hectares. Open from Wednesday to Sunday, it offers exhibitions, activities, guided tours and events to raise awareness of ecological issues. Free of charge and surrounded by greenery, this family-friendly venue offers discovery and exchange through exhibitions, workshops, conferences, concerts and well-being activities. A varied program is offered by a committed team.

The jewel-like bottles enhance the sensory experience offered by this prestigious house of haute parfumerie.

label: Parc Suzanne Lenglen
comment: The Parc omnisports Suzanne Lenglen, a place for relaxation and sport, offers a wide range of activities in a varied plant environment. Rhododendrons, azaleas, Japanese cherry trees and maples line a hilly path. Children have access to play areas. The educational urban farm at 82 rue Henri Farman is home to animals such as dwarf goats, Ouessant sheep, chickens, turkeys, geese, ducks and rabbits, for the enjoyment of nature-loving families.

label: Maison de Balzac
comment: The Maison de Balzac, in the heart of Passy, is the writer's last home. It was here that he wrote "La Comédie humaine". The museum exhibits his personal objects, first editions and documents on his close friends and family. Exhibitions and events are organized here. A library, concerts and readings complete the visitor experience.

label: La Mi Fa
comment: In the heart of the 11th arrondissement, Mi Fa, a neighborhood bistro nestled in a quiet side street, charms with its friendly atmosphere and artistic flair. New features include live painting performances. This atypical place celebrates authentic French cuisine, with dishes made from fresh, seasonal produce, guaranteeing impeccable quality.

Le Montmartrain

A unique experience to rediscover Montmartre!

label: Institut Booster
comment: Booster, an institute specializing in men's skin care, offers a range of services including facials, body treatments, waxing and massages. In a masculine setting with soothing blue and gray tones, a team of skilled beauticians is on hand to help you look and feel your best. Their expertise enables them to meet your specific needs for a well-groomed, confident look.

label: Big Bus Paris - Stop: Centre d'Informations - Av de l'opéra
comment: Big Bus' double-decker bus tours are the perfect way to discover Paris. Passengers hop on and off the bus as they please. One is immersed in the history, culture and architecture of Paris with commentary - informative and entertaining - available in 11 languages. From the buses' upper deck, you can admire the iconic Parisian monuments.

label: Les Pinces
comment: The Marais district is undergoing a gustatory revival with Les Pinces restaurant. Specializing in lobster, this crustacean comes from Brittany, Canada or the United States, depending on arrivals. It is prepared oven-roasted or in toasted bread, in an explosion of flavors. The addition of home fries adds a gourmet touch to this feast. An unmissable culinary stopover for lovers of exceptional products.

label: Église de la Madeleine
comment: The Madeleine church, a symbol of Haussmann-style Paris, stands between the Place de la Concorde and the Opéra Garnier. Built between 1764 and 1842, it is an atypical Greek temple without a cross or steeple, commissioned by Napoleon. Corinthian columns lead to an interior richly decorated with neo-Byzantine sculptures, paintings and mosaics by Charles-Joseph Lameire. The church features a famous organ by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll, and offers top-quality classical music concerts all year round.

label: Église et Square Sainte-Odile
comment: The church of Saint-Odile, in the 17th arrondissement of Paris, near the Porte de Champerret, is distinguished by its Byzantine architecture, with three domes and a 72-meter bell tower. Clad in pink sandstone brick, they capture the attention of visitors. The church's sumptuous interior is overflowing with decorations: sculptures, stained glass windows, a glass altar and mosaics. Next door, the peaceful Square Sainte-Odile offers trees, flowers and a playground.

label: Les Galeries Lafayette Paris Haussmann - Le Gourmet
comment: Since 1991, Galeries Lafayette Le Gourmet has been the place to be for French gastronomy, both in-store and online. With 3,500 m2 of floor space, the store brings together markets, grocery stores, cellars, boutiques and restaurants. Each floor offers mouth-watering discoveries: market and catering in the basement, world cuisine, patisserie and chocolaterie on the first floor, Le Gourmet tables and cellar on the second floor. A total immersion in the world of gastronomy.
description: Since 1991, Galeries Lafayette Le Gourmet has been the place to be for French gastronomy, both in-store and online. With 3,500 m2 of floor space, the store brings together markets, grocery stores, cellars, boutiques and restaurants. Each floor offers mouth-watering discoveries: market and catering in the basement, world cuisine, patisserie and chocolaterie on the first floor, Le Gourmet tables and cellar on the second floor. A total immersion in the world of gastronomy.

label: Musée national Jean-Jacques Henner
comment: Jean-Jacques Henner, winner of the famous Grand Prix de Rome for painting in 1858, began his career in Alsace and ended it in Paris, adorned with multiple distinctions. Much of his prolific work is now on show in a superb private mansion built during the Third Republic, near the Parc Monceau. An invitation to the public to rediscover the work of an exceptional artist of his time.

label: Puma Store
comment: True to the brand's standards, this store stands out for its focus on fashion rather than specialized sports equipment. It features a wide selection of soccer shirts from the leading African teams, all made by Puma. A must for fashion and soccer enthusiasts looking for trendy, authentic products.

label: Jardin de l'église évangélique luthérienne Saint-Jean-Denys-Bulher
comment: Square Denys Bülher is an oasis of calm and serenity, untouched by the hustle and bustle of the city. Little-known to the general public, this garden, adjoining the parish church of Saint-Jean, offers a haven of peace conducive to contemplation. The presence of a charming half-timbered house lends a special cachet to this modest but welcoming space. Perfect for a Zen interlude in the heart of the city.

label: Marie Labarelle
comment: Marie Labarelle, an architect by profession, distinguishes herself by her ability to create original pieces from quality materials, with surprising design, elegant proportions and poetic curves. Her creativity and know-how enable her to offer unique, refined creations that will delight lovers of design and art.

Her creativity and know-how enable her to offer unique, refined creations that will delight lovers of design and art.

label: Quai liberté - Table de Wu et guinguette
comment: The on-board restaurant seats 80, with a breathtaking view of the Statue of Liberty, and features bistronomic cuisine by Chef Alfredo Martin. Located along the banks of the Seine, the guinguette, open from May to October, extends over 1000m2. It offers a festive, friendly atmosphere where you can enjoy street food, beers and cocktails at attractive prices. Enjoy a unique culinary and festive experience right in the heart of Paris!

label: Studio Harcourt Paris
comment: Since 1934, Studio Harcourt has been illustrating French excellence with its distinctive light. Immerse yourself in the world of black and white cinema and have your images immortalized by renowned experts. Labelled a "living heritage company", it unveils its treasures and invites you to discover its heritage. Café Harcourt is open Tuesday to Thursday from 10am to 6pm, and on Fridays and Saturdays until 11pm to extend your visit. The exhibition is open Monday to Saturday, 10am to 6pm.

label: Nadine Delépine
comment: Since 1991, Nadine Delépine has been designing jewelry in Paris, inspired by nature, travel and the hustle and bustle of Parisian life. Each piece is handcrafted in her boutique workshop, showcasing artisanal know-how and the "Fabriqué à Paris" label. Materials are carefully chosen and lovingly crafted for unique, personalized jewelry. Discover Nadine Delépine's authentic creations, imbued with poetry and delicacy.

label: REDIRECT 301 - 4 roues sous 1 parapluie
comment: Discover Paris in an original way with 4 wheels under 1 umbrella! Climb aboard the legendary 2CV for an intimate guided tour. Explore the sumptuous avenues and narrow cobbled streets of the City of Light in the company of a driver in a Saint James sailor suit. Enjoy the comfort of a 2CV equipped with cushions, blankets and a sunroof for a unique experience. Choose from a range of themes and let your chauffeur tell you all about them. A tailor-made escapade for a unique discovery of Paris!

label: Brasserie Bellanger
comment: In the heart of the lively district between Poissonnière and Barbès, Brasserie Bellanger invites you to savor authentic, mouth-watering French cuisine (b?uf bourguignon, sôle meunière...) in a classic Parisian brasserie atmosphere. The selection is limited to guarantee the freshness of the products, while offering affordable prices. A must for a convivial French culinary experience.

label: Le Baratin
comment: Le Baratin, an authentic Parisian bistro, offers a magnificent selection of natural wines and delicious local cuisine. It's the ideal place to indulge and discover the delights of French gastronomy. A must for lovers of good food and culinary discoveries in Paris.

label: Les Prairies de Paris
comment: Marseille-based petticoat brand Les Prairies de Paris has passed on a passion for beautiful materials to its designer, Laëtitia Ivanez. Today, she dresses women with modern cuts and impeccable finishes, perpetuating the brand's heritage of quality and elegance.
description: Marseille-based petticoat brand Les Prairies de Paris has passed on a passion for beautiful materials to its designer, Laëtitia Ivanez. Today, she dresses women with modern cuts and impeccable finishes, perpetuating the brand's heritage of quality and elegance.

label: Twinkie breakfasts
comment: Located in the heart of Paris's lively Étienne Marcel district, Twinkie Breakfasts takes its name from a delicious cupcake beloved of young Americans. In a New York loft atmosphere, you can enjoy bagels, cheesecakes, soups, pancakes and French toast. The highlight of this place? A generous brunch served daily, except Mondays. Enjoy a culinary experience that's both authentic and deliciously inspired.

label: Atelier Cologne
comment: Atelier Cologne, the first Maison de Parfum dedicated to Cologne, presents Cologne Absolue, a revolutionary collection combining citrus and noble essences. Each fragrance intensely captures the emotion of a precious moment, offering balanced creations with an exceptional scent. An ode to elegance and olfactory originality.

label: Steak Point – Yves-Marie Le Bourdonnec
comment: Located on the first floor of Galeries Lafayette, Steak Point offers a gourmet break for carnivores in the middle of a shopping spree. The menu features a tempting selection of burgers, meat tartars, bavettes and beef pavés. Dishes are prepared in front of guests, guaranteeing impeccable freshness and quality. A perfect option for recharging the batteries before resuming your visit to the shelves of the legendary Parisian department store.

label: L'Astrance
comment: The L'Astrance restaurant, close to the Trocadero and overlooking the Eiffel Tower, is orchestrated by talented Michelin-starred chef Pascal Barbot. Each course promises an unforgettable culinary experience, with a succession of surprising and delicious dishes. There's no a la carte menu here, just surprise. Prior reservation is essential for this exceptional gastronomic experience.

label: Nouveau Casino
comment: Located in the vibrant Oberkampf district, the Nouveau Casino is a veritable musical institution, showcasing the rock and electro scenes. An emblematic venue for trendy music, it's the place to be for fans of today's sounds. As well as being a concert venue, the Nouveau Casino transforms itself into a club, offering a festive and convivial atmosphere. A must for night owls in search of new musical discoveries.

additional_information: ['Concerts are usually scheduled from 7:30 pm. The club is open from midnight.']

label: Comédie-Française - Salle Richelieu
comment: Since 1680, the Comédie-Française has welcomed over 1,000 authors and 2,600 plays to its repertoire. The Salle Richelieu, designed by architect Victor Louis, offers an Italian-style auditorium seating 860. Every week, a varied program of shows alternates between the two venues. A fine theatrical tradition that has endured for over three centuries.

label: Square Auguste Renoir
comment: Located near Porte de Vanves, the Auguste Renoir garden celebrates the memory of the famous painter. Popular with bocce players and children alike, it offers facilities suitable for all. The garden is also home to a shared garden area, ideal for getting together and socializing. An ideal place to relax in the heart of the city.

label: Le Cambodge
comment: Discover unique Cambodian cuisine at this family-run restaurant. Take control by writing down your order for a personalized experience. Savor authentic dishes prepared with passion. And best of all, take your favorite dishes home with you to prolong the pleasure. A memorable culinary experience awaits you!

label: Clasico Argentino (Place des Vosges)
comment: Clasico Argentino, an Argentinian oasis in the heart of Paris, offers bewitching South American flavors. Close to Place des Vosges, this restaurant offers homemade empanadas and helados to be enjoyed at the counter, with a breathtaking view of the emblematic arcades. Take these Argentinian delights on a picnic in the Marais gardens. El Carrito food truck invites you to discover Argentina in Paris. Enjoy this sensory culinary escapade!

label: Maison Caillau
comment: The Maison Caillau boutique offers quality hairdressing accessories, handcrafted in France: combs, barrettes, headbands, knots... It also offers a wide range of beauty accessories, including brushes, tweezers, mirrors and more. A must for lovers of quality, French-made products.

label: Marlusse et Lapin
comment: The Marlusse et Lapin bar, discreetly tucked away, offers a surprising interior: a hotel room enlivened by a young, festive clientele in search of refreshments. Sofas, beds, desks and sewing machines create a warm atmosphere ideal for convivial moments. With its varied menu of affordable drinks, its many exotic "shots" and its lively atmosphere, this place is a must for lively evenings.

label: Cop-Copine
comment: At Cop-Copine, originality is the order of the day, with off-trend, unstructured and asymmetrical garments that enhance the feminine silhouette. Inspired by men's suits, the designs feature patchworks of materials with a touch of Asian influence. A bold and inventive brand that likes to play with fashion codes to offer a unique and resolutely modern style.

label: Le Cinquante
comment: Ideally located at 50 rue de Lancry, Le Cinquante seduces with its retro 50s ambience. Just 50 m from the Canal Saint-Martin, this bar with its vintage decor offers a warm, intimate setting. Two hidden rooms allow you to socialize until 2am. The menu features local dishes, cocktails and a selection of wines. Concerts enliven the evenings. An unmissable address for an immersion into the festive world of the 50s.

label: Breakfast In America - Right Bank
comment: Discover the innovative concept of American-style breakfasts to get your day off to a great start! Enjoy a variety of sweet and savory dishes such as pancakes, scrambled eggs, crispy bacon, fresh fruit, yogurt and much more. A balanced feast to recharge your batteries and make the most of your morning. A treat for the taste buds to share with family and friends!

label: Le Petit Journal Saint-Michel
comment: Just a stone's throw from the Luxembourg Gardens, the Petit Journal Saint-Michel, anchored in the Latin Quarter, pays homage to the cultural effervescence of Saint-Germain-des-Prés in the 50s. A hushed atmosphere, a live jazz band and a dinner concert make this place a must for music lovers. Immerse yourself in the swinging Paris of the 20th century and enjoy a warm and enchanting evening.

additional_information: ['Every day, concerts from 8:30 pm. Consumption without meal: 1 drink, serving as entrance fee, from 20€ to 25€. Students: from 11€ to 15€. Subsequent drinks: 7€ to 10€.']

label: Goûtu
comment: Le Goûtu offers a selection of fresh, tasty sandwiches, made to order, for just 1?. For those with a sweet tooth, more elaborate options are available for up to 3? On the menu: Mimosa egg, cucumber, tomato tartar, salad; Chiffonnade de Jambon blanc, beurre salé... A treat for the taste buds at a low price!

label: Pathé Wepler
comment: The Pathé Wepler cinema, with 14 screens on two sites, offers optimal conditions for a quality cinematic experience. All are air-conditioned and tiered, with high-definition sound for total immersion. Spacious seats guarantee comfort and relaxation. A varied program of French and original films means that moviegoers can enjoy a wide range of films all year round.

street: 14 boulevard de Clichy - 8 avenue de Clichy

label: Le Ragueneau
comment: In the heart of Paris's 1st arrondissement, Ragueneau enjoys a privileged location, close to cultural gems such as the Palais-Royal, the Comédie Française, the Louvre and the Opéra de Paris. In addition to its services as a tearoom, it regularly hosts jazz music evenings, offering visitors a unique and spellbinding experience. An exceptional place where art, history and relaxation come together in harmony.

label: Bouillante à La Samaritaine
street: La Samaritaine - 1er étage - 9 rue de la Monnaie

label: Bibliothèque nationale de France - Bibliothèque-musée de l’Opéra
comment: The Opera Library-Museum, guardian of its rich historical heritage dating back three centuries, offers visitors the chance to plunge into its prestigious past. Through thematic temporary exhibitions and a permanent gallery, the museum unveils a captivating array of meticulously sculpted paintings, drawings and set models. A true invitation to explore the fascinating world of opera, between tradition and modernity.

additional_information: ['Research library (reading room): Monday-Saturday, 10am-5pm. Exhibitions: daily (except for exceptional closures), 10am-5pm.']

label: Dodo
comment: Created in 1995, Dodo is the first jewel to offer talking messages. The collection, inspired by animals, features original, meaningful pendants. Messages of love, friendship or humor enable wearers or givers to communicate their emotions with subtlety. Dodo pendants help strengthen emotional bonds in a tender, playful way.

label: Le Zèbre de Belleville
comment: Le Zèbre, in Belleville, is an exceptional cabaret where talented artists put on incredible acts: a fluttering trapeze artist, captivating jugglers, a mischievous magician and an impressive tightrope walker. After the show, they share a drink or even a dance with the audience. Le Zèbre also offers concerts and circus workshops. An unforgettable experience of laughter, emotion and sharing, a must at Le Zèbre de Belleville.

label: Paris Store
comment: For those who love Asian cuisine, this store is a veritable paradise. You'll find everything you need to concoct authentic dishes: rice, noodles, spices, condiments, teas, fruit, vegetables, seaweed, soups, tofu, pastries... Connoisseurs and expatriates alike flock to discover the culinary treasures of Asia. A true voyage of the senses through the flavors and aromas of the Orient.

label: Bar La Sardine
comment: Nestled in a secret little square in the 10th arrondissement, this wine and tapas bar is a veritable oasis. Its terrace is a popular summer retreat. Enjoy daily specials, fresh salads and original tapas. Quality, innovative cuisine delights the taste buds of customers in search of authentic flavors.

label: Espace de glisse rue Léon Cladel
comment: Located on rue Léon Cladel, near the Bourse, the skate park is a first for the city. This picturesque pedestrian-only street, lined with Haussmann-style buildings, attracts rollerblading, skateboarding and scooter enthusiasts. A 60-metre track, recognizable by its green color, welcomes teenagers and families. Curious onlookers admire the acrobatics of the riders in a festive atmosphere. A great initiative to revitalize the town and provide a leisure space for all.

label: Aux Trois Violons - Matouchka
comment: Located in the heart of Paris, between the emblematic squares of Bastille and République, Aux Trois Violons - Matouchka is a must for lovers of Russian gastronomy. Come and discover delicious dishes from the cold, such as zakouski, pelmini borch and chachliks. The authentic, tasty cuisine is enhanced by a fine selection of vodkas. Every evening, an orchestra entertains at dinner, adding a festive touch to this unique culinary experience.

label: La Colline Skincare
comment: In just fifteen years, this brand has established itself as a benchmark in cell biology. Swiss know-how and Parisian sophistication combine in products of pure design for a unique sensory experience. The refined ambience and contemporary architecture, blending white and red, create an environment conducive to relaxation and serenity, reminiscent of the Alps and technological expertise. A perfect combination for in-depth pampering.

label: Maison Ryst Dupeyron
comment: Since its creation in 1905, the prestigious Maison Ryst Dupeyron has excelled in the art of vintage wines and spirits. Proud of its family heritage, it is renowned for its Armagnacs of exceptional quality. In addition to its range of distinguished Armagnacs, the house offers a unique selection of rare vintage whiskies and ports, as well as a wide variety of top-of-the-range wines. An essential reference for lovers of excellent spirits.

label: Casino de Paris
comment: The famous Casino de Paris, an emblematic music-hall venue, has played host to great artists such as Line Renaud and Serge Gainsbourg. Today, stars such as Jacques Higelin, Alain Souchon, Ben Harper, Gad Elmaleh, Muriel Robin and Jamel Debbouze perform here. Its varied programming includes musicals such as Starmania and Chicago, as well as original shows like Stomp and Arturo Brachetti. An essential stage for French and international culture.

label: Chez Moune
comment: Formerly Pigalle's women's cabaret, this club now offers an eclectic, cutting-edge musical program combining electro, house and deep house. Open Wednesday to Saturday from 11.30pm to 6am, it offers lively, trendy evenings. Take advantage of free admission on Wednesdays and Thursdays to discover this not-to-be-missed venue on the Paris nightlife scene.

Open Wednesday to Saturday from 11.30pm to 6am, it offers lively, trendy evenings. Take advantage of free admission on Wednesdays and Thursdays to discover this not-to-be-missed venue on the Paris nightlife scene.

label: La Coupole
comment: Since 1927, La Coupole has embodied the history of Montparnasse with its emblematic Brasserie and Dancing. Its art deco decor, listed as a historic monument, is ideal for your events. Enjoy a menu rich in flavors, created by the Chef and his passionate team. Fresh produce is sublimated to offer you the great classics of the brasserie, convivial dishes reflecting the soul of the place. Tradition and modernity blend elegantly in this unique setting.

label: Supernature
comment: The organic canteen offers a simple, friendly setting, with uncluttered decor and attentive service. Walls adorned with paintings of meadows and cows add a rustic touch. The menu includes soups, salads, cheeses, desserts, a cheeseburger and pumpkin risotto, all fresh, organic and homemade. A real treat for the taste buds in a warm, environmentally-friendly atmosphere.

label: Studio des Ursulines
comment: The Studio des Ursulines is known for its youth-oriented programming, featuring art house films. These screenings are designed to introduce children to original and profound cinematographic works. What's more, meetings between film buffs are regularly scheduled to discuss and debate the films being screened. A great initiative to awaken young minds to the richness of the world of cinema.

label: Samaritaine Paris Pont-Neuf
comment: La Samaritaine, a Paris landmark, is more than just a department store. Its century-old history reflects a unique creativity. After 16 years of closure, this Parisian landmark is back with a fresh, dynamic style. Between beauty and young designers' creations, discover the French art of living. La Samaritaine attracts visitors from all over the world in search of Parisian authenticity and irresistible charm.

label: Puzzle Michèle Wilson
comment: Discover Michèle Wilson jigsaw puzzles: artistic, eco-friendly and stimulating! Made in France from wood sourced from sustainable forests, these puzzles cut reproductions of works of art into small pieces faithful to the original motif. A perfect balance between creativity, ecology and challenge!

label: Les Mah-Boules
comment: Located in the 18th arrondissement, Les Mah-boules is both a bar and a place to relax, with pétanque lanes, foosball tables, dartboards, pinball machines and even karaoke. It's the ideal place to have fun and share a convivial moment with friends, colleagues or family. An original and friendly entertainment venue to discover without further delay.

label: L'Européen
comment: In the heart of Paris, opposite the Gare de Lyon, you'll find L'Européen, a legendary brasserie with undeniable charm. Renowned for its warm ambience and refined decor by SLAVIK, this cult address offers a unique setting. Its terrace is perfect for enjoying the lively boulevard Diderot while sipping a coffee or savoring a delicious meal. L'Européen combines tradition and modernity for memorable moments. An address not to be missed in the heart of the capital.

label: Bernardaud
comment: Since 1863, the prestigious Limoges porcelain manufacturer, acquired by Léonard Bernardaud in the 19th century, has combined traditional expertise with bold modern creativity. The company offers a refined range of tableware, limited editions signed by renowned designers, and a charming collection of jewelry. Centuries-old expertise at the service of beauty and elegance.

label: La Contre Allée
comment: Come and discover a warm and colorful haven of peace, where a Japanese chef who is an expert in French cuisine regales you with his delights. On sunny days, you can also enjoy your favorite dishes on the restaurant's sunny terrace. An ideal place for a gourmet getaway full of flavors and discoveries!

label: Café des 2 moulins
comment: Start your day with a delicious breakfast at Paris's famous Café des 2 Moulins. Do you know this place where Amélie Poulain had her adventures? Sit down at a table in this mythical place and perhaps, like her, meet your destiny. A magical gourmet experience awaits you.

label: Le Grand Véfour
comment: In the heart of the Palais Royal garden gallery, discover an exceptional Parisian institution: the gastronomic restaurant run by talented chef Guy Martin. Renowned for its refined and creative cuisine, this establishment promises an unforgettable culinary experience in the heart of the capital. An address not to be missed by lovers of good food and top-level gastronomy.

An address not to be missed by lovers of good food and top-level gastronomy.

label: Devour
comment: With Devour, discover the authentic flavors of Paris, far off the beaten tourist track. Taste traditional dishes and local wines, visit boutiques and chat with artisans. Savor croissants in the Marais or cheeses in the Latin Quarter, and discover Hemingway's legacy.

label: Gibus
comment: Le Gibus, a popular gay club near Place de la République in the 11th arrondissement of Paris, offers eclectic evenings such as "BBB" (RnB), "Bictch Party" (remixed pop) and "Excite" (house). Whatever the style, the aim is to get party-goers from all over Europe moving. Renowned for its renowned DJs and quality performances, the Gibus, with its young and dynamic team, knows how to satisfy its night owls.

label: United Colors of Benetton
comment: Founded in Italy in the 1960s, Benetton was initially renowned for its sweaters and cardigans. Proudly sporting 48 colors per collection, the brand now enjoys international renown. Its basic clothing for the whole family stands out for its excellence and durability, making Benetton a fashion staple.

label: Musée Rodin Paris
comment: Ideally located in the heart of Paris, the Rodin Museum is exceptionally close to the Eiffel Tower and Les Invalides. In an enchanting setting combining an 18th-century mansion with a 3-hectare sculpture garden, you can admire Rodin's masterly work. Between the rocaille architectural elegance of the Hôtel Biron and the splendor of the sculpture garden, your visit promises to be unforgettable.

label: Le Jardin des Plantes - Muséum national d'histoire naturelle
comment: The Jardin des Plantes, in the heart of Paris and founded four centuries ago, is world-renowned for its greenery. Covering 2.5 hectares, visitors can stroll among ancient trees, imposing statues and winding paths. The garden is home to unique plant collections and historic galleries such as the Grande Galerie de l'Évolution, highlighting biodiversity. The Menagerie and Grandes Serres offer a tropical immersion in the heart of the city.

label: Centre Wallonie-Bruxelles
comment: The Centre Wallonie-Bruxelles showcases emerging and established artists from the Wallonia-Brussels Federation in Paris and France. With a varied palette ranging from visual and performing arts to cinema and literature, it helps promote the Belgian art scene. A showcase of creativity and diversity to discover.

label: Renaud Pellegrino
comment: Renaud Pellegrino never ceases to innovate, offering new models while revisiting his cult creations. His expertise in fashion is reflected in every piece, combining elegance and originality. With a keen sense of allure and an eye for uniqueness, he continues to radiate his creative talent through his collections.

label: Le Bateau de Safran
comment: Discover an exceptional 400 m² collection of authentic and surprising objects, unearthed by Sophie Lescot during her travels in India. This boutique offers an extraordinary shopping experience, combining culture and craftsmanship. A true invitation to travel through carefully selected, one-of-a-kind treasures.

label: Cucina Africa
comment: The Cucina restaurant, the fruit of collaboration between Ducasse Restaurant and GL events, opens at the Maison de la Mutualité under the direction of Jean-Michel Wilmotte. The cuisine is authentic and generous, with first-rate ingredients for simple dishes such as pizzette, antipasti, linguine alle vongole, Di Pesce, Tiramisu, Zuppa Inglese and homemade gelato al cioccolato. Quality Italian wines are also available to accompany this exquisite feast.

label: Parc zoologique de Paris - Muséum national d’histoire naturelle
comment: Discover the Parc Zoologique de Paris on 14.5 hectares of unspoilt nature. Explore five biozones over 4km, home to over 3,100 animals of 255 different species. Watch bush dogs, manatees and European otters evolve in their natural habitat. Close to the Porte Dorée metro station, the zoo offers a range of practical services. Enjoy an unforgettable experience focused on animal welfare and discovery.

label: Église Saint-Ephrem des Syriaques
comment: In the heart of Paris' Latin Quarter, near the Sorbonne University, lies the parish of Saint-Ephrem. Built in the 18th century on 14th-century foundations, this Syriac Catholic church is a historic gem. In addition to its history, Saint-Ephrem offers a varied cultural program, including classical music concerts. A visit combining heritage and art, for a unique spiritual and cultural experience in Paris.

label: Paroisse Saint-Pierre du Gros Caillou
comment: The neo-classical Saint-Pierre du Gros Caillou parish church features a façade inspired by Antiquity, with Doric columns, sculpted friezes and triangular pediments. Built in the 18th century, the church is distinguished by its imposing bell tower and harmonious proportions. An emblematic monument of the district, it attracts many visitors, testifying to the history and cultural richness of Paris. Its architectural beauty and peaceful ambience appeal to lovers of serenity during religious ceremonies.

label: Ground Control Paris
comment: Ground Control, located in a former SNCF warehouse in the 12th arrondissement, offers a multi-purpose living space. The "Zone franche" includes a market, a stage for acoustic concerts, a photo studio and an art gallery. The 1,500 m² "Grand verger" terrace offers a peaceful refuge from the hustle and bustle of the city. The "Halle à manger" offers a variety of foreign cuisines, from Mexican to African. A unique experience to discover.

label: Les 110 de Taillevent
comment: Immerse yourself in a warm and friendly atmosphere, savoring dishes prepared by passionate chefs. Let yourself be guided by professional service in this exceptional establishment. This brasserie, a landmark of French gastronomy, will meet all your expectations. With friends, family or for a business meal, come and enjoy a unique culinary experience.

label: Square Jean XXIII
comment: Square Jean XXIII, located behind the majestic Notre-Dame de Paris cathedral, offers a quiet refuge from the hustle and bustle of the city. Dotted with inviting benches and shady trees, it's the ideal spot for a relaxing break or a quick meal away from the cathedral's constant stream of visitors. The unobstructed view of the building's chevet adds a touch of magic to this undeniably charming little corner of greenery.

label: Bicloune
comment: Located under an arch on the Viaduc des Arts, the Bicloune showroom-boutique offers a wide range of bikes: new, vintage and second-hand. In addition to bicycles, Bicloune also offers accessories, spare parts and repair services. A must for bike enthusiasts looking for quality products and professional service.

label: Popelini
comment: Located in the Marais district of Paris, Popelini is renowned for its delicious cream puffs. Available in a variety of flavors, these little marvels satisfy every taste bud. From classic flavors such as coffee, chocolate or praline for purists, to original variations such as pistachio, caramel or rose for lovers of novelty, there's something for everyone. An explosion of tastes for an unforgettable sweet experience.

label: Ciné 13 Théâtre
comment: In the heart of Montmartre, close to the famous Moulin Rouge, you'll find Ciné 13 Théâtre, renowned for its intimate 100-seat venue. This dynamic space combines theater, music and dance, offering an abundance of creative opportunities. An artistic crossroads where unique events such as the Festival Mises en Capsules, short film screenings, acoustic concerts and much more follow one another. A cultural address not to be missed in Paris.

label: Vasimimile
comment: Vasimimile invites you to shine on your bike with accessories made in France near Grenoble. Vests, armbands, belts, our products combine originality and visibility. Discover our special PARIS vest, comfortable, practical and uniquely designed. Adjustable, ergonomic and made in France, it ensures safety and style for your bike rides in the capital. Treat yourself or a loved one to the Vasi Izocel Vasimimile vest, for safe and stylish cycling in Paris!

label: Nodus
comment: Since 1995, Nodus has been revolutionizing men's fashion with shirts and ties in refined colors, made from quality materials such as silk, linen, cotton and cashmere. In addition to its range of shirts and ties, the brand also offers matching jackets, sweaters, polo shirts and accessories for a complete, elegant look. A true invitation to refinement and elegance for the modern man.

label: Écluse des Récollets
comment: The Récollets lock, one of the nine double locks on the Canal Saint-Martin built in 1825, can be seen along the canal, surrounded by the charming Grange aux Belles and Bichat footbridges. Close to the Square des Récollets and Jardin Villemin, it offers a breathtaking view of the Hôtel du Nord, made famous by Marcel Carné's film of the same name starring Arletty. A romantic walk steeped in history in the heart of Paris.

label: Au Bourguignon du Marais
comment: Le Bourguignon du Marais, on the banks of the Seine, continues to delight with its traditional cuisine and Parisian savoir-faire. On the menu are the great bistro classics: ?ufs en meurette, veal kidneys with mustard, escargots, foie gras... But the star of the show is the b?uf bourguignon, simmered in its own cocotte. To complete the feast, choose from a fine selection of wines. A delight for the taste buds to savor in a warm, authentic setting.

label: Mobilier national / Les Gobelins
comment: The Mobilier National, founded in 1663, furnishes official palaces including the Élysée Palace. The Manufacture Nationale des Gobelins, founded in the 15th century, offers guided tours of its 17th-century site. These workshops produce continuously. In 1937, the three historic factories merged at Gobelins, exhibiting nearly 200,000 pieces in the Galerie de 1914, blending tradition and modernity.

label: Marché Saint-Eustache - Les Halles
comment: In the heart of the French capital, you'll find a charming food market inaugurated in 2005. Some twenty merchants offer an enticing variety of products: fruit and vegetables, some organic, cosmetics, meats, wines... A must-see for lovers of fresh, quality produce, ideal for discovering the delights of Parisian gastronomy.

label: Au bonbon royal
comment: In the heart of the 17th arrondissement, near the Parc Monceau, you'll find Au Bonbon Royal, a veritable sweet heaven. Its magnificent 19th-century façade is a real eye-catcher, and inside you'll find a wealth of delicious creations inspired by traditional craftsmanship. Chocolates from all over the world, melting ganaches, exquisite truffles, irresistible orangettes... a mouth-watering assortment awaits you. For the curious, all these products are also available online. Don't miss this unique gustatory experience in this sweet showcase!

comment: At the heart of the intersection between public and private space, Le Plateau is positioned as a major cultural hub. This space dedicated to contemporary creation offers a unique synergy between the visual arts, dance and music. A veritable artistic crossroads where different forms of expression intersect and intermingle. A true source of inspiration and creation for all art lovers.

label: Cirque Romanès
comment: At Porte Maillot, you'll find the big top of the Romanès circus. No caged wild beasts here, but a show where poetry reigns supreme, acrobatics defy gravity and gypsy dance bewitches. A unique universe where magic happens, talents meet and emotions are palpable. Discover this atypical circus combining art, tradition and modernity in a whirlwind of colors and sensations.

additional_information: ['Saturday and holidays, 4pm and 8:30pm; Sunday, 4pm. December 31st: from 9pm to dawn for the "Grand réveillon Tzigane"']

label: Candelaria
comment: La Candelaria, a Mexican taqueria popular with hipsters and trendy expatriates, hides a secret bar renowned for its refined cocktails. Muffled ambience, stone walls and comfortable armchairs create a warm atmosphere, accompanied by a soundtrack selected by talented DJs. This venue has set the trend for sophisticated cocktail bars in Paris.

label: Épicerie Générale
comment: L'Épicerie Générale, in South Pigalle (SoPi), offers French, organic and seasonal products to eat in or take away. For those in a hurry, a ready-made organic picnic basket is ideal, to be collected from the store or delivered. Choose a wicker case or games to rent for your country lunches. Two addresses: SoPi and 43 rue de Verneuil in the 7th arrondissement.

label: Le Ritz Club Paris
comment: The Ritz Club Paris, located in the heart of Place Vendôme, is one of the capital's most prestigious wellness addresses. Featuring a CHANEL treatment menu, one of Paris's most emblematic swimming pools, a fitness area with personalized coaching, a private club and a hairdressing area entrusted to Australian hairstylist-star David Mallet, this exceptional venue promises a moment of incomparable relaxation and luxury.

label: Bateaux Parisiens
comment: Come aboard Bateaux Parisiens for a magical cruise on the Seine! Enjoy an hour's discovery of Paris's most beautiful monuments aboard heated, fully-glazed boats. With audio guides in 14 languages, immerse yourself in the history and architecture of the capital. Admire the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, Notre-Dame and much more from the outdoor terrace. An unforgettable adventure awaits you!

An unforgettable adventure awaits you!

label: The naked shop
comment: The Naked Shop reinvents the store concept by offering products in bulk, thus reducing the use of plastic. In addition to sustainable items, it features local products with returnable packaging to limit waste. 90% of its catalog comes from French manufacturers, emphasizing quality and craftsmanship. A simple gesture towards more responsible consumption.

label: Chez Michel
comment: Close to the Gare du Nord train station is a restaurant with the charm of a Parisian bistro, offering a culinary escape to the heart of Brittany. Behind the stoves, chef Thierry Breton revisits Breton classics to offer authentic, refined cuisine: simmered dishes, game, shellfish and other regional specialties that reveal all his savoir-faire. A unique gastronomic experience to discover without delay.

label: Emmaüs Alternatives
comment: 60 years after Abbé Pierre founded the first Emmaus community, 15,000 people united by shared values and determination are still working to combat exclusion. Emmaus Boutiques offer clothing, shoes, books, CDs and DVDs at reduced prices. Profits go directly to the association's actions.

label: La Maison des métallos
comment: La Maison des métallos in Belleville, Paris, uses live art to foster social and environmental transitions. Its monthly program includes performances, installations, workshops and more. Collaborating with artists, partners and residents, it stimulates the transitions movement by addressing themes relevant to today's society. Each CoOP (CoOPérative artistique) is an opportunity to discover and participate in a committed artistic vision.

label: Parc Monceau
comment: Parc Monceau, created by the Duc de Chartres in the 17th century, is a jewel in Paris's 8th arrondissement. The gilded gates open onto a verdant space, adorned with statues, majestic trees and a variety of birds. Here you'll find the Renaissance arcade of the Hôtel de Ville and the Musée Cernuschi, dedicated to Asian art. Surrounded by luxurious buildings, this haven of peace is popular with Parisians and tourists alike, with play areas for children.

label: Librairie-boutique de l’Institut du Monde Arabe
comment: Explore the Institut du Monde Arabe bookshop for a unique cultural journey. Discover a wide selection of books, CDs, videos, postcards, posters and crafts from the Arab region. Immerse yourself in this enriching experience and appreciate cultural diversity. Don't hesitate to discover this Ali Baba's cave brimming with artistic and literary treasures.

label: Bouillon Chartier Montparnasse
comment: Founded on the idea of quality meals at affordable prices and customer loyalty, Bouillon Chartier has been a listed historic restaurant since 1984. In 2019, Bouillon Chartier Montparnasse will be reborn, offering quality cuisine at affordable prices, blending tradition and modernity to satisfy lovers of good food.

label: Il Carpaccio
comment: Savor Italy in the heart of Paris at Il Carpaccio, nestled in the prestigious Royal Monceau. In a luminous baroque decor designed by Philippe Starck, let yourself be enchanted by exceptional Italian cuisine. The desserts, designed by the renowned Pierre Hermé, promise an explosion of flavors. And as soon as the sun comes out, relax on the charming patio for an authentic culinary experience.
