street: Le Royal Monceau Raffles Paris - 37 avenue Hoche

label: Guignol Saint-Lambert
comment: Le Guignol Saint-Lambert, a puppet theater in the 15th arrondissement, has been delighting young and old alike since 1934. Located in the heart of the eponymous square, this magical venue offers top-quality shows that captivate audiences with the magic of puppetry. A living tradition that has delighted audiences for decades.

label: Musée-librairie du Compagnonnage
comment: The Compagnonnage movement is showcased in two emblematic locations in Paris. The Musée-librairie du Compagnonnage in Saint-Germain-des-Prés retraces the history of the movement with guided tours and specialized books. In the 19th arrondissement, the Aux Arts et Sciences réunis restaurant is a favorite of Compagnons Charpentiers. Its decor showcases the carpenter's trade, and a secret room contains works of art from the 19th century, offering a fascinating immersion experience.

label: Pianovins
comment: Le Pianovins, a Michelin-starred and Gault & Millau-acclaimed restaurant, boasts a crack team: a chef and sommelier who worked with Guy Savoy. In an intimate 20-cover setting, this establishment offers exceptional French cuisine, sublimated by seasonal produce. A must for lovers of refined gastronomy.

label: Le Duplex Paris
comment: Located near the Arc de Triomphe, Le Duplex is a trendy club appreciated by a young clientele. Its theme nights are very popular. The club's restaurant, Le Vogue, serves French cuisine in a cosy, trendy setting. The venue can be fully privatized for unusual events, such as its elegant bowling alley dedicated to special events. For more information, visit www.leduplex-event.com.

label: Le Stella
comment: An emblematic restaurant of the 50s, this chic brasserie is renowned for its fresh oysters delivered daily, its succulent seafood platters, and its variety of traditional French specialties. A true gastronomic institution, it will delight lovers of authentic, refined cuisine in an elegant, timeless setting. An unmissable stopover for lovers of fine dining.

label: La Bonbonnière de Marie
comment: Come and dine at Marie's Bonbonnière, in the heart of the Champ de Mars gardens. Discover a wide choice of mouth-watering dishes: salads, crêpes, hot dogs, pizzas, sandwiches, waffles, cotton candy, ice creams. Take advantage of the peaceful atmosphere to relax, while admiring the century-old swings and the "Eiffel Tower" spinning tops that won a prize at the Lépine competition in 2003. A unique place not to be missed on your visit to Champ de Mars.

label: Théâtre du Gymnase Marie Bell
comment: Opened in 1820, the Théâtre du Gymnase was originally a training ground for students at the Conservatoire. It has been the birthplace of many works by great authors such as Marcel Pagnol, Jean Cocteau and Sacha Guitry. Classified as a historic monument and located on the Grands Boulevards, this theater today offers a rich program of comedies, perpetuating its tradition of excellence.

label: Non Solo Cucina
comment: The Sicilian trattoria exudes a warm and friendly atmosphere, perfect for family vacations. Its cuisine offers a wide variety of dishes, from seafood and mortadella to ricotta and local wines. Every bite is a journey to the heart of Sicily, an authentic and delicious culinary experience.

label: Alambic comédie
comment: Ideally located between Montmartre's Sacré-C?ur Basilica and the Porte de Clignancourt flea market, l'Alambic Théâtre offers a varied program all year round. Comedies, classics and children's shows are on offer, satisfying a wide audience. Acting classes are also available for aspiring actors. A must for lovers of live theater in Paris.

label: Chapelle Sainte-Rita
comment: Chapelle Sainte-Rita is located on the first floor of a building acquired in 1955, on Boulevard de Clichy. It occupies a central position, halfway between the Sainte-Trinité church and the Sacré-C?ur basilica in Montmartre. This place of worship offers an oasis of serenity in the midst of the hustle and bustle of Paris. Thanks to its strategic location, it attracts many devotees and visitors in search of contemplation and spirituality.

label: La Générale
comment: La Générale offers artists of all disciplines an environment conducive to creation. Members of the association and their guests find a space adapted to their artistic needs. Managed by the association "La Générale Nord-Est", this creative cooperative offers a shared workspace where everyone can express themselves and develop their art in an original way.

label: Boucheron
comment: Founded in 1893, Boucheron is a household name in the world of jewelry. With 150 years of experience, it continues to dazzle with its unrivalled expertise. As the leading jeweler on Place Vendôme, Boucheron imposes its unique style. Diamonds, rubies, emeralds, sapphires and topazes, sublimated by the savoir-faire of the House. A prestigious heritage, elegant and refined, testifying to Boucheron's passion and excellence for over a century.

label: Les Toits Parisiens
comment: Discover Les Toits et Couvreurs Zingueurs de Paris, dedicated to roofs from Slate to Zinc. Materials, objets d'art, clothing and tools await you. Ridge ornaments, slates, dormers, bull's-eyes, weathervanes... come and discover the unique zinc and copper creations of ornamentalist Jean-Pierre Lebureau, Meilleur Ouvrier de France. Embellish your interior and exterior with these exceptional pieces.

label: FNGIC
comment: The FNGIC, France's leading association of tour guides, offers a variety of guide profiles and guided tours on its website. Sorted by language, region, theme, target audience and accessibility, you'll easily find the ideal guide for your tours. What's more, place an ad visible to FNGIC members for tailor-made proposals. Make the most of your guided tours with FNGIC!

label: Cérémonie de non-mariage
comment: Every September, lovers can celebrate their love in an original way with Montmartre's non-proposal ceremony, inspired by George Brassens. In front of the mayor and an emotional audience, this unique event ends near the "Je t'aime" wall in Square Jehan Rictus. To take part, contact the Mayor of the 18th arrondissement on +33 (0) 1 53 41 17 82 or by email at dominique.lemoine@paris.fr. A great way to declare your love in a special way!

label: Musée de l’Ordre de la Libération - Hôtel national des Invalides
comment: Immerse yourself in the history of the Compagnons de la Libération, Free France and the Resistance through three galleries and six rooms. Discover the manuscripts of General de Gaulle, the concentration camps and the memories of the fighters. Uniforms, weapons, clandestine press, transmitters and camp relics will transport you back to this historic period. A moving and enriching exhibition not to be missed.

label: EP7
comment: Located opposite the Bibliothèque nationale de France - François Mitterrand, EP7 is an atypical cultural café. With its impressive façade of 12 screens broadcasting digital programming and artistic works over 133 m², it attracts the curious in search of original discoveries. Inside, a dynamic atmosphere reigns around workshops, DJ sets and exhibitions. Please note: no on-site catering, but two terraces to enjoy the urban setting.

label: The Shell
comment: Located on the Grands Boulevards, The Shell seduces with its wide range of cocktails, including the unmissable Old Cuban. Decorated in shades of pink by Dorothée Meilichzon, the elegant ambience provides a perfect setting for savoring its creations. For a breathtaking view, head to the 2nd bar, The Shed, perched on the roof. A chic and refined experience to be discovered without delay.

label: La Boule Noire
comment: Located in Pigalle, La Boule Noire is a landmark venue in the 18th arrondissement. Formerly a renowned cabaret, it is now a concert venue showcasing young rock, pop and variety talents. Dynamic and friendly, this trendy venue offers a varied program that will appeal to music lovers in search of something new. With its intimate atmosphere and modern sounds, La Boule Noire is a must for music lovers in Paris.

label: L'oasis d'Aboukir
comment: Nestling at the intersection of rue d'Aboukir and Petits Carreaux, a plant wall, the work of Patrick Blanc, a pioneer of the concept, rises majestically over 25 meters. This lush vertical garden enriches the neighborhood with a remarkable ecological diversity of over 7,000 plants and 237 species, offering a breath of fresh air and greenery to urban passers-by.

label: Paris Bike Tour
comment: Since 2002, Paris Bike Tour has been offering bicycle tours of the city, offering a unique discovery experience. Tours last 3 hours by bike or 4 hours by electric bike, revealing the many facets of Paris. Combined tours include tastings or visits to museums such as the Louvre. Private themed tours and corporate events are also available. Bike rentals start at 12? per half-day, and Paris Bike Tour has been awarded the "Accueil vélo" label.

label: Musée de Montmartre - Jardins Renoir
comment: The rue Cortot studios have been home to famous artists such as Renoir, Camoin, Friesz, Dufy, Valadon and Utrillo. The Musée de Montmartre exhibits a collection of works by Toulouse-Lautrec, Modigliani, Steinlen and others. Immerse yourself in the history of the Butte on a guided tour of its legendary studios and cabarets. The Renoir Gardens overlook the vineyards of Clos Montmartre. An artistic and historical escapade not to be missed!

label: Klay
comment: Klay, a sports club established in the Montorgueil district, combines elegance and sobriety. With 2,000 m² of space in a former industrial factory, it offers a unique blend of retro furniture, state-of-the-art equipment, metal beams, staircases and an original glass roof. A chic yet authentic ambience for high-end sports enthusiasts.

label: Paroisse Saint-Séverin
comment: A magnificent example of the flamboyant Gothic style, the 13th- and 15th-century church is captivatingly detailed in its architecture. Its thousand-year-old bell tower houses the oldest bell in Paris, dating from the 15th century. Inside, you'll discover a 17th-century choir, twisted pillars, 17th-century paintings and rare 14th-century stained glass, not to mention 15th- and 16th-century windows. Renowned sacred music concerts are regularly held here.

label: Les Caves Populaires
comment: This cosy bar with its retro charm, red mosaic façade and eclectic decor, invites you to enjoy a variety of cocktails, beers and wines. Cheese plates and charcuterie boards are the perfect complement to the tasting experience. Here, regulars and newcomers rub shoulders in a lively, relaxed atmosphere typical of authentic neighborhood bistros.

label: Le Grand Pan
comment: With its high-quality local cuisine and friendly atmosphere, the "Grand Pan" bistro is a must. Epicureans and gourmets alike are delighted to find themselves in this establishment. Careful selection of seasonal produce and a warm welcome make this bistro one of the best in the area.

label: Dynamo
comment: Originating in New York, indoor cycling is all the rage in Paris, particularly near the Opéra Garnier. At Dynamo, sports enthusiasts can enjoy intense 45-minute cycling sessions, supervised by an experienced coach. These sessions are enlivened by playlists specially designed by renowned DJs, adding a touch of dynamism and motivation to the workout. A truly unique and motivating experience in the heart of the French capital.

label: Grey Paris - Duty free shop
comment: Right in the heart of Paris, between the Louvre and the Opera, the Louvre Grey perfumery is an essential Duty Free Shop. Cosmetics, watches, jewelry, bags, luggage, spirits... You'll find a wide selection of renowned brands. The latest trends and exclusives await you for an unforgettable high-end shopping experience.

You'll find a wide selection of renowned brands. The latest trends and exclusives await you for an unforgettable high-end shopping experience.

label: Dôme de Paris - Palais des Sports
comment: Since 1960, the Palais des Sports, recognizable by its large aluminum dome, has been a showplace. Internationally renowned, it plays host to the biggest stars and world-famous musicals, and offers a modular arena-shaped auditorium seating 2,500 to 6,200. Appreciated for its excellent visibility and human dimension, this venue is a favorite with artists and spectators alike.

label: Boutiques du Palais des Congrès
comment: Discover a refined world of high-end ready-to-wear and quality fittings to enhance your style. Among prestigious brands such as Escada, Nodus, Tumi, Lancel, Weill, Georges Rech, Lacoste, Gérard Darel and Sephora, find the trendy pieces that reflect your elegance. Let yourself be seduced by brands renowned for their expertise and excellence, for an exceptional shopping experience.

label: Jean-Marc Maniatis
comment: Renowned hairstylist Jean-Marc Maniatis presents his sophisticated new salon. In a chic neighborhood, this refined space offers a luxurious experience. The warm, elegant décor invites you to relax. A team of passionate professionals offers personalized treatments. This high-end salon is the place to be for prestige enthusiasts. Jean-Marc Maniatis has become a benchmark for luxury and elegance. A visit to this salon will be an unforgettable experience.

label: Paroisse Saint-Jacques du Haut Pas
comment: Built in the 12th century in the Latin Quarter of Paris, the Saint-Jacques du Haut Pas church is a historical treasure classified as a historic monument. Its chapel dedicated to the Virgin Mary, with its sculptures and stained-glass windows, is remarkable. Every detail testifies to the skill of the craftsmen. A guided tour reveals the secrets of this architectural gem, a witness to the capital's past. Between legends and history, the church invites you on a journey back in time to better understand its spirituality.

label: Ankka
comment: Three French friends discovered salad bars in New York and decided to import them to France, creating Ankka. Choose from homemade salads, wraps, piadines, tartines, soups and desserts for a light, personalized experience. At Ankka, enjoy a delicious lunch without worrying about calories or budget. Delivery is also available for added convenience. Discover a new, healthy approach to fast food at Ankka!

label: Franquette
comment: This bistro, near Place de Clichy, offers home cooking with Mediterranean flavors. Dishes are presented in tapas style, offering small portions at low prices for a varied tasting experience. Local products are given pride of place, accompanied by natural wines from small producers. The short but tempting menu is renewed daily to delight the taste buds. A friendly, gourmet place in the heart of the city.

label: Musée Maxim's
comment: The Pierre Cardin Museum, the fruit of the famous couturier's passion for the Belle Époque and Art Nouveau, is located above the legendary Maxim?s restaurant, an emblem of the 1900s. Spread over three floors, it plunges us into the luxurious intimacy of a courtesan who attracted the high society of the era, surrounded by treasures by Tiffany, Majorelle and Massier. A true immersion in the glamorous and mischievous Paris of the era!

label: Alléno Paris - Pavillon Ledoyen
comment: Located in the gardens of the Champs-Élysées, Alléno Paris - Pavillon Ledoyen is a renowned gastronomic restaurant. Its Art Deco decor creates a sumptuous ambience. Under the direction of chef Yannick Alléno, the restaurant holds three Michelin stars. L'Abysse offers tasty sushi and sake, while Le Pavillon offers an intimate atmosphere with its counter and terrace. A prestigious address combining luxury and gastronomy.

L'Abysse offers tasty sushi and sake, while Le Pavillon offers an intimate atmosphere with its counter and terrace. A prestigious address combining luxury and gastronomy.

label: Théâtre de la Madeleine
comment: The Théâtre de la Madeleine, one of the most prestigious private theaters in Paris, appeals to a discerning public with its Anglo-Saxon architecture and its location between Place de la Madeleine and Saint-Augustin church. Its eclectic program combines classic plays with contemporary creations, offering a diversified panorama of theater. A must-see for lovers of live entertainment in search of an enriching cultural experience.

label: Bellefeuille - Saint James Paris
comment: The Bellefeuille restaurant at the Saint James Paris hotel combines elegance and romance. Headed by chef Julien Dumas, it offers tasty cuisine featuring local produce cooked to traditional, high-quality recipes. Committed to eco-responsibility, the establishment favors a seasonal approach, using organic produce from the Clos de Nonville kitchen garden. A production that respects the environment.

label: Brasserie Bofinger
comment: Brasserie Bofinger, between Place des Vosges and Opéra Bastille, is an Alsatian institution in Paris. Its historic decor and authentic atmosphere make it a unique place where the traditional soul persists. Must-try specialities: sauerkraut, Kougloff revisited as French toast, apple strudel. An address for lovers of Alsatian gastronomy right in the heart of the capital.

label: Désirée
comment: Located in the 11th arrondissement, Désirée is more than just a café florist. Committed to an eco-responsible approach, Désirée campaigns for a fairer, more transparent economy. Its bouquets, made exclusively with seasonal French flowers, are available in limited quantities. With only 15 arrangements per day, each bouquet is unique, guaranteeing an exceptional floral experience. You can now order these marvels online.

label: Pâtisserie Aoki
comment: Renowned Japanese pastry chef Sadaharu Aoki has conquered Paris with his unique creations, blending French traditions with Japanese freshness. Fascinated by French culture, he opened his first stores in the capital, attracting the attention of major fashion houses. In 2011, his boutique in the 6th arrondissement opened its doors, offering exquisite, original creations that reflect his talent and passion. A delicious fusion of two gourmet cultures to savor!

label: Alcazar
comment: Immerse yourself in a modern, festive atmosphere at L'Alcazar, a bar-restaurant where fusion cuisine meets electro beats. Experience live cooking under the glass roof, and let yourself be charmed by this London brasserie. From Thursday to Sunday, the mezzanine is transformed into a club with renowned DJs. And don't miss their Sunday brunch, featuring traditional and international dishes. L'Alcazar offers an unforgettable culinary and musical experience.

label: Florence Porteseil
comment: Want to discover Parisian treasures with a passionate tour guide? Since 2015, enjoy friendly tours with family, friends or colleagues. From the Louvre to Orsay, via the Musée Rodin, Monet's Water Lilies at the Orangerie, the Sainte Chapelle and Père-Lachaise. Book your visit on my website, in the Contact section. I look forward to guiding you!

label: Eiffel Croisières
comment: Embark on a unique experience with Eiffel Croisières with a Bistronomique or Prestige cruise on the Seine. Departing from the Pont Alexandre III for the Bistronomique and from the Port de Debilly for the Prestige, enjoy lunch or dinner while admiring the splendors of Paris. From 59? for the Bistronomique and 79? for the Prestige (excluding drinks), treat yourself to a moment of pleasure and discovery in the heart of the capital.

label: Mojito Lab Paris
comment: Here's a unique place, the Temple du Mojito, where you can explore some twenty original recipes for this iconic cocktail. In addition to tasting these creations, you'll have access to specialized training and a counter where you can buy everything you need. A not-to-be-missed experience for mojito lovers in search of new flavors!

label: MK2 Quai de Loire
comment: MK2 cinemas, created by Marin Karmitz, offer a unique experience for moviegoers. Some multiplexes offer red "love seat" sofas, perfect for couples who want to hold hands in front of a romantic film. Single people can also enjoy the comfort of the armchairs. A boutique offers a selection of cinematic products to prolong the pleasure. An exciting and comfortable cinematic experience at MK2.

label: Step dance and music
comment: Since 1993, Step Dance, a dance school in the 11th arrondissement of Paris, has been offering a variety of classes for all levels and ages. You'll find styles such as Rock, Tango, Salsa, Reggaeton, Hip Hop, Zumba... Whether you're a beginner or an experienced dancer, Step Dance is sure to satisfy. Take advantage of a free, no-obligation trial class to find the one that's right for you. Embark on a rewarding dance experience at Step Dance!

label: Barbot
comment: Le Barbot, Les Maquereaux's fourth address, is a Montmartre bistro on Avenue Trudaine offering French wine, moules-frites and fresh fish. Enjoy the terrace, vintage interior, bistro dishes and a selection of bottles. Menu: moules-frites, fish to share, couteaux persillés, oysters, coquelets, fish soup, tapas de la mer. A Parisian bistro highlighting seafood.

label: Robert et Louise
comment: Immerse yourself in the heart of Paris, in a rustic setting featuring checkered tablecloths and copper pots. You'll be charmed by the warm, rustic atmosphere of this restaurant. But what makes this place so famous are its delicious meats, cooked to perfection in the fireplace at the back of the room. A real little corner of the countryside in the heart of the capital, to be discovered without delay for an authentic and tasty culinary experience.

label: Parc Montsouris
comment: Parc Montsouris, an oasis in the 14th arrondissement of Paris since 1869, offers a peaceful setting with its lake, sculptures and lush vegetation. Students from the Cité Universitaire relax here, and gourmets love the Pavillon Montsouris. Birdwatchers can observe various species, and there's a meteorological observatory and the Paris meridian stele. The water reservoir, open on Heritage Days, is full of surprises. Enjoy this haven of peace!

label: Centre sportif Suchet
comment: Located close to the Ranelagh gardens, the Auteuil racecourse and the Bois de Boulogne, the Stade Suchet offers a variety of sports facilities. Mainly dedicated to soccer and basketball, it also features an athletics track and tennis court. An ideal place for sports enthusiasts wishing to indulge in a variety of activities while enjoying the green surroundings.

label: Le 39V restaurant
comment: Le 39V, nestled in the heart of Paris, offers a breathtaking view of Avenue George V. Redecorated by designer Raphaël Navot, the restaurant showcases French craftsmanship. Much more than just a place to dine, it's a warm and welcoming space where authenticity and kindness reign supreme. Frédéric Vardon's cuisine, respectful of nature and tradition, combines elegance with a commitment to taste. Le 39V embodies French culinary heritage with passion and rigor.

label: WHSmith
comment: "Discover the largest British bookshop in France! Immerse yourself in a unique literary universe where you'll find a multitude of books in English for all tastes and ages. A must for book lovers and enthusiasts of English-speaking culture. Don't wait any longer to explore this hidden nugget in the heart of France!"

label: Jean-Louis Scherrer
comment: Discover the prestigious flagship of the Jean-Louis Scherrer fashion house, ideally located near the Champs-Élysées avenue. Here you'll find an exceptional selection of the finest creations by this heir to Christian Dior. From womenswear and leather goods to the men's, children's, shoes, lingerie and fragrance collections, each piece embodies the excellence and timeless elegance for which the brand is renowned.

label: Institut Danielle Lanstère
comment: Discover chocolotherapy at Institut Danielle Lanstère, a true gourmet celebration for wellness enthusiasts. Thanks to the antioxidant virtues of cocoa, this exceptional treatment offers a unique experience. The facial revitalizes and purifies the skin in depth, while the body massage provides a sensation of absolute relaxation while sublimating the skin. Treat yourself to a moment of softness and relaxation, for radiant skin and a soothed mind.

label: Élysée boutique officielle
comment: Find Boutique Élysée - Présidence de la République products in the main store and on the 1st floor of the Galeries Lafayette Gourmet store. Give original gifts with 100% made-in-France products such as bowling games, boules, candles and the essential Nemo plush.

label: Académie Franck de Roche
comment: The Franck de Roche Academy provides training for aspiring hairdressers. As part of its students' training, it regularly offers free haircuts to those willing to serve as models. An ideal opportunity to get a new haircut without spending a penny!

label: Le Club des 5
comment: Five friends breathe new life into the legendary Club des 5, in the heart of Les Batignolles. With original recipes, a warm welcome and formidable efficiency, this place is sure to delight lovers of inventive, regressive cuisine. An address not to be missed for a unique and convivial culinary experience!

label: Théâtre du Palais-Royal
comment: In the heart of the 17th century, the Théâtre du Palais-Royal was born, with shows by Molière and Lully. Today, it offers an eclectic program of comedies, original creations and shows dedicated to young audiences. A place steeped in history that continues to enliven the Parisian theater scene with diversity and modernity.

label: Square Trousseau
comment: Located near the famous Bastille, Square Trousseau stands on the remains of the Hospice des Enfants-Trouvés. Embellished by a charming bandstand, it hosts a lively annual garage sale from late September to early October. It's a not-to-be-missed opportunity to unearth treasures and enjoy the friendly atmosphere of this lively Paris neighborhood.

label: Monsieur Poulet
comment: Monsieur Poulet offers a wide range of organic cotton t-shirts and sweatshirts, certified by Max Havelaar, GOTS and Oeko-tex. The designs are created by online graphic artists, adding a touch of originality. The brand combines ecology, ethics and style, offering unique and responsible clothing. A conscious and ethical way to consume fashion, without compromising on looks.

label: Musée Edith Piaf
comment: Immerse yourself in the world of Edith Piaf at the museum-apartment dedicated to this icon of French chanson. Nestled in Ménilmontant, where La Môme began her career, this intimate space is brimming with treasures: personal objects, earthenware and even her legendary black dress. An immersion in the life of this unforgettable artist, with a boutique offering books and audio aids to prolong the experience. A visit rich in emotions and memories.

label: Théâtre du Lido
comment: Immerse yourself in the world of Lido2Paris! Following its reopening, the famous Champs-Elysées venue presents a new production of the legendary Cabaret. Directed by Jean-Luc Choplin, Robert Carsen's staging promises a breathtaking spectacle. For the first time in Paris, Cabaret will be performed in English with surtitles. Don't miss these 60 exceptional performances at the end of 2022 in this emblematic venue. A unique experience you must not miss!

additional_information: ['From December 1, 2022: Tuesday to Saturday 8 pm; matinees Saturday and Sunday 3 pm']

label: Chaillot - Théâtre national de la Danse
comment: The Chaillot - Théâtre national de la Danse, beneath the Place du Trocadéro overlooking the Eiffel Tower, is a fine work of Art Deco. Designed by Jacques Carlu, Louis-Hippolyte Boileau and Léon Azéma, it features works by Maurice Denis, Edouard Vuillard and Pierre Bonnard. Classified as a Historic Monument in 1980, this theater made history by hosting the creation of the world's first national and popular theater, as well as the signing of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.

label: Le Memphis
comment: Located on the Grands Boulevards, the Memphis is an original club with several dancefloors on two levels. Its musical program ranges from 60s to techno, with Latin rhythms thrown in for good measure. Its kitsch atmosphere and leopard-print banquettes attract a festive clientele for dancing with friends. The Memphis also offers afternoon tea dances, making it a must for night owls in search of entertainment!

label: Parc de la Butte du Chapeau Rouge
comment: The verdant park designed by architect Louis Azéma, between Mouzaia and Danube, was created in 1939 on a former gypsum quarry hill. Offering splendid views over the Pré Saint-Gervais plain, it abounds in majestic trees, belvederes, vast lawns and clumps of heather. In addition, it hosts concerts during the Paris Quartier d'été summer festival, offering a haven of peace and exceptional panoramic views.

label: Aquarium tropical
comment: The Palais de la Porte Dorée, a listed historic monument, is home to the Tropical Aquarium and the Museum of the History of Immigration. With almost 5,000 animals, from the waters of Asia to the exotic fauna of Africa and South America, visitors discover crocodiles, sharks and piranhas. Since 2007, the site has also been home to two albino alligators, symbols of cultural diversity in France. An enriching experience for the whole family!

label: Cabine Studio Harcourt Paris
comment: Since 1934, Studio Harcourt has been immortalizing celebrities such as Josephine Baker, Jean Dujardin and Laetitia Casta. Renowned for its black-and-white portraits and distinctive lighting, in 2011 this legendary studio launched its Photo Booths, a genuine invitation to become part of the legend. Embodying the studio's glamorous style and technical quality, these cabins let you become an icon in just a few minutes.

label: Théâtre Daunou
comment: The 450-seat Théâtre Daunou is located in the heart of Paris's Opéra district. Its programming focuses on comedy, offering an entertaining and dynamic show for spectators in search of laughter and good humor. A must-see venue for a fun-filled evening in the capital.

additional_information: ['Depending on the show. Usually 9pm. Sunday matinees.']

label: Ban Thaï Spa
comment: In the heart of Saint Germain des Prés, Ban Thaï Spa offers a luxurious experience. The décor by a Thai designer invites serenity. The Bangkok-trained team offers a variety of rejuvenating massages. Each massage can be enjoyed as a duo for a unique experience. Spa Ban Thaï offers foot massages, traditional Thai massages and aromatic oil massages, with a hammam session for total relaxation.

label: La mécanique ondulatoire
comment: Nestled in a lively neighborhood, this bar with its industrial design attracts music fans looking for something new. Its eclectic program promises wild evenings of rock, jazz and electro. Plunge into a festive atmosphere and let yourself be carried away by the lively rhythms. Whether you're sipping cocktails with friends or dancing the night away, this trendy venue is sure to win you over. A must for lovers of good music and trendy venues.

label: Shingane
comment: Shingane, a restaurant located in eastern Paris behind Père-Lachaise, offers authentic, delicious Korean cuisine, setting it apart from its Asian neighbors. The dishes on offer are a real invitation to a unique and exotic gustatory voyage. An address not to be missed for lovers of exotic and refined flavors.

label: Maison du Vitrail
comment: Come and discover the unique expertise of Mr. Andrieux, a passionate master glassmaker, in the age-old art of creating and restoring stained glass windows, emblems of French heritage. From painting on glass to meticulous cutting and delicate lead setting, immerse yourself in the three key stages of this noble craft tradition. A fascinating immersion in an exceptional craft, where every gesture reveals an exceptional know-how.

label: Le Dôme
comment: Since 1898, the famous Montparnasse venue Le Dôme has been delighting diners with its Art Deco decor: wood panelling, stained glass windows, imposing lampshades and leather banquettes. A meeting point for the arts and politics in Paris, the spacious dining room and terrace welcome diners in an elegant atmosphere. Seafood and fish, such as red mullet and bouillabaisse, are the hallmarks of the restaurant's cuisine. An exceptional place not to be missed!

label: Théâtre de Poche Montparnasse
comment: The Théâtre de Poche Montparnasse in Paris is one of the capital's most renowned private theaters. Formerly a café, it was transformed into a theater in 1943. Since 1984, it has had a second 100-seat auditorium, enabling it to welcome a wider audience. Its varied programming and diverse shows offer performances throughout the day, providing a rich and captivating theatrical experience.

label: Silencio Club
comment: Paris's trendy Silencio is located on rue Montmartre. Created by David Lynch, this club offers a unique atmosphere. From midnight onwards, there are concerts, performances and musical sets, accompanied by finger food and cocktails. Before midnight, only members are allowed in. Find out more on the website. Immerse yourself in this mysterious universe, suspended in time, at Silencio.

label: Le Pot O'Lait
comment: Crêpes and galettes, both savoury and sweet, are real delights to be savoured with pleasure. With a topping of jam or melted chocolate, these simple, authentic dishes provide an undeniable feeling of well-being. Perfect for breakfast, afternoon tea or dinner, crêpes and galettes satisfy every gourmet craving. Let yourself be seduced by their bewitching fragrance and irresistible texture in every bite.

label: Marché de la création Paris Montparnasse
comment: Discover the Edgar Quinet creative market, a veritable open-air art gallery featuring paintings, sculptures, ceramics, marquetry, stained glass and many other forms of artistic expression. Meet the artists and talk directly with them for privileged and enriching moments. A unique artistic experience not to be missed! Follow them on their Facebook page to make sure you don't miss a thing: https://www.facebook.com/egs.edgarquinet/

label: Musée d'art et d'histoire du Judaïsme
comment: Discover the Musée d'art et d'histoire du Judaïsme in Paris, in the historic Marais district. This 17th-century venue is brimming with unique religious objects and works of art, offering a fascinating insight into the history of Jews in France, Europe and North Africa. In addition to the permanent tour, temporary exhibitions, cultural events and educational activities enrich your visit. Immerse yourself in Jewish culture in France in a captivating experience.

label: Les Ombres Quai Branly
comment: Les Ombres restaurant, on the Quai Branly, is a must-visit address in Paris. Headed by Alain Ducasse-trained Alexandre Sempere, it offers a refined culinary experience inspired by the Mediterranean. Dishes featuring seasonal produce, perfect cooking and tasty juices, all with a breathtaking view of Paris and the Eiffel Tower. A meal at Les Ombres promises to be delicious and memorable for food lovers.

label: Chez Bouboule
comment: Discover the originality of Chez Bouboule! This atypical eatery on Avenue Trudaine, near Montmartre, promises a real moment of relaxation. Enjoy tapas or traditional cuisine, and make the most of the pétanque court for a spirited game. Whatever your level, the important thing is to share a convivial moment. And don't forget the quality wine list to accompany your dishes. At Bouboule, aperitifs become a pure delight!

label: Christian Louboutin
comment: Each and every Christian Louboutin creation deserves a proper setting. These shoes are not mere accessories, but veritable jewels for the feet. Each pair has its own universe, its own style, and its own charm. Christian Louboutin doesn't just design shoes, he tells a story through each of his works. An invitation to travel, to femininity, to glamour. An alcove for each pair, a jewel case for each foot.

label: Mamagoto
comment: Mamagoto offers original and tasty dishes, featuring carefully selected quality products. During the day, it's a lively bistro ideal for a lunch break with friends or colleagues. In the evening, the atmosphere transforms into a tapas bar and refined cocktails. The menu changes with the seasons, inviting you to discover surprising new combinations of flavors. Mamagoto is a must for lovers of inventive, authentic cuisine.

label: Ô Chateau
comment: With over 50 wines by the glass and 1,000 by the bottle, Ô Chateau is one of Paris's must-visit wine bars. From gourmet platters to small plates to share, enjoy quality cuisine for a convivial dinner. Awarded "Best Wine List" in France by Terres de Vin in 2017, this exceptional venue will delight lovers of fine vintages. Three private rooms are also available for your private events.

label: Art 42 - Urban Art Collection
comment: Located in the 17th arrondissement of Paris, Art 42 - Urban Art Collection is the first street art and post-graffiti museum in France. Covering 4,000 m², it presents over 150 works by major artists such as Banksy, JR, Shepard Fairey, Bault and Madame. Frescoes, sculptures, stencils, collages and prints offer an immersive artistic experience. Open Tuesdays and Saturdays, this museum celebrates the creativity of contemporary artists. Each guided tour offers a unique approach to the works. Art 42 is a place of exchange for art enthusiasts.

label: Maachi Djelani
comment: Maachi Djelani, an original hairdresser, offers nocturnal haircuts on the nights of the full moon. His salon, open all night, attracts a loyal clientele in search of a unique experience. Set in the historic center of Paris, this unusual location is the place to book for a magical experience. Each cut is a work of art, created with passion and precision to achieve breathtaking results. A unique experience to share, for sublimated hair and enhanced confidence.

label: L'Ile aux Images
comment: In the heart of Paris, on the Île Saint-Louis, is L'Île aux Images, a gallery specializing in the sale of historic photographs dating from 1839 to 1980, posters and original lithographs on various artistic themes such as Art Nouveau, Art Deco, advertising and fashion. Each document is accompanied by a certificate of authenticity, guaranteeing the quality and originality of the works. A unique journey through time with authentic pieces.

label: Les Ateliers du Père Lachaise associés
comment: The Père Lachaise district, in the 20th arrondissement of Paris, is a veritable paradise for lovers of contemporary art. The area's artists - painters, sculptors, engravers and photographers - are very dynamic. Meet them, observe their techniques, admire their works and engage in enriching discussions. A total immersion in the creativity and talent of the artists in the Père Lachaise district.

label: La chambre aux confitures
comment: Come and discover the Chambre aux Confitures boutique in the charming Marais district. With over a hundred jars lined up, gourmets will be spoilt for choice. The jams, genuine artisan creations, are concocted using only fresh fruit and sugar, with no added preservatives, flavor enhancers or colorants. An explosion of sweet, fruity flavors awaits you in this unique setting.

label: Carrousel du Louvre
comment: Welcome to the Carrousel du Louvre reception desk! Since 1993, this shopping center has been home to leading gift and accessory brands, symbols of French excellence. Between shopping and culture, visitors are immersed in an emblematic Parisian landmark, with grandiose architecture and direct access to the Louvre Museum. Hosts and hostesses are on hand to guide and guide visitors, and to help them with information, tax relief, reservations and other needs.

label: CheZ Aline
comment: Come and enjoy delicious snacks and desserts, prepared with care, in a warm atmosphere. Located in a former butcher's shop near Bastille, this place blends tradition and modernity for a unique culinary experience. The quality of the dishes and the speed of service will delight your taste buds. Don't miss this paradise for food lovers!

label: Paroisse Saint-Médard
comment: Saint-Médard church, a 12th-century jewel in the Latin Quarter, replaces a Merovingian oratory. A witness to the history of Paris, it closed during the Terror in 1793. But it resumed its activities in 1801. Today, an emblematic site steeped in history and spirituality, it offers a peaceful atmosphere for visitors in search of serenity. Each stone tells the story of Paris' past, bearing witness to the centuries that have shaped the City of Light.

label: Théâtre du Soleil - La Cartoucherie
comment: The Théâtre du Soleil, located at the Cartoucherie de Vincennes, is an emblematic cultural venue. Nestled in the Bois de Vincennes, it offers a varied program of theater, dance and music. Lovers of the performing arts will be delighted by the diversity of the shows on offer. Each performance is an opportunity to discover new talent and experience the magic of live performance.

label: Palais des Glaces
comment: In the heart of Paris's 10th arrondissement, near the Place de la République, lies the Palais des Glaces, a popular venue for comedy fans. In addition to comedy shows, its two halls offer a diverse program including theater, improvisation, music and children's shows. A veritable sanctuary of laughter in Paris, this venue guarantees a festive and unforgettable experience for its audiences.

label: Brasserie Thoumieux
comment: Situated in the 7th arrondissement, between the Invalides and the Eiffel Tower, the Thoumieux brasserie's unique decor is a blend of antique objects and contemporary elements. A rock?n?roll atmosphere pervades. In the kitchen, the chef skilfully revisits great classics at affordable prices. A must for food lovers looking for a unique experience.

label: Clown Bar
comment: The Clown Bar, nestled in the former buvette of the prestigious Cirque d'Hiver, just a stone's throw away, offers an exceptional setting listed as a historic monument. With its clown ceramics, this unusual place is home to a Japanese chef who concocts delicious traditional bistro dishes. The Clown Bar is a must-visit bistro in the Haut Marais, offering a unique and authentic culinary experience.

label: Amici Miei
comment: In the heart of Paris, this atypical place offers delicious wood-fired pizzas and other Italian specialties that attract a loyal clientele. No need to make a reservation, just wait at the counter or on the terrace to enjoy a meal or share dinner with friends. The warm, friendly atmosphere makes it a must for lovers of traditional Italian cuisine in search of pleasure and sharing. An experience not to be missed!

label: Au Bistrot de la Montagne
comment: In the Latin Quarter, close to the Pantheon, the bistro La Montagne specialises in welcoming groups. You will be welcomed in a historic setting dating from the 13th century, with dressed stones and exposed beams. The place - and its four rooms of different capacities - adapts to any request and any event (weddings, seminars, meetings...). A wide choice of fixed or optional menus is available.

label: Galerie J. Kugel - Antiquaires
comment: Since 2004, Galerie J. Kugel has been based in the Hôtel Collot, a building dating from 1840 on the Quai Anatole France. Specializing in objets d'art from the Middle Ages to the 19th century, it offers a rich collection of goldsmith's and silversmith's work, furniture, sculpture, paintings and precious treasures. A veritable Ali Baba's cave for lovers of art and beautiful things.

label: Le Merle Moqueur
comment: Located in one of Paris's most charming districts, close to the picturesque Rue des Cinq Diamants, this Butte aux Cailles pub attracts young students and lovers of rum and house vodka. The lively atmosphere makes it a favorite meeting place for regulars. It's a great place to make friends, and the musical atmosphere encourages you to sing along! Prices are very affordable.

The lively atmosphere makes it a favorite meeting place for regulars. It's a great place to make friends, and the musical atmosphere encourages you to sing along! Prices are very affordable.
street: 11 rue de la Butte aux Cailles

label: Le Bar Hemingway
comment: The Hemingway Bar at the Ritz Paris, a tribute to the author of "Paris est une fête", is a favorite with artists and writers for its hushed, elegant ambience. Wood panelling, leather armchairs and a library attract celebrities. Head bartender Colin Field offers a varied menu of whiskies, ports, beers and classic cocktails, accompanied by delicious tapas. To enter the Bar Hemingway is to plunge into the history and prestige of one of the capital's most famous bars.

label: Bel Canto
comment: Come and enjoy a unique experience combining opera and quality French cuisine in our Bel Canto restaurants. Our singers interpret famous arias for a spellbinding atmosphere. Discover our Dinner and Show formula from 93? Per person, with a choice of three courses from our semi-gastronomic menu. Book now for a magical evening in Paris or Neuilly-sur-Seine at Le Bel Canto!

label: HD Diner
comment: Diners have long been an integral part of American culture. In Paris, HD Diner offers an authentic experience with hamburgers, typical fast food dishes and gourmet desserts. All served in a retro 50s atmosphere, reminiscent of the Happy Days era. Fast, delicious home cooking in a warm, friendly atmosphere.

label: Cathédrale Notre-Dame de Paris et son trésor
comment: Notre-Dame de Paris cathedral, a Gothic masterpiece, was built between the 13th and 15th centuries. Restored by Viollet-le-Duc in the 19th century after the French Revolution, it fascinates visitors with its stained glass windows, towers, gargoyles and panoramic views. In 2013, it celebrated its 850th anniversary by welcoming eight new bells. Its forecourt, France's ground zero, remains a symbolic place.

additional_information: ['Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday, 7.45am to 7pm; Thursday, 7.45am to 10pm; Saturday and Sunday, 8.15am to 7.30pm. Concerts generally take place on Tuesdays at 8.30pm. Auditions on the great organ take place on Sundays at 4pm. The Treasury is open Monday to Saturday, 9:30am to 6pm (until 9pm on Thursdays) and Sundays, 1pm to 5:30pm. The Towers of Notre-Dame are temporarily closed to visitors']

label: Chez Ma Cousine
comment: Since 1928, Chez Ma Cousine, a typical Montmartre cabaret-restaurant, has attracted locals and tourists alike. Its retro decor and live entertainment immerse us in the atmosphere of Paris in the Roaring Twenties. Its generous, traditional cuisine, prepared with quality ingredients, delights the taste buds. Attentive service and a varied artistic program make Chez Ma Cousine an essential part of Parisian cultural and gastronomic life. Chez Ma Cousine charms with unforgettable moments.

label: Le Speakeasy
comment: Located near the Place de l'Étoile and the Arc de Triomphe, the Speakeasy plunges us into the atmosphere of Chicago in the Roaring Twenties. This piano bar with its refined decor is perfect for jazz lovers. Every evening from 7.30pm, music lovers gather for spellbinding performances. On Fridays and Saturdays, the Speakeasy becomes a club, inviting night owls to dance the night away. On the gastronomic side, refined cuisine accompanies a varied selection of wines. Succumb to the charm of the Speakeasy!

label: Chez André
comment: Founded in 1936, the establishment has preserved its period ambience, with a zinc bar and 1930s bistro tables. The menu features authentic dishes from our childhood: frog legs, bouillabaisse, leg of lamb and seafood. Traditional, refined bourgeois cuisine, accompanied by a selection of wines by the glass. A culinary journey back in time.

label: Jardin Truillot
comment: Covering an area of 5,600 m², the permanently accessible Truillot garden links the Voltaire and Richard Lenoir boulevards in the 11th arrondissement. Designed by landscape architects Marie-Odile Ricard and Jean-Marc Le Névanic, this green space features a shared garden, two play areas, a vast 1,600 m² lawn and a wall dedicated to street art. A veritable oasis of greenery in the heart of the city, where everyone can enjoy a wide range of outdoor activities.

label: Cimetière de Montmartre
comment: The Montmartre cemetery, opened in 1825, is the third largest in Paris, covering 11 hectares. With its varied trees and Caulaincourt bridge, it offers a peaceful atmosphere. Close to the Sacré-C?ur Basilica, it boasts some 20,000 concessions. The tombs of Stendhal, Zola and Dalida can be found here. Dalida's is the most visited. A peaceful and rewarding stroll.

label: Wepler
comment: The Place Clichy brasserie, frequented by Picasso, Modigliani and Truffaut, seats 100 and remains open from 8am to 1am. Seafood lovers will be delighted by its generous platters. Also try the "joue de b?uf au Riesling" or the "haricots coco frais au gingembre". Wepler was awarded the "Tables et Auberges de France" label in 2006 for its quality cuisine.

label: Edith
comment: Restaurant Edith, nestled in Paris's Golden Triangle, is distinguished by the innovative cuisine of chef Guillaume Dunos. His modern interpretation of Escoffier classics, in an Art Deco setting, offers a distinguished dining experience. Creative dishes, fresh produce and friendly service round out the excellence of the place.

label: Marché Saxe-Breteuil
comment: The Saxe-Breteuil market in Paris, between the École Militaire and Unesco, offers a variety of fresh local produce. Strolling through the stalls is like plunging into a whirlwind of scents and colors, for a unique sensory experience. An ideal place for lovers of healthy, gourmet cuisine, and for those curious about French gastronomy. A true culinary discovery for epicureans in search of new flavors.

For technology enthusiasts, 7 multimedia workstations are available. A true haven of knowledge and entertainment in the heart of the city.

label: Le Grenier
comment: Located in the 17th arrondissement, near Place des Ternes, Le Grenier is a friendly, family-run café-théâtre. For decades, it has been offering entertaining dinner shows. Every day, a new program showcases diverse talents such as magicians and comedians. The venue can also be rented for special events. Le Grenier is a must for a lively evening out in Paris.

Thursdays, Fridays and Saturdays are punctuated by a bewitching mix of Rap and R&B music, and international artists for unforgettable evenings. The place to be for trendy, relaxed evenings in Paris.

A must for lovers of luxury and elegance à la française.

Ideally located near the Gare de l'Est and Gare du Nord stations, it's the perfect place for a gourmet break. The menu highlights the flavours of Brittany, notably with a Sunday brunch called "Traou Mad", meaning "good things" in Breton. A must for lovers of French cuisine and conviviality.

On offer: musical evenings featuring renowned artists, lectures by experts, unique exhibitions, private collections to discover, and captivating screenings. Find out more about all these events on the dedicated website. An unmissable cultural experience for jazz aficionados!

comment: Uniqlo, Japan's ready-to-wear specialist, sets up shop in the heart of the Marais district. In a renovated 19th-century foundry by designer Masamichi Katayama, the brand presents its colorful, casual collections. Over 3 floors and 820 m², discover a wide selection of jeans, shirts and t-shirts near Place des Vosges. A must for fashionistas in search of style and quality at affordable prices.

label: Le Point Ephémère
comment: Le Point Éphémère, on the Canal Saint-Martin, supports artists in their projects. It offers residencies, public performances and urban interventions, welcoming all artistic disciplines. Studios are available for the free creation of visual artists, musicians and dancers. With a concert hall and exhibition space, artists can share their talent with audiences beyond the center's walls.

label: Les Papilles
comment: Discover a unique place, combining the warm ambience of a bistro, the refined selection of a wine cellar and the delicacy of a delicatessen. The place to be for lovers of exceptional food and wine. Immerse yourself in a tasty and convivial universe that's sure to charm you!

label: Chapelle expiatoire
comment: In the heart of Paris lies the Chapelle expiatoire, a neoclassical and romantic monument built from 1815 onwards during the reign of Louis XVIII. Located on a former revolutionary cemetery, it pays tribute to the royal family and historical figures such as Louis XVI, Marie-Antoinette, the Countess du Barry, Charlotte Corday and Olympe de Gouges, who were buried in 1793. A visit to this emblematic site offers a fascinating journey through the Ancien Régime and the French Revolution.

label: Galeries Lafayette Champs-Élysées
comment: Galeries Lafayette has relocated to the Champs-Élysées avenue, offering 6,500 m² of space on four floors. In an Art Deco building, visitors can enjoy a unique shopping experience, combining fashion, gastronomy and perfumery, in a majestic, luminous setting. A must for Parisians and tourists in search of a chic, trendy getaway.

label: Marché couvert Batignolles
comment: The Batignolles covered market, open Monday to Saturday, is housed in a hall built in 1979. It offers a variety of tempting stalls: Lebanese, Moroccan and African caterers, Italian and Iberian products, as well as non-food stalls including jewelry, gifts and repair services. A must for lovers of exotic flavors and artisanal products.

label: Paroisse Saint-Antoine des Quinze-Vingts
comment: Built between 1902 and 1903, the church's neo-Gothic architecture stands in the heart of the 12th arrondissement. The renowned organs, created by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll and Joseph Merklin, add a special dimension to this place steeped in history and religious fervor. Every detail of the building reveals the work of craftsmen of yesteryear, offering visitors a unique experience combining architectural beauty and spiritual emotion.

label: Le Son de la Terre
comment: Moored on the Quai de Montebello, the "Son de la Terre" offers a breathtaking view of Notre-Dame de Paris. Designed by the Seine Design agency, this elegant space has been a unique venue in the heart of the capital since 2023, with its panoramic view over the Seine. This bistronomic restaurant celebrates world cuisine, hosts concerts and club nights, and welcomes artists in residence. Modular, it offers private spaces and a mobile stage, as well as a large 200m2 terrace with in-house cuisine and original cocktails. An address not to be missed!

His fashion is distinguished by its joie de vivre, bright colors and unique character. The materials he uses are both feminine and luxurious. In 2012, he broadened his horizons by launching his first home linen collection.

label: Musée des Arts décoratifs
comment: The Musée des Arts Décoratifs boasts one of the world's largest collections of nearly one million works, reflecting the French art of living from the Middle Ages to the present day. It offers a unique panorama of the history of furniture, tableware, jewelry, design, textiles, fashion, graphics and advertising. This museum is the quintessential showcase for the arts and crafts and creative industries.

With its cobbled courtyards and friendly atmosphere, this shopping destination offers a unique selection for the home: furniture, tableware, lighting, objets d'art and decoration. The picturesque entrances via rue Saint-Paul, rue Ave Maria, rue des Jardins Saint-Paul and rue Charlemagne add a charming touch to this authentic experience.

A must for food lovers in search of new culinary discoveries.

label: The Club

Recognizable by its captivating blue facade, this bar is inspired by Parisian hotel bars with a touch of rock. Its menu of cocktails and top-of-the-range club sandwiches will delight the taste buds with refined dishes such as foie gras, King Crab or Bavarian Roast Beef. The Club offers lively evenings with DJ sets, mini-concerts and mixology workshops for party lovers. Perfect for a gourmet and festive getaway in Paris.

label: Fred Perry
comment: Fred Perry, the famous fashion brand, has its origins in the tennis talent of its founder. The laurel wreath, symbol of victory, recalls Fred Perry's sporting past. Through collections for men and women, the brand embodies an unmistakably British sportswear chic. A brand with an undisputed sporting pedigree, a symbol of English elegance and refinement.

label: Artcurial
comment: The Hôtel Marcel Dassault, built in 1844, is home to Artcurial, a prestigious auction house located on the Champs-Élysées. In addition to its art sales, Artcurial offers an art bookshop and a café, creating a complete cultural venue. It is also possible to rent the premises for events and receptions, offering an exceptional setting for special occasions. A must for art and history lovers.

label: Annabel Winship
comment: Discover Annabel Winship's ultra-feminine shoes, which combine elegance and humor. Fashion-conscious Parisian women fall for girly models such as Cherry Chéri, Grrrr! and Twilight. With their round toes and small heels, these shoes are perfect for those who want to assert their femininity with style. A subtle blend of whimsy and sophistication to be adopted without hesitation!

label: La Cité de la Mode et du Design
comment: This fashionable, cutting-edge design venue boasts a bright green, ultra-modern exterior. Wooden walkways facilitate circulation between levels, offering a unique experience. Spectacular views can be enjoyed from the panoramic terrace. Dining and entertainment options are varied: Wanderlust, Café Oz rooftop, Dad and Garage are oases for lovers of good taste and lively evenings.

label: La Galerie de l'Instant
comment: Located in the heart of the Marais district, the Galerie de l'Instant regularly presents high-quality photo exhibitions, attracting a large and enthusiastic public. Access to these exhibitions is entirely free, offering everyone the chance to discover the works of talented artists. A must for photography enthusiasts in search of artistic discoveries.

additional_information: ['Monday, 2-7 pm; Tuesday-Saturday, 11 am-7 pm; Sunday, 2:30-6:30 pm.']

label: MK2 Bibliothèque
comment: The MK2 Bibliothèque complex offers 14 cinemas, 2 restaurants and a boutique. In "Le Store", you'll find books, DVDs and the latest gadgets. The designer restaurants overlook the towers of the Bibliothèque Nationale de France, which surround a 1,200m² garden. The cinema also features 12 VR pods. To find out more, visit http://mk2vr.com/.

label: Piscine Roger Le Gall
comment: The Roger Le Gall swimming pool at Porte de Vincennes is very popular with Parisians for its high-quality sports facilities. Open to the public, two pools are available: a 50 m x 15 m pool and a 25 m x 12.5 m pool reserved for clubs. Built in 1967, it welcomes all levels of swimmers. In summer, the roof opens to make way for sunbathing on the lawn. Naturists are also welcome on Monday, Wednesday and Friday evenings.

label: Le Troquet
comment: Le Troquet, Christian Etchebest's restaurant, perfectly embodies the spirit of the neighborhood bistro. Its ambiance, decor and service are charming, not to mention its menu featuring local delicacies: lamb from Mauléon, Basque black pudding parmentier, cured local ham... All with a selection of quality wines. For all its refinement, Le Troquet remains a friendly, accessible place.

All with a selection of quality wines. For all its refinement, Le Troquet remains a friendly, accessible place.

label: Petit Bateau
comment: Since its creation in 1918 with the famous little knickers, this children's brand has made a name for itself among adults. Today, the range has diversified to include everything from infant bodysuits to chic mother's coats. A success story that combines comfort, quality and style for the whole family.

label: Librairie Le Moniteur
comment: Le Moniteur is ideally located at the Cité de l?architecture et du patrimoine, facing the majestic Eiffel Tower on the Place du Trocadéro. This bookshop is renowned for its specialization in books on architecture and construction. A must for enthusiasts and professionals in the sector in search of resources and inspiration.

label: Les Grandes Serres du Jardin des plantes - Muséum national d'histoire naturelle
comment: The Museum's greenhouses, renovated by Nathalie Crinière, reopened in 2010. These classified spaces offer a new kind of immersion: between tropical forests, deserts and New Caledonian landscapes, visitors travel through contrasting environments. The magic is still working, with an enriched experience thanks to a redesigned museography. Discover and preserve our environment.

label: Okuda
comment: Nestled in the heart of the Alma district, Okuda stands out as one of the nuggets of Japanese gastronomy in Paris. The atmosphere is one of sobriety and elegance, with hostesses gracefully dressed in iconic kimonos. In the kitchen, a festival of refined, delicate flavors delights guests' taste buds, offering an exceptional culinary experience. More than just a meal, Okuda promises an unforgettable taste journey.

label: Théâtre du Ranelagh
comment: Today's 300-seat auditorium retains its cachet, with carved oak panelling decorating the orchestra and balconies, and a painted coffered ceiling. Listed on the supplementary inventory of historic monuments since 1977, the hall's preserved architectural appeal is an added attraction.

label: Le Mauri7
comment: In Strasbourg - Saint-Denis, in the 10th arrondissement, discover Mauri7, a bar with a warm, relaxed atmosphere. Its kitsch decor, with its mix of cinema posters and retro record sleeves, creates an endearing atmosphere. Attentive waiters guarantee a lively evening with no fuss, perfect for aperitifs. Popular with night owls, it's the ideal place to extend the party into the night. A successful evening guaranteed in this dynamic Paris neighborhood!

label: Eric & Lydie
comment: Since 1994, Eric and Lydie have been designing delicate collections of costume jewelry, inspired by nature, antique jewelry and Art Deco style. Each enchanting, timeless piece is meticulously crafted in their workshop in France. A perfect fusion of tradition and modernity, for unique and refined creations.

label: Boutique et atelier Sakina M'Sa
comment: The Comorian designer creates original pieces combining structured volumes, precise topstitching and streamlined cuts. Bright colors add a glamorous touch to her creations, while retaining an artisanal feel. Her basement workshop and the vintage space next door are a testament to her talent and unique style.

label: Conservatoire national supérieur d'art dramatique
comment: The CNSAD, near the Grands Boulevards in Paris, trains drama students and offers training courses for working actors. Courses combine theory and practice for complete preparation. A major theater institution, the school imparts knowledge and techniques for artistic excellence. Students benefit from top-level teaching for a successful career in the performing arts.

label: by notsobig
comment: Discover a playful, creative world at Notsobig, the concept store dedicated to children. You'll find whimsical stuffed animals, Bauhaus-inspired toys and designer clothes for toddlers. With original and irresistible products, Notsobig also offers quality soft toys and ready-to-wear for children aged 0 to 10. Immerse yourself in a world where little ones' imaginations take center stage!

label: Bruno Barthélemy
comment: Discover spectacular guided tours of Paris with a passionate guide. Explore four fascinating themes: popular 19th-century Paris, crime mysteries, the Palais Royal and the village of Montmartre. Immerse yourself in history with fascinating anecdotes and emotionally-charged sites. An immersive experience for unforgettable memories.

label: Tricotin
comment: Discover the famous Chinese canteen in Chinatown! At Tricotin, you'll find a friendly, lively atmosphere, with a varied menu of dishes from China, Thailand, Vietnam and Cambodia. Delicious soups, steamed dishes, exquisite noodles and stir-fried rice dishes await you at affordable prices. The success of this place has even given rise to a sister restaurant. The sober decor and large tables add to the authenticity of the experience. A Chinese address not to be missed!

label: Bobbi Brown Studio
comment: Bobbi Brown, New York's renowned cosmetics brand, recently opened a boutique in the chic Marais district, near Place des Vosges. In a studio-style space, all the brand's products are at your disposal, with qualified staff on hand to guide you. Make-up lessons are offered in a private salon to enhance your beauty naturally. An invitation to reveal your elegance in all simplicity.

label: Mémorial des Martyrs de la Déportation
comment: Located at the tip of the Île de la Cité, the Memorial to the Martyrs of the Deportation pays tribute to the French victims deported to the Nazi camps. Inaugurated in 1962 and designed by the architect Georges-Henri Pingusson, this site invites visitors to reflect and pass on the memory.

street: Square de l'Île de France - 7 quai de l'Archevêché
additional_information: ['Daily, 10am-6.30pm. Last admission to rooms: 6pm; last admission to crypt: 6:15pm. Closed on the first Monday of every month and on May 1st. Length of visit: 1 hour']

label: Colorova
comment: Located in the Saint-Germain-des-Prés district, Colorova is the brainchild of two former classmates from the École Ferrandi. This tearoom offers a varied menu for lunch, but it's above all for its delicious pastries that the place stands out. Gourmets can indulge at any time of day. With its mix of mottled furniture and industrial ambience, this establishment has plenty of charm for a delightful sweet break.

label: Passion Luxe
comment: Discover our sale-depot specialized in new and second-hand luxury goods. Each item is authenticated before sale, and can be validated by our experts for 60 euros. Wide selection of leather goods, shoes, accessories (scarves, jewelry, belts, hats). Payment by instalments up to 4 times free of charge, personal shopper service. Private lounge available to relax during your visits.

additional_information: ['Monday to Saturday, 11 a.m. to 7 p.m. without appointment and by appointment, 9 a.m. to 11 a.m']

label: Café Richelieu
comment: Come and discover Café Richelieu, located just a stone's throw from the Napoleon III apartments, where you can savor the delights of Maison Angelina, a veritable benchmark for French gourmet delights. Open for breakfast, dinner, brunch and tea, Café Richelieu will satisfy all your gourmet desires. Please note, however, that an entrance ticket to the Louvre Museum is required to access this little haven of delights.

label: La Bocca
comment: Come and discover the delights of Italy in a charming two-level setting, where eclectic furnishings add a touch of character. Let yourself be seduced by the Italian specialties on offer, with a daily changing menu featuring simple yet exceptional quality products. A refined gustatory experience awaits you in this warm and welcoming place.

label: Pierre Hermé (Vaugirard)
comment: Celebrated pastry chef Pierre Hermé is behind such incredible creations as Ispahan, Plénitude and 2,000 Feuilles. Always guided by the pleasure of the senses, he has revolutionized the art of pastry-making. In his boutique, you can savor his delicious pastries, macaroons and chocolates bearing his prestigious signature.

label: Picturesque Voyages
comment: As a teacher and nationally certified tour guide, Picturesque Voyages offers unique tours in English or French. Explore the exceptional gardens of Paris, Versailles, Chantilly and Giverny in small groups or individually. Immerse yourself in the influence of gardens on art, design and gastronomy through enriching visits. Discover the inspiration of chefs, designers and perfumers to make your experience unforgettable.

label: Accor Arena
comment: The Accor Arena, the world's 3rd largest concert arena, welcomes the greatest international and French artists such as John Legend and Céline Dion. But that's not all! It also offers top-level sports, from tennis to funboarding. In the heart of Paris, easy to reach, it offers bars, a terrace and a 1500m² skating rink. With 60,000 visitors per season, the rink offers field hockey matches and ice dance shows. Enjoy an unforgettable experience at the Accor Arena!

label: Cité Internationale des Arts
comment: The Cité internationale des arts in Paris is home to over 1,000 artists from 55 countries in 325 residency studios. Designed by architect Olivier-Clément Cacoub in 1965, the site has expanded over the years. It reflects a fusion of cultural policies and artistic projects. Discover the artists in residence at http://bit.ly/1UDdJaK.

label: L'Avant-Comptoir
comment: Discover a warm and friendly atmosphere in this typical South-West tapas bar, where a lively and festive atmosphere reigns around the counter. Let yourself be charmed by a varied selection of tasty small plates and a wide range of quality wines, perfect for enhancing your taste buds during this unique tasting experience. Prepare yourself for a memorable culinary experience, rich in flavors and sharing, in this authentic and welcoming venue.

label: La Compagnie des vins surnaturels
comment: Located near the Marché Saint-Germain in the 6th arrondissement, this chic, friendly wine bar boasts a marble fireplace, elegant glass roof and old stone walls. With a list of 3,000 quality wines and perfect finger food, tasting is a real treat. The atmosphere is peaceful and relaxed, and don't miss the "mystery wine" at 12? for a chance to win the bottle by guessing its provenance. A perfect address for an evening out with friends or lovers!

label: La Grande Récré
comment: La Grande Récré, a veritable toy paradise, offers a wide range of products for all ages. From the timeless charm of traditional games to the latest cyber-games and timeless plush toys, Lego and Barbie, there's something for everyone. Whether for toddlers or adults, this toy supermarket satisfies every desire for leisure and entertainment, from 0 to 77 years of age.

label: Bibliothèque Publique d'Information - BPI
comment: The Bibliothèque Publique d'Information (BPI), in the heart of Paris, in the Centre Pompidou, offers rich collections, reading spaces, varied cultural activities (conferences, debates, documentary film screenings) and captivating temporary exhibitions. Discovery tours are also offered to help visitors better appreciate the premises and services. A must for culture and knowledge lovers!

label: Église Saint Bernard de la Chapelle
comment: In the heart of the vibrant Goutte d'Or district, Saint-Bernard church unfolds, built from 1858 to 1861 by Auguste-Joseph Magne. A monumental, historic landmark, it is a jewel of neo-Gothic style, with sumptuous interior decoration and one of Aristide Cavaillé-Coll's emblematic organs. Its wall still resonates with the revolutionary spirit instilled by Louise Michel during the Paris Commune.

label: Kifune
comment: Just a stone's throw from Porte Maillot, Kifune is the place to go for refined Japanese cuisine in Paris. As one of the capital's finest establishments, its impeccable quality and authentic ambience are sure to win over fans of Japanese flavors. A place not to be missed for an exotic and delicious culinary experience.

label: Square Louise Michel
comment: Square Louise Michel, famous for its 222 steps leading up to the Sacré C?ur Basilica, runs alongside the Butte Montmartre. With its gently sloping paths, it is much appreciated by tourists and artists alike for its panoramic views and lush vegetation. Paul Gasq's fountain and exceptional trees, including two 17-metre-high orange trees, add to the beauty of the place. A must-see visit to Montmartre to take full advantage of this enchanting setting.

label: A2Z Art Gallery
comment: Located in the heart of Saint-Germain-des-Prés, A2Z Art Gallery specializes in contemporary art and design. It showcases international artists and designers, with a particular focus on the Chinese art scene. Thanks to its exchange platform, it fosters collaboration between the Chinese and European art scenes, offering a unique space for artistic discoveries and encounters.

label: Chez Denise - A La Tour de Monthéry
comment: One look at the restaurant's wooden facade and you're immersed in the warm atmosphere of an authentic neighborhood bistro. The menu features hearty dishes such as veal kidneys with mustard sauce, beef onglet, calvados tripe, pot-au-feu and Charolais rib steak. For over 30 years, Denise has welcomed customers until 5am, attracting a loyal clientele accustomed to the popularity of the establishment, which is often fully booked even late at night.

label: Free’p’Star
comment: Discover a trendy boutique specializing in vintage 70s clothing. A true haven for lovers of rock and retro looks. Immerse yourself in a unique atmosphere where vintage style meets today's trends. A collection that will seduce fashionistas in search of originality and authenticity. Immerse yourself in the world of the seventies and enhance your wardrobe with unique pieces full of character.

label: Rip Curl Store Paris
comment: Founded by two surfing enthusiasts, this Australian clothing brand is inspired by the dynamic world of board sports. With a unique, on-trend style, it offers original, colorful collections that reflect the free spirit of surf culture. Perfect pieces for fashion lovers looking for comfort and style, while remaining true to the brand's sporting spirit. An invitation to adventure through creations that celebrate nature.

label: Café Oz Rooftop
comment: Café Oz Rooftop, a popular Australian café, occupies the roof terrace of the Cité de la Mode et du Design, in Paris's 13th arrondissement. It's the ideal place to relax, enjoy a cool drink, nibble and sway into the wee hours of the morning, taking in the splendid view of the Seine and its architectural wonders.

Each bite is a culinary journey rich in emotion. Whether you're a fan of Indian cuisine or looking for a new taste experience, Jaipur Café is sure to meet your expectations. Enjoy an unforgettable experience, seduced by the magic of spices and exotic flavors.

Located in an elegant setting on Avenue de Wagram, near the Arc de Triomphe, this space showcases an assortment of decorative candles, scented gift sets and skincare products. A chic, soothing atmosphere awaits you in the heart of this design showcase.

label: Paris Toujours
comment: Discover Paris your way with Paris-Toujours! Specializing in made-to-measure stays, this agency offers unique programs for everyone. From accommodations to private tours, restaurants and shows, everything is designed for an authentic Parisian experience. Take advantage of exclusive, tailor-made services to explore the capital and its region. Paris-Toujours guarantees unforgettable moments in Paris!

label: Androuet - Fromager
comment: For over a century, Maison Androuet has perpetuated its exceptional expertise in the selection and maturing of authentic cheeses. Working in partnership with the finest producers, Maison Androuet's cheese ripeners maintain close ties to guarantee unrivalled quality. The undisputed leader in its field, Maison Androuet is the ambassador for small-scale producers, highlighting the richness of France's terroirs.

label: Acqua di Parma
comment: Founded in 1916 in Parma, Italy, the Acqua di Parma brand made a name for itself with its first fragrance, "Colonia d'Acqua di Parma", famous for its refreshing notes. Specializing in eaux de cologne, the brand offers unique creations presented in bottles designed by glass artisans. A symbol of exclusivity, the Acqua di Parma boutique in Paris is the only one of its kind in France, offering an exceptional olfactory experience for lovers of luxury fragrances.

label: Claude Colliot
comment: In his intimate culinary space, the chef sublimates exceptional ingredients, selected for their freshness and origin. In a refined setting combining modernity and tradition, he expresses his creativity through tasty and surprising dishes. Each plate is a work of taste, an invitation to a journey of the senses and the discovery of unique flavors. A delight for food lovers in search of unforgettable culinary experiences.

label: restaurant LE Drugstore
comment: Chef Éric Frechon's LE Drugstore restaurant offers innovative cuisine that's open to the world, far from conventional. The menu offers dishes that are free, fresh, joyful and festive, with spectacular creations. The aim is to create a culinary experience rich in emotion, with attentive service. A place where every guest enjoys an exceptional meal. Renowned chef with 3 Michelin stars.

label: Marché Bastille
comment: In the heart of Paris, with the majestic July Column in the background, lies one of the capital's most important markets. No fewer than a hundred merchants set up their stalls, offering an incredible variety of products. Enough to satisfy all the desires and needs of visitors eager for discoveries and flavors. A true immersion in the heart of French art de vivre.

label: Chapelle Saint-Patrick
comment: St. Patrick's Chapel, founded in 1775, combines neoclassical and baroque styles. Its colorful stained glass windows create a warm atmosphere for the faithful. In addition to mass, cultural and community activities are held here, strengthening bonds within the community. A place of faith and sharing, it embodies the richness of the Catholic Church in Paris, inviting discovery in the heart of the capital.

label: Théâtre Antoine
comment: The Théâtre Antoine, in the République district, offers a varied and captivating program. From comedy to readings to classics, there's something for everyone. The very young are not forgotten, with specially adapted shows. Immerse yourself in this magical place of wonder. A unique experience awaits you at the Théâtre Antoine!

label: Passage du Havre
comment: Le Passage du Havre, a shopping mall renovated in 2012, boasts 40 boutiques with flagship brands such as Fnac, Sephora, Nature et Découvertes, Caroll, Courir and Normal. This iconic Parisian landmark features a tree-lined garden and terrace for relaxing after a visit to Starbuck's, Maison Pradier or Prêt-à-Manger. Services available: tax-free shopping, chargers, toilets, free wifi, ATM, photo booth, Amazon lockers, and more.

label: Kei
comment: Located between the Louvre and the Palais-Royal, Kei restaurant in Paris is run by Michelin-starred chef Kei Kobayashi, who trained with Alain Ducasse. His sophisticated, inventive French cuisine subtly blends Japanese touches. The 5- or 8-course lunch menu and 6- or 8-course dinner offer an exceptional culinary experience in this exceptional setting.

label: Restaurant du Palais Royal
comment: The prestigious Michelin-starred Restaurant du Palais Royal is located in the heart of the Jardin du Palais-Royal in Paris. In an elegant, contemporary setting, it offers a unique culinary experience. Chef Philip Chronopoulos and his brigade offer refined French cuisine, with an emphasis on quality dishes and impeccable service. Flavors combine with subtlety to create dishes full of emotion. An exceptional address, a true tribute to French gastronomy.
