label: Porte Saint-Martin
comment: The Porte Saint-Martin, built in 1674 for Louis XIV, stands 18 m high along the boulevard of the same name, designed by P. Bullet. Nearby, cultural venues include the Théâtre de la Porte Saint-Martin (1781), the Théâtre du Splendid and the Théâtre de la Renaissance. Nearby, the Passage Brady offers numerous Indian restaurants and the Marché Saint-Martin features a Baltard-style market. Come and enjoy a unique historical and culinary experience close to the Porte Saint-Martin.

Savor the delights of French gastronomy and share this culinary heritage. Offer a unique taste journey with these must-have sweets!

label: Maison de Beauté Carita
comment: Founded in 1946, luxury cosmetics brand Carita has established its Maison de Beauté on the prestigious Faubourg Saint-Honoré in Paris. This exceptional location combines an institute and a boutique. In the institute, you can enjoy a moment of relaxation with facial and body treatments, make-up sessions or a haircut by expert hairdressers. The boutique offers a wide range of luxury treatments. A must for beauty and well-being enthusiasts.

label: Studio de l'Ermitage
comment: Located in the heights of Ménilmontant, Studio de l?Ermitage has a rich and singular history. Once a Brun cookie factory, this former small factory has been transformed into a unique venue for artistic creation. Today, it has established itself as an essential concert venue, offering an eclectic musical program. In addition to concerts, theatrical evenings and film screenings regularly enliven this atypical venue.

label: Mémorial arménien
comment: Erected to commemorate the Armenian genocide of 1915, the monument to Reverend Father Komitas in Paris reflects the martyrdom of the Armenian people during the First World War. Inaugurated on April 24, 2003 by Bertrand Delanoë, Mayor of Paris, and the Armenian Ambassador to France, Mr. Nalbandian, this memorial is a vibrant and solemn tribute.

label: Marionnettes du Parc Montsouris
comment: The Parc Montsouris puppet theater, opened in 1930, is a must-see destination in Paris's 14th arrondissement. With its warm atmosphere, it attracts many visitors in search of magic. Its varied program will captivate children and adults alike, for unforgettable moments with family, friends or solo. Come and discover this magical place!

label: Marché Aguesseau
comment: The Aguesseau market, nestled in the Place de la Madeleine, is a little paradise for your taste buds, where you'll find quality fruit, vegetables, fish, shellfish and charcuterie. A must for all lovers of fresh, tasty produce. A real treat for the senses in a warm, authentic setting.

label: La Pâtisserie Cyril Lignac (Paul Bert)
comment: In the lively rue de Paul Bert, chefs Cyril Lignac and Benoît Couvrand come together to offer a unique culinary experience. Their boutique is bursting with delights: crusty breads, mouth-watering viennoiseries and elegant pastries. Must-tries include Équinoxe and revisited classics such as éclair, baba au rhum and tarte au citron. A true gourmet pleasure in a charming and delicious setting.

label: Temple Sri Manika Vinayakar Alayam - Temple de Ganesh
comment: The Hindu temple of Ganesha, nestled in the heart of the Indian district of La Chapelle, is a place to celebrate the Hindu festivals of the calendar. Rue Pajol becomes the colorful stage for these festivities, which sometimes spill outside the temple. Devotees come here to pray before imposing statues of deities from the Hindu pantheon such as Ganesh, Durga, Ayyappan, Vishnu and Bhaivara. A spiritual and cultural immersion to be discovered in this lively district of Paris.

label: Le Zorba
comment: Located in Belleville, Bar-PMU Zorba offers a friendly, cosmopolitan atmosphere, open from 5am to 2am. Varied music, DJs and concerts on Thursdays, Fridays and Saturdays from 8pm to 2am, Manouche Jazz Jam Session on Thursdays and Sundays from 8pm to midnight. Afters on Saturdays and Sundays from 5am to 9am, with dancing in the basement and heated terrace in winter. Perfect for lively evenings!

label: Takara
comment: Opened in 1953, Takara is one of the pioneering Japanese restaurants in Paris, nestled in the capital's Japanese Quarter. Its menu emphasizes authenticity and tradition, offering diners a culinary experience rich in Japanese flavors. A must for lovers of Asian cuisine looking for a truly immersive taste experience.

label: Käramell
comment: The Käramell boutique, in the heart of Rue des Martyrs, is a real eye-catcher with its colorful window display. Lena, a Swede, invites you into a gourmet universe of Nordic flavors. At Käramell, Swedish sweets are king. Come and enjoy a sweet and exotic experience with original Scandinavian sweets, jams, honeys and surprises. A unique taste journey!

label: Grande Synagogue de Paris
comment: The Grande Synagogue de Paris, nicknamed the Synagogue de la Victoire, was inaugurated in 1874 and has been a listed historic monument since 1987. At 36 metres high, it combines Romanesque, Byzantine and Second Empire styles. Inside, a 28-meter nave houses superb organs and colorful stained-glass windows donated by Gustave de Rothschild. Numerous ornaments, including a solid silver candlestick, decorate this central location for Paris's Jewish community. A must-see.

comment: L'Atelier, under the direction of Joël Robuchon, is an haute gastronomie restaurant. Nestled near the Arc de Triomphe in the Publicis Drugstore, it takes its inspiration from Japanese restaurants with its long-bar-tasting concept. Offering a relaxed culinary experience, l'Atelier is a must for lovers of fine dining in Paris.

label: Glacier Berthillon
comment: The Berthillon ice cream parlour, located on the Ile Saint-Louis, is famous for its exquisitely flavored artisanal ice creams. Free from preservatives and sweeteners, its creations seduce with delicate flavors such as wild strawberry and pink grapefruit. The creamy textures and noble ingredients used, such as milk and eggs, make them a gastronomic gem. Berthillon is a must for gourmets in search of natural delights.

label: Le Costes
comment: Le Costes, bar and lounge restaurant, attracts celebrities with its Jacques Garcia decor, relaxing music, warm lounges and magnificent patios. As secret stars, they enjoy exceptional cuisine with flavors from around the world. Why not let yourself be tempted by this unique experience?

Modern and sophisticated, these temples to nail care, in privileged collaboration with the famous OPI brand and its rich range of 200 shades, welcome you for manicures, nail polish application and even pedicure sessions at attractive rates. With over fifteen locations across Paris, a beauty break at ColorForever Nail Bar is a must.

label: Le Floréal
comment: In the 10th arrondissement, near the Canal Saint-Martin, a former bar-tabac has been transformed into a trendy brasserie with a New York feel. The ultra-modern décor, inspired by Mondrian, invites customers to enjoy delicious dishes at affordable prices. The elevated terrace is perfect for a drink al fresco. The storefront, reminiscent of the style of architect Charlotte Perriand, will appeal to connoisseurs. A trendy and friendly place not to be missed.

label: Jugetsudo
comment: The Jugetsudo boutique invites you to discover teas from the prestigious Maruyama Nori house, founded in Japan in 1854. On the first floor, immerse yourself in a Zen atmosphere to taste and purchase these aromatic delights. Descend to the basement and immerse yourself in a vaulted cellar where the traditional tea ceremony takes place. An authentic experience that will delight lovers of Japanese culture and fine flavors.

comment: Discover the bistronomic cuisine of Château Poivre, combining gourmet goodness and quality. Flavors blend harmoniously to offer an explosion of tastes on the palate. Dishes prepared with care, using fresh seasonal produce. Accompany your meal with a selection of natural biodynamic wines to enhance every bite. An invitation to an exceptional culinary journey, in a warm and refined setting.

label: Shakespeare and Company Bookshop
comment: Next to Notre-Dame de Paris, on the banks of the Seine, is the Shakespeare and Company Bookshop. Housed in a traditional house, it embodies the cultural link between France, England and the United States. Readers can sit upstairs, immersed in a vast selection of books. Specializing in English-language literature, the bookshop stays open late into the evening, a haven for word lovers.

label: Y's Yohji Yamamoto Paris Louvre
comment: Since 1971, Japanese couturier Yohji Yamamoto has been sublimating the art of clothing by skilfully blending traditional feminine and masculine codes. A brilliant jack-of-all-trades, he has collaborated with iconic brands such as Adidas and Mandarina Duck. His style is characterized by bold layering, clean lines and sober hues, making him a master in the art of timeless elegance.

label: Parc des Buttes-Chaumont
comment: The Parc des Buttes Chaumont, one of the largest green spaces in Paris, is unique. Its 25 hectares of rolling hills offer superb views over Montmartre. Built on former quarries, it features grottoes, waterfalls, a suspension bridge and a beautiful perched folly. Exotic and indigenous trees adorn the park, which is home to seagulls, moorhens and mallard ducks around the lake. Children will find games and gourmet restaurants to make the most of this exceptional place.

comment: La Nouvelle Eve, near the Moulin Rouge, evokes the atmosphere of the "Roaring Twenties" with its sumptuous decor of midnight-blue velvet walls and glittering stars. Every evening from April to October, this cabaret offers a breathtaking show combining classical and modern choreography, emblematic French cancan, and 5 international acts in an exhilarating "century show". Succumb to its warm welcome, friendly atmosphere, refined cuisine and resolutely Parisian revue.

label: Mariage Frères - Le Marais
comment: A true paradise for tea lovers, this French institution offers an incredible selection of over 500 varieties. In a retro-colonial setting, visitors delight in delicious house specialties, both sweet and savory, all made from top-quality teas. A refined, gourmet experience not to be missed by enthusiasts of this age-old beverage.

A fun and entertaining activity for young and old alike!

This atypical site, steeped in history, is a veritable haven of culture and change of scenery in the midst of urban hustle and bustle. A true invitation to discovery and wonder.

At the same time, it spotlights young nuggets on the contemporary art market. A must for art lovers in search of unique discoveries and great names in contemporary creation.

An emblematic site for national gatherings, it is open to all, and offers a breathtaking view of the famous Parisian monument. Locals and visitors alike gather on its vast lawns to share a picnic, listen to music and contemplate the glittering Eiffel Tower after dark. A mythical place in the heart of the French capital.

label: Maison de Nicolas Flamel
comment: Nicolas Flamel's 15th-century house in Paris is the oldest in the city. Run by Flamel and his wife Pernelle as a home for the poor, it demanded prayers in exchange for lodging. Flamel, a renowned alchemist, is said to have discovered the philosopher's stone. Listed as a historic monument, the house features a carved stone facade and now houses a restaurant, offering the chance to discover its history.

label: Musée de la Libération de Paris - Musée du général Leclerc - Musée Jean Moulin
comment: The Musée de la Libération de Paris, dedicated to General Leclerc and Jean Moulin, is located on the Place Denfert-Rochereau. Inaugurated in 2019 to commemorate the 75th anniversary of the Liberation of Paris, it traces the history of these figures and of this major event. Located on the historic site of Denfert-Rochereau, the museum offers an immersive experience, including Rol-Tanguy's underground command post. Its aim is to inform the public about this key period, hence the free access to its collections. An indispensable place of memory for understanding this crucial period.

label: Lacoste
comment: Created in 1933 by René Lacoste, the Lacoste polo shirt symbolizes elegance and casualness with its famous crocodile. Whether on the tennis court or in the city, this iconic garment has conquered the world with its classic design and quality. Whether worn to work or with friends, the Lacoste polo combines comfort and elegance in all circumstances. Timeless, it remains a must-have in men's wardrobes, appreciated for its sporty, sophisticated style.

label: Maxim's
comment: In the magnificent Belle Époque setting of Pierre Cardin's restaurant, guests enjoy exceptional dishes. Carefully selected products offer a refined and unforgettable culinary experience. An elegant atmosphere and attentive service add to the magic of this emblematic place where gastronomy rhymes with perfection.

label: Colonne Vendôme
comment: The Vendôme Column, erected in the heart of Place Vendôme in 1810, stands 44 metres high. A tribute to the valiant soldiers of Austerlitz, it was inspired by the majestic Trajan column in Rome. Its shaft, fashioned from 1,200 cannons captured from Russian and Austrian armies, is adorned with bas-reliefs evoking trophies in the style of Antiquity. A symbol of grandeur and heroism that stands proudly in the French capital.

additional_information: ['The Vendôme column is visible from the outside but cannot be visited.']

label: L’Oya Café
comment: L'Oya, an atypical café in the Gobelins district of Paris (13th arrondissement), has an original concept: a collection of 500 board games to try out. There's something for everyone. The passionate owners unearth treasures from all over the world for an eclectic selection: strategy, sport, chance, culture... For a small fee, you can enjoy a drink while playing your favorite game to your heart's content. Games available for purchase. A friendly place to discover without delay!

label: Moonshiner
comment: This bar, named in tribute to Prohibition-era moonshine, offers an authentic experience. To get there, walk past Da Vito's pizzeria and push open the metal door to the cold room. The hushed, jazzy ambience transports you back in time. In addition to cocktails and beers, you can choose from 83 different whiskies. It's an immersion in history and taste that's not to be missed.

label: Lucas Carton Paris
comment: Founded in 1732, La Table Lucas Carton is a prestigious place that blends tradition and modernity. Its Art Nouveau and contemporary decor showcase a refined cuisine blending high-end dishes with exotic flavors. For a more affordable experience, Lucas' Marché is accessible via the Galerie de la Madeleine. Finally, the "Le Jardin du Lucas" terrace offers an exceptional view of the church and Place de la Madeleine for unforgettable culinary moments in Paris.

label: Tiffany & Co. (Champs-Élysées)
comment: Tiffany & Co, the famous New York brand, inaugurates its Paris flagship on the most prestigious avenue in the City of Light. On 930 m², the luxury and refinement of American haute joaillerie is elegantly on display. In addition to iconic collections such as Fiançailles, Tiffany Keys and Atlas®, the showroom features a sumptuous spiral staircase and a majestic central chandelier. A true visual enchantment for lovers of beauty and elegance.

label: La Ferme du Rail
comment: La Ferme du Rail, along the Petite Ceinture, combines urban agriculture and solidarity. A prizewinner in the "Réinventer Paris" competition, it features a vegetable garden, a greenhouse, the Passage à Niveau restaurant and a wooden building for some 20 people in social reintegration. The restaurant, open to all, cooks fresh local produce from the farm, grown using permaculture and aquaponics. A fine ecological and solidarity-based initiative in the heart of the capital.

label: Ken Club
comment: Located on the banks of the Seine in Passy, the Ken Club extends over 1,600 m² of exceptional space, all on one level. The first fitness club in Paris to benefit from natural lighting, it boasts a high-end, invigorating atmosphere. In addition to state-of-the-art sports equipment, this private club offers a relaxing interlude in the spa, with five treatment cabins, steam rooms and sauna, as well as a 14-metre swimming pool ideal for unwinding.

label: Big Bus Paris
comment: Discover Paris with Big Bus and explore the City of Light at your own pace. Take advantage of the red and blue tours to see the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre and Montmartre. Our multilingual commentary, double-decker bus and Deluxe Seine cruise await you. Hop on and off freely all day long, thanks to our app. Enjoy a flexible and unforgettable sightseeing experience in Paris with Big Bus Tours.

label: Cerruti 1881
comment: The Italian men's ready-to-wear brand stands out for its quality, style and craftsmanship. In addition to apparel, it offers a wide range of accessories such as watches, perfumes, leather goods, jewelry, eyewear, ties, shoes and writing instruments. This complete collection offers a luxurious and elegant masculine universe, true to Italian excellence and refinement.

label: Meltdown Paris
comment: Le Meltdown, a hangout for video game and e-sport enthusiasts near Place de la Bastille. Immersive atmosphere with barcraft, Mario Bros, League of Legends and Starcraft games, regular tournaments. E-sport competitions broadcast live on screens, friendly atmosphere for meetings and relaxation. The perfect meeting place for Parisian gamers in search of conviviality and fun.

label: Le Café Barge
comment: Once used to transport oil, the barge steeped in history is now a convivial venue appreciated by epicureans in search of unique experiences. Overlooking the Seine, Café Barge attracts with its warm atmosphere, tempting menu and refined cocktails. Ideal for enjoying a delicious meal while taking in the view of the water and the quays of Paris. A must for food lovers looking for an original setting.

label: Restaurant Guy Savoy - Monnaie de Paris
comment: Michelin-starred chef Guy Savoy, a true artist in the kitchen, delights his guests with dishes that are as beautiful as they are delicious. In his restaurant, nestled in the Monnaie de Paris along the Seine, he sublimates every product. Masterful cooking, delicate textures, harmonious flavors: an exceptional gustatory journey to the heart of generosity and goodness.

label: Théâtre Laurette
comment: The Théâtre Laurette, located between Goncourt and République, offers an eclectic and varied program. Audiences can enjoy comedy, classical and contemporary plays, improvisation, stand-up comedy and live music. The stage also plays host to shows for younger audiences from 2 years upwards. A great opportunity to enjoy the artistic and cultural wealth offered by this emblematic Parisian venue.

label: H&M (Champs-Élysées)
comment: In search of its own style, H&M will satisfy every taste. From chic to casual, urban to sportswear, the Swedish brand offers collections for the whole family. In its brand-new flagship designed by renowned architect Jean Nouvel, discover the latest fashion trends over 2,700 m². A must for fashionistas in search of the latest trends!

label: La Gaîté Lyrique
comment: La Gaîté Lyrique, a Parisian cultural institution, is committed to the cultural, social, democratic and environmental spheres. With the Fabrique de l'époque, it encourages new modes of artistic collaboration and citizen participation. Concerts, debates, performances, workshops... bring together all those passionate about creation and collective action. A key venue for energizing the capital's cultural life.

label: Frenchie
comment: Fancy a culinary journey between tradition and modernity? Head for Frenchie in Paris' Sentier district. This bistro offers French cuisine reinvented with an international touch, in a retro New York decor. Need a break? Frenchie to go, at 9 rue du Nil, offers quality takeaway meals. And to prolong the pleasure, discover the Frenchie wine bar across the street, at 6 rue du Nil. A convivial gastronomic experience for lovers of good food.

label: Galerie Mathgoth
comment: Located in the dynamic 13th arrondissement, Mathilde and Gauthier Jourdain's gallery is dedicated to urban art. Mathgoth showcases renowned artists such as Jace, David Walker, Lee Jeffries, Cope2 and Morten Andersen. Since 2012, enthusiasts have been able to acquire exclusive lithographs, sublimated by the artists' personal touch.

label: Ralph Lauren
comment: Ralph Lauren perfectly embodies the essence of American fashion, subtly blending elegance and discretion through collections inspired by iconic American symbols. Its spacious 1,200 m² flagship store even features a restaurant for a unique shopping experience. A must for lovers of refined, timeless style.

label: Musée de la magie - Musée des automates
comment: Opened in 1993, the Musée de la Magie offers a fascinating journey into the world of illusion. With its unique collections, interactive games, optical illusions and a show highlighting the ancient art of magic, it promises an unforgettable experience. Magician guides reveal the mysteries of this art, while the Musée des Automates exhibits over 100 amazing machines. At the touch of a button, visitors are immersed in a world of creativity and surprises. An experience combining dreams, technology and magic that's a must-see!

label: Les calèches de Versailles
comment: Discover the charms of Paris aboard a Versailles horse-drawn carriage! Our professional team offers horse-drawn carriage tours for individuals and groups, from Wednesday to Sunday. Their experience in the field enables them to adapt and organize sightseeing tours in complete safety. Let us guide you on an original tour of the City of Light!

label: L'Alsace
comment: Brasserie L?Alsace, a Champs-Elysées institution since 1968, opens its doors to you 24/7 with the authenticity of a Parisian brasserie. Discover the delights of Alsatian cuisine, with specialties such as sauerkraut and local wines. Plus, indulge in a variety of fresh seafood. An emblematic place for lovers of good food!

label: Théâtre du Châtelet
comment: The Théâtre du Châtelet, designed by architect Gabriel Davioud, opened in Paris in 1862, on the Place du Châtelet. The venue offers a varied program including musicals, operas, ballets, concerts and musical theater. Performances take place in the 2,048-seat main auditorium and on the ephemeral stage in the Grand Foyer. Guided tours are also available to discover this exceptional venue.

label: Bis Boutique Solidaire
comment: The boutique offers a unique opportunity to give clothing a second life. Collected, sorted and sold, these items support the professional reintegration of people in difficulty. By enriching your wardrobe, you're also taking part in an excellent social action. It's a responsible and supportive approach that's definitely worth adopting!

label: Le Mansart
comment: Le Mansart, with its skilful blend of traditional and modern decor, is the place to be for hipsters in "SoPi" (South Pigalle). A warm welcome, cutting-edge music, tasty finger food and even a table soccer table rare in Paris make this ultra-trendy establishment a place to see and be seen. Run by the same pros as Chez Jeannette and Le Floréal, Le Mansart is definitely the star of this lively district's trendy scene.

label: Fondation des Artistes
comment: The Foundation promotes contemporary creation through moral and financial actions in support of the graphic and plastic arts. It oversees studio spaces for contemporary artists and the Maison nationale des artistes. Since 2006, the Maison d?art Bernard-Anthonioz has organized exhibitions highlighting current artistic creation.

label: La Favela Chic
comment: Come and enjoy an exotic experience in this tropical restaurant-club! Under the direction of chefs Thierry Marx and Michel Bras, chef Benjamin Darnaud will introduce you to festive, colorful Brazilian cuisine. After your meal, plunge into a caliente atmosphere on the dance floor, with Latin and retro hits to keep you dancing all night long. Don't miss the Petit Club and Pop Up Galerie, for a unique Parisian evening!

label: Green River Cruises
comment: Take an unforgettable cruise with Green River Cruises in Paris, between the Jardin des Plantes and the Bibliothèque Nationale. Depart from the Cité de la Mode et du Design for one-hour excursions to the Louvre at 50? per passenger (minimum 6 persons). Opt for a romantic cruise to the Eiffel Tower (1H30) at 390?, or charter a boat for 2 to 12 people for a magical evening on the Seine, day or night, from 1H to 3H. Experience magical moments in Paris.

label: Lanvin
comment: The magnificent showcases of Alber Elbaz, artistic director of Lanvin, the famous fashion house launched by Jeanne Lanvin in 1909, impress. In 2012, to mark a decade of remarkable creations, he unveiled a special "Happy" collection, reflecting his love for the brand's signature feminine elegance. His talent and vision have propelled Lanvin to the top of the fashion industry.

label: L'Ambroisie
comment: Since 1986, L'Ambroisie, a prestigious restaurant, has nestled in the heart of the Marais district, under the splendid arcades of Place des Vosges, replacing a former goldsmith's store. Bernard and Mathieu Pacaud, starred chefs, father and son, welcome guests. In an 18th-century setting with Aubusson tapestries, period parquet flooring and period furniture, l'Ambroisie offers an extraordinary culinary experience, a true journey back in time to the heart of French gastronomy.

label: Arc de Triomphe
comment: Dominating the Champs-Élysées, the Arc de Triomphe is a symbol of French history. Commissioned by Napoleon I in 1806 to celebrate the victory of the Grande Armée, this monument pays tribute to the battles and generals of the First Empire. The eternal flame of the Unknown Soldier lights up the terrace every evening, providing a breathtaking spectacle. From the top, the view of the Champs-Élysées is breathtaking, day and night. A must-see to discover the grandeur of Paris.

label: O'nesty bar
comment: The O'nesty bar, located in the boutique hotel of the same name and designed by renowned designer Ora Ïto, attracts a hip and famous clientele, close to the Place des Victoires. Its futuristic ambience, blending vegetation and Japanese inspiration, creates a warm atmosphere. Come and enjoy a wide selection of original cocktails in this chic and exotic setting. A must for a sophisticated experience.

label: Le Comptoir Général
comment: Le Comptoir Général is a unique combination of bar, restaurant, art gallery and store, a museum dedicated to the art of the ghetto. African culture takes pride of place in the cocktails, the artists on display, the dishes and the food store. Its attractive brunch attracts many gourmands to the banks of the Canal Saint-Martin. A place not to be missed for an experience rich in discoveries and flavors.

label: Theo Théâtre
comment: Located close to Porte de Versailles, Théo Théâtre offers a diverse program that will delight adults and young people alike. In addition to shows accessible to all, this establishment offers acting classes for amateurs of all levels. A rich and varied cultural offering, ideal for beginners or advanced students of the dramatic arts.

label: Jardin des Tuileries
comment: The Jardin des Tuileries, designed by André Le Nôtre in the 16th century, is a magnificent French garden between the Louvre and Place de la Concorde, with sculptures and ponds for relaxing. Nearby, the Musée de l'Orangerie exhibits Monet's masterpieces, with free guided tours in French. In summer, the Fête des Tuileries attracts lovers of merry-go-rounds and sweets. This emblematic Parisian landmark combines relaxation, culture and entertainment.

June, July and August: daily, 7am-11pm. The evacuation of the public begins 30 minutes before closing time.']

label: Fondation d'entreprise Pernod Ricard
comment: The Fondation d'entreprise Pernod Ricard, heir to the patronage of Société Ricard, supports young artists in the visual arts. Located between the Place de la Concorde and the Place de la Madeleine, this space is home to a wide range of activities designed to promote contemporary creation: exhibitions, conferences, presentation of the Ricard Corporate Foundation Prize. A must for art lovers in search of discovery and inspiration.

label: Oh! Happy Paris
comment: Located in the Grands Boulevards district, Oh! Happy-Paris is a festive, interactive cabaret, the only one of its kind in France. Since 2007, this heir to the legendary Chorus Café has been putting on memorable shows revisiting musical hits from the 80s to the present day. Audiences join in by singing along with the artists, creating a convivial atmosphere. This "music live" restaurant promises rhythmic evenings combining music and gastronomy for everyone's enjoyment.

additional_information: ['Dinner and show from 8pm. Live show from 10:15pm. Clubbing night from 11.30pm.']

label: Jardin Berthe Morisot
comment: Located in the Tolbiac district of Paris, the Berthe Morisot garden offers a real change of scenery, with its undulating terrain and majestic conifers. Stone waterfalls add a touch of freshness and originality to this peaceful setting. Younger guests can enjoy climbing on the playground equipment or blossoming in the creative sandbox. A natural, fun getaway for the whole family.

label: La Mangerie
comment: Located in the famous Marais district, La Mangerie is a warm and welcoming place to enjoy tapas and savory treats. Its friendly brunch welcomes families at weekends, offering children a space to play under the attentive supervision of a nanny while parents enjoy their meal in peace and quiet. An address not to be missed for relaxing family moments.

label: Au Moulin à Vent
comment: Discover the perfect marriage of Salers meats and Beaujolais wines. The full-bodied flavors of these quality meats blend perfectly with the finesse and subtlety of the vintages from this renowned wine region. A harmonious blend of terroir and savoir-faire for incomparable culinary pleasures. Treat yourself to an authentic culinary experience by combining these two exceptional products!?? #Gastronomie #Terroir #PlaisirsCulinaires

label: Parc de Belleville
comment: In the 19th century, Belleville was a peaceful rural village with farms and mills. Haussmann's construction attracted the working classes. Since 1988, the 45,000 m² Belleville park has offered a magnificent view over Paris. Children can play in a playful wooden village with stairs and slides. The park features a waterway with cascades, a belvedere offering panoramic views over Paris and grape-producing vines in homage to the village's wine-growing past.

label: Ferme urbaine René Binet
comment: In 2019, at the Jardin René Binet in the heart of the city, an innovative urban farm will set up and flourish, offering a soothing haven of greenery. Open to all, it raises awareness of urban agriculture and the ecological services provided by animals. La Ferme de Paris promotes essential links between nature, society and urban planning, contributing to a sustainable environment for all.

label: Le Caveau des Oubliettes
comment: Le Caveau des Oubliettes, a live music club in Paris' Latin Quarter, attracts fans of jazz, blues, funk, soul and world music. Keziah Jones and Lucky Peterson often play there. Comedians offer stand-up routines on Saturday evenings. Close to Notre-Dame, this venue offers a unique atmosphere where music transports. Admission is free, and all you need to enjoy the show is a drink.

label: Pari Roller
comment: Every Friday evening, the Pari Roller association invites thrill-seekers on rollerblades. Meet at 10 p.m. sharp in Place Raoul Dautry, between the Tower and Gare Montparnasse in the 14th arrondissement. Return to the same place around 1am. To ensure everyone's safety, it's best to master the art of braking before embarking on the adventure. On your skates, get set, go! ?????

label: Breizh Café
comment: Located in the heart of the Marais district, Breizh Café offers a veritable gustatory voyage to Brittany. Traditional or revisited galettes and crêpes, accompanied by a selection of quality ciders, will delight the taste buds of gourmets. The warm ambience of the light wood-panelled dining room invites conviviality, perfectly reflecting Breton hospitality. With three locations in Paris, this crêperie is a must for lovers of authentic Breton cuisine.

comment: Come and discover our boutique specializing in luxury brands! You'll find clothes and accessories from top designers such as Gaultier, Yamamoto and Dries Van Noten at very attractive prices. Take advantage of discontinued items to treat yourself to exceptional pieces without breaking the bank. An unmissable opportunity to combine style and bargains!

label: Marché Grenelle
comment: Shopping near the Eiffel Tower is a chic and authentic experience. Between the florists, including an organic one, and the colorful stalls of fresh fruit and vegetables, you'll also find a variety of shops. A typically Parisian atmosphere, with plenty to fill your basket with quality produce to delight your taste buds. A gourmet moment to enjoy in the heart of the capital.

label: Spa Paris Thémaé
comment: Immerse yourself in the enchanting world of tea at the Parisian spa Thémaé, where this age-old beverage is at the heart of cosmetics. The exclusive 4 Teas Complex cleverly combines the benefits of regenerating white tea, revitalizing black tea, soothing red tea and detoxifying green tea. Let yourself be enchanted by the ceremonial treatments, the tranquil ambience and the soberly refined décor that reflect a resolutely Japanese spirit.

label: La Maison de l'Aubrac
comment: Élisabeth and Christian Valette, farmers in Laguiole and restaurateurs in Paris, are passionate about celebrating local gastronomy. Their farm supplies the famous Aubrac beef, which is featured prominently in their restaurants. La Maison de l'Aubrac, close to the Champs-Élysées, offers an authentic culinary experience. Melt-in-the-mouth Aligot, creamy Laguiole cheese, crispy Farçous... An unmissable tasting experience where Aubrac beef is the star.

label: Arnaud Delmontel
comment: For over ten years, this baker-patissier has been a fixture on the chic Rue des Martyrs. The originator of the famous "Renaissance" baguette, he was the official baker to the Élysée Palace in 2007. His store combines tradition and modernity for a unique gourmet experience. A not-to-be-missed address for lovers of artisan know-how and authentic flavors.

The refined ambience orchestrated by designer Aline Asmar d'Amman will make your experience even more memorable.

label: Gare de Paris-Nord
comment: Gare du Nord, Europe's leading railway station, is home to 59 shops on 5 levels. Here you'll find attractive brands such as Five Guys, Roberta, Maison Pradier, De Neuville, Sephora, Mango, Etam, Celio, Jennyfer, Naf Naf, Hema... Our retailers are there to give you a warm welcome, whether you're on a shopping spree, travelling or simply on the move. A wide choice to satisfy all your desires!

comment: Brasserie La Baleine specializes in white, lager and amber beers, and offers tasty, original recipes. Open to direct sales, it supplies individuals, professionals and associations alike. Discover quality craft beers and support a local company passionate about its brewing expertise.

label: Yves Thuriès - Chocolatier récoltant
comment: Yves Thuriès puts chocolate at the heart of its expertise. Presented in different forms such as praline rochers, flavored ganaches, fruit jellies, confectionery, pastries, ice creams and macaroons, each product is meticulously designed. The raw materials are rigorously selected by master chocolatiers before being processed daily. The results can be savoured in the boutiques of this renowned chocolatier-confectioner.

label: Maison Deyrolle
comment: Located between the Musée d'Orsay and the Musée Maillol, Maison Deyrolle, in the 7th arrondissement, is much more than just a store. Founded in 1831, it is a world reference in taxidermy and entomology. On the 1st floor of 46 rue du Bac, visitors can admire exceptional pieces: colorful butterfly boxes, surprisingly realistic mammals and birds. Maison Deyrolle attracts a wide public to draw inspiration from this unique setting.

label: Bibliothèque Benjamin Rabier
comment: At the heart of the Cité des Sciences et de l'Industrie de la Villette, the Benjamin Rabier library offers a rich and diverse range of reading material. With 500 books for adults, almost 4,500 comic strips, and a children's collection of over 20,000 books, there's something for everyone. What's more, 9 multimedia stations are available to enhance visitors' experience. A must-see destination for reading enthusiasts of all ages.

label: Nomadeshop - Le meilleur de la glisse urbaine
comment: The store is a landmark for inline skating enthusiasts. It offers a variety of materials, equipment and accessories for this urban sport, as well as for fans of urban stilts and street surfing. In addition to sales, rollerblading lessons are available for beginners wishing to progress. It's the place to be for all fans of these fashionable disciplines.

label: Abbey Bookshop Paris
comment: Since 1989, the Canadian bookshop Abbey Bookshop has been nestled in the charming Latin Quarter, precisely in the Dubuisson mansion. This must-see address offers not only a rich selection of Canadian books, but also no fewer than 35,000 English-language titles. An emblematic place where reading enthusiasts are sure to find something to their liking among this vast literary collection.

With quality products like L'Oréal Professionnel and Kérastase, your satisfaction is their priority. Bonus: no need to book an appointment! TCHIP, for a hairstyle that highlights your natural beauty.

label: France Tourisme
comment: Discover Paris and France with France Tourisme! More than 100 must-do activities await you: cruises on the Seine, museum visits, Eiffel Tower climbs, panoramic bus rides, excursions to Versailles, Disneyland Paris, Mont St Michel, the Loire Castles, Normandy or Champagne. label: Galleria Continua Paris
comment: Galleria Continua, in the heart of the Marais district, brilliantly blends art and gastronomy. Food from around the world blends with French flavors in this atypical three-floor venue. Contemporary works by major artists such as Michelangelo Pistoletto and Anish Kapoor attract visitors, as does the inaugural exhibition by JR, with whom the gallery has collaborated. A subtle alliance between art and cuisine in a captivating place.

label: Cimetière de Picpus
comment: The Picpus cemetery in Paris, at the heart of the French Revolution, is an active necropolis. It includes a private enclosure and a small cemetery where the victims of the guillotine in 1794 are laid to rest. Reserved for families, this place steeped in history is maintained by the descendants of the original donors. Among the graves are names from the aristocracy, including that of La Fayette, adorned with an American flag. This symbolic site saw Colonel Stanton pay tribute to La Fayette in 1917.

label: Spa Cinq Mondes - Samaritaine Paris Pont-Neuf
comment: Cinq Mondes, the French benchmark for treatments inspired by the beauty rituals of the five continents, has set up shop at La Samaritaine with a brand-new concept. Like a warm, chic apartment, this spa and boutique offers a unique experience. Located on the Rivoli side, overlooking a garden, this 400 m2 space is a haven of peace in the heart of the capital. With seven treatment rooms, a private hammam and a scrub room, it promises regeneration and well-being.

label: Café Dad
comment: In this brasserie, run by three Normandy cooking enthusiasts, home-style gastronomy takes pride of place, with generous, tasty dishes served at any time of day. Every day, a new menu features dishes made with fresh produce. Diners enjoy these dishes in a warm atmosphere, comfortably seated in velvet armchairs or on the sunny terrace.

label: Chalet des îles - Daumesnil
comment: The Chalet des îles Daumesnil, located on Ile de Reuilly in the heart of the Bois de Vincennes, was recently transformed into "l'île Anaë". Since February 2023, this former 19th-century Swiss pavilion has become the country home of gin house Anaë and chef Manon Fleury. In this bucolic setting, they promote fairness, inclusion and respect for living things. A true haven of peace, the Chalet des îles Daumesnil offers a natural break in the heart of the capital.

label: Athénée théâtre Louis-Jouvet
comment: Renowned for its splendor and renowned acoustics, the Athénée Théâtre Louis-Jouvet is one of Paris?s must-see Italian-style theaters. Its eclectic program features major works of theater, opera and even jazz. Inaugurated in 1896 and listed as a historic monument, this exceptional venue has been dedicated to public service since 1982, embodying a cultural heritage of inestimable value.

label: Kilomètre25
comment: Located under the Paris ring road on the border between Paris and Pantin, Kilomètre25 is a creative open-air venue. From June 3 to October 31, the venue hosts techno and house nights with international artists. Exhibitions and shops offer tattoos, thrift shops and harnesses. On Friday and Saturday evenings, a troupe of performers fuses circus and dance. A diverse program will delight fans of electronic music.

label: Oh ! César by César Palace Paris
comment: At the foot of the Montparnasse Tower, the Oh! César cabaret offers a unique experience combining restaurant, cabaret and club. Come and experience an unforgettable dinner and show in a glamorous and funny universe where talented artists will amaze you. Dancers, acrobats, comedians, magicians and musicians put on a magical, interactive show. After the show, extend your evening in the club until 1:45 with cocktails and dancing for a magical night at Oh! César!

After the show, extend your evening in the club until 1:45 with cocktails and dancing for a magical night at Oh! César!
additional_information: ['Lunch from 12pm, show from 2pm to 3.15pm and afternoon dance from 3.15pm to 4pm. Dinner from 7:30 pm, show from 10 pm to 11:15 pm and club until 1:45 am. Check the website for the days of the show.']

label: Boulinier
comment: Located in the legendary Latin Quarter, the Boulinier bookshop has been seducing customers with its plethora of products since 1845. Used books, CDs, vinyls, DVDs: you name it, this den of knowledge has it. Nestled in the heart of Paris?s student quarter, this institution offers affordable prices and a warm, inviting atmosphere. A must for culture lovers in search of treasures.

label: Musée des Arts et Métiers
comment: Immerse yourself in the history of technology at the Musée des Arts et Métiers, housed in the former abbey of Saint-Martin-des-Champs. The collections cover seven fascinating fields, covering developments since the 16th century: scientific instruments, construction, transport and more. You'll discover such treasures as the automaton La Joueuse de tympanon (1784), Foucault's Pendulum (1851) and an aeroplane (1897). Don't wait any longer to take this exciting tour to the Arts et Métiers metro station.

label: Église Saint-Louis de la Salpêtrière
comment: The elegantly styled Meridian dial sits on the south façade, overlooking the gardens behind the church. Its fine lines and precise numerals bear witness to the craftsmanship of the artisans, making it a functional and aesthetic work of art. The play of light and shadow makes it a unique visual spectacle, inviting visitors to contemplate its timeless beauty, a perfect marriage of art and science.

On one side, customers are captivated by 10 models of bangs in natural hair, easy to attach. On the other, 10 long hairstyles, executed in just 30 minutes! An eco-responsible approach completes this cutting-edge establishment.

label: École du Breuil - Arts et Techniques du paysage
comment: The École du Breuil in the Bois de Vincennes covers 23 hectares and is open to the general public. It features an arboretum, orchard, greenhouse and various plant collections. With 6,000 species listed, it is part of the Paris Botanical Garden. It also has a photo library and a specialized library. Each year, it trains around 300 students from the second year of secondary school up to professional degree level, and has been organizing guided tours since 2011.

additional_information: ['The École du Breuil is a school and is therefore closed to the public. However, access to the library is possible on Mondays, Wednesdays and Fridays, from 9am to 5pm, on Tuesdays, from 1pm to 6pm and on Thursdays, from 9am to 6pm. The Arboretum is freely accessible every day (see the website for opening hours).']

label: Hotel de Ville de Paris
comment: Since 1357, the Hôtel de Ville de Paris has been the seat of the Paris municipality. Rebuilt in neo-Renaissance style after the fire of 1871, this emblematic building is steeped in history. Guided tours are available on reservation, and feature the magnificent Salle des Fêtes, reminiscent of the Hall of Mirrors at Versailles. Free exhibitions attract a wide audience, offering an immersion into the political and cultural life of the capital.

label: Basilique Sainte Jeanne d'Arc
comment: The Basilique Sainte Jeanne d'Arc, in the Chapelle district of Paris, next to the church of Saint-Denys, is a site dedicated to Joan of Arc. This monument features exceptional stained-glass windows illuminating the interior, showcasing a superb bust and full-length statue of the saint. Fans of sacred art will marvel at the splendor of this site. A must-see visit to immerse yourself in its symbolic history.

A successful cinema outing!

The friendly atmosphere on the first floor contrasts with the more musical basement. Customers can enjoy excellent cocktails in a relaxed atmosphere.

Pleats, gathers, superimpositions and a play of materials intermingle in her dresses, available in sober tones such as black, gray and brown, but also in light hues such as white and ecru. Her creativity and attention to detail transform each of her creations into a wearable work of art.

comment: The Pavillon Montsouris, built in 1889 for the 1892 Universal Exhibition, is a historic French monument in a Paris park. This renowned restaurant offers traditional, high-quality cuisine in an exceptional setting. Enjoy unique dishes in an unforgettable gastronomic experience. The luxurious decor and elegant ambience add to the pleasure of savoring delicious food. Treat yourself to a culinary escapade and discover French art sublimated by talented chefs.

In addition to its spiritual function, it also hosts concerts, providing a space for celebration and culture in the heart of the city.

At the heart of the park, an imposing staircase decorated with ivy catches the eye. A fountain dating from 1714 keeps Parisians cool in the first rays of sunshine, unless they prefer to rest in the shade of the exotic trees lining the garden. A veritable oasis of calm and greenery in the heart of the capital.

Ekjo is a committed designer, conveying a message of respect and symbiosis with the world.

comment: The Théâtre de la Ville, in the heart of Paris, is rich in history. Opened in 1860, burnt down in 1871 during the Commune, renovated and renamed several times. Under Sarah Bernhardt for 25 years, becomes emblematic. Its magnificent façade is a historic monument. Varied program: theater, dance, concerts. A key venue on the Paris cultural scene.

All at very affordable prices, making Mirama a must for lovers of Chinese cuisine in Paris.

label: Pigalle Country Club
comment: The Pigalle Country Club, a former Pigalle girl bar, blends decadence with a subdued New York atmosphere. The owners have recreated the ambience of the Bushwick Country Club in a red and black décor, offering mysterious cocktails such as Johnny Thunders or Debbie Harry, accompanied by an eclectic playlist. This atypical venue combines a music bar and a micro-label producing limited-edition vinyls, with DJ sets and indie rock, pop and electro-punk concerts. A must for lovers of music and original cocktails.

label: Le cinéma des cinéastes
comment: The "Cabaret du Père Lathuille" has an eventful history. A former café-concert frequented by the likes of Édouard Manet, it became a cinema in the 30s. Its bilingual programming made it very popular, before being neglected after the war. Renovated with the help of Fanny Ardant, it became a reference point for cinema in Paris. The Bistrot des Cinéastes is also a popular venue for meetings and retrospectives.

label: Maison Georges Larnicol
comment: Georges Larnicol, a talented pastry chef from Brittany, inherited the family business before opening his third store in Paris in 2012. Winner of the "Meilleur ouvrier de France" in 1993, he seduces his customers with a wide range of sweet treats: chocolates, macaroons, caramels, bonbons and his specialty, the "kouignette", a revisitation of the famous kouign aman. For lovers of refined sweets, this is an address not to be missed!

Formerly the Garde-meuble de la Couronne and Ministère de la Marine, it is now open to the public on a daily basis. Visitors can explore the sumptuous apartments and salons with Confident headphones for a unique audio experience. Tours of 30 to 90 minutes are available, with a family option. The gallery regularly hosts masterpieces from the Al Thani Collection.

In addition to exhibitions, it offers guided tours, lectures, meetings, screenings, masterclasses and activities for all. With a library, auditorium and specialized bookshop, the MEP is a prestigious venue dedicated to the art of photography.

In addition to exhibitions, it offers guided tours, lectures, meetings, screenings, masterclasses and activities for all. With a library, auditorium and specialized bookshop, the MEP is a prestigious venue dedicated to the art of photography.
additional_information: ['Wednesday and Friday from 11am to 8pm; Thursday from 11am to 10pm; Saturday and Sunday from 10am to 8pm']

label: LM Bistro
comment: A few steps from the Arc de Triomphe, in the heart of the Meridien Étoile hotel, the Jazz Club Étoile has been hosting internationally renowned artists since 1975. In an elegant and hushed setting, music lovers come here to enjoy the quality programming. This musical moment is accompanied by a cocktail, a snack or a concert platter. A Jazzy brunch is proposed on Sunday around a buffet.

label: Le Musée du Fumeur
comment: In 2001, the Musée du Fumeur opened, bringing together plants, works of art and objects related to smoking. This unique collection shows the evolution of attitudes towards smoking. The act of smoking, imported by Christopher Columbus five hundred years ago, has gone global. Through 26 themes, the museum offers a fascinating panorama of smoking through the ages and across cultures, inviting deep reflection on this universal habit.

label: Marché Saint-Pierre
comment: The Marché Saint-Pierre district, at the foot of the Butte Montmartre, is a popular spot for fabric and haberdashery enthusiasts. Rue d'Orsel, Rue Charles Nodier, Rue Livingstone, Rue Seveste, Pierre Picard and Place Saint-Pierre are packed with fashion and decorating professionals, with well-known boutiques such as Dreyfus, Reine and Moline, as well as confidential but expert addresses. It's THE place to be for couture and home decor enthusiasts!

label: Pierre Sang on Gambey
comment: Talented chef Pierre Sang, revealed in 2011 by the TV show Top Chef, inaugurates his second restaurant in Paris, on rue Gambey, close to his first address. Having trained with renowned chefs, he offers a unique gastronomic experience, immersing diners in a culinary journey to his native Korea. An opportunity to savor refined, authentic cuisine, imbued with creativity and passion.

label: Église protestante unie - La Rencontre
comment: Located near the Gare du Nord and Gare de l'Est railway stations, La Rencontre Reformed Church is rooted in the history of the 16th-century Reformation. The result of the reunification of the churches in 1938, it was built when the Milton and Nord chapels merged in 1962. In its place of worship, it regularly hosts cultural events such as concerts, theater and choirs, providing a space for artistic encounters and exchanges in the heart of the city.

label: Cours de civilisation française de la Sorbonne
Merci
comment: A 1,500m² concept store offering a variety of decor, furniture, clothing and haute couture products, from everyday items to exclusives. Profits support a foundation for Malagasy women and children. For a gourmet lunch break, head for the Cantine Merci in the basement, with fresh dishes featuring local produce and seasonal vegetables, served in recycled crockery for an eco-responsible approach. A committed and delicious shopping experience!

label: Kinugawa Vendôme
comment: Kinugawa, a renowned Japanese restaurant in Paris, offers refined exotic cuisine overlooking the Tuileries. Each dish is an invitation to a sensory voyage, blending tradition and modernity for gourmets in search of escape. An unforgettable culinary experience in the heart of the City of Light, ideal for Japanese cuisine enthusiasts in search of unique discoveries.

label: Atelier des Lumières
comment: In the heart of Paris's 11th arrondissement, the Atelier des Lumières, housed in a former foundry, is an innovative exhibition space. Thanks to 140 video projectors and an immersive sound system, the continuous digital exhibitions offer an extraordinary experience. With its 3,300 m² of floor-to-ceiling space and 10-meter-high walls, this unique multimedia facility promises total immersion for visitors.

label: Île aux Cygnes
comment: The Île aux Cygnes artificial island is a peaceful jewel between the Grenelle and Bir-Hakeim bridges. Created in 1825, it is adorned with hundreds of trees, offering a unique and pleasant space. Sports enthusiasts love to work out in the open air, enjoying the view of the Eiffel Tower thanks to the sports facilities available. The 16-metre-high replica of the Statue of Liberty is the island's main attraction, enthroned majestically at its southern tip.

label: La Petite Ceinture
comment: The Petite Ceinture, a former railroad line surrounding Paris, has become a haven for urban biodiversity. With more than 200 plant species and 70 animal species, it offers magnificent bucolic walks. Former stations transformed into bars, restaurants and cultural spaces add to its charm. Open to the public in several arrondissements, there are plenty of surprises in store for lovers of nature in the city.

label: Théâtre La Cible
comment: Formerly a peepshow, the Théâtre La Cible has been converted into a space dedicated to humor. An emblematic venue where talented young artists got their start, it has seen the likes of Baptiste Lecaplain, Gaspard Proust and Bérengère Krief pass through its doors. An atypical scene that has revealed many of the great names in French humor.

label: Théâtre BO Saint-Martin
comment: Housed in a former bookshop specializing in comic strips, the BO theater offers a varied program focusing on humor, new talent, comedy and children's shows. Ideally located just a stone's throw from Place de la République, the BO Saint-Martin attracts audiences in search of quality entertainment. Evenings full of laughter and emotion await you in this warm and dynamic cultural venue.

label: Jeu de Paume Paris
comment: The Jeu de Paume, an art center in the heart of Paris, opened in 2004 in a building dating from 1862. It exhibits artists from the 20th and 21st centuries, and offers film cycles and educational activities. With its bookshop and café overlooking the Concorde, it is a place of artistic discovery, showcasing emerging and established artists. An invitation to contemplation and discovery of contemporary issues.

label: American Center for Art and Culture - Hôtel Mona Bismarck
comment: The Mona Bismarck American Center occupies a magnificent 19th-century mansion opposite the Eiffel Tower, in the 16th arrondissement. This cultural center showcases American culture and artistic creation through a variety of events: exhibitions, performances, artist residencies and colloquia. An essential address for discovering the artistic richness of the United States in Paris.

label: Square Saint-Gilles Grand Veneur - Pauline-Roland
comment: The Jardin Saint-Gilles Grand Veneur - Pauline Roland, nestled in a maze of alleyways away from the hustle and bustle of Paris, is an undiscovered yet magnificent haven of peace. With a breathtaking view of the façade of the Hôtel du Grand Veneur, this confidential garden offers visitors the opportunity to escape and enjoy moments of intimacy on its stone benches, in the shade of a rose arbour. A must for romantics in search of tranquillity.

label: Le Vaudeville
comment: Located opposite the Bourse and close to the Opera, Brasserie Vaudeville welcomes you all week long for your events. Since 1918, this Parisian establishment with its Art Deco charm has seduced you with its timeless ambience. Renowned for the quality of its produce and its traditional French cuisine, Brasserie Vaudeville is a must for lovers of fine dining.

label: Whisper Club Paris
comment: With 1,000 m² of space spread over two levels, three podiums and dozens of dancers every night, the Whisper Club Paris is one of the largest strip clubs in the capital. It is also one of the most famous. The reasons for this success? The establishment proposes every evening an uninterrupted show from 10 p.m. to 5 a.m.: strip-tease, lap dance and pole dance, the whole assured by professional international dancers. Privatization possible within the framework of a company or private evening.

label: Catimini
comment: Since its creation in 1972, Catimini has distinguished itself with cheerful, colorful fashion, specially designed to accompany children in their various activities. The brand offers a wide range of mixed-weave clothes adapted to their desires, reflecting both originality and practicality. Whether they're playing, growing or blossoming, Catimini knows how to meet the needs and expectations of the youngest, while adding a touch of fantasy to their wardrobe.

label: BELOM Paris
comment: BELOM Paris offers moments exclusively for men, in a unique Montmartre setting. Customers can enjoy shaving and beard trimming in the pure tradition of barbers. A hairdressing service is also available to perfect their look. Men who are more concerned about their appearance can also enjoy lightening, coloring or even waxing (nose, ears, hands). A moment of beauty and pampering just for them.

label: Studio Harcourt Paris
comment: Discover the Harcourt studio, a living heritage company, on an exclusive 2-hour tour. Explore its expertise in photography and its collection of exceptional works. Immerse yourself in its history, admire its famous settings and its exhibition space brimming with treasures and legendary portraits. Soak up the luxury of photography and its rituals. Finish with a gourmet break at the Café Harcourt for a unique experience at the heart of the studio's artistic universe.

label: Kintaro
comment: A genuine Japanese canteen with a refined design, it features an open kitchen where every flavour is revealed. Ramens take pride of place, accompanied by delicious curry, tasty yukiniku, succulent chukadon and crispy tonkatsu. A true invitation to a gastronomic journey to the heart of Japan!

label: Centre Tapovan
comment: Ayurvedic massage, an ancestral Indian tradition, is becoming increasingly popular in the West. In Paris, the Tepovan salon is the place to go for a relaxing interlude. In addition to massages, you can practice yoga, discover Ayurvedic cuisine, sip herbal teas and read specialized books. A complete immersion in the Indian world of well-being, within easy reach of the capital.

label: Café Studio
comment: Café Studio is much more than a café: it's a vegetarian flea market, creative workshops and a friendly atmosphere thanks to upcycling and vintage. For gourmets, vegan options and vegetarian brunch on weekends. Sewing, drawing and vegetable dyeing workshops, accompanied by an eco-responsible creations boutique. Events such as dress sales and plant sales are organized on a regular basis. Le Café Studio is all about common sense, creativity and craftsmanship, making every visit an enriching experience.

label: Roger La Grenouille
comment: The frog leg remains the signature dish of this restaurant, which has been a benchmark since the 1930s. Today, this restaurant offers bistro-style cuisine, revisiting traditional recipes to delight the taste buds. An institution where local gastronomy is sublimated with creativity.

label: Le Bistrot de Pékin
comment: Located just off the Champs-Élysées, Bistrot de Pékin invites you on a culinary journey to the heart of China. Its rich and varied menu offers an authentic immersion in traditional Chinese cuisine, to the delight of lovers of exotic flavors. An unmissable address for discovering new gustatory horizons.

label: Ateliers Lison de Caunes
comment: Renowned master craftswoman Lison de Caunes perpetuates the French tradition of straw marquetry, inherited from her grandfather, decorator André Groult. Specializing in the restoration of antique furniture, she collaborates with prestigious decorators and architects. In her workshops, she creates unique pieces in straw marquetry, blending tradition and modernity. Since 2015, she has been offering her own collection of furniture, combining traditional craftsmanship and contemporary design.

label: La Villa Papillon
comment: In the heart of the lively Montorgueil district, discover delicious Thai cuisine at this charming restaurant. Enjoy traditional, exotic and authentic dishes in a friendly atmosphere. Let yourself be swept away by memorable flavors, as each bite delights your taste buds. Come and enjoy a unique culinary experience in this magical place that will transport you to Asia with its surprising flavors.

label: Restaurant Jacques Faussat
comment: In the 17th arrondissement, Jacques Faussat treats his guests to refined cuisine with a South-West accent. His elegant, comfortable restaurant is the perfect setting for savoring the creative dishes of the Michelin-starred chef since 2004. Inspired by his travels, his generous, flavorful cuisine evolves with the seasons, enhanced by exotic spices. Crowned with three toques from Gault & Millau, Jacques Faussat offers an unforgettable gastronomic experience.

label: Musée Pierre Cardin Passé-Présent-Futur
comment: The Pierre Cardin Museum moved to Paris in November 2014, close to the Centre Pompidou, in a former tie factory in the Marais district. The "Passé-Présent-Futur" exhibition offers a journey through 50 years of the couturier's creations, with over 200 emblematic models and a selection of furniture, hats, shoes and jewelry over 1,000m² and 3 levels. A unique opportunity to explore Pierre Cardin's creative universe in Paris.

label: Bucherer
comment: The House of Bucherer, in the heart of the Golden Triangle of Haute Horlogerie, displays its 31 luxury brands over 2,200m². Expertise and excellence characterize this world's largest store dedicated to exceptional watchmaking, offering pieces of rare beauty. Bucherer also stands out for its award-winning jewelry and creations, crafted in its Swiss workshops. Each piece bears witness to the talent and passion of the company's craftsmen.

label: Freddy's
comment: The "Cosi" restaurant offers high-quality products, with meats selected by Hugo Desnoyer and bread fresh from the in-house oven. Tapas and planchas are prepared in front of you in an open kitchen. Sit at the counter or on a stool to enjoy these delicious portions. A fine wine list accompanies these tasty dishes, highlighting local produce. An authentic culinary experience to discover today.

label: Bus Toqué
comment: Embark on an unforgettable experience aboard the Bus Toqués, double-decker restaurant buses offering panoramic views of the monuments of Paris. Le Champs-Élysées immerses you in the atmosphere of a Parisian Café, while Le Saint-Germain 1920 transports you to the glamour of Art Deco in the Roaring Twenties. With a kitchen, bar and 12 tables for 1 to 8 guests, these buses offer a flexible culinary experience. Each table is equipped with a tablet offering information on 96 Paris tourist sites in 6 languages, for an enriching discovery of the capital.

label: Jardin Nelson Mandela
comment: Jardin Nelson Mandela at Les Halles overlooks the Bourse du Commerce, Saint-Eustache church and the Forum des Halles canopy. Children aged 7 to 11 can enjoy a 2,500 m² adventure playground with trampoline, megachines, spring bridge and Dino Wall. Sports shoes must be worn. A 400 m² playground designed by Romain Froquet features soccer fields, basketball courts and ping-pong tables. A playful and sporty getaway in the heart of Paris for youngsters!

additional_information: ['The Nelson Mandela Garden is open 7 days a week, 24 hours a day. The adventure playground is open every day except Monday. Opening hours depend on the season.']

label: Le Comptoir Baulois
comment: Discover this warm and atypical place between the Madeleine and the department stores: a former bookshop converted into a delicatessen, tea room and wine cellar. Enjoy cosy lunches on site or to take away, and let yourself be tempted by specialities from Brittany and beyond. In an unspoilt setting with wood panelling and large mirrors, savour top-quality French cuisine that changes with the seasons. A gourmet invitation you won't be able to resist.

label: L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon - Saint-Germain
comment: In the renowned chef's studio, up to forty guests can be seated around the counter overlooking the kitchen. It's a real feast for the eyes to watch the dishes being prepared, before enjoying the surprising creations made from exceptional products. An unforgettable culinary experience.

label: Havaianas
comment: Created in Brazil in 1962, this brand of flip-flops was first sold on Brazilian beaches. Over time, these plastic shoes, available in over 20 colors, conquered the world from the 2000s onwards. In 2006, Havaianas Slim was launched, a version specially designed for women.

label: Fleur de mai
comment: In Paris's Chinatown, the Fleur de Mai canteen hides an exceptional cuisine behind its modest façade. With no frills, its dishes are skilfully prepared: free-range chicken steamed in salt, salt-and-pepper-fried pork ribs, abalone marmite, duck tongues. The real star is the shrimp ravioli soup, renowned throughout the capital. A delight for the taste buds!

label: Le bLind Bar
comment: Located near the Champs-Élysées, the bLind Bar is a jewel of the Champs-Élysées House, chic and uncluttered. Designed by Philippe Di Méo, the counter is a visual highlight. Here, expert mixologists prepare customized cocktails and delicious bites. Perfect for a get-together with friends or a business meeting, bLind Bar is the ideal address for a memorable moment. A must for those who love a good night out.

label: Cirque Bormann
comment: Cirque Bormann, inherited for 7 generations, enchants with its breathtaking acts: juggling, horses, trapeze and clowning. Located in the 15th arrondissement of Paris, this exceptional venue, in partnership with the city council, offers a unique experience: a 250m² reception hall, a 1000-seat big top and a 150m² annex space. Immerse yourself in this magical and fascinating world, under the baroque Bormann big top. An unforgettable circus escapade you simply must experience!

label: Bois de Vincennes
comment: The Bois de Vincennes, to the east of Paris, offers many sites to discover: the École du Breuil, the Jardin d'agronomie tropicale, the Ferme de Paris, the Maison Paris Nature. The Château de Vincennes, steeped in history, is a must-see. The Parc Floral, with its miniature golf course, slides and free summer events, is a family favorite. Boating, horse racing, festivals... A wide range of activities to enjoy on your own or in a group. A getaway not to be missed!

label: Maison de l'Unesco
comment: The Maison de l'Unesco, near the Eiffel Tower, has fascinated visitors since 1958. Renowned architects such as Bernard Zehrfuss and artists such as Joan Miró have contributed to its creation. The star-shaped main building houses treasures by Picasso and other famous artists. Guided tours allow visitors to admire its architecture, with numerous public events such as exhibitions and concerts. The boutique, open weekdays, completes the experience offered by this prestigious venue.

label: Fondation Azzedine Alaïa
comment: The Fondation Azzedine Alaïa, located at 18 rue de la Verrerie in the Marais district, occupies a 19th-century building that was once the home of fashion designer Azzedine Alaïa. Recognized as a public institution in 2020, it preserves its collections and organizes exhibitions dedicated to fashion, photography and design. Visitors can also admire the designer's Studio through a window.

label: RAP Paris
comment: The RAP grocery store is a must for lovers of Italian gastronomy. You'll find a meticulous selection of authentic products such as wines, cheeses, antipasti, pasta, cold meats, preserves, coffee, condiments, cakes and typical pastries. In addition, cooking classes and wine tastings are offered on a regular basis for a true Italian culinary immersion. A perfect place for gourmets in search of authenticity and transalpine flavors.

label: Parc de Bagatelle - Jardin botanique de Paris
comment: Parc de Bagatelle, the jewel in the crown of the Bois de Boulogne, was built in just 64 days following a challenge between Queen Marie-Antoinette and the Comte d'Artois in 1775. This botanical garden is a haven of peace in the heart of the city, with its peaceful promenades, majestic trees, splendid rose garden, exotic pagoda and romantic setting. Exhibitions, concerts and cultural events regularly enliven this magical place, offering visitors an unforgettable experience.

It's a veritable artistic voyage, blending diverse forms of expression to the delight of audiences in search of new discoveries.

A poetic experience for all the family!

Respectful of the environment, this store offers a wide range of products, including international collections. On the second floor, a space dedicated to make-up and a care institute are available for the well-being of customers. A must for lovers of natural beauty and French elegance.

label: Jòia par Hélène Darroze
comment: Michelin-starred chef Hélène Darroze's Jòia restaurant is in Paris's 2nd arrondissement. The cozy, refined ambience evokes a Parisian home with wood and iron. The menu features family-style southwestern French cuisine, with touches of New York, London and Italy. On the 1st floor, a convivial lounge bar offers cocktails and food to share. Recommended by Gault & Millau and the Michelin Guide, this is a must for lovers of fine Parisian cuisine.

comment: Nestled in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, the Hungarian Institute is a Parisian cultural mainstay. A veritable embassy of Hungarian culture, it offers a variety of artistic events: exhibitions, concerts, film screenings, literary evenings, symposia, conferences and Hungarian language courses. It provides an opportunity to discover the richness of Hungarian culture and strengthens the ties between Hungary and France, making it an unmissable stopover for lovers of exotic culture.

Whether it's for a friendly game with friends or an intensive training session, everyone will be able to flourish in this complete and modern structure.

label: Espace Fondation EDF
comment: The Fondation EDF, located in Saint-Germain-des-Prés, occupies an electrical substation designed in 1910 by architect Paul Friesé. Since 1990, over a million visitors have been attracted by its free and accessible nature. At the heart of its cultural activities, the Foundation is committed to educating future generations through exhibitions that combine art and education. Conferences, debates and school workshops are organized to raise awareness among tomorrow's citizens.

label: Le Duc des Lombards
comment: Renowned American pianist Bobby FEW has said that a good jazz club needs a quality piano, an owner open to creativity, an attentive audience, space for the musicians and a warm atmosphere. Le Duc des Lombards, a not-to-be-missed venue in Paris, welcomes the biggest names in jazz and gives young French musicians the chance to play together at jam sessions. With its decor by Elliot Barnes, the club offers over 300 concerts a year, as well as jams on Friday and Saturday evenings, providing a unique atmosphere.

Its friendly atmosphere and elegant decor make it a must for fans of fresh oysters, generously served seafood and subtly prepared fish. An address to remember for an exceptional culinary experience.

label: Square du Temple - Elie Wiesel
comment: Square du Temple, a former refuge of the Knights Templar in the 13th century, has a turbulent history marked by bloody repression. Today, it's a peaceful garden with a serene, verdant atmosphere. There are some remarkable exotic trees, including an 18-metre Byzantine hazel and a 17-metre Japanese sophora. Wildlife is also present, with numerous species of birds near the pond and natural waterfall. A true haven of peace in the city.

It organizes their first exhibitions, represents them at international fairs and dedicates monographs to them. Since 1998, an experimental space has hosted original projects. Specializing in Nouveau Réalisme, the gallery advises museums, proposes one-off exhibitions and publishes catalogs.

Three restaurants in Paris, including one in the 10th arrondissement, offer a delicious and authentic culinary experience.

Enjoy a unique culinary and cultural experience!

Visitors can also enjoy a solarium for relaxing in the sun. Various aquatic activities are on offer, including swimming and aquagym classes. A perfect place to relax and recharge in the heart of the city.

Chaillot offers a unique experience: meetings, workshops, dance evenings and film screenings enrich the experience for audiences of all levels.

label: Gare de Lyon
comment: The Gare de Lyon, in the 12th arrondissement, attracts 110 million visitors a year. Inaugurated in 1855 and refurbished by architect Marius Toudoire for the 1900 Universal Exhibition, its imposing architecture is a real eye-catcher. The Tour de l'Horloge offers a 67-metre-high panoramic view of the capital. With its halls and emblematic places like Le Train Bleu for refreshments, the station offers an unmissable shopping experience.

If you lack inspiration, let yourself be tempted by the delicious in-house creations. Another establishment is also located on rue Saint-Sauveur, in the 2nd arrondissement of Paris.

label: La Machine du Moulin Rouge
comment: La Machine du Moulin Rouge, formerly "La Loco", transformed into a cabaret in 2010, is world-famous. Le Central, which can accommodate up to 800 people, presents the hottest artists. Formerly the boiler room of the Moulin Rouge, this cosy venue brings together 400 party-goers. The bubble bar is ideal for cocktails with friends, especially during afterworks. The Bal de la Machine du Moulin Rouge offers themed evenings all year round. Visit their website for the full program.

comment: Inspired by London's famous Camden market, this deceptively gothic boutique offers a wide choice of products. In addition to its original creations, it offers a selection of jeans and t-shirts bearing the effigy of rock bands, straight from England. A unique atmosphere combining alternative style and imported products, for lovers of underground fashion.

label: Marché Beauvau - Marché d'Aligre
comment: The Beauvau market, between Bastille and Nation in Paris, is a must-see. Open 6 days a week, it offers a unique experience for locals and tourists alike. Divided into covered and open-air markets, you'll find well-known stalls such as café Aouba, Langlet-Hardouin cheese shop and Boucherie Végétarienne. And bargain hunters can unearth treasures among the brocanteurs selling accessories, fabrics and old books. A must-see in Paris.

An address that will satisfy lovers of authenticity and comfort.

comment: The Le Meurice Alain Ducasse restaurant offers an unforgettable gastronomic experience in a prestigious hotel in Paris. label: Réserve ornithologique - Bois de Vincennes
comment: In the heart of the Bois de Vincennes, a protected bird area offers two observatories equipped with identification panels. These facilities allow discreet observation of the different species present, without disturbing them. A rare opportunity for nature-lovers to discover the local ornithological diversity, while contributing to the preservation of these wonderful animals.

comment: Located near the Porte de la Chapelle, the Square Paul Robin offers visitors a place to relax for adults and play for children. Equipped with a playground and sandpit, it offers everyone the chance to enjoy pleasant moments in the open air. What's more, from May to September, concerts are programmed in the bandstand, adding a festive and convivial atmosphere to this charming park.

label: Panthéon
comment: The Temple de la Nation française, designed by Soufflot, was dedicated to the monarchy and to Saint Geneviève, patron saint of Paris. It became a temple to great men during the Revolution, and changed vocation in the 19th century. Since 1885, when Victor Hugo entered the Panthéon, it has housed the great figures of the French nation, from Voltaire to Simone Veil, not forgetting Rousseau, Zola and the Curies. A tribute to the history and greatness of France.

The Taylor Foundation, with its history and heritage, is a must for art lovers, an institution that encourages artistic creation through the ages.

label: Publicisdrugstore
comment: Located at the top of the Champs-Élysées, the Publicisdrugstore has been a luxury concept store in Paris since 1958. Gourmets can sample the cuisine of Chef Éric Frechon at LE Drugstore or at Joël Robuchon's Atelier Etoile, in a decor designed by Tom Dixon. A chic, gourmet address for everyone!

label: Centre culturel de Chine à Paris
comment: Opened in 2002, the Centre Culturel de Chine à Paris is the first cultural establishment created by the People's Republic of China in a Western country. It promotes exchanges between China and France through conferences, exhibitions, shows, visits and publications. It also offers Chinese language courses, forming a cultural bridge between East and West.

The bookshop area aims to become the benchmark for enlightened enthusiasts of the decorative arts, fashion and design, offering classic works, new releases and rare items. A place to discover and be inspired.

label: Théâtre de l'Oeuvre
comment: The Théâtre de l'uvre, opened in 1893 between the Place de Clichy and the Opéra district, has cultivated an avant-garde spirit from the outset. Founded by Aurélien Lugné-Poe, this emblematic venue has been supported by directors such as Pierre Franck, Georges Herbert, Georges Wilson, Gérard Maro and Frédéric Franck, all heirs to this perpetual quest for artistic renewal. A tradition of innovation that has successfully endured over the years.
