label: Musée de l'Histoire de la Médecine
comment: The museum's historical collections, among the oldest in Europe, are presented in a magnificent hall built between 1905 and 1907. This room, which bears witness to medical history, is located in an extension to the original building designed by architect Ginain for the "Collège de Chirurgie". Closed during the French Revolution, the building reopened in 1795 before the museum was created in 1955. The museum features portraits of 18th-century physicians, antique surgical instruments and a varied collection.

comment: Looking for a family outing? The Menagerie du Jardin des Plantes is perfect! Founded in Paris in 1794, it's one of the oldest zoos in the world. Come and admire a wide variety of species over its 5.5 hectares. La Menagerie contributes to the preservation of endangered species. Don't miss the singerie, the fauverie and the vivariums with rare animals. A fascinating family experience!

Enjoy refined menus prepared by the students, with lunch at 18? served on weekdays and dinner at 25? on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday evenings. label: Médiathèque Françoise Sagan
comment: Located in the 10th arrondissement of Paris, the Françoise Sagan multimedia library opened its doors in summer 2015. Located close to the Gare de l'Est railway station, it is part of the historic Clos Saint-Lazare site, surrounded by greenery. Renovations have restored the site to its full beauty. With a collection of almost 100,000 documents accessible to all, the library offers a rich cultural program in its many dedicated spaces.

label: CFA et lycée Belliard
comment: In the 18th arrondissement, the Lycée des Métiers de l'Hôtellerie Belliard offers a training restaurant run by GRETA students. These future chefs concoct menus worthy of the greatest chefs for the general public. An ideal opportunity to enjoy refined dishes at affordable prices. The restaurant is open for lunch and dinner, offering a unique gastronomic experience at any time of day.

label: Science Expériences
comment: Come and discover Science Expériences, an 850 m2 space in Bercy Village, making science accessible in a lively and entertaining way. With innovative experiences such as virtual reality and video mapping, explore subjects ranging from the Universe to the Abyss, via quantum physics. It's an immersive approach that will appeal to science novices and enthusiasts alike, thanks to its powerful emotions.

label: Les statues des trois Dumas
comment: The Place du Général Catroux is home to three sets of statues representing the generations of the Dumas family. The bronze statue of Alexandre Dumas père by Gustave Doré is remarkable, as is the stone statue of Alexandre Dumas fils sculpted by René de Saint-Marceaux. A poignant tribute to General Dumas, a former slave, is symbolized by broken iron irons by Driss Sans-Arcidet. Every May 10, a special ceremony honors the victims of slavery in this garden.

comment: Located near the Latin Quarter and the Quays of the Seine, Les Belles Plantes offers a unique setting in the Jardin des Plantes. After visiting the Museum National d?Histoire Naturelle or the Menagerie, relax in this bright and natural restaurant. The relaxed decor, with flowery wallpaper and wicker furniture, creates a warm atmosphere. The ideal place for a gourmet break in the heart of nature in Paris.

label: Le Servan

With experience in prestigious restaurants such as l'Arpège, l'Astrance and le Bristol, they offer quality bistronomic gastronomy. Located close to Père-Lachaise, this place seduces with its exquisite flavors and friendly atmosphere. A must for lovers of authentic culinary discoveries.

label: Marché Villette
comment: Located close to the Place du Colonel Fabien, this medium-sized food market is a true place of culinary discovery. Enjoy fresh, quality produce while admiring the imposing building designed by renowned architect Oscar Niemeyer. An experience combining pleasure for the taste buds and satisfaction for the eyes awaits you just a few steps away.

label: O’Kari Hammam Spa Paris
comment: Algerian-born Karima Lasfar created O?Kari Hammam in the Montorgueil district to offer an authentic spa experience. This all-female hammam is a haven of peace, adorned with mosaics and equipped with heated granite massage tables. Massages are performed using essential oils with relaxing, invigorating or draining properties. A unique place to relax and recharge your batteries, while preserving the tradition of the hammam.

label: Café de la Paix
comment: Café de la Paix, the restaurant of the InterContinental Paris Le Grand, is a listed monument. Facing the Opéra Garnier, this legendary Parisian landmark enjoys international renown. Built in the Napoleon III style, this emblematic establishment of French gastronomy offers exceptional cuisine orchestrated by Chef Laurent André.

label: Parc Kellermann
comment: Parc Kellerman, on the site of the former Thiers fortifications, is a major green space in the 13th arrondissement. Divided into a French-style upper section and a lower section, it offers a wide range of activities, including playgrounds, sports trails, soccer pitches and tennis courts. In summer, children can enjoy mobile toy libraries. Since 2017, a pedagogical urban farm with a variety of animals offers a rural atmosphere right in the heart of the city.

label: Salvatore Ferragamo
comment: Ferragamo, a legendary brand, dressed the great Hollywood stars of the 20s before founding its house in 1927. Today, in addition to iconic shoes, the brand offers ready-to-wear collections, fragrances, eyewear and leather goods. Always synonymous with shock and elegance, Ferragamo remains a benchmark in the world of fashion.

comment: At the Palais de Tokyo bookshop, you'll find a wealth of artistic objects, collectible multiples, contemporary editions and curiosities of all kinds. You'll find prototypes, games, captivating videos and toys. Particularly noteworthy is the wide selection of international press and national and international exhibition catalogs, sure to satisfy the most demanding art lovers.

label: Diep
comment: Discover the delicious Sino-Thai cuisine of Diep restaurant, near the Champs-Élysées. The authentic flavors of China and Thailand are brought to life by talented chefs. Every bite is an explosion of taste. Enjoy an unforgettable gastronomic experience in elegant surroundings. Reserve your table now for an exceptional moment.

label: Helptourists
comment: Discover Paris with our guided tours in German, for groups of 2 or more. Choose from 2 or 4-hour tours, or even half or full days. Explore Montmartre, the Marais or the covered passages. For food lovers, our culinary tours will delight you. For individuals or companies, our tours are suitable for all occasions. Immerse yourself in the City of Light for a unique experience!

label: Théâtre Astral
comment: Discover the Théâtre Astral, an enchanting venue dedicated to children in the heart of the Parc Floral de Paris! From February to November, the company invites you to share magical moments with playful, musical and humorous shows. Treat your children to an unforgettable moment of puppetry, mimicry and song, transporting them into a magical world. An outing that's sure to fill your little ones with wonder!

comment: Discover a wide selection of shoes for men and women, from classic models to the most trendy designs. Our collection offers shoes for every taste, from the most sober to the most original. What's more, we're proud to offer sizes from the smallest to the largest, so there's a shoe for everyone. Don't wait any longer to treat yourself to the comfort and style you deserve!

label: Bourse de Commerce - Pinault Collection
comment: The Bourse de Commerce - Pinault Collection, a renovated museum housed in a historic monument, offers an innovative dialogue between art past and present. Through its exhibitions and events, it offers a contemporary vision of art thanks to the Pinault Collection. Open to all art forms, it is aimed at a broad public, offering a committed and innovative perspective on contemporary art.

label: Marché couvert Saint-Didier
comment: Nestled in the chic 16th arrondissement, between the prestigious Place Victor Hugo and Place du Trocadéro, this market is packed with treasures. In addition to stalls offering gastronomic delights, there's a tempting pizzeria and trendy ready-to-wear boutiques. A must-see place where elegance meets indulgence, for a pleasant shopping and culinary interlude.

label: Cantine California
comment: La Cantine California, originally a food truck in Paris, opened a permanent restaurant in April 2014 in the 3rd arrondissement. The decor blends marble and rough wood, with a large counter and a convivial table d'hôte. The plates offer the same delights as the food truck, with organic products such as meat and eggs. The menu includes homemade burgers, tacos and desserts. The food truck is also present at certain Paris markets. Discover it for a healthy, gourmet break.

label: Big Bus Paris - Stop: Opéra, palais Garnier
comment: Big Bus' double-decker bus tours are the perfect way to discover Paris. Passengers hop on and off the bus as they please. One is immersed in the history, culture and architecture of Paris with commentary - informative and entertaining - available in 11 languages. From the buses' upper deck, you can admire the iconic Parisian monuments.

label: Musée d'Art moderne de Paris
comment: Opened in 1961, the Musée d'Art Moderne de Paris (MaM) showcases contemporary art in a variety of forms: painting, sculpture, installations, photography and video. With over 15,000 works representing the major currents of the 20th century, it exhibits masterpieces by Picasso, Gris, Matisse, Giacometti, Braque and Klein. In addition to the permanent collections, temporary exhibitions are held on a regular basis. A cafeteria and bookshop complete the visitor experience.

label: Passage des Princes
comment: The Passage des Princes, built in 1860, destroyed in 1985 and rebuilt in 1995, has a rich history. Located near the Palais Garnier and department stores, it blends perfectly with the surrounding Haussmann architecture. This passageway is packed with toy, model and video game stores, delighting young and old alike. Nestled at 97 rue de Richelieu, this temple to gaming offers infinite pleasure to all its visitors.

label: Canauxrama
comment: Looking for an original Paris getaway? Opt for the Croisière du Vieux-Paris along the Canal Saint-Martin, a romantic 2.5-hour stroll from the Bassin de la Villette. La Parisienne offers a "Bistrot-cosy" atmosphere during a 1h30 illuminated stroll along the Seine on Friday and Saturday evenings. Discover the guinguettes on the banks of the Marne or the lively cruise on the Canal de l'Ourcq. A unique experience in Paris!

label: Cojean
comment: Cojean, a pioneer in "new fast food", offers a quality lunch using natural, fresh ingredients: sandwiches, soups, wraps, mineral waters, all in a soothing setting. A healthy, balanced break for meals on the go. And let's not forget the homemade juices concocted on demand, with enigmatic names like Le Jardin dévasté or Think Pink. With 21 locations in Paris, Cojean has conquered the hearts of fast, healthy food lovers.

label: Anona
comment: In the Batignolles district, the Anona restaurant offers creative and eco-responsible cuisine. Here, the emphasis is on short circuits, waste reduction and limiting water and electricity consumption. The dishes are presented in dishes made of raw materials such as wood, cement, stoneware or glass.

label: Théâtre du Rond-Point
comment: In March 1981, the Théâtre du Rond-Point was founded by Jean-Michel Ribes, a leading figure in French theater. This unique venue showcases contemporary artistic creation and living authors. A cultural benchmark in France, it offers freedom and innovation to young talent. Its varied and audacious programming attracts a curious audience. In this way, the theater brings a breath of fresh air to the French theatrical landscape, enriching the country's cultural offering.

label: BarOurcq
comment: Located on the banks of the Bassin de la Villette, Barourcq is a popular bar for concerts and DJ sets. Its terrace, one of the basin's most inviting, comes alive in fine weather, offering a festive spot where you can enjoy the fresh air day and night. To add a playful touch, petanque games are even available for an impromptu game! The perfect place to spend a convivial moment in the heart of Paris.

label: Les Gourmandises de Nathalie
comment: Just outside the Duroc metro station is Les Gourmandises de Nathalie. This store offers a wide selection of traditional French sweets such as bêtises de Cambrai, négus de Nevers, pastilles Vichy, berlingots nantais and bergamotes de Nancy. Nathalie, the passionate owner, welcomes visitors with kindness and shares her love of sweets. An unmissable gourmet break for candy lovers!

label: City Locker
comment: City Locker offers secure lockers for 3 suitcases at 2 Euros per day. With video surveillance and 24-hour alarms, your belongings are safe and secure. Open 7 days a week from 8am to 10pm in 5 key districts, City Locker lockers can be booked online. Committed to quality, they have signed the Caring Attitude charter. Entrust your luggage with complete peace of mind!

label: Galerie Loft
comment: Since 1999, the gallery run by Jean-François Roudillon has established itself as the benchmark for discovering young talent in Chinese art. Chen Man, Guo Wei and Hong Hao are just some of the talented artists revealed by this space dedicated to the emerging creativity of a rapidly changing China. An invitation to plunge into a fascinating and constantly evolving artistic universe.

label: Musée Zadkine
comment: The Musée Zadkine, close to the Luxembourg Gardens, offers a unique immersion into the world of artist Ossip Zadkine. In the heart of a verdant garden adorned with sculptures, this house-workshop retraces the life of this major artist of the École de Paris. From the first primitive sculptures to the last lyrical works, Zadkine explored different artistic styles with freedom and vitality. A fascinating tour through the artistic evolution of an exceptional sculptor.

comment: In the heart of the Saint-Sulpice district, La Procure is a bookshop specializing in religious books and cultural items such as music, DVDs and magazines. Located in an emblematic neighborhood, it offers a wide choice of products to satisfy culture and spirituality enthusiasts. Don't hesitate to visit us to discover a world rich in knowledge and emotion.

label: Passage de Pondichéry
comment: In the heart of the 10th arrondissement's Indian quarter is Passage de Pondichéry, renowned for its authentic, refined cuisine at very affordable prices. Offering tasty, traditional dishes, this place attracts a clientele in search of unique culinary experiences. An invitation to discover the delights of India, Passage de Pondichéry is a reference for lovers of exotic gastronomy in Paris.

label: Maison des pratiques artistiques amateurs - Broussais
comment: The Maison des pratiques artistiques amateurs - Broussais, located in the 14th arrondissement, offers a variety of spaces dedicated to the performing and visual arts. Designed by architect Sébastien El-Haïk, this modern facility features a dance studio, theater rooms, a large workshop, a multidisciplinary performance hall, an exhibition gallery and a painting wall. Amateurs can rehearse, take part in workshops and attend performances in an environment conducive to creativity.

label: Église protestante unie des Billettes
comment: Les Billettes, a cloister and church of Catholic origin, stands proudly in the historic Marais district. Transformed in the 19th century to accommodate Lutheran worship, the church now offers regular concerts. As for the cloister, it serves as a backdrop for exhibitions showcasing talented young artists. A harmonious blend of religious heritage and cultural dynamism.

label: Restaurant Auguste
comment: Located in the chic 7th arrondissement, a stone's throw from the Rodin Museum and Les Invalides, Restaurant Auguste is a veritable gastronomic nugget. Headed by Michelin-starred chef Orieux Gaël, known for his commitment to preserving the oceans, this establishment takes you on a culinary journey rich in flavors between "Land and Sea". The contemporary, refined decor invites you to relax and savour an exceptional moment.

label: Musée de l'Illusion - Paris
comment: Do you know optical illusion? The Musée de l'Illusion comes to Paris after conquering 17 countries. This international museum offers a unique, gravity-defying experience. Come with your family or friends to discover incredible illusions and push back the limits of your perception. Whatever your age, this captivating world awaits you for an unforgettable experience. A stimulating and entertaining visit not to be missed!

label: Moulin Rouge
comment: Since 1889, the Moulin Rouge has been the world's most famous cabaret, immortalized by Toulouse-Lautrec. Stars such as Edith Piaf and Liza Minnelli have performed there. Featuring refined French cuisine by Chef Arnaud Demerville and Champagne, the "Féerie" revue transports you into a world of feathers, rhinestones and French Cancan with a troupe of 60 renowned artists. A magical evening to share with family, friends or lovers, in elegant attire.

label: Marché couvert de Passy
comment: Nestled beneath a charming shopping hall, the Passy food market is a veritable paradise for gourmets in search of authentic produce. With a fish market renowned for its freshness, a tempting Portuguese corner and a generous French cheese shop, this market offers an incomparable diversity of flavors. A must for lovers of good food and quality products.

A must for lovers of good food and quality products.

label: Au plat d'étain
comment: Since 1775, Au plat d'étain in Paris has been renowned for its tin soldiers, figurines and pewter dishes. It offers a wide selection of pieces from prestigious brands such as CBG Mignot, Lucotte and Marlborough. In addition to sales, the store offers repair, renovation and collection appraisal services. A must for rare object enthusiasts near Saint-Sulpice church.

label: Stéphanie de Bruijn - Parfum sur mesure
comment: In 2008, talented designer Stéphanie de Bruijn opened her boutique near the Musée d'Orsay in Grasse, famous for its perfumes. Her ready-to-perfume collection is offered at attractive prices. In its laboratory, a unique experience enables each customer to become a real perfumer by creating their own perfume after two appointments and a month of research. The "Parfum Couture" and "Essence Haute-Couture" ranges offer exclusive, intoxicating fragrances.

label: Théâtre de la Huchette
comment: Since 1948, this iconic theater has been home to some of the world's greatest actors. On its stage, Ionesco's La cantatrice chauve and La leçon have captivated audiences for decades. Always in search of something new, this legendary venue continues to explore contemporary texts and daring theatrical adventures.

label: Le Grenier à pain
comment: In 2015, Grenier à Pain on rue des Abbesses, run by Djibril Bodian, once again won the title of Best Baguette in Paris. The establishment supplies daily bread to the Élysée Palace for a year, and offers a wide variety of traditional homemade breads, viennoiseries, pastries and catering services. With 10 locations in Paris and Île-de-France, this bakery is a benchmark for lovers of good bread. Not to be missed!

label: Le Petit Ney
comment: The café littéraire associatif is a convivial place for literature lovers. You can share your passion for books, authors and words through discussions, debates, lectures, readings and writing workshops. This initiative combines culture, conviviality and associative commitment, offering a warm and enriching atmosphere for literature enthusiasts. Come and meet the books, the heroes of this unusual place!

label: Le Zakouski
comment: Located behind Montparnasse, this small, old-fashioned Russian bistro exudes a warm ambience that invites you to take a culinary break from the hustle and bustle of everyday life. Specialties from Eastern Europe will delight lovers of gastronomic discoveries. And let's not forget the musical evenings regularly organized for a complete voyage into Eastern European culture. An authentic and convivial experience not to be missed.

label: Le Bouchon et l'Assiette
comment: In the heart of the Basque Country, a young couple of talented chefs, trained in prestigious establishments, bring out the authentic flavors of the region through delicious dishes. Their cuisine combines tradition and creativity, delighting guests in search of new culinary experiences. In a convivial atmosphere, guests are whisked away on a gastronomic journey in magnificent surroundings, with each bite promising an exceptional moment of sharing.

label: Desmos, la librairie hellénique
comment: Located in the 14th arrondissement, Desmos is an expert bookshop in contemporary Greek literature, offering a wide range of poetry and novels. In addition to its rich selection of books, it offers modern Greek language courses, adapted to three different levels. A must for lovers of Greek culture wishing to explore the country's current language and literature.

label: L'Envue
comment: Come and discover Envue, a privileged location ideally situated between Place de la Madeleine and Concorde, close to the Faubourg and high-end boutiques. With its sunny terrace, it's the perfect place to enjoy lunch, dinner or simply relax over a drink with friends. Let yourself be charmed by this emblematic address in the 8th arrondissement, once known as "la Rue des Champs-Élysées".

label: Palais Brongniart
comment: The Palais Brongniart, commissioned by Napoleon, owes its name to architect Alexandre Théodore Brongniart (1808-1825). Inaugurated on November 4, 1826, it was the headquarters of the Paris Stock Exchange for almost one hundred and fifty years. Abandoned by stockbrokers for many years, the exchange ceased trading in 1987. Today, the site features a gallery dedicated to the history of the Bourse. Designed by A. Brongniart, the Palais has unfortunately not been open to the public since 2008.

label: La p’tite ferme de la Goutte d’Or
comment: Located in the square Alain Bashung, la p'tite ferme de la Goutte d'Or is an urban farm with chickens, sheep and rabbits. A true haven of nature in the heart of the city, offering an enriching interlude for young and old alike. Managed by Les Fermes d'Espoir, this educational farm raises awareness of animal and rural life in an urban environment.

label: Les bouquinistes de Paris
comment: The bouquinistes of Paris form an open-air bookshop on the quays of the Seine (right bank: Pont-Marie to Quai du Louvre; left bank: Quai de la Tournelle to Quai Voltaire). Heirs to the peddlers, they are now 240-stallards in 900 wagon-green boxes, listed as part of France?s intangible heritage.

label: Arlette Gruss
comment: Come and discover the prestigious Arlette Gruss big top, nestled in the heart of the Bois de Vincennes on the Pelouse de Reuilly. This traditional circus offers a breathtaking show featuring tightrope walkers, acrobats, wild animals, mimes and many other breathtaking surprises. Immerse yourself in a fairytale world and let the magic of the circus sweep you away under Europe's largest big top. An unforgettable experience for the whole family!

label: Gare Montparnasse
comment: Montparnasse station, the only 20th-century station in Paris, attracts 70 million passengers every year. Since 1994, the Jardin Atlantique has provided a green space in the heart of the city. Now a popular spot for shopping and fine dining, the station will soon be home to over 130 boutiques and restaurants, ranging from major brands to original concepts. Enjoy dishes prepared by renowned chefs such as Yann Couvreur, Pierre Hermé and Alain Duc.

label: Sayya
comment: Located in the 10th arrondissement, Sayya is a 375 m² space dedicated to well-being and alternative medicine. With over 50 practitioners using complementary methods, Sayya offers services designed to improve physical, emotional and mental well-being, as well as professional fulfillment. An ideal place to take care of yourself and find global harmony.

label: Bar à Champagne - Tour Eiffel
comment: Looking for a unique experience in Paris? Then head to the bar on the 3rd floor of the Eiffel Tower to enjoy a glass of Hériot rosé or white Champagne, selected by Alain Ducasse. The view of the City of Light is simply magical, especially if you enjoy your Champagne in a luminous glass. An unusual way to (re)discover the famous Iron Lady. Don't forget to book your entry at www.tour-eiffel.fr to access this exceptional venue.

label: Sola - Kosuke Nabeta
comment: Immerse yourself in an exquisite culinary fusion of French and Japanese cuisine, in an elegant Franco-Nipponese setting. Taste delicate compositions combining finesse and tradition for a unique culinary experience. This marriage of flavors and techniques promises an unforgettable gastronomic journey, between French refinement and Japanese simplicity. A sensory experience not to be missed for lovers of new culinary sensations.

label: La Dame de Canton
comment: La Dame de Canton, a Chinese junk near the Bibliothèque Nationale, offers live concerts, children's shows and private seminars. With its restaurant, bar and view over the Seine, it's the ideal place to enjoy Paris. Moored near the Quai de la Gare metro station, this unusual venue will appeal to visitors in search of adventure. A must for a unique Paris experience.

label: Square Sarah Bernhardt
comment: The splendid square in question is a natural jewel in the heart of the city. With more than 200 trees of 50 different species, cone-shaped yew trees and magnificent flowerbeds, it attracts visitors with its exceptional biodiversity. It's a haven of peace, with a serene atmosphere conducive to contemplation. Nature is showcased in all its splendor, providing an idyllic setting to recharge your batteries and enjoy moments of calm and beauty.

label: Fouquet - Quartier Opéra
comment: Founded in 1852, the Fouquet chocolate and confectionery shop, one of the oldest in Paris, is renowned for its excellent products and the traditional skills of its chocolatiers. You'll find a wide selection of chocolates and confectionery, including the famous caramel bonbon. The warm welcome and quality advice reinforce Fouquet's image of friendliness and professionalism. And don't forget our home delivery service, which combines comfort and indulgence.

A perfect blend of elegance and sportiness, these pieces reflect the unique style and spirit of this iconic champion. High-quality garments with clean cuts and comfortable fabrics, ideal for a casual yet refined look. Treat yourself to sporty elegance with the Serge Blanco clothing line.

label: Bob’s Juice Bar
comment: Bob's Juice Bar, in the 10th arrondissement of Paris, offers an American atmosphere with fresh juices, smoothies, sandwiches, salads, soups and muffins. This friendly spot is perfect for those with a passion for healthy cooking. Come and enjoy these delicacies prepared with care, without guilt. A gourmet wellness break awaits you at Bob's Juice Bar!

label: La barbière de Paris
comment: La Barbière de Paris, a veritable temple to men's well-being, offers its customers a unique experience in a 1950s setting. The program includes traditional shaving with a cabbage trimmer, beard trimming, hairdressing, waxing and other relaxing treatments. Comfortably seated in barber chairs, men find their haven of peace just a stone's throw from the Palais Garnier. A salon where masculinity rhymes with elegance and modernity.

label: Parc des Princes
comment: The Parc des Princes, with its 47,929 seats, is the legendary stadium of Paris Saint-Germain (PSG), a major European soccer team. The venue of choice for PSG's French championship and European Cup matches, it is sometimes transformed into a stage for concerts by artists of national and international renown.

label: Café Fluctuat Nec Mergitur
comment: The Fluctuat Nec Mergitur café on Place de la République celebrates Parisian resistance. The convivial café offers home cooking, local beers and organic wines. Open all day for coffee, meals or drinks, it also offers brunches and events. With a 150-seat terrace, water mirror and Wi-Fi, it's the ideal place to relax. pierre Tabouret / Café Fluctuat Nec Mergitur.

label: Galerie Gagosian
comment: Larry Gagosian is a renowned art dealer specializing in modern and contemporary art. He has opened several galleries around the world, from New York to Paris, London, Rome, Athens and Los Angeles. The Larry Gagosian Galleries have welcomed famous artists such as Georg Baselitz, Jeff Koons and Takashi Murakami. In France, Galerie Gagosian is located on rue de Ponthieu, near the Champs-Élysées, and a second address opened in Le Bourget in 2012.

label: Palais Galliera, musée de la Mode de Paris
comment: The Palais Galliera is home to the Musée de la Mode de la Ville de Paris, a sanctuary for fashion enthusiasts. Its collections of over 100,000 pieces offer a fascinating overview of the evolution of French clothing styles. In addition to temporary exhibitions, a library and documentation center are available by appointment. Come and discover the history of French fashion at the Musée Galliera!

label: Musée de la Chasse et de la Nature
comment: The Musée de la Chasse et de la Nature, located in the Marais district of Paris, is distinguished by its singular charm. Housed in two private mansions, it offers an extraordinary experience, immersing visitors in the captivating world of a passionate art lover. Works by great artists such as Rubens, Breughel and Chardin rub shoulders with contemporary creations that question our relationship with the animal kingdom. The artistic ambience of the period and the unusual treasures captivate curious minds, making this an ideal family outing.

label: Jardin des Arts - Albert Schweitzer
comment: The Jardin des Arts - Albert Schweitzer, located in the Marais district of Paris, is a green space redeveloped in 2020 following the merger of the Square Albert Schweitzer, the Cité des Arts garden and the French garden of the Hôtel d'Aumont. Its shady paths and flower-filled lawns make it an ideal place to relax, with beamed benches for a well-deserved break. Children will appreciate the dedicated play area. A pleasant getaway in the heart of the City of Light.

label: Les galeries d'art du Marais
comment: The Marais, a historic district with a rich heritage, is a veritable artistic treasure trove, with renowned art galleries such as Emmanuel Perrotin, Daniel Templon, Marian Goodman and Thaddaeus Ropac. These galleries, housed in private mansions, exhibit a wide range of works, from famous artists to emerging talents. A stroll through the Marais promises a fascinating cultural immersion for art lovers in search of inspiring discoveries.

label: Cité Florale
comment: The Cité Florale, in the Butte-aux-Cailles district, takes its name from the houses entwined with vines and colorful flowers on the balconies. Pastel facades rival each other in beauty, with flower pots in front of the doors. The streets bear poetic names: Glycines, Orchids, Iris, Liserons, Volubilis... A little corner of floral paradise ideal for strolling and escaping, where the local cats might even accompany you for a moment on their butterfly hunt.

label: Afaria
comment: Run by a duo of women, this bistro features authentic cuisine made from fresh seasonal produce. Guests can enjoy a variety of tasty tapas and generous dishes with the flavors of the Southwest. An invitation to discover regional gastronomy in a warm and friendly atmosphere.

label: Restaurant de l'Hôtel Dame Des Arts
Pierre Gagnaire
comment: Celebrity chef Pierre Gagnaire's restaurant near the Champs-Élysées is a gastronomic experience not to be missed. His inventive, flavorful cuisine, combining aesthetics and molecular gastronomy, delights the taste buds. The chef's artistic plates are veritable visual works of art. Listed in prestigious guidebooks, this restaurant is an institution of haute gastronomy not to be missed for a memorable culinary experience.

label: Guerlain
comment: Since 1828, Guerlain has embodied French elegance with its bewitching fragrances and high-quality products. Tradition and innovation combine to offer an unforgettable sensory experience. The art of body and facial treatments in Guerlain's exclusive spas is a pure moment of well-being and relaxation. Discover the intoxicating scents and delicate textures of Guerlain treatments to reveal your natural beauty.

label: Paroisse Saint-Étienne-du-Mont
comment: The church of Saint-Étienne-du-Mont, located in the Latin Quarter of Paris, a stone's throw from the Panthéon, impresses with its rich history. Built at the end of the 15th century, it contains exceptional treasures such as the rood screen dating from 1545, the only one of its kind in Paris, the shrine of Sainte-Geneviève and the grand gallery organ. A listed historic monument, this church is a must-see for art and history enthusiasts.

label: Acne Studios
comment: Founded in 1997, Acne Studios is a Swedish brand renowned for its creative style and ready-to-wear expertise. Its collections of jeans and accessories stand out for their originality and comfort. Appreciated by fashion enthusiasts, the brand offers unique and trendy pieces, perfect for asserting your style with authenticity. Discover the world of Acne Studios and let yourself be seduced by its bold, modern creations.
description: Founded in 1997, Acne Studios is a Swedish brand renowned for its creative style and ready-to-wear expertise. Its collections of jeans and accessories stand out for their originality and comfort. Appreciated by fashion enthusiasts, the brand offers unique and trendy pieces, perfect for asserting your style with authenticity. Discover the world of Acne Studios and let yourself be seduced by its bold, modern creations.

label: Musée de l’Armée - Invalides - Tombeau de Napoléon et Église du Dôme
comment: Built by Jules Hardouin Mansart between 1679 and 1706, the Dôme des Invalides is a 107-meter-high marvel of French architecture. It was renovated in 1989 for the bicentenary of the French Revolution, with 12 kilos of gold. Inside, a fresco by Charles de la Fosse depicts "Saint Louis handing his sword to Jesus Christ". This historic site is a military necropolis containing the tombs of such emblematic figures as Turenne, Vauban and Napoleon 1er. A visit steeped in history not to be missed.

label: Théâtre Le Bout
comment: Le Bout theater, in Pigalle, offers interactive shows for children aged 3 to 10, in an intimate 50-seat theater. Martin Leloup offers four captivating shows all year round: "La princesse au petit pois dans la tête" (3-8 years), "Toutankhamon et le Scarabée d'Or" (5-10 years), "Pierre et la princesse ensorcelée" (3-10 years) and "Au secours le prince Aubert a disparu" (4-10 years). A varied program for unforgettable moments!

label: Mauboussin
comment: Mauboussin revolutionized fine jewelry, making it accessible to all with its unique creations. This renowned house has also successfully diversified into watches, accessories and perfumes. A brand that knows how to adapt to the desires and needs of its clientele, offering products of impeccable quality and incomparable design.

label: Théâtre Saint-Georges
comment: The Théâtre Saint-Georges, the jewel in the crown of the "New Athens", is one of Paris's most popular theaters. With 500 seats, it attracts a varied audience of comedy fans every evening. Its eclectic program delights fans of both classical and contemporary theater. Its warm atmosphere makes it an ideal venue. Its Italian-inspired architecture offers a unique cultural experience. Discover this Parisian treasure!

label: L'Ogresse, théâtre de marionnettes
comment: L'Ogresse was created by Mutata, a native of the Kabylie mountains. In Paris, several people have contributed to making this project a reality. For the past 12 years, L'Ogresse has been an associative space dedicated to orality, music and puppetry. The space welcomes and supports young artists: musicians, storytellers, puppeteers, actors, directors, authors and clowns. These creators can present their work in a friendly, supportive atmosphere.

label: Le Bonhomme de Bois
comment: Le Bonhomme de Bois, inspired by the charming toy stores of yesteryear, offers a varied range of games, toys, childcare and decorative items, mainly designed in wood and fabric. Immerse yourself in a warm, authentic world in search of original, long-lasting gifts. Offer your children toys that encourage their development and imagination, all in a magical and enchanting setting.

label: Square Carpeaux
comment: The Montmartre square in Paris pays tribute to the artist Jean-Baptiste Carpeaux. With its bandstand, play areas and playgrounds, it offers a cheerful, convivial atmosphere. Ideal for relaxing outdoors, meeting new people and celebrating art in a verdant setting. A true interlude of happiness in the heart of the city.

label: Bistrot Benoit
comment: Bistrot Benoit, in the heart of the Louvre Museum, revisits traditional French cuisine with a contemporary twist. Enjoy emblematic dishes such as cassolette d?escargots or blanquette de veau in a typically Parisian setting. The team in white aprons and butterfly bows offers a selection of quality wines, all in a warm and welcoming atmosphere. For a gourmet experience in the heart of the bustling Louvre, head to Bistrot Benoit.

label: Jimmy Fairly
comment: Jimmy Fairly, optician-lens-maker, stands out for its unique frames, all designed in Paris with quality materials. For 99?, a pair of Jimmy Fairly frames can be donated to someone in need. This generous gesture embodies Jimmy Fairly's desire to make eyesight accessible to all, while ensuring that its products are top-of-the-range, elegant and made in France. Jimmy Fairly proves that combining style and solidarity is possible.

label: CityStasher Ltd
comment: Stasher offers a secure luggage storage service in partner stores and hotels for 6? for 24 hours and 5? for the following days, with insurance up to 1000?. Founded in 2015, Stasher has over 50 StashPoints in Paris and covers Europe. Book online at stasher.fr from hundreds of StashPoints, pay by card and receive a confirmation email with details. StashPoints are sealed for maximum security.

label: Hôtel Pauilhac
comment: Built in 1911 by architect Charles Lestrone, the Hôtel particulier Georges Pauilhac pays homage to its famous owner and gun enthusiast. Its façade, a blend of Art Nouveau and neo-Gothic, recalls the Nancy School and was designed by Camille Garnier. Inside, a gallery showcases the Pauilhac arms collection. A visual experience rich in history and elegance.

label: Le Parisien
comment: Located in the heart of Paris, Le Parisien is a brasserie with a unique ambience blending tradition and modernity. Its historic zinc bar stands side by side with a contemporary, well-appointed decor. Renowned for its homemade cuisine, it also boasts a terrace ideal for enjoying the fine weather. A popular spot for the neighborhood's trendy thirty-somethings, this brasserie is a true symbol of conviviality and modernity.

label: Le George
comment: Chef Simone Zanoni and Le George offer revisited Mediterranean cuisine based on sharing, with lighter, modernized dishes. This Parisian restaurant, awarded a Michelin star in 2017, skilfully combines contemporary influences with a Parisian ambience, offering dishes in half portions or to share. A must for lovers of revisited Mediterranean gastronomy.
